add("ELC-01","Entity-Level","Entity","All","Tone-at-the-top / ethics breaches enable override of controls and fraud.","—",
    "Code of conduct & ethics policy issued (policies/01-code-of-conduct.md, v1.0), acknowledged annually by all staff; conflict-of-interest declarations. An in-app acknowledgement register (governance module) captures each staff member's acknowledgement of the code-of-conduct version (idempotent per version) as sample-able, tenant-isolated evidence; policy issuance + the annual campaign remain an HR/PMO process.","Prev","Hybrid","Annual","CEO / HR","P1",
    "modules/governance (ethics_acknowledgements; POST /api/governance/ethics/acknowledge, GET /api/governance/ethics/register + GET /api/governance/readiness coverage % — gated 'users'); schema/governance.ts; drizzle/0202_governance.sql; cutover/governance.ts (ToE); docs/governance/elc-operating-manual.md (annual-campaign runbook + acknowledgement statement); scheduled governance_readiness reminder (bi.service REPORT_TYPES); seed-demo-governance.ts (first cycle); policies/01-code-of-conduct.md","Inspect signed policy + the acknowledgement register + the readiness coverage %.","Re-perform: a staff acknowledgement is recorded (idempotent per version) and appears in the register; GET /api/governance/readiness reports the acknowledgement coverage % of active staff and flags the outstanding (governance harness). Operating effectiveness accrues as the annual campaign runs (per the operating manual).","Acknowledgement register + coverage %","Partial")
add("ELC-02","Entity-Level","Entity","All","No independent oversight of financial reporting / ICFR.","—",
    "Audit committee charter (adopted v1.0) defining quarterly review of financial reporting, ICFR status and audit findings. An in-app oversight log (governance module) additionally records audit-committee meetings + the quarterly ICFR review & sign-off (icfr_reviewed flag, attendees, minutes ref, signed_off_by) as tenant-isolated evidence; holding the meetings remains a board process.","Det","Hybrid","Quarterly","Board / Audit Cttee","P2",
    "compliance/policies/04-audit-committee-charter.md (adopted v1.0); modules/governance (governance_oversight; POST/GET /api/governance/oversight + GET /api/governance/readiness cadence/overdue — gated 'users'); drizzle/0203_governance_round2.sql; cutover/governance.ts (ToE); docs/governance/elc-operating-manual.md (quarterly-meeting runbook + agenda/minutes templates); scheduled governance_readiness reminder; seed-demo-governance.ts (first meeting)","Inspect the charter + quarterly minutes + the oversight log + the readiness cadence.","Inspect minutes evidencing ICFR oversight each quarter; re-perform: a meeting + ICFR review/sign-off is recorded in the oversight log and GET /api/governance/readiness computes last-meeting / next-due (≤92d) and flags overdue (governance harness). Operating effectiveness accrues as quarterly meetings are held (per the operating manual).","AC charter + oversight log + cadence","Partial")
add("ELC-03","Entity-Level","Entity","All","Transactions executed without proper authority.","Authorization",
    "Documented delegation-of-authority / approval matrix (adopted v1.0) mapped to system roles & thresholds and mirrored in the approval-workflow engine (maker-checker) + GL-05 JE / EXP procurement / REV credit controls. An in-app DoA matrix (governance module) records the authority lines (area→role→limit) as queryable, sample-able evidence.","Prev","Hybrid","Annual","CFO","P3",
    "compliance/policies/03-delegation-of-authority.md §3 (DoA approval matrix ↔ permissions.ts roles + workflow engine); ITGC-AC-09 SoD; modules/governance (delegation_of_authority; POST/GET /api/governance/doa — gated 'users'); drizzle/0203_governance_round2.sql; cutover/governance.ts (ToE)","Inspect the DoA matrix; reconcile to RBAC roles + active workflow definitions.","Sample approvals respect the DoA thresholds + approver ≠ initiator (enforced by the workflow engine / GL-05); the documented matrix is captured in the DoA register (governance harness).","DoA approval matrix + register","Implemented")
add("ELC-04","Entity-Level","Entity","All","Misconduct undetected; no safe reporting channel.","—",
    "Anonymous whistleblower / ethics hotline (policies/02-whistleblower-policy.md, v1.0) with non-retaliation policy and case tracking. An in-app intake + case log (governance module) captures reports (anonymous-capable — the reporter is recorded only if they opt out of anonymity) with a status lifecycle (received→investigating→resolved/dismissed) handled by the audit committee/compliance; the hotline operation + non-retaliation policy remain a governance process.","Det","Hybrid","Continuous","Audit Cttee","P1",
    "modules/governance (whistleblower_cases; POST /api/governance/hotline/cases anonymous-capable, GET /api/governance/hotline/cases + PATCH .../:ref + GET /api/governance/readiness open/ageing vs 30d SLA — gated 'users'); schema/governance.ts; drizzle/0202_governance.sql; cutover/governance.ts (ToE); docs/governance/elc-operating-manual.md (intake/triage SOP); scheduled governance_readiness reminder; seed-demo-governance.ts (sample case); policies/02-whistleblower-policy.md","Inspect hotline setup + the case-log + resolution evidence + the readiness ageing.","Re-perform: an (anonymous) report is captured with a case_ref (reporter hidden when anonymous), the audit committee reviews the case log and advances a case with a handler recorded; GET /api/governance/readiness reports open cases + oldest age and flags any beyond the 30-day SLA (governance harness). Operating effectiveness accrues as cases are worked (per the operating manual).","Hotline case log + ageing","Partial")
add("ELC-05","Entity-Level","Entity","All","Fraud risks not identified / mitigated.","—",
    "Annual fraud risk assessment (adopted v1.0) covering revenue, expenditure, payroll, cash, JE override, master data & access — each fraud scenario mapped to its mitigating RCM control(s) with a residual-risk rating. An in-app fraud-risk register (governance module) additionally captures identified risks with likelihood/impact, mitigating controls, owner, and a review status + last-reviewed stamp as live, sample-able evidence.","Det","Hybrid","Annual","CFO / IA","P8",
    "compliance/policies/05-fraud-risk-assessment.md §3 (fraud risk register F1–F8 ↔ SoD/GL-05/EXP/REV controls); modules/governance (fraud_risks; POST/GET /api/governance/fraud-risks + PATCH .../:ref review — gated 'users'); drizzle/0203_governance_round2.sql; cutover/governance.ts (ToE)","Inspect the fraud risk register + ratings.","Inspect that identified fraud risks map to controls in this RCM (register F1–F8) and residual risk is rated; re-perform: a fraud risk is registered + reviewed → status advances + last_reviewed_at stamped (governance harness).","Fraud risk register","Implemented")
add("ELC-06","Entity-Level","Entity","All","Errors in results undetected by management.","Accuracy",
    "Management review of actuals vs budget/forecast with documented investigation of variances — system-supported and EVIDENCED. The budget-vs-actual report (GET /api/ledger/budget-vs-actual) flags MATERIAL variances per line (|variance| >= THB 1,000 AND >= 10% of budget, or unbudgeted actual spend) with material/requires_review flags and a review summary (material_count, requires_review_count, unfavorable_total). Management records a REVIEW SIGN-OFF (POST /api/ledger/budget-review/sign-off — a required follow-up note; captures the material-variance count + unfavourable total at review time) which is retained as append-only evidence (budget_reviews) and surfaced back on the report as last_signoff; the review history (GET /api/ledger/budget-reviews) is the sample-able audit trail of monthly variance review + follow-up.","Det","Hybrid","Monthly","CFO / Controller","P16",
    "budget.service.ts budgetVsActual(material/requires_review flags + review summary)/signOffReview/listReviews; budget.controller.ts (budget-review/sign-off, budget-reviews); schema/budgets.ts budget_reviews + migration 0144; cutover/budget.ts (ToE)","Inspect the materiality flagging on budget-vs-actual + the recorded sign-off (reviewer, material count, follow-up note) + the review history.","Re-perform: post an actual that breaches a budget materially, confirm the line is flagged material/requires_review and the summary counts it; sign off with a note, confirm the sign-off records the material count + unfavourable total and the report then shows last_signoff and the history lists it (re-performed by the budget harness).","Budget-vs-actual material-variance report + review sign-off log","Implemented")
add("ELC-07","Entity-Level","Entity","All","Financial-condition deterioration (liquidity, margin, receivables ageing, leverage) goes unnoticed between close cycles because management has no single, comparative view of the key financial KPIs.","Accuracy",
    "Management analytical review of financial KPIs — a single, canonical CFO scorecard (GET /api/finance/metrics/pack) computes ~31 finance KPIs (liquidity, working-capital efficiency/CCC, profitability, leverage, growth & cash, and receivables/payables health) DIRECTLY from the posted GL + sub-ledgers, each with prior-period / prior-year / budget comparatives and a RAG (green/amber/red) rating against a defined threshold. Every KPI drills through to the account-group rows behind it (GET /api/finance/metrics/:id/drill) so a movement can be investigated to the ledger, and a monthly trend (…/:id/trend) evidences the review over time. One definition (finance-metrics-constants METRICS) feeds the scorecard, the CFO dashboard, the scheduled KPI pack and the exec_scorecard, so the reviewed number cannot drift by surface. Read-only aggregation — no posting authority, no new SoD conflict.","Det","Hybrid","Monthly","CFO / Controller","P16",
    "finance/finance-metrics.service.ts (pack/trend/drill + execFinance); finance-metrics-constants.ts (METRICS registry + RAG bands + FIN_STATEMENT_MAP account groups); finance-metrics.controller.ts (GET /api/finance/metrics/pack|:id/trend|:id/drill, perms exec/fin_report/dashboard); bi.service.ts execScorecard (reads the canonical finance leg); cutover/finance-kpi.ts (ToE); docs/35-finance-oracle-grade-analytics-plan.md","Inspect the KPI scorecard: each KPI's value, comparatives (prior-period/prior-year/budget), RAG rating, and that a red KPI drills to the GL account rows behind it.","Re-perform: on a known seeded ledger every KPI equals its hand-computed value, RAG turns red past its threshold (e.g. overdue-AR %), the drill rows tie to the sub-ledger, and a non-finance role is denied the scorecard (finance-kpi harness).","CFO KPI scorecard (finance/metrics/pack) + drill/trend","Implemented")

add("SME-01","Entity-Level","Entity","All","SME single-user edition (docs/49): a control_profile='sme' company legitimately lets ONE operator hold every duty, so preventive maker-checker segregation cannot operate — an unreviewed self-approval could conceal error or fraud.","Authorization",
    "Compensating detective control for the relaxed SoD: (1) self-approval is fail-closed — only a tenant explicitly provisioned 'sme' (god-only, chosen at creation, upgrade-only to enterprise, never downgradable — 403 PROFILE_DOWNGRADE_FORBIDDEN) may self-approve, and ONLY through the single assertMakerChecker seam with a mandatory justification (400 SELF_APPROVAL_REASON_REQUIRED without one); every other principal (enterprise tenants, API keys, members, HQ) keeps the hard SOD block. (2) Every allowed self-approval writes an immutable evidence row (self_approvals: event/ref/user/amount/reason) plus a self_approved marker in the hash-chained audit_log. (3) The SME-01 review OPERATES BY DESIGN: every SME company is auto-provisioned an ACTIVE monthly sme_self_approval_review subscription at creation (recipient = the stamped external-accountant email; editable per tenant via admin/tenants/:id/sme-prefs, which re-points the subscription), and each run that finds self-approvals additionally raises a god-inbox platform notification — so both independent reviewers (accountant + platform owner) receive it without anyone remembering to configure it. (4) A persistent SME-mode banner tells every user the environment runs relaxed SoD.","Det","Hybrid","Monthly","External accountant / Platform owner","P10/P16",
    "common/control-profile.ts (assertMakerChecker + SelfApprovalBody); common/guards.ts (live control_profile); database/schema/self-approvals.ts + platform-sme-defaults.ts (0414); billing/platform-admin.service.ts (upgradeControlProfile, PROFILE_DOWNGRADE_FORBIDDEN); governance/governance-bi-reports.ts (sme_self_approval_review); apps/web app-shell.tsx (SmeModeBanner); docs/49-sme-single-user-edition-plan.md","Inspect: an enterprise tenant's self-approval → 403 SOD_*; an sme tenant's self-approval without reason → 400 SELF_APPROVAL_REASON_REQUIRED; with reason → allowed + self_approvals row; downgrade attempt → 403.","Re-perform on the sme cutover harness: enterprise block unchanged, sme reason-gated allowance writes evidence, the SME-01 report lists it, cross-tenant reads return nothing.","self_approvals rows + audit_log self_approved markers + scheduled SME-01 report runs","Implemented")

add("SME-02","Entity-Level","Entity","All","SME single-user edition (docs/49): SME-01 PRODUCES the self-approval review, but a detective control has no assurance value unless someone actually operates it — an unreviewed report is indistinguishable from no control. Without evidence that an independent reviewer examined each period's self-approvals, the compensating control cannot be relied upon by the auditor.","Authorization",
    "Period attestation over SME-01 (migration 0417): the two independent reviewers each SIGN OFF that they reviewed a period's self-approvals — the external accountant (a tenant user holding the dedicated `sme_review` duty, granted to a separate limited login so the review is independent of the single operator) signs the 'accountant' leg, and the platform owner (god, acting-as the tenant) signs the 'platform' leg. Each sign-off snapshots the reviewed count/amount and stamps who/when (sme_review_signoffs, unique per tenant/period/kind; leg DERIVED from the principal, never client input). A period with self-approvals is 'complete' only once BOTH legs sign; the SME-01 report surfaces the current-period attestation status and outstanding legs, and each report run raises the god-inbox nudge when a leg is still outstanding. The /sme-review screen shows the reviewer the period's self-approval evidence before they sign.","Det","Hybrid","Monthly","External accountant / Platform owner","P10/P16",
    "database/schema/sme-review-signoffs.ts (0417); governance/sme-review.service.ts (signoff/status/items/list; leg from isPlatformAdmin); governance/sme-review.controller.ts (api/sme-review/*, perms sme_review/exec/users); governance/governance-bi-reports.ts (attestation status + outstanding-leg nudge on sme_self_approval_review); shared/permissions.ts (sme_review duty); apps/web /sme-review page + nav; docs/49-sme-single-user-edition-plan.md","Inspect: for a period with self-approvals, status shows both legs outstanding; after the accountant signs, 'platform' remains outstanding and complete=false; after the platform owner signs, complete=true; a user without sme_review/exec/users → 403; cross-tenant status returns only the caller's own tenant.","Re-perform on the sme cutover harness: accountant leg signs (snapshots the period's self-approvals, platform outstanding), re-sign is idempotent, platform (god act-as) leg completes the period, the SME-01 report carries the attestation status, cross-tenant isolation holds, and an unauthorized principal is refused.","sme_review_signoffs rows (who/when/count per leg) + audit_log sme_review_signoff markers + the SME-01 report's attestation block","Implemented")

