add("REV-12","Revenue & Cash","Application","Accounts Receivable","Overdue receivables not pursued; collection lapses; further credit extended to a defaulting customer.","Valuation/Authorization",
    "AR collections worklist + escalating dunning ladder (reminder→legal) recorded per invoice (DUN-), with the per-stage notice DISPATCHED to the customer (email/SMS/LINE via the messaging gateway; delivery outcome + recipient logged); credit-status / credit-check hold (over-limit OR 90+ days overdue). The serious-overdue hold is ENFORCED at POS/portal order entry (CREDIT_OVERDUE) under the FOR-UPDATE tenant lock, single-sourced with the collections on_hold threshold so the two never drift.","Det/Prev","Auto+Manual","Per overdue invoice / per order","AR / Controller","P10/P16",
    "collections.service.ts (worklist, recordDunning+dispatch, runDunningSweep, creditStatus, creditCheck, SERIOUS_OVERDUE_DAYS); messaging.service.ts (notice delivery); pos.service.ts (createOrder CREDIT_OVERDUE); collections.controller.ts (incl. cron-callable /collections/sweep); bi.service.ts (ar_collections_dunning scheduled job, daily via runDue); /finance Collections UI; cutover/basics.ts (ToE)","Inspect aging→stage logic, notice dispatch, hold decision, automated+scheduled sweep + order-entry gate.","Worklist ages open AR; manual + automated (idempotent) + daily-scheduled dunning recorded AND the notice delivered (message_log, channel auto-picked from contact); held customer's credit-check denied; a 90+ defaulter is blocked at order entry while a good-standing customer orders (re-performed by the harness).","Dunning log + message_log; sweep/scheduler run log; credit-hold report; CREDIT_OVERDUE rejections","Implemented")
add("REV-13","Revenue & Cash","Application","Cash","Cash over/short never hits the books, or a cashier clears their own material drawer discrepancy — a shortage (theft/skimming) is buried because book-cash (1000) is never reconciled to the physical count, and no independent review gates a large variance.","Accuracy/Completeness/Authorization",
    "Till-close cash over/short GL posting + material-variance maker-checker (SoD): expected cash = opening float + CASH tenders (amount + tip: a cash tip physically enters the drawer and the sale's GL debits 1000 for total+tip, while payments.amount excludes it; tips on non-cash tenders never reach the drawer) + paid-in - paid-out - drops - cash refunds. On closeTill the variance (counted - expected) is POSTED to GL — short → Dr 5830 Cash Over/Short / Cr 1000 Cash; over → Dr 1000 / Cr 5830 — so the cash control account always tracks the physical count (idempotent per till via source=TILL_CLOSE). A variance at/above the materiality threshold (THB 100) posts the over/short as a DRAFT JE and parks the session in PendingApproval: a DIFFERENT user (manager) must approve (POST /api/payments/till/variance/:sessionNo/approve) before it is effective — self-approval → SOD_VIOLATION (binds even Admin); reject voids the draft. Sub-threshold variances post immediately. The till still closes either way (the cash has left the drawer); only the GL clearing of a material discrepancy is gated.","Prev/Det","Automated","Per shift close","Store Ops Mgr / Controller","P10/P16",
    "payments.service.ts (closeTill posts 5830↔1000, approveVariance/rejectVariance via ledger.approveEntry/rejectEntry SoD); payments.controller.ts (till/variance/:sessionNo/approve|reject, pos_till); schema/payments.ts till_sessions.variance_status/variance_journal_no + migration 0140 (account 5830); ledger COA 5830 Cash Over/Short; cutover/cashreport.ts (ToE)","Inspect the over/short JE direction + the materiality gate + the approver≠closer check + that a material variance posts a Draft (excluded from balances) until approved.","Re-perform: close with a small short → over/short posts to 5830 immediately (NotRequired); close with a material short → Draft JE + PendingApproval, self-approve blocked (SOD_VIOLATION), a different user approves → JE Posted; trial balance stays balanced throughout (re-performed by the cashreport harness).","Cash over/short JEs (5830); till variance approval trail","Implemented")
add("POS-07","Revenue & Cash","Application","Cash; Revenue","The close-of-day Z-tape can be altered after the fact — a shift's recorded sales/cash totals are mutated to conceal skimming, and there is no immutable, attested record an auditor can rely on to prove the day's takings as originally counted.","Completeness/Accuracy/Authorization",
    "Signed, tamper-evident Z-report archive (POS-07): closing a till computes the shift totals (gross sales, by-method, expected vs counted cash, over/short — see REV-13); a manager then SIGNS the Z-report (POST /api/payments/till/:sessionNo/z-report/sign, gated pos_close — distinct from the cashier's pos_till) which SNAPSHOTS those totals + the denomination count into an immutable record (xz_reports/xz_report_denominations) carrying a content_hash = sha256 over the canonical totals. Signing is only allowed once the till is Closed (TILL_NOT_CLOSED otherwise) and is idempotent per till (a second sign returns the existing record — no duplicate Z-tape). On read, the stored hash is RE-COMPUTED from the persisted totals and any mismatch is surfaced as hash_valid=false, so a later edit to the archived row is detectable. A sell-only Cashier (pos_sell) cannot sign — the attestation is a manager duty.","Det","Automated","Per shift close","Store Ops Mgr / Controller","P10/P16",
    "payments.service.ts (signZReport snapshots aggregateTill totals + denominations, content_hash via node:crypto, idempotent per till; getXzReport recomputes the hash → hash_valid; listXzReports); payments.controller.ts (till/:sessionNo/z-report/sign pos_close, xz-reports[/:id]); schema/payments.ts xz_reports + xz_report_denominations + migration 0157; permissions.ts pos_close (PosSupervisor); cutover/cashreport.ts (ToE)","Inspect the sign→SIGNED+content_hash flow, the closed-till precondition, the idempotency, and the hash recompute → hash_valid tamper flag.","Re-perform: close a till, sign the Z (SIGNED + 64-hex hash, denominations snapshotted), re-sign (already=true, same hash), fetch (hash_valid=true), tamper a persisted total (hash_valid=false), sign an open till (TILL_NOT_CLOSED), Cashier sign (403) — re-performed by the cashreport harness.","Signed Z-report archive + tamper-detection test","Implemented")
add("POS-08","Revenue & Cash","Detective","Cash; Bank","A PromptPay QR taking is captured at the till but the money never actually lands in the store's bank account (or lands short/late) and no one notices — the QR tender sits as 'settled' on the POS while the bank inflow is missing, so skimmed/failed/duplicated e-payments are not detected because the till's QR sales are never tied out to the bank statement per store per day.","Existence/Completeness/Accuracy",
    "PromptPay store-level auto-reconciliation (POS-08): POST /api/pos/promptpay-recon/run matches the store's PromptPay tenders (method PromptPay/QR or gateway=promptpay) for a business day against the imported bank-statement INFLOWS on the store's mapped settlement account — REUSING the bank reconciliation auto-match engine (modules/bank/match-engine.ts: amount within a cent, date within the ±5-day tolerance window, payer-ref containment), so there is ONE matcher scoped to the settlement account, not a second one. A matched inflow line is recorded (reconciled + matched_payment_no) exactly as the GL bank auto-match does; a tender left UNMATCHED is surfaced as a till/cash EXCEPTION (promptpay_till_exceptions, Open) mirroring the till-variance exception surface — it stays on the open worklist (GET …/exceptions?status=Open) until a manager (pos_close/exec) clears it, and a re-run that finds a late inflow auto-resolves the exception. The settlement-account map is a finance-config duty (PUT …/settlement-account, recon_prep/exec); running the reconciliation is recon_prep/pos_close/exec (a sell-only cashier is denied). Read-model over the tenders + statement lines — posts no GL, adds no posting authority (no SoD change).","Det","Automated","Per store per day","Store Ops Mgr / Controller","P10/P16",
    "bank/promptpay-recon.service.ts (setSettlementAccount/reconcile/listExceptions/clearException — reconcile reuses match-engine.greedyMatch); bank/match-engine.ts (shared amount/date/ref scoring, also used by bank.service.ts autoMatch); bank/promptpay-recon.controller.ts (/api/pos/promptpay-recon settlement-account|run|exceptions[/:id/clear], recon_prep/pos_close/exec); schema/promptpay-recon.ts pos_settlement_accounts + promptpay_till_exceptions + migration 0301 (RLS 0232); cutover/cash-banking.ts (ToE)","Inspect the reuse of the single bank match engine scoped to the settlement account, the matched-line recording, the unmatched→exception surface, and the recon_prep/pos_close/exec gating (a pos_sell cashier denied).","Re-perform (cash-banking): map a settlement account; seed 2 PromptPay tenders (500 with a bank inflow, 300 without); run recon → 1 matched (the inflow line reconciled to the payment), 1 unmatched → an Open exception for the 300; import a late inflow + re-run → the 300 matches and its exception auto-resolves; a manager clears a fresh exception → Resolved; a pos_sell cashier is denied (403).","PromptPay recon match log; open till-exception worklist","Implemented")
add("POS-10","Revenue & Cash","Application","Cash; Tips Payable (2300)","A card tip added after the authorization is manipulated — a server inflates the tip after the guest leaves (capturing more than the guest wrote on the slip), edits the tip after the charge has already settled, or the captured total balloons past the authorized hold — so the guest is over-charged, the tip pass-through (2300) is overstated, and there is no trail tying the charged tip back to the slip.","Accuracy/Authorization/Occurrence",
    "Tip-adjust-after-auth window (POS-10, migration 0309): the US-restaurant 'authorize now, add the tip, capture later' card flow. A card tender is AUTHORIZED for the bill amount at checkout (POST /api/payments {authorize:true} → status Authorized, no funds captured); staff then set the tip the guest wrote on the slip (POST /api/payments/:no/tip-adjust) and finally capture bill + tip (POST /api/payments/:no/capture). TWO preventive controls bound the adjustment: (1) PRE-CAPTURE ONLY — the tip can be set only while the tender is Authorized; a Captured/Settled/Voided/Refunded tender is immutable (TIP_ADJUST_CLOSED), so a settled charge can never be re-tipped. (2) POLICY CEILING — the tip may not exceed TIP_ADJUST_MAX_PCT of the authorized amount (default 25%, env-overridable) at BOTH adjust and capture time (TIP_OVER_LIMIT), so the captured total stays within the pre-auth cushion. EVERY adjustment is written to the append-only pos_tip_adjustments log (old→new tip, delta, the auth amount + ceiling in force, who/when) so the charged tip always ties back to the slip. On capture the tip posts to 2300 Tips Payable (Dr 1000 / Cr 2300, idempotent per payment — re-capture is a no-op), feeding the existing tip-pool/distribution flow (TIP-01) unchanged. The bill's revenue/VAT are recognised at the sale checkout, so only the added tip books here.","Prev/Det","Automated","Per card tip / per capture","Store Ops Mgr / Controller","P10/P16",
    "payments.service.ts (recordTender authorize-only branch; adjustTip pre-capture + ceiling guards + pos_tip_adjustments audit insert under row lock; capture re-asserts the ceiling, PSP capture for bill+tip, Dr1000/Cr2300 tip post idempotent per payment, listTipAdjustments); payments.controller.ts (:no/tip-adjust|:no/capture pos_sell/ar, :no/tip-adjustments read; TenderBody authorize flag); gateways.ts (authorize/capture on Mock/Stripe manual-capture/Opn preauth surface — reuses OmiseProvider preauth+capture, no new processor); schema/payments.ts pos_tip_adjustments + migration 0309 (RLS 0232, tenant-leading index); COA 1000/2300; cutover/tips.ts (ToE)","Inspect the authorize→adjust→capture state machine, the pre-capture-only + %-ceiling guards at both adjust and capture, the immutable pos_tip_adjustments trail, and the idempotent Dr1000/Cr2300 tip post on capture.","Re-perform (tips harness): authorize a 200 card bill → Authorized; adjust the tip above the 25% ceiling (60>50) → TIP_OVER_LIMIT; adjust to 40 within the window → logged; capture → Captured, total 240, tip posts +40 to 2300 and flows into the tip pool; adjust after capture → TIP_ADJUST_CLOSED; re-capture is idempotent (no double 2300 post); trial balance stays balanced.","pos_tip_adjustments audit log; 2300 tip accrual; over-limit/post-capture rejects","Implemented")
add("REV-14","Revenue & Cash","Application","Accounts Receivable; Bad-debt expense","An uncollectible receivable is written off the books without independent review — one person both declares the receivable uncollectible and posts the write-off, concealing a misappropriated customer collection (lapping) or removing a still-collectible balance.","Valuation/Authorization",
    "AR bad-debt write-off maker-checker (SoD): POST /api/finance/ar/write-off books the write-off (Dr 5720 Bad Debt Expense / Cr 1100 AR) as a DRAFT via the ledger maker-checker (GL-05) — excluded from the trial balance until a DIFFERENT user approves it (POST /api/ledger/journal/:entryNo/approve); a self-approval → SOD_VIOLATION (binds even Admin), and the pending write-off surfaces in the pending-approvals monitor automatically (it is a Draft JE). A non-positive amount → BAD_AMOUNT and a missing reason is rejected. The write-off register (GET /api/finance/ar/write-offs) lists every write-off Draft(pending)/Posted(approved)/Voided(rejected) with its amount for controller review.","Prev","Automated","Per write-off","AR / Controller","P10",
    "finance.service.ts writeOffAr/listWriteOffs; finance.controller.ts (ar/write-off, ar/write-offs); ledger COA 5720 Bad Debt Expense; reuses ledger.approveEntry maker-checker (GL-05); cutover/basics.ts (ToE)","Inspect the write-off → Draft (excluded from balances) → approve flow + the approver≠maker check + that nothing posts until approval.","Re-perform: request a write-off (Draft, 5720 unchanged), attempt self-approve (SOD_VIOLATION), approve as a different user; confirm 5720 bad-debt expense + 1100 relief only after approval; the register lists it (re-performed by the basics harness).","Write-off register + SoD test","Implemented")
add("REV-15","Revenue & Cash","Application","Accounts Receivable; Revenue","No single customer-of-record — B2C loyalty members and B2B accounts live in disjoint silos, so revenue-by-customer, a 360 view, and AR-by-customer cannot be reconciled to one identity (incomplete/duplicated customer reporting; AR mis-attributed).","Completeness/Accuracy",
    "Unified customer master: a single registry (customer_master) is the customer-of-record, LINKING the pre-existing silos — member_id → pos_members (B2C loyalty) and account_code → the B2B customer tenant (orders + AR) — without disturbing them. A 360 view (GET /api/customer-master/:no/360) joins both: loyalty tier/points + the B2B orders/stats and AR balance, and the 360 AR-outstanding TIES to the AR sub-ledger for that account (revenue/AR resolve to one record). Tenant-scoped (RLS). Create/link/search are gated by crm/exec/ar.","Det","Auto+Manual","Continuous / per customer","CRM / AR / Controller","P13",
    "customers.module.ts CustomerMasterService (create/list/get/link/view360 — reuses CustomersService.detail for the B2B side); customer-master controller (POST/GET /api/customer-master, :no/360, :no/link); schema/customer-master.ts customer_master + migration 0149; cutover/basics.ts (ToE)","Inspect the master registry + the 360 join across loyalty + AR + that 360 AR-outstanding ties to the AR sub-ledger.","Re-perform: create a customer-of-record linking a B2B account + a B2C member; GET 360 → loyalty tier/points present and AR-outstanding equals the AR sub-ledger for the account; search finds the record (re-performed by the basics harness).","Customer master register + 360 AR tie-out","Implemented")
add("REV-16","Revenue & Cash","Application","Cash; Revenue","A cashier issues a large refund without any independent review — refunding to themselves/an accomplice or reversing a real sale to skim the cash (refund fraud), because the refund moves money the moment one person requests it.","Authorization/Occurrence",
    "Refund maker-checker (SoD): a STANDALONE refund (POST /api/payments/refunds) at/above the materiality threshold (THB 1,000) is parked as a REQUEST (refund_requests) and MOVES NO MONEY — no payment_refunds row, the payment is not flipped — until a DIFFERENT user approves it (POST /api/payments/refund-requests/:id/approve); self-approval → SOD_VIOLATION; reject voids the request. Sub-threshold refunds run immediately, and a refund that is part of a goods-return is never gated (the return is the authorizing document, REV-07). The pending request auto-surfaces in the GOV-01 pending-approvals monitor and an inline approve/reject sits on the /approvals screen. The over-refund guard (REV-06) still binds at execution.","Prev","Automated","Per large refund","PosSupervisor / Controller","P10",
    "payments.service.ts refund (threshold gate → requestRefund), approveRefund/rejectRefund (SoD by username), listRefundRequests; payments.controller.ts (refund-requests/:id/approve|reject, pos_refund/ar/exec); schema/payments.ts refund_requests + migration 0151; finance.pendingApprovals (GOV-01 9th source); /approvals inline action; cutover/refund-approval.ts (ToE)","Inspect the threshold gate, the request-posts-nothing property, the approver≠requester check, and that the goods-return path is not gated.","Re-perform: a small refund runs immediately; a large refund parks PendingApproval (no payment_refunds row) + surfaces in GOV-01; self-approve → SOD_VIOLATION; a different user approves → the refund executes; reject moves no money (re-performed by the refund-approval harness).","Refund-request worklist + SoD test","Implemented")
add("REV-17","Revenue & Cash","Application","Revenue (pipeline / forecast)","Sales pipeline ungoverned — no lead-to-opportunity motion or controlled stage progression, so the revenue forecast is unreliable (opportunities skip stages, closed deals are silently re-opened, lost deals carry no reason), and converted leads don't attach to a customer-of-record.","Accuracy/Completeness",
    "CRM sales pipeline on the customer-of-record — UNIFIED spine (CRM-1, migration 0295): leads → qualify → CONVERT (creates/attaches a customer_master + a CRM account/primary contact + an opportunity; a converted/lost lead can't be re-converted) → ONE opportunity table (crm_opportunities) serves BOTH route families (/api/crm/pipeline and the legacy /api/pipeline adapters) and runs a controlled stage machine over the tenant-configurable pipeline_stages master (defaults seeded per tenant; probability tracks the stage row) where won/lost are TERMINAL on every route (OPP_CLOSED) and lost REQUIRES a reason on the governed route (LOST_REASON_REQUIRED). EVERY stage transition (incl. creation) writes the append-only crm_stage_history audit. Duplicate governance on the party model: creating a crm_account/crm_contact that matches an existing record on normalized tax-id/email/phone/company-name is refused 409 DUPLICATE_SUSPECT (steward force override); a confirmed duplicate is merged survivor-pattern (children repointed, soft-retired merged_into/by/at) and the merge is MAKER-CHECKED when children reassign (caller ≠ duplicate creator → SOD_VIOLATION). The weighted pipeline forecast = Σ open-opportunity amount × probability, with won/lost totals + win-rate — the revenue forecast finance relies on. Activities are logged per lead/opportunity. Tenant-scoped (RLS); gated crm/exec/ar (merge: crm/exec/masterdata).","Det","Auto+Manual","Continuous / per deal","CRM / Sales / Controller","P13",
    "crm-pipeline.service.ts (unified spine: stage machine over pipeline_stages, crm_stage_history, pipelineSummary, /api/pipeline adapter methods); pipeline.service.ts (thin adapter); crm/accounts/crm-accounts.module.ts (accounts/contacts, DUPLICATE_SUSPECT, audited merge); schema/crm-pipeline.ts crm_leads/crm_opportunities/crm_activities/crm_accounts/crm_contacts/crm_stage_history + migrations 0152/0294; cutover/basics.ts + cutover/pipeline.ts (ToE)","Inspect the lead-conversion → customer-of-record/account link, the unified stage machine (won/lost terminal on both routes, lost-reason required, stage-history audit), and the duplicate-detection + maker-checked merge.","Re-perform: create a lead, qualify, convert (→ CUS- + ACC- + OPP-, re-convert blocked), advance to won (terminal on BOTH routes — re-stage blocked OPP_CLOSED), lost without a reason blocked; stage history lists every transition; a duplicate account create → DUPLICATE_SUSPECT then force; the duplicate creator's merge with children → SOD_VIOLATION, a distinct user merges and children repoint; the weighted forecast + won total compute (re-performed by the basics + pipeline harnesses).","Pipeline stage-machine + stage-history + duplicate-governance tests","Implemented")
add("TIP-01","Revenue & Cash","Application","Cash; Tips Payable (2300)","Staff tips are skimmed or mis-paid — tips collected from guests are never paid out (the 2300 liability grows unexplained), more is paid out than was collected (theft via inflated tip-outs), or the cashier who rings sales also pays the tips (to self).","Completeness/Accuracy/Authorization",
    "Tip pooling / distribution with SoD: tips ride into 2300 Tips Payable on checkout (a staff pass-through liability, not revenue/VAT). A distribution (POST /api/restaurant/tips/distribute) pays the pooled tips out to staff for a period — Dr 2300 / Cr 1000 (cash) — clearing the liability; the amount is HARD-CAPPED at the available pool (collected − already distributed, bounded by the 2300 GL outstanding) so tips can never be over-paid (TIP_OVER_DISTRIBUTE). 2300 always reconciles to what is still owed to staff. SoD: distributing is a manager/finance duty (order_mgt/exec), segregated from the cashier who rings sales (pos_sell) — a cashier cannot pay tips to themselves (403).","Prev/Det","Automated","Per period / per payout","Store Ops Mgr / Controller","P10/P16",
    "restaurant/tip.service.ts (pool/distribute/list, outstanding2300 reconciliation, over-distribute guard); restaurant.controller.ts (tips/pool|distribute|list; distribute @order_mgt/exec); schema/restaurant.ts tip_distributions + tip_distribution_lines + migration 0146; payments.tip → 2300 on checkout; cutover/tips.ts (ToE)","Inspect the pool computation, the 2300↔collected reconciliation, the over-distribute cap, and the cashier-vs-manager SoD on the distribute route.","Re-perform: ring sales with tips (2300 accrues), a cashier's distribute → 403, a manager distributes by hours (Dr 2300 / Cr 1000, 2300 clears to 0, shares correct), a second over-distribute → TIP_OVER_DISTRIBUTE; trial balance balanced (re-performed by the tips harness).","Tip distribution register; 2300 reconciliation","Implemented")
add("REV-18","Revenue & Cash","Application","Accounts Receivable; Bad-debt expense; Allowance for Doubtful Accounts (1190)","AR is carried at gross with no provision for expected credit losses — receivables that are partly/wholly uncollectible are overstated (assets/equity overstated, bad-debt expense understated and untimely), and a single person could both set the provision and post it (manage earnings via the allowance).","Valuation/Authorization",
    "AR Allowance for Doubtful Accounts (ECL): a periodic, aging-driven provision — each open-AR bucket (current / 1-30 / 31-60 / 61-90 / 91-120 / 120+) carries a loss rate and the allowance = Σ(outstanding × rate) (a flat-percentage method is also supported). Computation upserts an UNPOSTED row (one per tenant/as-of-date); posting is MAKER-CHECKED — the poster must DIFFER from the computer (computer self-post → SOD_SELF_POST, binds even Admin) — and journals only the DELTA vs the prior posted allowance (increase: Dr 5720 Bad-Debt Expense / Cr 1190 contra-asset; decrease reverses) so 1190 carries the cumulative provision while 1100 gross AR is untouched. Posting routes through LedgerService.postEntry, so it respects the period lock (PERIOD_LOCKED) and a posted allowance can't be re-posted (ALREADY_POSTED).","Det/Prev","Auto+Manual","Period-end","AR / Controller","P10/P16",
    "finance/ar-allowance.service.ts (computeAllowance aging buckets/rates; postAllowance delta + SoD computer≠poster); finance.controller.ts (/api/finance/ar-allowance/compute|:id/post|GET, gated creditors/ar/gl_post/exec); schema/ar-allowance.ts ar_allowance + migration 0166; COA 1190; cutover/basics.ts (ToE)","Inspect the aging-bucket rates, the allowance computation, the delta posting (Dr 5720 / Cr 1190), and the compute-vs-post SoD.","Re-perform: compute an allowance over seeded aged AR (buckets × rates → allowance), the computer's self-post → SOD_SELF_POST, a different user posts the delta → 5720/1190 move by the provision, a re-post → ALREADY_POSTED (re-performed by the basics harness).","AR allowance register; provision JE; SoD test","Implemented")
add("REV-19","Revenue & Cash","Application","Revenue; Contract Liability / Deferred Revenue (2410); Refund Liability (2420)","Service/subscription/project revenue is recognized in the wrong period — booked up-front (or never deferred) instead of as the performance obligations are satisfied, and a multi-element contract's price is not split by standalone selling price — so revenue and the contract-liability are misstated (TFRS 15 / IFRS 15 non-compliance; revenue overstated/understated, deferred revenue mis-carried, expected refunds unprovided).","Accuracy/Cutoff/Completeness/Valuation",
    "TFRS 15 / IFRS 15 five-step revenue recognition engine (the 'real ERP' deferred-revenue model; the restaurant POS keeps immediate recognition). A contract carries one or more performance obligations; the transaction price is ALLOCATED across them in proportion to standalone selling price (allocateBySSP — Σ allocated == total_price EXACTLY, the rounding residual lands on the largest-SSP PO; Σssp≤0 → INVALID_ALLOCATION). On activation the full price raises the contract liability (Dr 1100 AR / Cr 2410 Deferred Revenue, viaSubledger so the AR control is respected). buildSchedule lays out the recognition plan — over_time POs straight-line their allocated price across the months start..end, point_in_time POs a single row at the satisfaction date — and is idempotent (rebuilds only UNRECOGNIZED rows; recognized rows are never touched). recognize() releases revenue for all schedule rows due in/through a period (Dr 2410 / Cr 4300 Recognized Revenue), marks the row + bumps the PO satisfied_pct/status, and is idempotent (an already-recognized row is skipped — no double post). accrueRefundLiability provisions expected returns (Dr 4300 contra revenue / Cr 2420 Refund Liability) posting only the DELTA vs the prior provision. All posting routes through LedgerService.postEntry so the period lock (PERIOD_LOCKED, GL-15/16) and the GL-17 audit trail bind; recognition is tenant-scoped (HQ/Admin must name a tenant → TENANT_REQUIRED).","Prev","Automated","Per contract / period-end","Revenue Accountant / Controller","P10/P13",
    "revenue/revrec.service.ts (createContract; allocateBySSP residual handling; activate Dr1100/Cr2410; buildSchedule straight-line/point-in-time idempotent; recognize Dr2410/Cr4300; accrueRefundLiability delta Dr4300/Cr2420); revenue/revrec.controller.ts (/api/revenue/contracts POST|GET|:id|:id/allocate|:id/schedule|:id/activate|recognize|:id/refund-liability, gated exec/ar/fin_report); schema/revrec-contracts.ts rev_contracts/performance_obligations/revrec_schedules/refund_liability + migration 0172; COA 2410/2420; cutover/revrec.ts (ToE)","Inspect the SSP allocation (sums exactly to price), the activation/recognition/refund postings, the straight-line vs point-in-time schedule, and the idempotency + period-lock + tenant-scoping guards.","Re-perform: create a contract (total 1000, SSP 800 over_time / 400 point_in_time) → allocate sums to 1000 with residual on the larger PO; activate → Dr1100/Cr2410 1000; build schedule (4+1 rows); recognize 2040-01 → 2410 falls 500 / 4300 rises 500; recognize again → 0 new; refund liability 10% → Dr4300/Cr2420 50 (re-performed by the revrec harness).","Contract register; SSP allocation; deferred-revenue roll-forward; recognition + refund JEs","Implemented")
add("REV-20","Revenue & Cash","Application","Revenue (4000); Cash (1000); VAT Output (2100)","A voucher/coupon campaign goes live without independent review (self-issued margin giveaway), a code is redeemed twice or after expiry/void under concurrency, an under-minimum sale takes the discount, or a voided code leaves no audit trail — revenue is understated by unauthorized or duplicated markdowns (POS-3, docs/41).","Occurrence/Accuracy/Authorization",
    "Voucher lifecycle control (migration 0292: voucher_campaigns + voucher_codes, RLS). (1) ACTIVATION IS MAKER-CHECKER: a campaign is created 'PendingApproval' and its codes redeem ONLY once a DIFFERENT user activates it via POST /api/vouchers/campaigns/:id/approve (creator self-approval → 403 SOD_VIOLATION — mirrors the price-rule G6 gate); the checkout redemption path reads status='Active' campaigns only. (2) ATOMIC SINGLE REDEMPTION: redemption at checkout (dine-in buildSale, POST /api/restaurant/orders/:orderNo/checkout voucher_code) runs a guarded UPDATE (WHERE state='issued' AND use_count < per_code_max_uses) inside the sale transaction — a concurrent second redemption claims 0 rows → 409 VOUCHER_ALREADY_REDEEMED and its sale rolls back; the campaign-wide cap increments under its own guard (VOUCHER_EXHAUSTED). Validity window (VOUCHER_EXPIRED/NOT_STARTED), min-spend (VOUCHER_MIN_SPEND) and channel gates are enforced server-side; the loyalty member-coupon wallet redeems through the SAME surface (guarded active→used; ALREADY_USED). The code is consumed only when its discount actually applies, and sale_ref/redeemed_by/redeemed_at record the redeeming sale. (3) VOID AUDITED: POST /api/vouchers/codes/:code/void flips only an issued code (redeemed → 409 CANNOT_VOID) stamping voided_by/voided_at/void_reason. Codes are crypto-random (unique per tenant); generation/maintenance is gated to the promo/marketing duties (R10 split — segregated from selling); a returned sale does NOT auto-release the code (consistent with promo usage; manual re-issue via bulk generate).","Prev","Automated","Per transaction","Marketing / Revenue Controller","P10",
    "campaigns/vouchers.service.ts (createCampaign PendingApproval; approveCampaign SOD_VIOLATION; generateCodes crypto-random unique retry; voidCode guarded + audited; previewForCheckout validity/min-spend/channel/cap checks incl. member_coupons; redeemAtCheckout guarded UPDATE + campaign-cap increment); campaigns/vouchers.controller.ts (/api/vouchers/campaigns[…]/approve|reject|end|codes|codes.csv|redemptions, codes/:code/void, validate — maintenance gated promos/pricelist/marketing/exec, validate open to sellers); restaurant/dine-in.service.ts buildSale voucher_code path (best-discount slot, consume-only-if-applied, atomic in-sale-tx redeem); schema/vouchers.ts + migration 0292 (RLS, tenant-leading indexes); web /loyalty/campaigns admin + /pos/register checkout voucher field; cutover/pricing.ts (ToE)","Inspect the maker-checker gate (pending campaign codes rejected at checkout; self-approval 403), the guarded-UPDATE redemption (state/use_count predicates), the validity/min-spend enforcement, and the void audit stamps.","Re-perform: create a 10% voucher campaign (min spend 100) as one user → codes do NOT redeem (VOUCHER_NOT_ACTIVE); creator self-approve → 403 SOD_VIOLATION; a distinct user approves → a generated code redeems at checkout (discount + balanced GL) and sale_ref recorded; the SAME code again → 409 VOUCHER_ALREADY_REDEEMED; an expired campaign's code → VOUCHER_EXPIRED; an under-minimum sale → VOUCHER_MIN_SPEND; void an issued code → audited, then redeem → rejected (re-performed by the pricing harness).","voucher_campaigns register (status/created_by/approved_by); voucher_codes state + sale_ref/redeemed_by + void stamps; redemption report GET /api/vouchers/campaigns/:id/redemptions","Implemented")
add("REV-21","Revenue & Cash","Application","Cash; Accounts Receivable (1100); Unapplied Customer Receipts (2220)","Customer cash is mis-applied or its application is untracked — a receipt covering several invoices is forced onto one (or keyed twice), an invoice is over-applied, unallocated cash disappears into the wrong account (or is shuffled between customers/invoices to conceal lapping), and an application can be silently un-done — so AR open balances, aging, dunning and the customer statement misstate what each customer owes.","Completeness/Accuracy/Authorization",
    "AR cash application with on-account tracking + threshold maker-checker: a worksheet (POST /api/finance/ar/cash-application) applies ONE receipt across MANY invoices (partial allowed) with fail-closed guards — Σ applications ≤ the receipt (APPLY_EXCEEDS_RECEIPT), each invoice's open balance never overshot INCLUDING pending applications (OVER_APPLIED), cross-customer application rejected (CUSTOMER_MISMATCH). The unapplied remainder parks ON-ACCOUNT — tracked per receipt (ar_receipts.unapplied_amount) and on GL 2220 Unapplied Customer Receipts (Dr 1000 / Cr 1100 applied / Cr 2220 remainder) — and is applied later via POST /api/finance/ar/apply-on-account (Dr 2220 / Cr 1100; INSUFFICIENT_UNAPPLIED guard incl. pending draws). An application batch at/over the threshold (THB 100,000, mirroring REV-16) parks PendingApproval — the cash banks fully on-account and NO invoice moves — until a DIFFERENT user approves (self-approval → SOD_VIOLATION; pending batches surface in the GOV-01 monitor). A reversal REQUIRES a reason and is audited in place (reversed flag + who/when/why; the cash returns on-account, Dr 1100 / Cr 2220). An Issued AR-linked credit note (ใบลดหนี้, TAX-07) is applicable as a credit line — re-aligning the AR sub-ledger to the 1100 relief the note posted at approval (CN_NOT_ISSUED / CN_NOT_AR_LINKED / CN_OVER_APPLIED guards) — and applied credit notes + on-account cash flow through the customer statement, aging (on_account/net_total) and the collections worklist. A deterministic auto-suggest (exact single-invoice match, else oldest-due-first) feeds the worksheet.","Prev","Automated","Per receipt / continuous","AR Clerk / Controller","P10",
    "finance/ar-cash-application.service.ts (createCashApplication guards + threshold park; applyOnAccount; approveBatch/rejectBatch SoD; reverseApplication reason-required audit; openItems worksheet feed; suggest deterministic FIFO); finance.controller.ts (/api/finance/ar/cash-application[|/suggest|/:batchNo/approve|reject|/:applicationNo/reverse], ar/open-items, ar/apply-on-account — gated ar / approvals+gl_close); schema/finance.ts ar_receipt_applications + ar_receipts.unapplied_amount + migration 0295; COA/CF_CLASSIFY 2220; finance.service.ts arAging on_account + customerStatement credit-note lines + pendingApprovals REV-21 source; collections worklist on_account; cutover/basics.ts (ToE)","Inspect the worksheet guards (receipt cap, per-invoice open-balance cap incl. pending, customer match), the on-account tracking (receipt unapplied ↔ GL 2220), the threshold park + approver≠poster check, and the reversal audit (reason, who, when).","Re-perform: apply one receipt across two invoices with an on-account remainder → invoices move, 2220 carries the remainder, TB balanced; over-apply → OVER_APPLIED; another customer's invoice → CUSTOMER_MISMATCH; Σ lines > receipt → APPLY_EXCEEDS_RECEIPT; apply-on-account later clears 2220 into 1100; a batch ≥ THB 100k parks (invoices unmoved) — self-approve → SOD_VIOLATION, a different user approves → invoices + GL move; reverse with a reason → invoice reopens + cash returns on-account, audit row carries reason/who (re-performed by the basics harness).","Cash-application register; on-account (2220) tie-out; SoD + reversal audit tests","Implemented")
add("REV-22","Revenue & Cash","Application","Revenue (pipeline / sales follow-up)","New leads and open deals are not followed up on time — an inbound lead sits untouched past the response SLA (and goes cold / to a competitor), a deal rots with no activity, or an overdue follow-up task is forgotten — so the pipeline forecast is unreliable and revenue is lost to neglect rather than to a real loss reason; and lead prioritisation is ad-hoc (no consistent, explainable scoring).","Completeness/Timeliness",
    "CRM sales-automation discipline (CRM-4) on the unified pipeline spine (migration 0307): every lead is scored by an EXPLAINABLE, versioned rules formula (source / size / contactability / engagement-recency → grade A–D; coefficients are code-reviewed in LEAD_SCORE_COEFFS, each score stamped LEAD_SCORE_VERSION with a persisted per-factor breakdown) so prioritisation is consistent and auditable. A tenant-configurable follow-up policy (crm_followup_settings: sla_hours, rotting_days, round-robin owners — change gated crm/exec) drives a DETECTIVE follow-up center (GET /api/crm/pipeline/follow-up) that surfaces, severity-ranked: NEW leads untouched (no activity logged) past the SLA, open follow-up tasks past their due date, and OPEN deals idle for rotting_days — the control: a lead must be touched within the SLA. New leads are auto-assigned round-robin across the configured owners. A schedulable daily digest (BI report type crm_followup_digest) re-runs the center, fires lead.stagnant into the automation engine and drops a notification on the alerts rail. The pipeline emits lead.created / opp.stage_changed / deal.won / deal.lost into the SAME no-code automation-rules engine (reusable by existing rules), and a rep can send email/LINE from the deal timeline (MessagingService + {{merge-field}} substitution) logged as a timeline activity. Read-only detective aggregation — posts nothing to the GL, no new SoD conflict.","Det","Auto+Manual","Continuous / daily","CRM / Sales Manager","P13",
    "crm-pipeline.service.ts (scoreLead/computeLeadScore + LEAD_SCORE_COEFFS/VERSION; followUpCenter SLA/rotting/overdue detective aggregation; getFollowupSettings/putFollowupSettings; nextRoundRobinOwner/assignLead; runFollowUpSweep digest; sendComms merge-field email/LINE; emitEvent lead.created/opp.stage_changed/deal.won/deal.lost); crm-pipeline.controller.ts (leads/:no/score, follow-up[/settings|/run], leads/:no/assign, opportunities/:no/comms, comms/merge-fields); automation.service.ts (CRM-4 event catalog); schema/crm-pipeline.ts crm_lead_scores/crm_followup_settings + migration 0307; bi report crm_followup_digest; cutover/pipeline.ts (ToE)","Inspect the explainable lead-score formula (coefficients + version + breakdown), the follow-up center's SLA-breach / overdue-task / rotting-deal detection against the tenant policy, the round-robin assignment, and the pipeline events reaching the automation engine.","Re-perform: a referral lead with company+email+phone scores grade A with a versioned breakdown; a cold contactless lead grades D; an aged untouched 'new' lead surfaces as an SLA breach and logging an activity clears it; new leads auto-assign round-robin across owners; the daily digest sweep reports breaches and fires lead.stagnant; closing a deal Won fires deal.won into an automation rule; sending comms from a deal resolves {{merge fields}} and logs a timeline activity (re-performed by the pipeline harness).","Lead-score register + follow-up SLA/rotting worklist + automation-event executions + comms activity log","Implemented")

add("REV-23","Revenue & Cash","Application","Accounts Receivable (1100); Accounts Payable (2000)","A trading partner is BOTH a customer (open AR) and a vendor (open AP), yet the two are settled in full both ways — cash paid out to the vendor while the same counterparty's receivable is chased — needlessly inflating gross AR and AP (mis-stating working capital and liquidity), tying up cash, and creating the collection/payment risk the offset would eliminate; or an offset is booked by one person with no independent review (a fictitious/over-stated netting could conceal an uncollectible receivable or an unauthorised write-down of a payable).","Existence/Accuracy/Authorization",
    "AR/AP netting & contra settlement (docs/41 FIN-8): for a counterparty that is both a customer and a vendor, an open AR balance is offset against an open AP balance with a SINGLE contra JE (Dr 2000 AP / Cr 1100 AR) that clears both sub-ledgers up to the netted amount, leaving the residual open. Fail-closed + maker-checked: a per-counterparty NETTING AGREEMENT must exist and be enabled (NETTING_NOT_AGREED / NETTING_DISABLED — the agreement is the counterparty↔vendor mapping authorising the offset), a per-counterparty THRESHOLD caps any one settlement's net (NETTING_EXCEEDS_THRESHOLD), a mandatory reason is required (REASON_REQUIRED), and nothing-to-net is rejected (NOTHING_TO_NET, needs BOTH open AR and open AP). The settlement is PROPOSED PendingApproval (no GL, no sub-ledger movement) and applied only when a DIFFERENT user approves (POST …/netting/settlements/:no/approve; proposer self-approval → 403 SOD_VIOLATION, binds even Admin; pending settlements surface in the GOV-01 monitor). At approval the net = min(open AR, open AP) [capped by the threshold / requested amount] is recomputed from CURRENT balances, allocated oldest-due-first across the customer's invoices and our bills (both absorb exactly the net, so the contra JE balances and the AR/AP controls stay tied to GL), and the netting statement (header + AR/AP offset lines) records exactly what was offset. Reject leaves everything untouched.","Prev","Automated","Per settlement","AR/AP / Controller","P10",
    "finance/arap-netting.service.ts (upsertAgreement counterparty mapping + enable/threshold; preview open AR/AP + proposed net; propose NETTING_NOT_AGREED/NETTING_DISABLED/NETTING_EXCEEDS_THRESHOLD/REASON_REQUIRED/NOTHING_TO_NET, PendingApproval no-GL park; approve SoD + recompute + contra JE Dr2000/Cr1100 + oldest-first AR/AP relief; getSettlement netting statement); finance.controller.ts (/api/finance/netting/agreements[|preview|/settlements[|/:no[|/approve|/reject]]] — gated creditors/exec / approvals+gl_close); schema/finance.ts netting_agreements/netting_settlements/netting_settlement_lines + migration 0309; finance.service.ts pendingApprovals REV-23 (ar_ap_netting) source; cutover/basics.ts (ToE)","Inspect the counterparty agreement gate (must exist + enabled), the per-counterparty threshold cap, the mandatory reason, the PendingApproval park (no GL until approval), the approver≠proposer check, and the recompute + oldest-first allocation that keeps the contra JE balanced and both sub-ledgers tied to GL.","Re-perform: seed a counterparty with open AR 1300 and open AP 900; preview shows proposed net 900 (residual AR 400 / AP 0); propose without a reason → REASON_REQUIRED; propose parks PendingApproval (net 900, no GL / sub-ledger movement) and surfaces in the GOV-01 monitor; self-approve → SOD_VIOLATION; a different user approves → contra JE Dr 2000 +900 / Cr 1100 −900, both AP bills Paid, the AR residual (INV-NET2, 400) stays open, and the netting statement lists the offset (AR 800+100, AP 300+600); propose without an agreement → NETTING_NOT_AGREED, against a disabled agreement → NETTING_DISABLED, above the threshold → NETTING_EXCEEDS_THRESHOLD, with no open AP → NOTHING_TO_NET (re-performed by the basics harness).","Netting-settlement register + netting statement; contra-JE (2000/1100) tie-out; SoD + agreement/threshold guards","Implemented")
add("REV-24","Revenue & Cash","Application","Contract Asset / Unbilled Receivable (1265); Contract Liability / Deferred Revenue (2410); Accounts Receivable (1100); Recognized Revenue (4300)","Revenue recognized on a contract is NOT distinguished from what has been billed — the engine can only ever carry a contract liability (billing the whole contract price up-front on activation), so revenue earned AHEAD of invoicing (an unbilled receivable / contract asset) is invisible, the balance-sheet split of contract asset vs contract liability is misstated, and when an invoice is finally raised the earned unbilled receivable is not reclassified to trade AR — breaching TFRS 15 / IFRS 15 / ASC 606 §105-107 (contract-asset / contract-liability presentation) and mis-stating both current assets and deferred-revenue liabilities.","Existence/Valuation/Cutoff",
    "Contract-asset / contract-liability split with an INDEPENDENT billing schedule decoupled from recognition (Track D Wave 1, TFRS 15 / IFRS 15 / ASC 606 §105-107). Billing is separated from the REV-19 recognition engine: revenue is recognized as performance obligations are satisfied while invoices are raised on their own milestone/period schedule. (1) The REV-19 activation is made OPTIONAL — bill_upfront (default TRUE) preserves today's Dr 1100 AR / Cr 2410 up-front billing (back-compat); set FALSE to decouple. (2) recognize() is now asset-aware: it first RELEASES any contract liability already billed in advance (Dr 2410) and the surplus recognized ahead of billing builds a CONTRACT ASSET / unbilled receivable (Dr 1265 / Cr 4300) — for an up-front-billed contract the liability always covers the amount so it reduces to the legacy Dr 2410 / Cr 4300. (3) A MAKER defines the billing milestones (POST …/billing-schedule; Σ planned ≤ contract price → SCHEDULE_EXCEEDS_CONTRACT). (4) A DIFFERENT user bills a milestone (POST …/bill) — the invoice RECLASSES the earned contract asset 1265 → 1100 AR and parks any billing-in-excess as a contract liability 2410; the biller may NOT be the milestone's maker (SOD_SELF_BILLING) and cumulative billing may never exceed the contract price (BILL_EXCEEDS_CONTRACT). (5) A detective /position tie-out reconciles cumulative recognized vs billed to the derived contract_asset = max(0, Σrecognized − Σbilled) / contract_liability = max(0, Σbilled − Σrecognized). All posting routes through LedgerService.postEntry so the period lock (PERIOD_LOCKED, GL-15/16) + GL-17 audit bind; tenant-scoped (RLS). No new COA (1100/1265/2410/4300 already exist + CF-classified operating).","Prev","Automated","Per contract / bill / period-end","Revenue Accountant / Controller","P10/P13",
    "revrec-billing/rev-billing.service.ts (defineBillingSchedule maker + SCHEDULE_EXCEEDS_CONTRACT; bill checker reclass Dr1100/Cr1265 + Cr2410 excess, SOD_SELF_BILLING + BILL_EXCEEDS_CONTRACT; position tie-out); rev-billing.controller.ts (/api/revenue/contracts/:id/billing-schedule POST|GET, :id/bill POST, :id/position GET — gated exec/ar/fin_report); revenue/revrec.service.ts (activate bill_upfront optional + billed_amount; recognize asset-aware Dr2410 then Dr1265 / Cr4300); schema/revrec-billing.ts rev_billing_schedules + rev_contracts.billed_amount + migration 0358 (0232-form RLS, leading (tenant_id, contract_id) index); COA 1100/1265/2410/4300; cutover/revrec-billing.ts (ToE)","Inspect the recognize asset-aware split (release 2410 first, build 1265 for the surplus), the billing-schedule maker + Σ-planned ≤ contract-price guard, the bill-side reclass (1265→1100, excess→2410) with the maker≠biller SoD and cumulative-billing cap, and the /position tie-out.","Re-perform (revrec-billing harness): activate a 1200 contract bill_upfront=false → billed 0; recognize 3 months (300) → contract asset 1265 rises 300, no 2410 moved; /position shows recognized 300 / billed 0 / asset 300; define a billing schedule (maker) → the maker billing it → 403 SOD_SELF_BILLING; a different user bills 200 → 1265→1100 reclass (asset 100 left); bill 400 → 100 clears the asset and 300 parks contract liability 2410; /position ties recognized 300 / billed 600 / liability 300 / asset 0; a milestone beyond the contract price → SCHEDULE_EXCEEDS_CONTRACT; a contract activated up-front (bill_upfront default) still releases 2410 on recognition (REV-19 back-compat); a second tenant sees 0 of the first tenant's contract/schedule (RLS).","Contract-asset / contract-liability roll-forward; billing-schedule maker-checker log; 1265↔1100 reclass tie-out; /position report","Implemented")
add("REV-25","Revenue & Cash","Application","Recognized Revenue (4300); Contract Liability / Deferred Revenue (2410); Contract Asset / Unbilled Receivable (1265)","A contract with VARIABLE consideration (rebates, refunds, performance bonuses/penalties, price concessions, usage/volume tiers) is recognized at a fixed price only — the variable amount is either ignored or booked in full with NO constraint, so revenue is OVER-stated by an amount that is not highly probable to survive (a subsequent reversal restates prior revenue), the estimate is never revisited as facts change, and a change in the estimate does not TRUE-UP the revenue already recognized on satisfied obligations — breaching TFRS 15 / IFRS 15 / ASC 606 §50-59 (estimating variable consideration by expected value or most-likely amount, constraining it to the amount highly probable not to reverse, re-estimating each period and catching up prior revenue). A single person could also set AND bless the estimate (manage earnings via an aggressive, unreviewed judgement).","Valuation/Accuracy/Cutoff",
    "Variable-consideration estimate + the constraint, as a maker-checker management judgement (Track D Wave 2, TFRS 15 / IFRS 15 / ASC 606 §50-59). Extends the REV-19 fixed-price engine (does not rebuild it). (1) A MAKER records an estimate (POST …/variable-consideration) computed by EXPECTED VALUE (Σ probability × amount; probabilities must sum to 1 → INVALID_PROBABILITIES) OR MOST-LIKELY amount (§53). (2) THE CONSTRAINT (§56-58) is the reviewed control: only the CONSTRAINED amount (highly probable not to reverse) — never the gross estimate — drives the recognizable transaction price, and a constrained amount ABOVE the estimate is rejected as over-recognition (CONSTRAINT_EXCEEDS_ESTIMATE). (3) The estimate is a JUDGEMENT, so approval is MANDATORY before it drives revenue: a DIFFERENT user must approve it (POST …/variable-consideration/:vcId/approve; the estimator self-approving → 403 SOD_SELF_APPROVAL) and only an Approved estimate can be applied. (4) RE-ESTIMATE each period (POST …/reestimate) recomputes the transaction price (fixed base + constrained variable), re-allocates by SSP, rebuilds only the UNRECOGNIZED schedule, and TRUES-UP already-recognized revenue via a cumulative catch-up (§88) — building a contract asset (Dr 1265) when recognized ahead of billing, or releasing the contract liability (Dr 2410) when billed up-front — and is idempotent (a re-run with no new approved estimate posts nothing; also guarded by LedgerService.alreadyPosted). All posting routes through LedgerService.postEntry so the period lock (PERIOD_LOCKED, GL-15/16) + GL-17 audit bind; tenant-scoped (RLS). No new COA (2410/1265/4300 already exist + CF-classified).","Prev/Detect","Automated","Per estimate / re-estimate / period-end","Revenue Accountant / Controller","P10/P13",
    "revrec-variable/rev-variable.service.ts (recordEstimate expected_value/most_likely + CONSTRAINT_EXCEEDS_ESTIMATE / INVALID_PROBABILITIES; approveEstimate SOD_SELF_APPROVAL; reestimate recompute price + re-allocateBySSP + buildSchedule + cumulative catch-up Dr2410/Dr1265 / Cr4300, idempotent); rev-variable.controller.ts (/api/revenue/contracts/:id/variable-consideration POST|GET, :id/variable-consideration/:vcId/approve POST, :id/reestimate POST — gated exec/ar/fin_report); reuses revenue/revrec.service.ts (allocateBySSP/buildSchedule/sumRecognized); schema/revrec-variable.ts rev_variable_estimates + migration 0359 (0232-form RLS, leading (tenant_id, contract_id) index); COA 2410/1265/4300; cutover/revrec-variable.ts (ToE)","Inspect the two estimation methods (expected value vs most-likely) and the probability-sum check, the constraint gate that caps the recognizable amount at the estimate (CONSTRAINT_EXCEEDS_ESTIMATE), the estimator≠approver maker-checker (SOD_SELF_APPROVAL) with approval mandatory before recognition, and the re-estimate cumulative catch-up (price recompute → re-allocate → rebuild unrecognized → true-up already-recognized revenue) and its idempotency.","Re-perform (revrec-variable harness): recognize 400 of a 1000 fixed-price contract; record an expected-value estimate {200@50%,0@50%}=100 constrained to 80; reestimate before approval is a no-op (approval mandatory); the estimator self-approving → 403 SOD_SELF_APPROVAL; a different user approves; reestimate → price 1080 (constrained 80, not gross 100), catch-up 32 builds contract asset 1265 and lifts 4300; a second reestimate posts nothing (idempotent); most-likely {100@30%,300@70%}=300 with a constrained amount above the estimate → CONSTRAINT_EXCEEDS_ESTIMATE; on an up-front-billed contract the catch-up releases 2410 instead of building 1265; a second tenant sees 0 of the first tenant's estimates (RLS).","Variable-consideration estimate register (expected-value/most-likely + constrained amount); estimate maker-checker approval log; re-estimate true-up (catch-up delta) posting; period re-estimate history","Implemented")
add("REV-26","Revenue & Cash","Application","Recognized Revenue (4300); Contract Liability / Deferred Revenue (2410); Contract Asset / Unbilled Receivable (1265)","A contract MODIFICATION (added/changed goods or services, or a price change) is MIS-CLASSIFIED or applied on an ad-hoc basis — the three TFRS 15 / IFRS 15 / ASC 606 §18-21 outcomes are conflated, so revenue is mis-stated: added distinct goods at their standalone selling price are folded into the existing contract (understating a genuinely separate contract) instead of a NEW contract (§20); a distinct-but-not-at-SSP modification is either ignored or catch-up-adjusted (§21a is PROSPECTIVE — re-allocate the remaining transaction price over the remaining obligations, NO catch-up — so a wrongful catch-up over/under-states prior revenue); or a NOT-distinct modification (§21b) is treated prospectively and the REQUIRED cumulative catch-up on the already-satisfied portion is NEVER booked (revenue mis-stated in the period of change). A wrong 'separate_contract' call in particular HIDES a required catch-up. A single person could also set AND bless the classification (an aggressive, unreviewed judgement manages earnings).","Accuracy/Cutoff/Completeness",
    "Contract-modification classification & re-allocation as a maker-checker management judgement (Track D Wave 3, TFRS 15 / IFRS 15 / ASC 606 §18-21). Extends the REV-19 fixed-price engine (does not rebuild it; reuses createContract/allocateBySSP/buildSchedule/sumRecognized). A MAKER records a modification (POST …/modify) with the added/changed obligations, the added price, and the management judgements distinct_flag + at_ssp_flag; the service CLASSIFIES it into exactly one of three and this classification IS the control: (1) separate_contract (§20 — distinct AND at SSP) → a NEW independent contract is created and the ORIGINAL is left untouched (no re-allocation, no catch-up); (2) prospective (§21a — distinct but NOT at SSP) → the remaining (unrecognized) transaction price + the added price is RE-ALLOCATED over the remaining performance obligations by relative SSP with NO catch-up (already-recognized revenue is frozen); (3) cumulative_catchup (§21b — NOT distinct) → the transaction price is recomputed, re-allocated by SSP, and a cumulative CATCH-UP is posted on the already-satisfied portion (Dr 2410/1265 ↔ Cr 4300, same asset-aware split as recognition; a downward modification reverses). The modification is a JUDGEMENT, so approval is MANDATORY before it drives revenue: a Pending modification changes nothing, and a DIFFERENT user must approve it (POST …/modifications/:modId/approve; the maker self-approving → 403 SOD_SELF_APPROVAL; re-approving an applied modification → MODIFICATION_NOT_PENDING). Approval APPLIES the classified effect; the GL post is guarded by LedgerService.alreadyPosted (idempotent) so the period lock (PERIOD_LOCKED, GL-15/16) + GL-17 audit bind; tenant-scoped (RLS). No new COA (2410/1265/4300 already exist + CF-classified).","Prev/Detect","Automated","Per contract modification","Revenue Accountant / Controller","P10/P13",
    "revrec-modifications/rev-modification.service.ts (modify classifies §18-21 from distinct_flag/at_ssp_flag → separate_contract | prospective | cumulative_catchup, records Pending with a preview effect, drives nothing; approve SOD_SELF_APPROVAL + MODIFICATION_NOT_PENDING then applies: applySeparate creates a new linked contract via createContract/allocateBySSP/buildSchedule, applyProspective inserts distinct POs + re-allocates the remaining consideration over remaining POs by SSP + rebuilds the unrecognized schedule with no catch-up, applyCumulative re-allocateBySSP + scales recognized rows + buildSchedule + posts the catch-up Dr2410/Dr1265 / Cr4300); rev-modification.controller.ts (/api/revenue/contracts/:id/modify POST, :id/modifications/:modId/approve POST, :id/modifications GET — gated exec/ar/fin_report); reuses revenue/revrec.service.ts (createContract/allocateBySSP/buildSchedule/sumRecognized); schema/revrec-modifications.ts rev_contract_modifications + migration 0360 (0232-form RLS, leading (tenant_id, contract_id) index); COA 2410/1265/4300; cutover/revrec-modifications.ts (ToE)","Inspect the §18-21 classification (distinct×at-SSP → the three outcomes), that separate_contract leaves the original untouched and creates a new contract, that prospective re-allocates the remaining price over remaining POs with no catch-up, that cumulative_catchup posts a catch-up on the satisfied portion, and the maker≠approver maker-checker (SOD_SELF_APPROVAL) with approval mandatory before it drives revenue.","Re-perform (revrec-modifications harness): recognize 400 of a 1000 contract; a NOT-distinct +200 modification classifies cumulative_catchup and (after a distinct approver — self-approve → SOD_SELF_APPROVAL) posts an 80 catch-up (Dr 1265 / Cr 4300) lifting recognized revenue to 480; a distinct-not-at-SSP +300 modification classifies prospective, re-allocates the remaining 900 over the remaining POs (Support 600→540, Add-on 360, satisfied Setup frozen at 400) with catch_up_delta 0 and no revenue movement; a distinct-at-SSP +500 modification classifies separate_contract, creating a new linked contract (total 500, PO 500) while the original stays total 1000 / recognized 400; a Pending modification drives nothing and re-approving an applied one → MODIFICATION_NOT_PENDING; a second tenant sees 0 of the first tenant's modifications (RLS).","Contract-modification register (type/added_price/distinct_flag/at_ssp_flag/effect_amount + new_contract_id link); modification maker-checker approval log (created_by/approved_by); cumulative catch-up (REVREC-MOD) posting; re-allocation schedule rebuild","Implemented")
add("REV-27","Revenue & Cash","Application","Contract Liability / Deferred Revenue (2410); Contract Asset / Unbilled Receivable (1265); Significant Financing Component Interest Income (4650); Interest Expense (5900); Recognized Revenue (4300)","A contract whose payment timing gives a MATERIAL financing benefit is recognized at the undiscounted (face) price — the significant financing component is ignored, so revenue is mis-stated (over-stated when the customer prepays, understated when payment is deferred) and the interest element is never separated from the revenue element, breaching TFRS 15 / IFRS 15 / ASC 606 §60-65 (adjust the promised consideration to its cash-selling-price present value and recognize the financing component as interest over the contract). Separately, the §120 DISCLOSURES are incomplete or do not tie to the ledger: the contract-liability rollforward (opening → billings → recognized → closing) does not reconcile to the GL contract-liability (2410) / contract-asset (1265) control accounts, and the remaining-performance-obligation (RPO / backlog) is not disclosed — so a reader cannot see how much revenue is deferred, how it moved, or how much is still to be delivered. The DISCOUNT RATE is a management judgement a single person could set AND bless (an aggressive/omitted rate manages the revenue↔interest split).","Valuation/Presentation & Disclosure/Completeness",
    "Significant-financing-component rate as a maker-checker judgement + a GL-reconciled revenue-disclosure pack (Track D Wave 4, TFRS 15 / IFRS 15 / ASC 606 §60-65 + §120). Extends the REV-19 recognition engine + Wave 1 billing (does not rebuild them; reuses the contract-asset 1265 / contract-liability 2410 balances). (A) Financing component (§60-65): a MAKER flags a material financing component and sets the discount rate (POST …/financing-component); the service discounts the transaction price to its cash-selling-price PRESENT VALUE and schedules the interest UNWIND by the effective-interest method (the same EIR primitive the lease engine uses, LSE-01) so Σ interest == face − PV exactly. The rows land Pending and DRIVE NOTHING until a DIFFERENT user approves the rate (POST …/financing-component/approve; the maker self-approving → 403 SOD_SELF_APPROVAL); run-financing on an un-approved component → FINANCING_NOT_APPROVED. Only an APPROVED component posts (POST …/run-financing, idempotent via LedgerService.alreadyPosted): advance (customer prepays — the entity BORROWS from the customer) Dr 5900 / Cr 2410 (interest expense; the contract liability accretes from PV toward face); arrears (deferred payment — the entity LENDS to the customer) Dr 1265 / Cr 4650 (interest income; the contract asset accretes from PV toward face). (B) Disclosure pack (§120): the contract-liability rollforward (GET …/disclosure/contract-liability-rollforward) reconstructs opening → additions (billings) → recognized → closing over 2410/1265 DIRECTLY from the GL journal lines so it RECONCILES to GL by construction (opening + additions − reductions = closing = GL); the RPO / backlog (GET …/disclosure/rpo) = Σ unrecognized allocated price, banded by expected timing (≤12m / >12m). All GL routes through LedgerService.postEntry so the period lock (PERIOD_LOCKED, GL-15/16) + GL-17 audit bind; tenant-scoped (RLS). New COA 4650 (added to the canonical COA + CF_CLASSIFY operating); the advance case reuses 5900.","Prev/Detect","Automated","Per financing component / per period disclosure","Revenue Accountant / Controller","P10/P13",
    "revrec-disclosure/rev-financing.service.ts (setFinancingComponent discounts to PV + builds the EIR unwind schedule so Σ interest = face − PV, records Pending; approveFinancingComponent SOD_SELF_APPROVAL flips Pending→Approved; runFinancing posts advance Dr5900/Cr2410 or arrears Dr1265/Cr4650, FINANCING_NOT_APPROVED guard, idempotent) + rev-disclosure.service.ts (contractLiabilityRollforward decomposes the GL 2410/1265 movements by source and reconciles closing to the GL balance; rpo sums unrecognized revrec_schedules planned amounts with a 12-month timing band); rev-disclosure.controller.ts (/api/revenue/contracts/:id/financing-component POST + /approve POST + GET, :id/run-financing POST, /api/revenue/disclosure/contract-liability-rollforward GET, /disclosure/rpo GET — gated exec/ar/fin_report); schema/revrec-disclosure.ts rev_financing_schedules + migration 0367 (0232-form RLS, leading (tenant_id, contract_id) index); ledger-constants.ts COA 4650 + CF_CLASSIFY; posting-events.ts REVFIN.INCOME/REVFIN.EXPENSE; bi report types contract_liability_rollforward + rpo_backlog; cutover/revrec-disclosure.ts (ToE)","Inspect that a material financing component discounts the transaction price to PV and unwinds the interest so Σ interest equals face − PV, that the discount-rate judgement is maker-checker (maker ≠ approver, SOD_SELF_APPROVAL) with an un-approved component unable to post (FINANCING_NOT_APPROVED), that advance (customer prepays) posts interest expense to 5900 with the contract liability 2410 accreting and arrears (deferred payment) posts interest income to 4650 with the contract asset 1265 accreting, and that the §120 contract-liability rollforward reconciles to the GL 2410/1265 control accounts and the RPO equals the unrecognized allocated price.","Re-perform (revrec-disclosure harness): a 1200 face at 12%/yr over 12 months discounts to PV 1064.94 and Σ interest 135.06 = face − PV, last closing balance = 1200; the maker self-approving → SOD_SELF_APPROVAL and run-before-approval → FINANCING_NOT_APPROVED; a different checker approves and run-financing posts 12 periods of interest EXPENSE to 5900 with the contract liability 2410 accreting toward face (idempotent re-run posts 0); an arrears component accretes the contract asset 1265 against interest income 4650; the contract-liability rollforward reads opening 0 + billings 300 − recognized 100 = closing 200 = GL 2410; the RPO = 900 unrecognized allocated price banded within 12 months; a second tenant sees 0 of the first tenant's financing/RPO (RLS).","Financing-component schedule (PV/face/interest + EIR unwind) with the discount-rate maker-checker approval log (created_by/approved_by); REVFIN interest postings (4650/5900); §120 contract-liability rollforward reconciled to GL; RPO / backlog by contract with timing band","Implemented")
add("CRM-07","Revenue & Cash","Application","Revenue (pipeline / account planning)","B2B account relationships are ungoverned — a company's parent/subsidiary structure is not modelled (so pipeline cannot be rolled up to the buying group, and re-parented accounts can loop), a deal is worked without documenting WHO decides (no buying committee, so the forecast rests on a single unverified contact), and there is no account plan (owner, target, product-line coverage) — so strategic accounts are pursued ad-hoc, whitespace (un-targeted product lines) is invisible, and the account-based revenue forecast is unreliable.","Accuracy/Completeness/Authorization",
    "B2B account/contact 360 DEPTH (CRM-7, migration 0365) on the REV-17 CRM spine. Account HIERARCHY: crm_accounts gains a self-referential parent_account_id; PATCH /api/crm/accounts/:no/parent rejects a self-parent (SELF_PARENT) and any link that would close a loop (HIERARCHY_CYCLE), and GET /api/crm/accounts/:no/hierarchy returns the ancestor chain + direct children + a SUBTREE pipeline roll-up (Σ open weighted amount across the account and all descendants) so pipeline ties to the buying group; a survivor-merge re-parents the duplicate's child accounts so the hierarchy stays intact. Buying COMMITTEE: crm_opportunity_contacts records which contacts sit on a deal, each with a role (decision_maker/champion/influencer/evaluator/blocker/user) + influence weight — a committee contact must belong to the deal's account (CONTACT_ACCOUNT_MISMATCH), a contact appears at most once per deal (COMMITTEE_DUP), and at most one is_primary. Account PLANS: crm_account_plans is a GOVERNED draft -> active -> closed plan carrying an owner, objective, strategy, target revenue and target product categories validated against item_categories (UNKNOWN_CATEGORY); a plan activates only when it has an owner AND an objective (PLAN_INCOMPLETE), the lifecycle is enforced (PLAN_NOT_DRAFT / PLAN_NOT_ACTIVE, a closed plan is immutable PLAN_CLOSED), and GET /api/crm/accounts/:no/whitespace surfaces the product categories the account is NOT yet being pursued for (active item_categories minus the union of active-plan targets). All three tables tenant-scoped (RLS, canonical 0232 policy, tenant-leading indexes); the surface gates crm/exec/ar. No GL post.","Prev/Det","Automated","Per account / continuous","Sales / Account Manager / Sales Manager","P13",
    "modules/crm/account-depth/crm-account-depth.module.ts (setParent SELF_PARENT/HIERARCHY_CYCLE cycle guard; hierarchy ancestors+children+subtree open-weighted roll-up; addCommitteeMember CONTACT_ACCOUNT_MISMATCH/COMMITTEE_DUP + single is_primary; listCommittee/removeCommitteeMember; createPlan APL- + target-category validation UNKNOWN_CATEGORY; updatePlan PLAN_CLOSED guard; activatePlan PLAN_NOT_DRAFT/PLAN_INCOMPLETE; closePlan PLAN_NOT_ACTIVE; whitespace active-plan targets vs item_categories); crm/accounts/crm-accounts.module.ts (merge re-parents child accounts); schema/crm-pipeline.ts crm_accounts.parent_account_id + crm_opportunity_contacts + crm_account_plans + migration 0365 (RLS, tenant-leading indexes); cutover/pipeline.ts (ToE, CRM-7 checks)","Inspect the account-hierarchy cycle guard + subtree pipeline roll-up, the buying-committee account-membership + uniqueness + single-primary rules, the account-plan draft->active->closed lifecycle + category validation, and the whitespace derivation.","Re-perform: link a subsidiary under a parent, then parenting the parent under its own child -> HIERARCHY_CYCLE; the hierarchy read rolls a child's open deal into the parent's subtree weighted pipeline; add a buying-committee member (is_primary) then re-add the same contact -> COMMITTEE_DUP and a contact from another account -> CONTACT_ACCOUNT_MISMATCH; create an account plan (APL-) with a valid target category, an unknown category -> UNKNOWN_CATEGORY, activate a complete draft -> active, re-activate -> PLAN_NOT_DRAFT, activate an incomplete draft -> PLAN_INCOMPLETE, close -> closed; whitespace reports the targeted category as covered and the rest as whitespace; a T1 user sees none of HQ's account plans (RLS) (re-performed by the pipeline harness CRM-7 checks).","Account hierarchy + subtree pipeline roll-up; buying-committee register (role/influence/primary); governed account-plan lifecycle + whitespace coverage read","Implemented")
add("CRM-08","Revenue & Cash","Application","Revenue (retention / renewal pipeline)","A strategic B2B account slips toward CHURN with no early warning — declining engagement (deals go quiet, no activity logged), open support cases pile up (escalated / SLA-breached), the pipeline dries up — and no one notices until the account has effectively lapsed; and renewal/expansion revenue is not tracked as its own forward pipeline, so a due renewal is simply missed (a won account with no renewal in flight silently drops off). The account-based retention forecast is unreliable and revenue is lost to neglect rather than to a competitor on the merits.","Completeness/Accuracy/Timeliness",
    "B2B account HEALTH / churn surveillance + renewal-expansion pipeline (CRM-15, migration 0370) — a read-only DETECTIVE layer on the REV-17 CRM spine. A per-account health SCORE is computed by an EXPLAINABLE, code-reviewed weighted formula (base 60, clamped 0..100, with a persisted per-factor breakdown — same posture as the CRM-4 lead score, no trained model) from ACCOUNT-SPECIFIC signals: engagement recency (days since the last activity logged across the account's deals), open pipeline (Σ open weighted amount), open / escalated (P1-P2) / SLA-breached support cases (service_cases, SVC-4/5, grouped by account), and win/loss balance; the score is BANDED healthy (≥70) / watch (40-69) / at_risk (<40) and GET /api/crm/account-health returns the CHURN WATCHLIST ranked worst-first with band counts (filterable by band). RENEWAL/EXPANSION opportunities are tagged crm_opportunities.deal_type (new|renewal|expansion; PATCH /api/crm/opportunities/:no/deal-type) and GET /api/crm/account-health/renewals is the forward pipeline (Σ weighted) PLUS the renewal GAP queue — accounts with a won deal but NO open renewal (the churn-risk population). A schedulable daily SNAPSHOT (POST /api/crm/account-health/snapshot / BI report crm_account_health) persists the score to crm_account_health_snapshots (upsert per account/day, mirrors project_health_snapshots) for trend (GET …/health/history). The company AR/credit position (creditStatus) is surfaced as CONTEXT (tenant-level, company_level=true) but deliberately NOT folded into the per-account score. Tenant-scoped (RLS, canonical 0232 policy, tenant-leading indexes); the surface gates crm/exec/ar (snapshot crm/exec). No GL post.","Det","Automated","Per account / daily","Sales Manager / Account Manager / Customer Success","P13",
    "modules/crm/account-health/crm-account-health.module.ts (computeHealth explainable weighted score + band + breakdown; gatherSignals 4 grouped queries — open pipeline / last-activity join opps⋈activities / open-escalated-breached cases by account; accountHealth; portfolio churn watchlist ranked worst-first + band filter + counts; renewalPipeline forward pipeline + renewal-gap queue; setDealType new/renewal/expansion; captureAllHealth idempotent snapshot per account/day; healthHistory trend); schema/crm-pipeline.ts crm_opportunities.deal_type + crm_account_health_snapshots + migration 0370 (RLS, tenant-leading indexes); service_cases (tenant_id, account_id) index; bi report-registry crm_account_health + bi-generate crm_account_health branch (captureAllHealth action job); cutover/pipeline.ts (ToE, CRM-15 checks)","Inspect the explainable per-account health formula (engagement / pipeline / support-case / win-loss factors + banding), the churn watchlist ranking, the renewal/expansion pipeline + renewal-gap detection, and the idempotent snapshot + trend.","Re-perform: an engaged account (recent activity + open deal) scores in the healthy band with an explainable breakdown; an account with open escalated + SLA-breached cases and no open pipeline scores in the at_risk band; tagging a deal renewal surfaces it in the renewal pipeline (weighted); a won account with no open renewal is flagged a renewal gap; the portfolio watchlist ranks at_risk first and filters by band; a snapshot captures a dated score per account (re-run same day is idempotent) and appears in the account's health history; the crm_account_health report type is registered; a second tenant cannot read the first tenant's account health (RLS) (re-performed by the pipeline harness CRM-15 checks).","Per-account health score register (band + explainable breakdown) + churn watchlist; renewal/expansion forward pipeline + renewal-gap queue; daily health snapshot + trend","Implemented")
add("CRM-09","Revenue & Cash","Application","Revenue (sales forecast governance)","The sales forecast reported to management is UNGOVERNED — it rests on a single system-weighted number with no rep->manager accountability (a rep's own commit is never captured or reconciled, so over-optimism or sandbagging is invisible), it is never SNAPSHOTTED so forecast-vs-actual accuracy cannot be measured after the fact, and pipeline COVERAGE (open pipeline vs the commit target) is not tracked — so a thin, unbacked forecast or a quota with too little pipeline behind it goes unnoticed until the period closes short.","Accuracy/Completeness/Timeliness",
    "Sales FORECASTING depth (CRM-12, migration 0378) — a governance layer over the REV-17 pipeline forecast. Rep->manager OVERRIDE roll-up: crm_forecast_submissions records per (period, owner) a rep's own commit / best-case / pipeline number under a governed draft->submitted status (POST /api/crm/forecast/submission, upsert per period/owner); GET /api/crm/forecast/depth is the MANAGER ROLL-UP — each rep's submitted forecast reconciled against the system-weighted forecast (commit at full value + best-case/pipeline risk-weighted) with the VARIANCE surfaced, plus totals, a category WATERFALL (commit -> best-case -> pipeline build-up of the forecast) and pipeline COVERAGE (open pipeline / the submitted-commit target, >=3x healthy). Dated SNAPSHOTS: a schedulable period snapshot (POST /api/crm/forecast/snapshot / BI report crm_forecast_snapshot) persists the forecast + the period's ACTUAL won to crm_forecast_snapshots (idempotent per period/day, mirrors crm_account_health_snapshots), so GET /api/crm/forecast/history is the forecast-vs-actual ACCURACY trend (actual / forecast per period). Both tables tenant-scoped (RLS, canonical 0232 policy, tenant-leading indexes); the surface gates crm/exec/ar (submission + snapshot crm/exec). No GL post.","Det","Automated","Per period / continuous","Sales Manager / Sales Operations / VP Sales","P13",
    "modules/crm/forecast/crm-forecast.module.ts (systemByOwner weighted forecast by rep; depth manager roll-up — system vs submitted forecast + variance + totals; forecastOf commit-full + best-case/pipeline weighted; waterfall category build-up; coverage open-pipeline / submitted-or-system commit target; submit rep override upsert draft->submitted; listSubmissions; captureSnapshot idempotent per period/day + actual-won-in-period; accuracy/history forecast-vs-actual trend); schema/crm-pipeline.ts crm_forecast_submissions + crm_forecast_snapshots + migration 0378 (RLS, tenant-leading indexes); bi report-registry crm_forecast_snapshot + bi-generate crm_forecast_snapshot branch (captureSnapshot action job); cutover/pipeline.ts (ToE, CRM-12 checks)","Inspect the rep->manager submission roll-up + system-vs-submitted variance, the pipeline-coverage ratio, the category waterfall, and the idempotent period snapshot + forecast-vs-actual accuracy trend.","Re-perform: a rep submits a period commit/best-case (draft->submitted) and it appears in the manager roll-up reconciled against the system-weighted forecast with the variance; the coverage ratio = open pipeline / the submitted-commit target; the waterfall's commit->best-case->pipeline stages build up to the forecast total; capturing a snapshot persists the forecast + the period's actual won (re-run same day is idempotent) and the history shows the forecast-vs-actual accuracy %; the crm_forecast_snapshot report type is registered; a second tenant cannot read the first tenant's submissions/snapshots (RLS) (re-performed by the pipeline harness CRM-12 checks).","Rep->manager forecast-override roll-up + system-vs-submitted variance; pipeline-coverage + category waterfall; dated forecast snapshot + forecast-vs-actual accuracy trend","Implemented")
add("CRM-10","Revenue & Cash","Application","Revenue (territory / quota governance)","Sales territories and quotas are NOT persisted governed master data — a territory's boundaries (regions / segments / product lines) and the reps that own it live in spreadsheets or someone's head, and quota attainment is measured against an ad-hoc number passed at report time rather than an approved target. So there is no auditable link from a rep's result to an owned territory + an agreed quota, no team roll-up of attainment up the sales hierarchy, and a rep's or a region's shortfall to plan is invisible until the period closes.","Accuracy/Completeness/Authorization",
    "Persisted TERRITORY & QUOTA management (CRM-11, migration 0385) — a governance layer over the REV-17 pipeline. crm_territories is named territory master data with match CRITERIA (regions / segments / product categories, jsonb), a self-referential parent_territory_id for a team ROLL-UP hierarchy, and a manager; crm_territory_members assigns reps (role rep | manager); crm_quotas holds a per-period TARGET for an owner or a territory (scope + subject, upsert per period/scope/subject) so attainment is measured against an auditable quota rather than a number passed at request time. GET /api/crm/territory/attainment is the roll-up: won-in-period per owner vs the owner quota, and per territory the Σ of its members' won across the whole SUBTREE vs the territory quota (a parent's attainment includes its descendants). POST /api/crm/territory/territories[/:code/members], POST /api/crm/territory/quotas gate crm/exec; reads gate crm/exec/ar. All three tables tenant-scoped (RLS, canonical 0232 policy, tenant-leading indexes). No GL post.","Det","Automated","Per period / continuous","Sales Operations / Sales Manager / VP Sales","P13",
    "modules/crm/territory/crm-territory.module.ts (createTerritory TERR- code + parent link; listTerritories; getTerritory members+children; addMember/removeMember upsert; setQuota owner|territory upsert per period/scope/subject; attainment — won-in-period per owner vs owner quota + territory subtree roll-up vs territory quota via recursive subtreeWon); schema/crm-pipeline.ts crm_territories + crm_territory_members + crm_quotas + migration 0385 (RLS, tenant-leading indexes); cutover/pipeline.ts (ToE, CRM-11 checks)","Inspect the territory hierarchy + criteria, the rep-membership assignment, the per-period owner/territory quota persistence, and the attainment roll-up (owner vs quota, territory subtree vs quota).","Re-perform: create a parent + child territory and assign a rep to the child; set an owner quota + a territory quota for the period; a won deal for the rep counts toward its owner attainment (won vs quota) and rolls up into the parent territory's subtree_won vs the territory quota; the territory read lists its members; a second tenant cannot see the first tenant's territories (RLS) (re-performed by the pipeline harness CRM-11 checks).","Territory master + criteria + hierarchy; rep-membership register; per-period owner/territory quota; attainment roll-up (owner + territory subtree)","Implemented")
add("CRM-11","Revenue & Cash","Application","Revenue (lead / deal nurture cadence)","Multi-step outreach on leads and open deals is manual and ungoverned — a rep is meant to touch a prospect on a cadence (day 0 email, day 3 call, day 7 follow-up) but there is no playbook and no tracking, so a nurtured lead or deal silently DROPS OUT of the follow-up (a step is skipped or forgotten), the touches are not logged as auditable activity, and there is no way to run the due outreach systematically. Revenue is lost to inconsistent, unrecorded follow-up rather than on the merits.","Completeness/Timeliness","Det","Automated","Per enrolment / continuous","Sales / SDR / Sales Manager","P13",
    "Sales SEQUENCES / cadences (CRM-8, migration 0392) on the REV-17 spine + the CRM-6 comms rail. crm_sequences is a named playbook; crm_sequence_steps is its ordered steps (channel email/line/sms/task + wait_days + subject/body); crm_sequence_enrollments enrols a lead or opportunity (unique per sequence/entity, ALREADY_ENROLLED guard; SEQUENCE_INACTIVE / SEQUENCE_NO_STEPS / ENTITY_NOT_FOUND guards). The due-runner ADVANCES each active enrolment whose next step is due: it sends the step via MessagingService (best-effort; a 'task' step is a reminder only), LOGS the touch as an auditable crm_activities entry (source='sequence'), and schedules the next step by its wait_days — until the last step (status -> completed). A rep may stop an enrolment (status -> stopped); advancing a non-active enrolment is rejected (ENROLLMENT_NOT_ACTIVE). POST /api/crm/sequences[/:code/enroll], POST …/enrollments/:id/[advance|stop], POST …/run-due (crm/exec); the run-due sweep is schedulable as the BI report crm_sequence_run (module-owned BiReportSource provider, docs/46). Reads gate crm/exec/ar. Three tables tenant-scoped (RLS, canonical 0232 policy, tenant-leading indexes). No GL post.","Det","Automated","Per enrolment / continuous","Sales / SDR / Sales Manager","P13",
    "modules/crm/sequences/crm-sequences.module.ts (createSequence SEQ- code + steps; listSequences/getSequence; enroll — entity + active + steps guards, ALREADY_ENROLLED; advance — send via MessagingService best-effort + log crm_activities source='sequence' + schedule next by wait_days + complete on last step; stop; runDue due sweep; CrmSequenceBiReports BiReportSource crm_sequence_run); schema/crm-pipeline.ts crm_sequences + crm_sequence_steps + crm_sequence_enrollments + migration 0392 (RLS, tenant-leading indexes); bi report-registry crm_sequence_run; cutover/pipeline.ts (ToE, CRM-8 checks)","Inspect the sequence + steps definition, the enrolment guards, the advance send + activity logging + next-step scheduling, the completion + stop lifecycle, and the schedulable due-runner.","Re-perform: create a 2-step cadence (email now + a task after 3 days); enrol a lead (active, first step due now); advance step 1 -> the email is executed and logged as a sequence activity, enrolment stays active; advance the last step -> enrolment completes and further advance is rejected (ENROLLMENT_NOT_ACTIVE); the due-runner advances a fresh due enrolment; an enrolment can be stopped; the crm_sequence_run report type is registered; a second tenant cannot see the first tenant's sequences (RLS) (re-performed by the pipeline harness CRM-8 checks).","Sequence + step playbook; enrolment register; cadence advance with logged touches + next-step scheduling; completion/stop lifecycle; schedulable due-runner","Implemented")
add("CRM-12","Revenue & Cash","Application","Revenue (CPQ bundles / tiered discount authority)","CPQ bundle pricing and large-discount authority are ungoverned: a bundle (multiple products sold as one SKU, priced below the sum of parts) has no product-cost basis captured, so a bundle's blended margin can silently fall below the company's floor without CPQ-01's per-line check ever seeing it; and EVERY breach of the discount ceiling — a 6% overage or a 60% giveaway — routes to the same single approver tier, so there is no escalation to executive sign-off for a materially larger discount. Bundles can hide margin erosion, and a large discount clears the SAME low bar as a small one.","Occurrence/Accuracy/Authorization",
    "CPQ guided selling depth (CRM-14, migration 0399) — extends CPQ-01, no new maker-checker rail. BUNDLES: cpq_bundles/cpq_bundle_items define a bundle SKU with each component's cost captured; POST …/quotes/:id/lines/bundle EXPANDS the bundle into ordinary quote_lines (bundle_code-tagged, one row per component carrying its captured unit_cost) — so the EXISTING CPQ-01 metricsFromLines()/sendQuote() floor check automatically covers the bundle's blended margin with NO core-service duplication; a bundle cannot be used to hide margin erosion. TIERED discount-approval matrix: cpq_settings.exec_discount_pct is an optional second, higher discount ceiling; a breach at/under it still needs any cpq_approve holder (manager tier, CPQ-01 unchanged), but a breach ABOVE it requires a caller holding `exec` specifically (quote_approvals.required_tier records which tier applied; TIER_APPROVAL_REQUIRED on a mismatched approver) — so a materially larger discount escalates past the standard approver. GUIDED SELLING: GET /api/cpq/recommendations is a read-only, EXPLAINABLE co-purchase surface (which other configs the same customer bought in a different Accepted quote, ranked by frequency — no trained model, mirrors the G2 market-basket-affinity posture) — informational, not itself a control. Bundle/recommendation reads gate exec/cpq; bundle creation is masterdata (mirrors config/rule creation). Two new tenant tables + three ALTERs (0232 RLS, tenant-leading indexes).","Prev","Automated","Per quote send / approval","Sales / Sales Manager / Executive","P10",
    "cpq.service.ts (createBundle/listBundles/getBundle; addBundleLine expands a bundle instance into bundle_code-tagged quote_lines with captured component unit_cost; sendQuote computes requiredTier from exec_discount_pct and stamps quote_approvals.required_tier; approveDiscount enforces the exec-tier gate — TIER_APPROVAL_REQUIRED when a non-exec cpq_approve holder attempts an exec-tier approval; getSettings/updateSettings expose exec_discount_pct; recommendations co-purchase read over quotes.configId + bundle-expanded quote_lines.itemCode); cpq.controller.ts (/api/cpq/bundles[/:code], /api/cpq/quotes/:id/lines/bundle, /api/cpq/recommendations); schema/cpq.ts cpq_bundles + cpq_bundle_items + quote_lines.bundle_code + cpq_settings.exec_discount_pct + quote_approvals.required_tier, migration 0399; cutover/cpq-approval.ts (ToE, CRM-14 checks)","Inspect the bundle-to-quote_lines expansion (captured component cost, no core floor-check change), the exec-tier threshold computation on send + the enforced approver-tier check on approve, and the co-purchase recommendation read.","Re-perform (cpq-approval harness): create a 2-component bundle (one thin-margin, one healthy) and add it to a Draft quote -> 2 bundle-tagged lines; sending the quote catches the BLENDED margin breach via the unmodified CPQ-01 check -> PendingApproval, and a plain cpq_approve holder (no exec) clears it (margin-only breach stays manager-tier); set an exec-tier discount ceiling, add a healthy-margin bundle with a discount above it -> PendingApproval, a plain cpq_approve holder is BLOCKED (403 TIER_APPROVAL_REQUIRED), an exec-permission holder clears it; accepting the bundle quote then makes its components surface as a mutual recommendation; a second tenant cannot see the first tenant's bundle (RLS).","Bundle master + component cost register; bundle-expansion audit trail (shared quote_lines, CPQ-01 floor coverage); tiered discount-approval log (required_tier on quote_approvals); co-purchase recommendation read","Implemented")
add("CRM-13","Revenue & Cash","Application","Revenue (pipeline stage governance)","The sales pipeline advances with NO governed exit criteria and NO work-in-progress discipline: a deal is dragged into a later stage (Qualified / Proposal / Negotiation) with no deal amount, no expected close and no contact of record — so the weighted revenue forecast rests on empty, unqualified deals — and there is no cap on how many open deals may sit in a stage, so a stage silently overloads and deals stall unworked. Pipeline hygiene is unenforced and the stage-weighted forecast is unreliable.","Accuracy/Completeness/Authorization",
    "CRM-7 kanban depth (migration 0406) — a per-stage PLAYBOOK on the REV-17 pipeline enforced server-side in the SAME governed setStage path (so it binds on the board drag, the list 'Move to…', and the bulk multi-select alike). Each stage may define (a) REQUIRED-FIELD exit criteria: a whitelist-validated set of opportunity fields (amount / expected close / primary contact / account / customer / owner / notes) that must be POPULATED before a deal can advance INTO the stage — an unmet move is refused STAGE_REQUIREMENTS_UNMET listing the missing fields (skipped only for Lost, since abandoning a deal is never blocked on data-completeness); and (b) a WIP LIMIT: a cap on how many OPEN opportunities may sit in the stage at once — a move that would exceed it is refused WIP_LIMIT_EXCEEDED (ignored for the terminal Won/Lost stages). Configuring a playbook (WIP limit + required fields + coaching guidance) is a supervisor duty (crm/exec; an unknown required-field key is rejected BAD_REQUIRED_FIELDS, a negative cap BAD_WIP_LIMIT); the config is tenant master data (HQ with no tenant cannot set a tenant playbook). Every resulting stage move remains audited in crm_stage_history (REV-17). One tenant table (crm_stage_playbooks, RLS 0232, tenant-leading index); reads gate crm/exec/ar. No GL post.","Prev","Automated","Per stage move","Sales / Sales Manager","P13",
    "crm-stage-playbook.service.ts (assertStageEntry — the required-field + WIP gate called from setStage; listView — stages + playbook config + live open counts for the board WIP badge; putPlaybook — whitelist-validated upsert, BAD_REQUIRED_FIELDS/BAD_WIP_LIMIT/TENANT_REQUIRED); crm-pipeline.service.ts setStage (invokes the gate before the write) + bulkSetStage (per-item result over the governed path); crm-pipeline.controller.ts (GET /api/crm/pipeline/playbooks, PUT …/playbooks/:stageId gated crm/exec, POST …/opportunities/bulk-stage); schema/crm-pipeline.ts crm_stage_playbooks + migration 0406; web crm-client.tsx (WIP badge + required-field/guidance on the kanban column, supervisor playbook editor, list-view bulk move); cutover/pipeline.ts (ToE, CRM-7 checks)","Inspect the per-stage playbook config (WIP limit + whitelist-validated required fields + guidance), the enforced required-field + WIP gates on setStage (both refusal codes), the bulk move riding the SAME governed path, and the supervisor-only / tenant-scoped configuration.","Re-perform (pipeline harness, CRM-7 checks): configure the Qualified stage with a required amount + a WIP cap; advancing a no-amount deal into Qualified is refused STAGE_REQUIREMENTS_UNMET (missing amount); a sized deal advances; the next sized deal past the cap is refused WIP_LIMIT_EXCEEDED (limit echoed); clearing the WIP limit (null) then admits it; a bulk stage move advances a multi-select and reports per-item moved/failed (a valid deal succeeds while an unknown opp fails NOT_FOUND — never atomic across deals); an unknown required-field key is rejected BAD_REQUIRED_FIELDS; HQ (no tenant) cannot configure a T1 stage playbook.","Stage playbook config (WIP limit + required-field exit criteria + guidance); enforced STAGE_REQUIREMENTS_UNMET / WIP_LIMIT_EXCEEDED gate; bulk-move per-item audit; crm_stage_history trail","Implemented")
add("CRM-14","Revenue & Cash","Application","Revenue (customer-interaction record)","The record of what actually happened on a deal is FRAGMENTED and MUTABLE — a customer's touches are scattered across separate lists (activities in one place, stage changes in another, comms and cadence touches elsewhere) with no single chronological view, so an auditor (or a rep taking over the account) cannot reconstruct the interaction history and a lost/disputed deal cannot be reviewed end-to-end; and internal collaboration/decision notes on the deal, where recorded at all, can be silently edited or deleted after the fact — so the account's decision trail is neither complete nor tamper-evident, and a colleague flagged for input is not reliably notified.","Completeness/Timeliness/Accuracy",
    "CRM-8 unified activity timeline + collaboration feed (migration 0407). ONE canonical, tenant-scoped, newest-first read (GET /api/crm/timeline?entity_type=&entity_no=) merges EVERY touch on a lead/opportunity/account into a single chronological stream: activities across all channels (call/email/meeting/note/task incl. outbound comms 'comms', inbound replies 'inbound', cadence touches 'sequence'), stage transitions (crm_stage_history), and linked CPQ quotes — an account rolls up its opportunities' streams — so the interaction history is reconstructable in one place, nothing siloed. The COLLABORATION FEED (crm_feed_posts) is APPEND-ONLY: a posted internal note is immutable (no update/delete path — the schema carries no updated_at and no mutation endpoint exists), so the decision/collaboration trail on the customer record cannot be silently rewritten; @-mentions in a note are validated against the tenant's ACTIVE users (unknown/other-tenant handles dropped) and each mentioned user is routed a DIRECTED notification (notifications.target_username — visible only to that user within the tenant, additive + backward-compatible with the role/broadcast rail). Entities are existence-checked in the caller's tenant before any read/write (BOLA-safe; unknown entity -> 404, bad entity_type -> 400). Reads gate crm/exec/ar; one tenant table (crm_feed_posts, RLS 0232, tenant-leading index) + one directed-target column on notifications. No GL post.","Det","Automated","Per interaction / continuous","Sales / Sales Manager / IA","P13",
    "crm-timeline.service.ts (timeline — merges crm_activities all-sources + crm_stage_history + linked quotes + crm_feed_posts, account rolls up its opportunities; listFeed; postFeed — append-only insert + validateMentions against active tenant users + directed notification per mention; requireEntity BOLA existence check); crm-timeline.controller.ts (GET /api/crm/timeline, GET/POST /api/crm/feed, gated crm/exec/ar); notifications.module.ts visibleTo (widened for target_username — directed rows visible only to that user, legacy NULL rows unchanged); schema/crm-pipeline.ts crm_feed_posts + schema/system.ts notifications.target_username + migration 0407; web deals/[oppNo]/deal-client.tsx (feed composer + @mention highlight, feed folded into the deal timeline); cutover/pipeline.ts (ToE, CRM-8 timeline/feed checks)","Inspect the unified timeline merge (all activity sources + stage history + quotes + feed in one sorted stream; account roll-up), the append-only feed (no mutation path), the @mention validation + directed-notification routing, and the BOLA existence checks.","Re-perform (pipeline harness, CRM-8 checks): a deal's timeline merges an activity + two stage transitions + a feed note into one newest-first stream; a feed note posts (201) with a valid @mention resolved and an unknown @handle dropped; the mentioned user receives a directed notification while the AUTHOR does not; an account timeline rolls up its opportunity's activity; posting/reading a timeline for an unknown opportunity is refused 404 NOT_FOUND and a bad entity_type 400.","Unified customer-interaction timeline (all sources); append-only collaboration feed; directed @mention notifications; BOLA existence checks","Implemented")
add("CRM-15","Revenue & Cash","Application","Revenue (quote pricing basis)","Quote unit prices are TYPED FREELY per line — there is no governed, approved price list a quote must draw from, so the price a rep quotes has no auditable basis (was it the current list price? an expired promo? a number invented at the desk?), the same item can be quoted at different prices across reps with nothing to reconcile against, and a superseded price keeps being used because nothing enforces an effective date. Revenue is quoted off an ungoverned, unauditable price basis.","Accuracy/Completeness/Authorization",
    "CPQ PRICEBOOKS (CRM-14, migration 0408) — a governed, effective-dated price list a quote is priced FROM instead of ad-hoc typed unit prices. cpq_pricebooks is MASTER DATA created under the `masterdata` duty (like configs/rules/bundles; an author with only `cpq` is refused 403), carrying a currency, an active flag and an inclusive effective window (from/to; a from>to window is rejected BAD_EFFECTIVE_WINDOW); cpq_pricebook_entries hold the per-item unit price (item_code -> unit_price, upsert). When a quote is created against a pricebook (quotes.pricebook_id, the audited pricing basis), each line whose item/config code has an entry takes the PRICEBOOK price — on BOTH the config path (by product_configs.code) and the free-line path (by item_code) — while a line the book doesn't cover keeps its resolved price. The book is validated at quote time: it must belong to the tenant (else PRICEBOOK_NOT_FOUND 404), be active (PRICEBOOK_INACTIVE) and be effective on the business day (PRICEBOOK_NOT_EFFECTIVE) — so a superseded/expired list cannot be used. The resulting price still flows through the CPQ-01 margin floor (a below-cost pricebook price still parks the quote in PendingApproval), so pricebooks and the floor COMPOSE — the pricebook governs the *basis*, CPQ-01 governs the *outcome*. Two tenant tables (0232 RLS, tenant-leading indexes) + quotes.pricebook_id; the pricing logic is a dedicated CpqPricebookService (the CPQ facade stays under the service-size ratchet). No new GL post.","Prev","Automated","Per quote","Sales / Sales Manager / Master-data","P10",
    "cpq-pricebook.service.ts (createPricebook/listPricebooks/getPricebook/upsertEntries — masterdata; resolveUsable validates tenant+active+effective window -> PRICEBOOK_NOT_FOUND/INACTIVE/NOT_EFFECTIVE; applyToLines re-prices the built quote lines by item code + recomputes the subtotal); cpq.service.ts createQuote (sets each line's item_code, calls applyToLines when pricebook_id is supplied, records quotes.pricebook_id) — the CPQ-01 floor runs on the repriced lines unchanged; cpq.controller.ts (GET /api/cpq/pricebooks[/:code] exec/cpq, POST /api/cpq/pricebooks[/:code/entries] masterdata, quote body pricebook_id); schema/cpq.ts cpq_pricebooks + cpq_pricebook_entries + quotes.pricebook_id, migration 0408; web cpq/page.tsx Pricebooks tab (create + entries + list); cutover/cpq-approval.ts (ToE, CRM-15 checks)","Inspect the pricebook master-data CRUD (masterdata-gated) + entries, the effective-window/active validation at quote time, the line-price resolution on both the config and free-line paths, the recorded pricing basis (quotes.pricebook_id), and that the CPQ-01 floor still governs a pricebook price.","Re-perform (cpq-approval harness): create a pricebook + entries (masterdata; a cpq-only author is 403); a quote priced against it takes the pricebook price on a covered line (typed price ignored) and keeps the typed price on an uncovered line, recording quotes.pricebook_id; a config-path quote prices from the book by config code; a below-cost pricebook price still trips CPQ-01 -> PendingApproval; an expired book -> PRICEBOOK_NOT_EFFECTIVE, an inactive book -> PRICEBOOK_INACTIVE, an unknown book -> PRICEBOOK_NOT_FOUND, a from>to window -> BAD_EFFECTIVE_WINDOW; a second tenant sees none of the first tenant's pricebooks and cannot price from one (404).","Pricebook master + effective window; per-item price entries; quote pricing-basis (quotes.pricebook_id); effective/active validation; CPQ-01 floor composition","Implemented")
add("CRM-16","Revenue & Cash","Application","Revenue (customer-master data quality)","The customer master (CRM accounts) degrades unmonitored — key fields go unfilled or hold junk (a missing/blank tax-id, an unparseable email, an ownerless account, an account with no contact of record), so the data revenue rests on is incomplete and unreliable and no one can see WHICH records need cleanup; duplicate accounts accumulate silently (the same company entered twice with a slightly different name), fragmenting a customer's revenue/AR and inflating the pipeline, because duplicates are only checked at create time (exact key) with no proactive surveillance of near-duplicates; and account merges — which repoint children and rewrite ownership — leave no dedicated audit trail. Master-data quality and de-duplication are ungoverned.","Completeness/Accuracy",
    "CRM DATA-QUALITY governance (CRM-17, migration 0409). SCORING: CrmDqService scores each non-merged account on the completeness AND validity of its master-data fields — tax_id (present + 13 digits), email (present + parseable), phone (present + ≥9 digits), owner (assigned), contact (≥1 active contact of record), industry, website, size — as an explainable weighted score summing to 100 (present-but-invalid earns nothing, so junk is caught, not just blanks), banded good(≥80)/fair(≥50)/poor. GET /api/crm/dq is the worst-first WORKLIST (+ band counts) so cleanup is targeted; GET …/dq/account/:no returns the per-field breakdown; a schedulable idempotent daily snapshot (crm_dq_scores, upsert per account/day) drives the trend + the crm_dq_scan BI report (module-owned BiReportSource). DUPLICATE SURVEILLANCE: GET /api/crm/dq/duplicates proactively scans the tenant's accounts for likely-duplicate PAIRS — exact normalized tax_id/email/phone OR a fuzzy name match (nameSimilarity Dice-trigram ≥ threshold, legal-suffix-stripped) — ranked strongest-first, extending the existing create-time DUPLICATE_SUSPECT (exact-key) check with near-duplicate detection; a confirmed pair is resolved through the EXISTING maker-checked survivor merge (caller ≠ duplicate creator when children reassign → SOD_VIOLATION; REV-17). MERGE AUDIT: every merge now writes an append-only crm_merge_log row INSIDE the merge transaction (survivor, retired duplicate, children reassigned, survivorship-filled fields, who/when; a MERGE_CONFLICT rollback discards it), read at GET /api/crm/dq/merge-log. Reads gate crm/exec/ar; the snapshot job crm/exec. Two tenant tables (crm_dq_scores, crm_merge_log; 0232 RLS, tenant-leading indexes). No GL post.","Det","Automated","Continuous / daily scan","Sales Ops / Master-data / CRM","P13",
    "crm/dq/crm-dq.service.ts (computeDq weighted completeness+validity → score/band/breakdown; worklist worst-first + band_counts; accountDq; captureAllDq idempotent snapshot; dqHistory; duplicateCandidates fuzzy nameSimilarity + exact tax/email/phone; mergeLog read); crm-dq.controller.ts (GET /api/crm/dq[/account/:no|/history/:no|/duplicates|/merge-log] crm/exec/ar, POST …/dq/snapshot crm/exec); crm-dq-bi-reports.ts (crm_dq_scan BiReportSource); crm/accounts/crm-accounts.service.ts merge (writes crm_merge_log inside the transaction; existing SOD_VIOLATION maker-checker unchanged); common/text-similarity.ts (normalizeName/nameSimilarity/normalizeKey); schema/crm-pipeline.ts crm_dq_scores + crm_merge_log + migration 0409; bi report-registry crm_dq_scan; web crm-client.tsx Data-quality tab (worklist + duplicate surveillance + merge log); cutover/pipeline.ts (ToE, CRM-17 checks)","Inspect the DQ scoring (completeness + validity, present-but-invalid scored not-ok), the worst-first worklist + band counts, the idempotent snapshot + BI report, the proactive near-duplicate surveillance vs the create-time exact check, and the append-only merge log written atomically with the maker-checked merge.","Re-perform (pipeline harness, CRM-17 checks): a complete account scores good, a name-only account scores poor listing its missing fields, an invalid tax_id/email is scored not-ok; the worklist ranks worst-first with band counts; the snapshot is idempotent per account/day and feeds the trend + a registered crm_dq_scan report; a near-duplicate pair (shared phone + near-identical name) surfaces with reasons; the earlier maker-checked merge is recorded in the merge log (survivor + children reassigned + who); a second tenant's accounts are absent from the first tenant's worklist (RLS).","CRM data-quality score + worklist + breakdown; idempotent snapshot + BI report; near-duplicate surveillance pairs; append-only merge audit log","Implemented")
add("CRM-17","Revenue & Cash","Application","Revenue (marketing/campaign attribution accuracy)","A won deal's revenue is credited to a SINGLE marketing touch — the lead source that first captured it — so campaigns that influenced the deal later in the cycle get no credit while the source campaign is over-credited. Campaign ROI is therefore mis-stated, and multi-touch marketing-spend decisions rest on inaccurate attribution: there is no way to distribute a deal's value across all the campaigns that touched it, and no assurance that attributed campaign revenue even reconciles to the won revenue it is derived from (double-counting or leakage would go unnoticed).","Completeness/Accuracy",
    "MULTI-TOUCH campaign attribution (CRM-15, migration 0413). Each campaign TOUCHPOINT on an opportunity is recorded in crm_campaign_influence (campaign_name is CRM-owned free text — no cross-domain FK/join into the marketing tables; touch_type + touched_at order the journey; POST /api/crm/attribution/opportunity/:oppNo/touch, OPP_NOT_FOUND guard). A WON deal's amount is then distributed across its touchpoints under an explicit, selectable attribution MODEL — first_touch / last_touch / linear / u_shaped (position-based 40/20/40) — and GET /api/crm/attribution?model=&months= aggregates attributed revenue per campaign over a server-bounded window (default 6mo, clamped 1..24), with a per-opportunity breakdown at GET …/opportunity/:oppNo. CRITICALLY every model CONSERVES the total: the weights sum to 1 and the rounding residual is absorbed by the last touch, so Σ attributed = the deal amount, and the report exposes a reconciled invariant (total_attributed == won-with-touches revenue) — attribution can neither double-count nor leak. An OPEN deal attributes nothing (only won revenue is distributed). Extends the single-touch crm_source_roi read; the report is a schedulable BI report (crm_attribution, module-owned BiReportSource). Reads gate crm/exec/ar. One tenant table (0232 RLS, tenant-leading index). No GL post.","Det","Automated","Continuous / per marketing review","Marketing / Sales Ops / CRM","P13",
    "crm/attribution/crm-attribution.service.ts (addTouch OPP_NOT_FOUND; weightsFor first/last/linear/u_shaped + distribute residual-absorbing conservation; opportunityInfluence per-deal per-model breakdown; attribution per-campaign roll-up + reconciled invariant, server-bounded window); crm-attribution.controller.ts (GET /api/crm/attribution[?model&months], GET …/opportunity/:oppNo, POST …/opportunity/:oppNo/touch — crm/exec/ar); crm-attribution-bi-reports.ts (crm_attribution BiReportSource); schema/crm-pipeline.ts crm_campaign_influence + migration 0413; bi report-registry crm_attribution; crm.module wiring; web deal-client.tsx attribution card; cutover/pipeline.ts (ToE, CRM-15 checks)","Inspect the touchpoint recording (chronological, OPP_NOT_FOUND guard), the four attribution models' weightings, the revenue-conservation (residual absorbed so Σ attributed = deal amount), the reconciled invariant on the report, and the open-deal-attributes-nothing rule.","Re-perform (pipeline harness, CRM-15 checks): three touchpoints on a 100,000 deal are recorded chronologically; a touch on an unknown opp -> OPP_NOT_FOUND; before Won the deal attributes 0; on Won u_shaped splits 40k/20k/40k, first_touch 100k on the first, last_touch 100k on the last, linear conserves exactly (33,333.33+33,333.33+33,333.34=100,000); the report aggregates per campaign with total_attributed == won-with-touches and reconciled=true under both u_shaped and linear; the registry exposes the crm_attribution report type.","Per-campaign attributed-revenue report (per model) + the reconciled (revenue-conservation) invariant; per-opportunity touchpoint breakdown; schedulable crm_attribution BI report","Implemented")
add("CRM-18","Revenue & Cash","Detective","Delivered-project renewal completeness (recurring revenue leakage)","A project is DELIVERED and then nothing happens on the commercial side — the customer represents a renewal / expansion opportunity, but no one systematically ensures a renewal motion exists, so recurring revenue silently lapses. Delivered-project business has no back-flow into the sales pipeline, and there is no worklist of delivered projects that lack a renewal, so churn goes unnoticed until the customer is gone.","Completeness/Accuracy",
    "CRM↔PPM back-flow (CRM-18, migration 0415). A project counts as DELIVERED when it has passed its final phase gate to the 'closed' lifecycle phase (PROJ-26: the current phase = the target of the latest GO gate). GET /api/crm/project-renewals lists every delivered project, correlated to its CRM account by customer_no, and flags a GAP — a delivered project that has an account but no renewal raised yet — as the detective worklist (with delivered/raised/gap counts). POST /api/crm/project-renewals/:projectCode/raise raises the renewal as a governed, IDEMPOTENT action: the project must be delivered (PROJECT_NOT_DELIVERED otherwise), it must have a CRM account for its customer (ACCOUNT_NOT_FOUND otherwise), and a project can raise only ONE renewal (RENEWAL_EXISTS on a repeat). The renewal opportunity itself is created through the CRM pipeline service (CRM-domain write — the projects module is untouched, no golden-master drift) and tagged deal_type='renewal', so it flows into the CRM-08 renewal pipeline; the project->opportunity link is recorded in project_renewals (the idempotency key). So delivered-project business is systematically surfaced for renewal — none silently lapses. Reads gate crm/exec/ar. One tenant table (0232 RLS, tenant-leading index). No GL post; no project row mutated.","Detect","Automated","Continuous / per delivered project","Sales Ops / Account Management / PMO","P13",
    "crm/project-renewals/crm-project-renewals.service.ts (deliveredProjectIds via the latest GO phase-gate = 'closed'; listRenewals delivered + account correlation + gap flag + counts; raiseRenewal PROJECT_NOT_DELIVERED/ACCOUNT_NOT_FOUND/RENEWAL_EXISTS, creates the opp via CrmPipelineService + deal_type='renewal' + records project_renewals); crm-project-renewals.controller.ts (GET /api/crm/project-renewals, POST …/:projectCode/raise — crm/exec/ar); crm-project-renewals.module.ts (imports CrmPipelineModule; no cycle); schema/crm-pipeline.ts project_renewals + migration 0415; crm.module wiring; web portfolio-page renewal back-flow panel; cutover/pipeline.ts (ToE, CRM-18 checks)","Inspect the delivered-project derivation (final phase gate at 'closed'), the account correlation by customer_no, the detective gap flag, and the idempotent maker of the renewal opportunity through the CRM pipeline service (PROJECT_NOT_DELIVERED / ACCOUNT_NOT_FOUND / RENEWAL_EXISTS guards).","Re-perform (pipeline harness, CRM-18 checks): a project that is not delivered -> PROJECT_NOT_DELIVERED; deliver it (a phase gate to 'closed', independently GO-approved); the delivered project surfaces as a renewal GAP (has an account, no renewal); raising creates a renewal opportunity (deal_type='renewal', amount from the contract) that appears in the CRM-08 renewal pipeline; raising again -> RENEWAL_EXISTS; the project is then no longer a gap; a delivered project whose customer has no CRM account -> ACCOUNT_NOT_FOUND.","Delivered-project renewal worklist (delivered + gap counts, per-project renewal status); the raised renewal opportunity (deal_type renewal) + the project->opportunity link","Implemented")
add("CPQ-01","Revenue & Cash","Application","Revenue (4000); Accounts Receivable (1100)","A sales rep builds a quote (CPQ) applying discounts with NO cost, NO margin and NO discount-approval workflow — so a quote can be priced below cost or over-discounted and then accepted straight to GL revenue (Dr 1100 / Cr 4000) with only a weak same-person check on accept. Margin leakage / selling below the authorised floor goes undetected until after the sale is booked.","Occurrence/Accuracy/Authorization",
    "CPQ margin-floor & discount-approval maker-checker (SVC-1): each quote line carries a unit_cost, so on SEND the quote's effective discount% (gross list to net after discounts) and margin% (net vs cost) are computed and checked against a per-tenant FLOOR (cpq_settings: min_margin_pct default 20 / max_discount_pct default 15). A quote that breaches the floor (discount% > max OR margin% < min) is BLOCKED from send/accept: it parks in PendingApproval and opens a quote_approvals row (floor snapshot + breaching actuals) — it cannot reach Accepted (and cannot recognise revenue) until a DIFFERENT authorised user approves it (POST …/quotes/:id/approve; author self-approval -> 403 SOD_SELF_APPROVAL, and the checker duty cpq_approve is segregated from the author duty cpq — SoD R20). Reject returns the quote to Draft for re-work (approver != author). A within-floor quote sends normally (unchanged path). The existing accept-side maker-checker (acceptor != author, SOD_VIOLATION -> GL) is retained.","Prev","Automated","Per quote send / approval","Sales / Controller","P10",
    "cpq.service.ts (metricsFromLines discount%/margin%; getFloor per-tenant cpq_settings; sendQuote floor gate -> PendingApproval + quote_approvals; approveDiscount / rejectQuote SOD_SELF_APPROVAL; getSettings/updateSettings); cpq.controller.ts (/api/cpq/quotes/:id/[send|approve|reject], /api/cpq/settings, /api/cpq/approvals — gated exec/cpq / exec/cpq_approve); schema/cpq.ts quote_lines.unit_cost + quotes.discount_pct/margin_pct/requires_approval + cpq_settings + quote_approvals, migration 0328; permissions.ts cpq/cpq_approve + SoD R20; cutover/cpq-approval.ts (ToE)","Inspect the per-line unit_cost + the send-time discount%/margin% computation, the per-tenant floor lookup, the PendingApproval park + quote_approvals audit row on breach, the block on accepting an un-approved quote, and the author!=approver self-approval guard on approve/reject.","Re-perform (cpq-approval harness): set floor 20% margin / 5% discount; an in-floor quote (margin 40%, discount 0) sends -> Sent; a thin-margin quote (margin 10%) -> PendingApproval and accept -> INVALID_TRANSITION; author self-approve -> SOD_SELF_APPROVAL; a different user approves -> Sent, then accept -> Accepted + AR 50000 posted with an approved quote_approvals row; a 10%-discount quote -> PendingApproval, author self-reject -> SOD_SELF_APPROVAL, a different user rejects -> Draft; a second tenant sees 0 of the HQ quotes/approvals (RLS).","Quote margin/discount register; quote_approvals maker-checker log; PendingApproval to approve/reject audit; SoD guard","Implemented")

# ---- Service Contracts ----
add("SVC-02","Revenue & Cash","Application","Service revenue; Service-contract renewal value","A service contract silently lapses at end_date with no renewal action (recurring revenue lost, service continuity broken), OR it is renewed at an arbitrarily inflated price by the same person who proposes it — a renewal-price uplift beyond the authorised ceiling, or an auto-renew that raises price, is applied with no independent sign-off, so the contract's recurring value grows uncontrolled (revenue/AR mis-stated on an unapproved basis) and the renewal is both raised and approved by one hand.","Accuracy/Authorization/Segregation of Duties",
    "Service-contract renewal & expiry control (SVC-3, docs Track-2): a renewal PROPOSAL computes the successor value from the base × (1 + uplift_pct/100). A within-ceiling proposal (uplift ≤ the per-tenant threshold contract_renewal_settings.max_auto_uplift_pct, default 5%, and NOT an auto-renew that would raise price) auto-approves and creates the successor service_contracts row at once (linked via renewed_to_contract_id, old contract renewal_status='renewed'). A proposal that exceeds the ceiling, OR any auto-renew with a price rise, is parked `pending` and the successor is created ONLY when a DIFFERENT user approves (approved_by ≠ requested_by → SOD_SELF_APPROVAL) — the proposer cannot approve their own uplift. Reject leaves the old contract untouched (renewal_status='declined'); an already-renewed contract cannot be re-renewed (CONTRACT_ALREADY_RENEWED) and only one renewal is in flight at a time (RENEWAL_IN_FLIGHT). Detective side: GET /api/service/contracts/expiring?days=N lists Active contracts nearing end_date with NO renewal in flight (renewal_status not pending/renewed) so an expiring contract is actioned before it lapses. The uplift ceiling is change-gated to exec (PUT /api/service/renewal-settings). Never touches the SLA-event / subscription-billing paths.","Prev/Det","Automated","Per renewal / continuous","Service Manager / Financial Controller (segregated)","P13",
    "service/contract-renewal.service.ts proposeRenewal (new_value = base×(1+uplift); threshold gate; auto-approve+createSuccessor within ceiling; UPLIFT_INVALID/CONTRACT_ALREADY_RENEWED/RENEWAL_IN_FLIGHT) / approveRenewal (SOD_SELF_APPROVAL, RENEWAL_NOT_PENDING, createSuccessor + old renewal_status='renewed') / rejectRenewal (renewal_status='declined') / expiring (near-end_date, no renewal in flight) / get|putSettings (max_auto_uplift_pct, exec); contract-renewal.controller.ts POST /api/service/contracts/:id/renew [+ /renewals/:id/approve|reject], GET /api/service/contracts/expiring, /api/service/renewals, GET|PUT /api/service/renewal-settings; schema/service.ts service_contracts renewal cols + contract_renewals + contract_renewal_settings (migration 0331); cutover/contract-renewal.ts (ToE)","Inspect the uplift computation (new_value = base×(1+uplift)), the auto-approve-within-ceiling vs park-pending-over-ceiling gate, the maker-checker approve (approver ≠ proposer), the successor-contract creation + old-contract renewed link, and the expiring detective read (excludes renewed / in-flight).","Re-perform: a within-threshold (3%) renewal auto-approves and creates the successor at base×1.03; an over-threshold (20%) renewal parks pending with no successor; the proposer self-approving → SOD_SELF_APPROVAL; a distinct approver approves → successor contract created + old one renewal_status='renewed'; reject leaves the old contract (declined); an auto-renew with a small uplift is still gated; the expiring worklist lists a near-expiry contract with no renewal in flight and excludes renewed ones; a T1 tenant cannot see/approve an HQ renewal (RLS) (re-performed by the contract-renewal harness).","Renewal register (pending/approved/rejected) + successor-contract link; expiring-contract worklist; SoD self-approval block","Implemented")
add("SVC-01","Revenue & Cash","Application","Revenue; Warranty/service cost; Inventory (replacement goods)","Free warranty service or replacement goods are granted without entitlement — a serialized unit whose warranty has EXPIRED (or a fault the coverage type does not cover) is repaired/replaced free of charge, or one person both requests and authorizes a zero-charge claim, so unauthorized free service/goods leak out (revenue/cost mis-stated, inventory consumed) with no independent check that the unit was actually in coverage.","Occurrence/Accuracy/Authorization",
    "Warranty & entitlement registry with coverage-authorization maker-checker (SVC-2, migration 0329): a per-tenant warranty_terms catalogue (coverage_months + coverage_type parts/labor/full) and an installed_base serialized-unit registry (serial unique per tenant, tied to a customer + item + term) whose warranty_end is COMPUTED at registration (sold_date + coverage_months). A warranty_claims claim is COVERAGE-CHECKED at raise — in coverage = reported_date within [warranty_start, warranty_end] AND the unit's coverage_type covers the claim kind ('full' covers any; else the kinds must match. An in-coverage claim AUTO-AUTHORIZES free (charge 0, disposition repair) — it is contractually covered. An OUT-OF-COVERAGE claim (expired, or a kind the term does not cover) parks status='pending' and moves nothing: it can be actioned only by authorizeClaim/rejectClaim, which enforce the SVC-01 control — the authorizer/rejector MUST differ from the requester (authorized_by ≠ requested_by → 403 SOD_SELF_APPROVAL, binds even Admin), so no single person can grant themselves free service/goods on a non-covered unit; a non-pending claim re-decided → CLAIM_NOT_PENDING; a reject needs a reason. A distinct authorizer may set a real charge (paid repair) or deliberately authorize charge 0 (a free-service override). Two DETECTIVE reads: GET /api/service/warranty/expiring?days=N (active units whose warranty_end falls within N days — a renewal / proactive-service worklist) and GET /api/service/warranty/coverage-exceptions (the OVERRIDE REGISTER — claims authorized FREE that were actually out of coverage, exactly the population an auditor samples). Tenant-scoped (RLS, canonical 0232 policy); reads gate exec/marketing, catalogue/registry writes masterdata, claim raise exec, authorize/reject approvals. No GL post in v1 (a service-order cost posting is future work).","Prev/Det","Automated","Per claim / continuous","Service Manager / Controller","P10",
    "modules/service-warranty/service-warranty.service.ts (createTerm; registerUnit warranty_end = sold + coverage_months; createClaim coverage check → in-coverage auto-authorize free / out-of-coverage park pending; authorizeClaim SOD_SELF_APPROVAL + charge; rejectClaim reason-required + SoD; expiring; coverageExceptions override register); service-warranty.controller.ts (/api/service/warranty/terms|units[/:id]|claims[/:id/authorize|reject]|expiring|coverage-exceptions — gated exec/marketing read, masterdata write, exec raise, approvals authorize/reject); schema/service-warranty.ts warranty_terms/installed_base/warranty_claims + migration 0329 (RLS, tenant-leading indexes, serial/claim unique per tenant); cutover/warranty.ts (ToE, 20 checks)","Inspect the computed warranty_end, the coverage check (window + kind), the auto-authorize-free vs park-pending split, the authorizer≠requester maker-checker (SOD_SELF_APPROVAL), and the expiring + coverage-exceptions detective reads.","Re-perform: create a 12-month full term; register a unit sold today → warranty_end = sold + 12mo; an in-coverage claim auto-authorizes free (charge 0); a claim on an expired unit parks pending; a parts-only unit + a labor claim is out of coverage (kind mismatch); the requester self-authorizing → 403 SOD_SELF_APPROVAL; a DISTINCT authorizer approves with a charge (paid) or free (override); the free out-of-coverage override appears in coverage-exceptions (the in-coverage + paid ones do not); expiring(30d) surfaces a soon-expiring unit; a distinct user rejects with a reason; RLS isolates a second tenant (re-performed by the warranty harness).","Warranty-term catalogue + installed-base register (computed warranty_end); claim coverage snapshot; SOD_SELF_APPROVAL test; coverage-exceptions override register; expiring worklist","Implemented")
add("SVC-04","Revenue & Cash","Application","Service revenue; Customer-service obligations / SLA response (no direct GL in v1)","A customer request or complaint that arrives by email is DROPPED or lost — no support case is created, so a service obligation (and any warranty / revenue / liability exposure behind it) goes untracked and unresolved; OR the inbound email webhook is unauthenticated, so a forged or replayed message injects or mutates cases; OR a case is advanced through an ad-hoc, ungoverned status lifecycle so its resolution/closure state and the record of customer communication are unreliable and incomplete.","Completeness/Accuracy/Authorization",
    "Service Cloud — Support Cases + Email-to-Case (SVC-4, migration 0350): a per-tenant service_cases register (case_no unique per tenant, a governed status lifecycle new → open → pending → resolved → closed with reopen → open, priority P1–P4, owner/assignee, optional CRM contact link) and an append-only case_email_messages trail (each inbound customer→us / outbound us→customer message, deduped per tenant on the provider Message-ID). The COMPLETENESS control is Email-to-Case: a @Public @NoTx webhook (POST /api/service/email-to-case/inbound/:tenantCode) receives the provider-parsed email and is AUTHENTICATED by the per-tenant email shared secret / HMAC over the raw body (verifyInboundWebhook — a configured HMAC secret REQUIRES a valid signature, an optional timestamp enforces a 300s freshness window against replay → WEBHOOK_STALE, a bad secret → BAD_INBOUND_SECRET, and in production an unconfigured secret is FAIL-CLOSED → INBOUND_UNVERIFIED); the tenant is resolved from the path code (UNKNOWN_TENANT). Every authenticated inbound is then matched — (1) a per-case thread token embedded in the reply (subject/body/In-Reply-To/References) threads onto the exact case; (2) else the sender address threads onto their most-recent OPEN case; (3) else a NEW case is OPENED — so no inbound customer email is ever dropped (completeness), and a reply onto a resolved/closed case REOPENS it. Redeliveries are idempotent (Message-ID dedupe). The lifecycle is GOVERNED: assign (→open), pending, resolve, close and reopen enforce valid transitions (CASE_NOT_ACTIVE / CASE_ALREADY_CLOSED / CASE_NOT_CLOSED / CASE_CLOSED), and an outbound reply embeds the case thread token so the customer's reply threads back. Tenant-scoped (RLS, canonical 0232 policy, tenant-leading indexes); the authenticated surface gates exec/marketing. No GL post in v1 (a service-order / billable-time posting is future work).","Prev/Det","Automated","Per case / continuous","Service Manager / Support Lead","P13",
    "modules/service-cases/service-cases.service.ts (handleInbound: resolve tenant by code → assertSecret verifyInboundWebhook (HMAC/static/stale/unconfigured) → Message-ID dedupe → matchCase thread-token/contact-open-case → thread-or-create, reopen on reply; createCase case_no + thread token; assignCase/setPending/resolveCase/closeCase/reopenCase governed transitions; addReply outbound + caseThreadMark); service-cases.controller.ts (ServiceCasesController /api/service/cases[/:id[/assign|pending|resolve|close|reopen|reply]] gated exec/marketing; CaseEmailInboundController @Public @NoTx POST /api/service/email-to-case/inbound/:tenantCode); case-thread.ts (svct_ token mint/mark/parse); schema/service-cases.ts service_cases + case_email_messages + migration 0350 (RLS, tenant-leading indexes, case_no unique per tenant, Message-ID unique per tenant); cutover/service.ts (ToE, SVC-4 checks)","Inspect the inbound-webhook authentication (HMAC-over-rawBody, timestamp freshness/replay, prod fail-closed), the tenant resolution from the path code, the three-way match (thread token → open-case-by-sender → new case) that guarantees no dropped email, the Message-ID idempotency, and the governed status transitions.","Re-perform: an inbound email with no matching case OPENS a new case (source=email, thread token minted); a reply carrying the case thread token threads onto the same case; a reply from the same sender with no token threads onto their open case; a redelivered Message-ID is ignored (idempotent); a reply onto a resolved case reopens it; an inbound with a bad secret → BAD_INBOUND_SECRET and a stale timestamp → WEBHOOK_STALE; the lifecycle transitions enforce (resolve a closed case → CASE_NOT_ACTIVE, reopen an active case → CASE_NOT_CLOSED); a second tenant cannot see the first tenant's cases (RLS) (re-performed by the service harness SVC-4 checks).","Support-case register (governed lifecycle) + append-only inbound/outbound email trail; Email-to-Case webhook HMAC/tenant-resolution rejects; Message-ID idempotency; no-dropped-email completeness (new-case-on-unmatched)","Implemented")
add("SVC-05","Revenue & Cash","Application","Service revenue; Customer-service SLA commitments / service obligations (no direct GL in v1)","A contracted service-level commitment on a support case silently lapses — a case has no computed first-response or resolution target, so the desk cannot tell whether a customer entitlement is being met, a breach goes unnoticed and unremediated (service liability / churn / SLA-credit exposure), and no worklist surfaces the cases that are past due, so the completeness of the SLA obligation over the case population is unmonitored.","Completeness/Accuracy",
    "Service Cloud — per-case Entitlement / SLA tracking (SVC-5, migration 0352): the SVC-4 service_cases object is extended with an SLA ENTITLEMENT — a tier (Standard/Bronze/Silver/Gold/Platinum, mirroring the #666 contract SLA tiers) whose first-response + resolution targets (hours) are COMPUTED into first_response_due_at / resolution_due_at, anchored on the case open time, at creation and whenever the entitlement is (re)set (POST /api/service/cases/:id/entitlement — recomputes the due times off the original open time and re-evaluates the breach flags). The first outbound reply (addReply) is the FIRST RESPONSE: it stamps first_responded_at and sets response_breached = responded after first_response_due_at; resolveCase stamps resolution_breached = resolved after resolution_due_at. The DETECTIVE control is GET /api/service/cases/sla/breaches — the worklist of OPEN cases (new/open/pending) whose first-response (no response yet, past due) or resolution (past due, not resolved) SLA is currently breached, each tagged breach_kind response/resolution/both — exactly the population a service manager must action so no commitment lapses unseen. Additive columns on the already-RLS-scoped service_cases (no new table); tenant-scoped; the authenticated surface gates exec/marketing. No GL post in v1 (an SLA-credit / service-order posting is future work).","Prev/Det","Automated","Per case / continuous","Service Manager / Support Lead","P13",
    "modules/service-cases/service-cases.service.ts (CASE_SLA tier→hours map; slaDue(tier, anchor) computes first_response_due_at/resolution_due_at; createCase applies the entitlement at open; setEntitlement recomputes off opened_at + re-evaluates breaches; addReply stamps first_responded_at + response_breached; resolveCase stamps resolution_breached; slaBreaches detective worklist over open past-due cases, breach_kind response/resolution/both); service-cases.controller.ts (POST /api/service/cases/:id/entitlement, GET /api/service/cases/sla/breaches, sla_tier accepted on create — gated exec/marketing); schema/service-cases.ts service_cases SLA columns + migration 0352 (additive on the RLS-scoped table); cutover/service.ts (ToE, SVC-5 checks)","Inspect the tier→hours due-time computation (anchored on open time), the first-response stamp + breach on the first outbound reply, the resolution breach on resolve, the entitlement recompute + breach re-evaluation, and the breaches detective worklist (open past-due population).","Re-perform: create a case with a Gold entitlement → resolution_due_at = opened + 8h, first_response_due_at = opened + 2h; re-set the entitlement to Bronze → due times recompute off the original open time (resolution = opened + 72h); a first reply stamps first_responded_at + response_breached vs the due; resolve after the resolution due → resolution_breached=true; a case opened with a due time in the past appears in GET /cases/sla/breaches with breach_kind; a responded/resolved case drops out of the worklist; a second tenant cannot see the first tenant's breaches (RLS) (re-performed by the service harness SVC-5 checks).","Per-case SLA entitlement (tier + computed first-response/resolution due times); first-response & resolution breach flags; SLA-breach worklist (breach_kind)","Implemented")
add("SVC-06","Revenue & Cash","Application","Service revenue; Customer-service quality / self-service knowledge (no direct GL in v1)","Knowledge published to customers is unreviewed — a knowledge-base article reaches customers (and drives their self-service decisions) without any independent review, so inaccurate or unauthorized guidance is published by a single hand (the author self-publishes); AND the effectiveness of self-service is unmeasured — there is no record of whether the knowledge base actually deflected a case or the customer still had to open one, so case-deflection / self-service performance is invisible and unmanaged.","Accuracy/Authorization/Completeness",
    "Service Cloud — Knowledge Base + Case Deflection (SVC-6, migration 0355): a per-tenant kb_articles register (article_no unique per tenant) with a GOVERNED publish lifecycle draft → published → archived. An article is authored as a draft (editable only while draft — a published article is immutable, ARTICLE_NOT_DRAFT), and the SVC-06 MAKER-CHECKER is the publish: draft → published ONLY by a user who is NOT the author (published_by ≠ author → 403 SOD_SELF_PUBLISH), so no one publishes their own unreviewed knowledge; archive is published → archived (ARTICLE_NOT_PUBLISHED otherwise). Self-service is GET /api/service/kb/search?q= over PUBLISHED articles only (title/body/tags, view-count incremented on the hits) with a helpful/not_helpful feedback signal. The DETECTIVE side is the case-deflection log kb_deflections — POST /api/service/kb/deflect records each KB-assisted interaction (query, article, deflected=true self-served / false a case was opened, optional case link) — and GET /api/service/kb/deflection-stats returns the deflection rate + top articles, the population a service manager reads to gauge self-service effectiveness. Both tables tenant-scoped (RLS, canonical 0232 policy, tenant-leading indexes); the surface gates exec/marketing. No GL post.","Prev/Det","Automated","Per article / continuous","Knowledge Manager / Service Manager (segregated author≠publisher)","P13",
    "modules/service-kb/service-kb.service.ts (createArticle draft + author; updateArticle draft-only ARTICLE_NOT_DRAFT; publishArticle SVC-06 maker-checker published_by ≠ author → SOD_SELF_PUBLISH; archiveArticle; search published-only + view bump; feedback helpful/not_helpful; logDeflection kb_deflections; deflectionStats rate + top articles); service-kb.controller.ts (/api/service/kb/articles[/:id[/publish|archive|feedback]], /search, /deflect, /deflection-stats — gated exec/marketing); schema/service-kb.ts kb_articles + kb_deflections + migration 0355 (RLS, tenant-leading indexes, article_no unique per tenant); cutover/service.ts (ToE, SVC-6 checks)","Inspect the draft→published→archived lifecycle, the draft-only edit guard, the publish maker-checker (published_by ≠ author → SOD_SELF_PUBLISH), the published-only search surface, and the deflection log + deflection-rate detective read.","Re-perform: author a draft article; the author self-publishing → 403 SOD_SELF_PUBLISH; a DIFFERENT user publishes → status='published', published_by set; editing a published article → ARTICLE_NOT_DRAFT; search returns the published article (and not a draft), incrementing its views; a helpful vote increments the counter; a deflected interaction and a case-opened interaction are logged and deflection-stats returns the rate (deflected/total) + top articles; archive a published article; a second tenant cannot see the first tenant's articles/deflections (RLS) (re-performed by the service harness SVC-6 checks).","KB article register (governed publish lifecycle) + author≠publisher SOD_SELF_PUBLISH test; case-deflection log + deflection-rate detective read; published-only self-service search","Implemented")

# ---- Quality / Manufacturing — CAPA (QMS-2) ----
add("QC-02","Quality & Manufacturing","Application","Quality / rework & scrap cost; inventory (defective goods); warranty & recall exposure (no direct GL in v1)","Quality problems are dispositioned one-off (mfg-depth quality disposition, supplier gr_claims) with NO MANAGED corrective-action loop: a root cause is never formally identified, an action plan is never tracked to completion, and — most critically — a corrective/preventive action is CLOSED with no INDEPENDENT check that it actually worked, OR it is closed by the very person who owned it (self-sign-off). So recurring defects persist, the root cause is never truly fixed, and a CAPA can be marked 'effective/closed' by one hand with the underlying problem still live.","Completeness/Accuracy/Authorization/Segregation of Duties",
    "CAPA (Corrective & Preventive Action) lifecycle with effectiveness sign-off (QMS-2, migration 0332): a first-class per-tenant CAPA register (capas: capa_no unique per tenant, a generic NULLABLE source_type/source_ref link to an NCR/gr_claim/complaint/audit/manual origin — deliberately NOT a FK, so it stands alone; problem_statement, root_cause, action_type corrective/preventive/both, owner, target_date) with child action items (capa_actions, status pending/done, completed_by/at). The lifecycle is open → in_progress (first action added) → pending_verification (submit — blocked with NO_ACTIONS if no action plan exists) → closed | cancelled. The QC-02 CONTROL is the effectiveness verification: a CAPA reaches 'closed' ONLY via verify by a user who is NEITHER the owner NOR the creator (verified_by ≠ owner/created_by → 403 SOD_SELF_APPROVAL, binds even Admin) AND ONLY when every child action is 'done' (else ACTIONS_INCOMPLETE), recording effectiveness_result. An 'ineffective' verification REOPENS the CAPA (in_progress) rather than closing it — the root cause was not resolved. A distinct verifier may also reject the verification (evidence insufficient, REASON_REQUIRED) sending it back to in_progress; a non-pending CAPA re-verified → NOT_PENDING_VERIFICATION. DETECTIVE read: GET /api/quality/capa/overdue?days=N surfaces open (not closed/cancelled) CAPAs whose target_date has passed — the corrective-action loop is slipping. Tenant-scoped (RLS, canonical 0232 policy); reads gate quality/quality_approve/exec, create/own/actions/submit quality/exec (owner duty), verify/reject quality_approve/exec (independent verifier duty). New SoD rule R21 (quality vs quality_approve). No GL post in v1.","Prev/Det","Automated","Per CAPA / continuous","Quality Manager / QA verifier (segregated)","P10",
    "modules/quality-capa/capa.service.ts (createCapa capa_no + open; addAction seq + open→in_progress; completeAction pending→done; submit → pending_verification, NO_ACTIONS guard; verify QC-02: NOT_PENDING_VERIFICATION → SOD_SELF_APPROVAL (verified_by ≠ owner/created_by) → ACTIONS_INCOMPLETE → effective=closed / ineffective=in_progress; reject REASON_REQUIRED + SoD; cancel; overdue detective); capa.controller.ts (/api/quality/capa[/:id[/actions[/:actionId/complete]|submit|verify|reject|cancel]]|overdue — reads quality/quality_approve/exec, own quality/exec, verify/reject quality_approve/exec); schema/quality-capa.ts capas/capa_actions + migration 0332 (RLS, tenant-leading indexes, capa_no unique per tenant); permissions.ts quality/quality_approve + SoD R21; cutover/quality-capa.ts (ToE, 20 checks)","Inspect the CAPA lifecycle states, the submit NO_ACTIONS guard, and the verify() maker-checker: the verified_by ≠ owner/created_by self-approval block, the all-actions-done gate (ACTIONS_INCOMPLETE), the effective→closed vs ineffective→reopen split, and the overdue detective read.","Re-perform: create a CAPA (defaults owner=creator, links a gr_claim source) + two actions (open→in_progress); submit → pending_verification; verify while actions pending → ACTIONS_INCOMPLETE; the owner self-verifying → 403 SOD_SELF_APPROVAL; complete all actions; a DISTINCT verifier marks effective → closed (effectiveness_result + verified_by recorded); re-verifying a closed CAPA → NOT_PENDING_VERIFICATION; an 'ineffective' verification reopens to in_progress; reject without a reason → REASON_REQUIRED and owner self-reject → SOD_SELF_APPROVAL; submit with no actions → NO_ACTIONS; cancel → cancelled; overdue(0d) lists a past-target open CAPA and excludes the closed one; a T1 tenant cannot see/verify an HQ CAPA (RLS) (re-performed by the quality-capa harness, 20 checks).","CAPA register (lifecycle + effectiveness_result) + child-action completion log; SOD_SELF_APPROVAL + ACTIONS_INCOMPLETE tests; overdue-CAPA worklist","Implemented")

# ---- CRM / Loyalty ----
# LYL-01/LYL-02 were proposed IDs in the original design blueprint (docs/14-crm-members-points-worldclass-
# design.md §5, v0.1) for member-enrolment identity and atomic earn/redeem — neither ever shipped as a
# distinct, harness-tested control under those IDs; that ground is covered instead by MKT-03 (config
# segregation + the FOR UPDATE earn/redeem lock, see the Revenue & Cash / Marketing narrative) and by the
# member-enrolment uniqueness constraints. They are intentionally NOT backfilled here (nothing to test under
# those IDs). LYL-03..17 below ARE narrated (docs/process-narratives/19-marketing-pricing-loyalty.md) and
# harness-tested (tools/cutover/src/compliance.ts) — backfilled from that harness (previously only LYL-17 was
# entered here).
add("LYL-03","CRM — Loyalty","Application","Loyalty Points Liability (2250); Loyalty Points Expense (5700)","The loyalty points sub-ledger (pos_member_ledger) is not tied out to the GL, or the liability accrual double-posts / omits a fair-value re-measurement — the TFRS 15/IFRS 15 contract liability is misstated.","Valuation/Completeness/Existence",
    "Points-liability tie-out (`GET /api/loyalty/liability`) reports outstanding points × fair value (`baht_per_point`) against control account 2250, exposing `posted_liability` vs `unposted_value`. `POST /api/loyalty/liability/post` reconciles 2250 to the target by posting only the delta since the last run (`Dr 5700 / Cr 2250` on a net grant; reversed on a net redemption/forfeiture) — watermarked on `pos_member_ledger.id` and idempotent (deterministic `sourceRef` + a unique `(tenant_id, watermark_id)` on `loyalty_posting_runs`), so a re-run with no new movement posts nothing. Explicitly tenant-scoped (an HQ/Admin caller must pass `tenant_id`). Basis = ALL members (not just active), so deactivation never desyncs the GL.","Prev/Det","Automated","Per accrual run / continuous","Loyalty Admin / GL Accountant","P10/P13",
    "loyalty/member.service.ts (liability, postLiability); ledger/ledger.service.ts (accrueLiability); loyalty/loyalty.controller.ts (GET /api/loyalty/liability, POST /api/loyalty/liability/post, gated loyalty/marketing/exec/gl_post); schema/loyalty-runs.ts loyalty_posting_runs + migration 0102; cutover/compliance.ts (LYL-03 checks)","Inspect the tie-out calculation, the watermarked/idempotent accrual posting, and the tenant-scoping guard.","Re-perform: an earn/redeem movement is posted, the tie-out reports outstanding × fair value on 2250; POST .../post posts the delta (Dr 5700/Cr 2250), the TB stays balanced, and a re-run with no new movement posts nothing (idempotent); an HQ-tenant run with no points finds none (tenant-scoped) — re-performed by the LYL-03 harness checks (8 assertions).","Liability tie-out report; loyalty_posting_runs; GL JE (source=LOYALTY)","Implemented")
add("LYL-04","CRM — Loyalty","Application","Loyalty Points Liability (2250); Loyalty Points Expense (5700)","Points that should have expired (per `expiry_days`) are never written off, overstating the outstanding points liability indefinitely (breakage never recognised).","Valuation/Completeness",
    "`POST /api/loyalty/expire` computes each member's redeemable balance (earned within `expiry_days`, net of redemptions/adjustments) under a per-member `FOR UPDATE` lock and writes the excess off as an append-only `Expire` ledger row (negative points), decrementing the balance. Idempotent — a second run finds the balance already at the redeemable floor and expires nothing more. The next liability accrual then releases the matching GL amount (`Dr 2250 / Cr 5700`, breakage).","Prev/Det","Automated","Per expiry run (daily via the maintenance sweep, LYL-06)","Loyalty Admin / GL Accountant","P10/P13",
    "loyalty/member.service.ts (expirePoints, expireForTenant); schema/loyalty-members.ts pos_member_ledger txn_type='Expire'; cutover/compliance.ts (LYL-04 check)","Inspect the redeemable-balance calculation, the FOR UPDATE lock, and the idempotency guard.","Re-perform: aged points expire (breakage) under lock and release the GL liability (Dr 2250/Cr 5700); a second run with no further aging expires 0 more points — re-performed by the LYL-04 harness check.","pos_member_ledger Expire rows; accrual delta","Implemented")
add("LYL-05","CRM — Loyalty","Application","Loyalty Points Liability (2250); Loyalty Points Expense (5700)","The loyalty liability is not accrued before a period locks, so a closed period's trial balance omits points earned/redeemed/expired within it (understated/overstated liability at close).","Completeness/Cutoff",
    "`closePeriod`/`closeYear` (ledger.service.ts) call `accrueLiability` for every tenant BEFORE locking the period, dated within the closing period; at year-end the resulting 5700 expense closes to Retained Earnings while 2250 remains on the balance sheet. Best-effort — a loyalty-accrual hiccup is recorded but never blocks the financial close.","Prev","Automated","Per period close","Controller / GL Accountant","P10/P13",
    "ledger/ledger.service.ts (closePeriod/closeYear → accrueLiability); cutover/compliance.ts (LYL-05 check)","Inspect the close-period hook invoking the loyalty accrual before the lock.","Re-perform: close a period with an active points balance → loyalty_accrual.posted=true and the delta ties to the outstanding liability — re-performed by the LYL-05 harness check.","closePeriod response loyalty_accrual block","Implemented")
add("LYL-06","CRM — Loyalty","Application","Loyalty Points Liability (2250)","Expiry + accrual rely on someone remembering to call them manually — a missed run lets the sub-ledger and GL drift apart indefinitely.","Completeness",
    "`POST /api/loyalty/maintenance/run` runs the whole cycle per tenant (expire aged points, then accrue/release the liability) in one call; an Admin caller sweeps all tenants (RLS bypass), a tenant user sweeps its own, `tenant_id` limits it to one. Best-effort per tenant — one tenant's closed period/error is recorded in `results[]` and never aborts the others. Driven by an external scheduler (a daily GitHub Actions workflow, opt-in) since the API has no in-process scheduler (multi-instance-safe).","Prev/Det","Automated","Daily (scheduled)","Loyalty Admin / GL Accountant","P10/P16",
    "loyalty/member.service.ts (sweepMaintenance); loyalty/loyalty.controller.ts (POST /api/loyalty/maintenance/run, gated exec/gl_post/masterdata); .github/workflows/loyalty-maintenance.yml; cutover/compliance.ts (LYL-06 check)","Inspect the sweep's per-tenant expire→accrue sequencing and the scheduled trigger.","Re-perform: the sweep expires aged points then re-accrues the liability per tenant, tallying totals across tenants — re-performed by the LYL-06 harness check.","Sweep results[] log; workflow run history","Implemented")
add("LYL-07","CRM — Loyalty","Application","Loyalty Points Liability (2250)","A member (or a colluding operator) burns points for a reward without a hard stock/eligibility/limit check, or a redemption code is reused (double-dip on the same reward).","Occurrence/Valuation",
    "`POST /api/loyalty/rewards/:id/redeem` burns points under a `FOR UPDATE` member lock, validating sufficient balance, `tier_min`, an atomic `stock>0` guard, and `per_member_limit` before decrementing the balance and writing a Redeem ledger row (releasing the GL liability). Issues a single-use `loyalty_redemptions` code (`RDM-YYYYMMDD-NNN`); `POST /api/loyalty/redemptions/:code/use` is a one-way `issued→used` transition under `FOR UPDATE` (a second use → `ALREADY_USED`). All reward/redemption/coupon reads & writes are explicitly tenant-scoped (RLS is bypassed for Admin).","Prev","Automated","Per redemption","Loyalty Admin / CRM Reviewer","P10/P11",
    "rewards/rewards.service.ts; schema/loyalty-rewards.ts loyalty_rewards/loyalty_redemptions/member_coupons + migration 0103; cutover/compliance.ts (LYL-07 checks)","Inspect the FOR UPDATE lock, stock/limit guards, the single-use code transition, and tenant scoping.","Re-perform: a reward burn issues a single-use code and releases the GL liability; a second use of the same code → ALREADY_USED; a cross-tenant code use/read is blocked — re-performed by the LYL-07 harness checks.","loyalty_redemptions register; GL liability delta","Implemented")
add("LYL-08","CRM — Loyalty","Application","Loyalty Points Liability (2250)","A member's tier is stale/manually gameable, or a mission/stamp-card reward is claimed more than once (double-granted bonus points or duplicate coupon).","Accuracy/Occurrence",
    "`POST /api/loyalty/tiers/recompute` (and the maintenance sweep) recomputes each member's tier from lifetime points against the `loyalty_tiers` ladder under a per-member `FOR UPDATE` lock, appending a `loyalty_tier_history` audit row on any change. Missions (`loyalty_missions`/`loyalty_mission_progress`) record progress at the till (serialized per member under `FOR UPDATE`) and grant their reward — bonus points via an Adjust ledger row, or a coupon — exactly once: `claimedAt` is set under `FOR UPDATE` and a second claim → `ALREADY_CLAIMED`; an incomplete mission → `MISSION_INCOMPLETE`.","Prev/Det","Automated","Per recompute / per claim","Loyalty Admin / CRM Reviewer","P10/P13",
    "gamification/gamification.service.ts; loyalty/member.service.ts (recomputeTiers, recomputeTiersForTenant, tierJourney); schema/loyalty-gamification.ts loyalty_tier_history/loyalty_missions/loyalty_mission_progress + migration 0104; cutover/compliance.ts (LYL-08 check)","Inspect the tier-recompute audit trail and the single-claim lock on mission rewards.","Re-perform: lifetime points cross a tier threshold → tier changes + a history row; a completed mission claim grants the bonus once, a second claim → ALREADY_CLAIMED — re-performed by the LYL-08 harness check.","loyalty_tier_history; loyalty_mission_progress claimedAt","Implemented")
add("LYL-09","CRM — Loyalty","Application","Loyalty Points Liability (2250)","A member self-refers or refers the same member twice to farm bonus points, or a referral reward is granted more than once.","Occurrence/Valuation",
    "`POST /api/loyalty/referrals` records a referral (self-referral blocked by id and by phone; a member can be referred at most once — a partial unique on `referred_member_id` → `ALREADY_REFERRED`). `POST /api/loyalty/referrals/:id/reward` grants both sides their bonus points exactly once — `status` flips to `rewarded` under a `FOR UPDATE` lock on the referral row (a second call → `ALREADY_REWARDED`); the two member rows are locked in deterministic ascending-id order to prevent an ABBA deadlock under concurrent rewards. Explicitly tenant-scoped.","Prev","Automated","Per referral","Loyalty Admin / CRM Reviewer","P10/P11",
    "referrals/referrals.service.ts; schema/loyalty-referrals.ts loyalty_referrals + migration 0105; cutover/compliance.ts (LYL-09 check)","Inspect the refer-once partial-unique guard, self-referral blocks, and the single-reward FOR UPDATE transition.","Re-perform: a referral rewards both members once; a second reward call → ALREADY_REWARDED; a cross-tenant reward attempt → not found — re-performed by the LYL-09 harness check.","loyalty_referrals status/rewarded_at","Implemented")
add("LYL-10","CRM — Loyalty","ITGC","All","The consumer member app's authentication (phone-OTP) is brute-forceable, leaks whether a phone is enrolled, or a member token can reach staff-only functions / another member's data.","Restricted access/Authorization",
    "`POST /api/member/auth/request-otp` resolves the member by explicit shop code + phone (RLS bypassed on this public route) and issues a single-use, 5-minute, scrypt-hashed 6-digit OTP (rate-limited to one live code/60s), always returning `{sent:true}` so it never leaks phone-enrolment status. `POST /api/member/auth/verify-otp` checks the code under expiry + a ≥5-attempt bound — the counter is an auto-committing atomic guarded UPDATE (`@NoTx`) so a wrong-code 401 cannot roll back the increment — and mints a member JWT `{role:'Member', tenantId, memberId, permissions:[]}`. Every `/api/member/*` route is `MemberGuard`-gated (rejects any non-member token) and self-scoped (the member is taken from the token — no member-id input), so a member token is rejected by every `@Permissions`-gated staff route and can only ever act on itself; PDPA per-purpose consent self-service (`source='self'`) is likewise self-scoped.","Prev","Automated","Continuous","IT Security / Loyalty Admin","P11",
    "member/member-auth.service.ts; member/member.guard.ts; member/member.controller.ts; schema/member-otp.ts member_otps + migration 0106; cutover/compliance.ts (LYL-10, LYL-10b, LYL-10c checks)","Inspect the OTP hashing/expiry/attempt-bound, the MemberGuard self-scoping, and the consent self-service scoping.","Re-perform: OTP login mints a member token, a staff route (/api/loyalty/members) rejects it (403); a member self-manages PDPA consent (self-scoped); 5 wrong guesses lock the code (the correct code is then also rejected) — re-performed by the LYL-10/10b/10c harness checks.","member_otps attempt counter; member token claims","Implemented")
add("LYL-11","CRM — Loyalty","Application","Loyalty Points Liability (2250)","A lucky-draw outcome is client-influenceable or unaudited (rigged draw), a prize is oversold beyond its stock, or the spin cost is not actually charged before a prize is granted.","Occurrence/Valuation",
    "`POST /api/loyalty/wheels/:id/spin` (and the member self-spin) draws exactly one segment server-side using a cryptographic (`node:crypto`) weighted RNG over the in-stock, positive-weight segments only — the member cannot influence the outcome, and every spin is recorded in `loyalty_spins` (provably fair). Under one `FOR UPDATE` member lock: a daily free spin costs nothing, otherwise `cost_points` is burned (a Redeem ledger row, releasing the GL liability) after an insufficiency check; a points prize is an Adjust row, a coupon prize issues a `member_coupons` row; limited stock is decremented by an atomic guarded UPDATE (`stock>0`) so a prize cannot be oversold (a lost race → `PRIZE_OUT_OF_STOCK`, no charge).","Prev","Automated","Per spin","Loyalty Admin / CRM Reviewer","P10/P11",
    "wheels/wheels.service.ts; schema/loyalty-wheels.ts loyalty_wheels/loyalty_wheel_segments/loyalty_spins + migration 0107; cutover/compliance.ts (LYL-11 check)","Inspect the weighted-RNG draw, the cost-burn-before-prize ordering under the member lock, and the atomic stock guard.","Re-perform: a free spin costs nothing, a paid spin burns cost_points before the prize is granted, and a stocked-out segment is never awarded twice (atomic guard) — re-performed by the LYL-11 harness check.","loyalty_spins outcome log; ledger Redeem/Adjust rows","Implemented")
add("LYL-12","CRM — Loyalty","Application","All (PDPA / marketing)","A segmented campaign is sent to a member who opted out of marketing (PDPA violation), or a scheduled/manual send race double-delivers the same campaign (duplicate spend/annoyance, unaudited).","Completeness/Occurrence",
    "`loyalty_campaigns` targets all / an RFM segment / a tier / today's birthdays, sent now or at `schedule_at` (fired by a dedicated `@NoTx` cron route, `run-due`). Every targeted member is resolved tenant-scoped; a `marketing_opt_in=false` member is never delivered to — logged `skipped` (PDPA) — and every recipient (sent/skipped/failed) is audited in `message_log`. Sending is claim-first: the campaign is atomically flipped `draft|scheduled→sent` and COMMITTED (under `@NoTx`) BEFORE any message goes out, so a crash/rollback (esp. the cron's former whole-sweep transaction) can never re-open it for a duplicate blast — at-most-once delivery is durable, not dependent on the transaction surviving.","Prev/Det","Automated","Per campaign send","Marketing / Loyalty Admin","P10/P13",
    "campaigns/campaigns.service.ts; schema/loyalty-campaigns.ts loyalty_campaigns + migration 0108; cutover/compliance.ts (LYL-12, LYL-12b checks)","Inspect the opt-out filter, the per-recipient audit log, and the claim-first commit-before-delivery ordering.","Re-perform: a segmented send skips opted-out members and audits every recipient; a re-send of an already-sent campaign → ALREADY_SENT; a scheduled campaign fires exactly once across repeated run-due calls — re-performed by the LYL-12/12b harness checks.","message_log per-recipient audit; campaign status transition","Implemented")
add("LYL-13","CRM — Loyalty","ITGC","All","A single role holds both duties of a CRM single-duty conflict (e.g. configure a reward AND redeem at the till) enabling self-dealing loyalty value, because a coarse legacy permission bundles both.","Authorization/Segregation of Duties",
    "Four standalone granular permissions (`crm_member`, `crm_points_adjust`, `crm_reward`, `crm_campaign`) and three SoD rules — R14 `crm_reward ✗ pos_sell`, R15 `crm_points_adjust ✗ crm_member`, R16 `crm_campaign ✗ crm_points_adjust` — are enforced by the same preventive `assertNoSodConflict` gate used for every other role assignment (ITGC-AC-09): assigning a conflicting set is blocked (422 `SOD_CONFLICT`) unless justified with `allow_sod_override`+`reason`. Config endpoints are gated `crm_* OR` the coarse legacy permission, so existing coarse roles keep working while a single-duty CRM role stays SoD-clean.","Prev","Automated","Per role assignment","Controller / IT","P10/P11",
    "packages/shared/src/permissions.ts (crm_member/crm_points_adjust/crm_reward/crm_campaign; SOD_RULES R14–R16); admin-users.service.ts (assertNoSodConflict); cutover/compliance.ts (LYL-13 check)","Inspect the crm_* permission definitions, the R14–R16 rule set, and the endpoint gating.","Re-perform: assigning crm_reward+pos_sell together → 422 SOD_CONFLICT (R14); a single-duty crm_reward-only role is assigned cleanly — re-performed by the LYL-13 harness check.","SoD conflict-report; role-assignment test","Implemented")
add("LYL-14","CRM — Loyalty","Application","All","A member claims a partner privilege they don't qualify for (tier too low), a claim code is reused at the partner, or a privilege is claimed beyond its stock/per-member limit.","Occurrence/Authorization",
    "A member claims a privilege (tier-gated by a minimum lifetime-points threshold, same gating as rewards) under a `FOR UPDATE` lock on the privilege row — eligibility re-checked, stock decremented by an atomic `stock>0` guard, per-member limit counted over non-void claims — issuing a single-use `PRV-…` code. The partner redeems it via a one-way `claimed→used` transition under `FOR UPDATE` (`ALREADY_USED` on reuse); the code is globally unique and the redeem is tenant-scoped, so one tenant cannot redeem another's code.","Prev","Automated","Per claim/redeem","Loyalty Admin / CRM Reviewer","P10/P11",
    "partners/partners.service.ts; schema/loyalty-partners.ts loyalty_partners/loyalty_privileges/loyalty_privilege_claims + migration 0109; cutover/compliance.ts (LYL-14 check)","Inspect the tier gate, the atomic stock/limit guards, and the single-use claimed→used transition.","Re-perform: a qualifying member claims a privilege (single-use code), the partner redeems it once (2nd use → ALREADY_USED); a below-tier member's claim → TIER_TOO_LOW; a limit/stock-exhausted claim is blocked — re-performed by the LYL-14 harness check.","loyalty_privilege_claims status","Implemented")
add("LYL-15","CRM — Loyalty","Application","All","A cross-tenant aggregate leak in the loyalty analytics dashboard exposes one tenant's member/financial data to another, or the reported liability doesn't reconcile to the posted GL figure (misleading monitoring).","Restricted access/Valuation",
    "`GET /api/loyalty/analytics` returns, for ONE tenant only (HQ/Admin must pass `?tenant_id` — no cross-tenant aggregate), member counts + tier mix, points movements, the redemption funnel, the points-liability fair value vs the posted GL 2250, the breakage rate, and churn risk (dormant ≥90d members holding points). Every aggregate query is explicitly tenant-scoped. Read-only — a detective monitoring control supporting MKT-05/06.","Det","Automated","On demand","Marketing / Loyalty Admin","P16",
    "loyalty-analytics/loyalty-analytics.service.ts; loyalty-analytics/loyalty-analytics.controller.ts; cutover/compliance.ts (LYL-15 check)","Inspect the tenant-scoping on every aggregate and the liability-vs-GL reconciliation figure.","Re-perform: the analytics overview returns liability/funnel/churn figures scoped to the caller's tenant only; an HQ caller with no tenant_id is required to name one — re-performed by the LYL-15 harness check.","Analytics overview response; churn drill-down list","Implemented")
add("LYL-16","CRM — Loyalty","ITGC","All","A forged/unsigned LINE identity token mints a member session for the wrong member, or a dev/mock login bypass is reachable in production, enabling account takeover via LINE.","Restricted access/Authorization",
    "`POST /api/member/auth/line` (and the staff enrol-line/link-line routes) verifies the LIFF idToken via the shared `verifyLineIdToken` — production calls LINE's `oauth2/v2.1/verify` against `LINE_LOGIN_CHANNEL_ID`; a `mock:<userId>` token is accepted ONLY when no channel id is configured (non-prod). The verified `lineUserId` resolves the member WITHIN the requested tenant (`pos_members.line_user_id`, a one-LINE-↔-one-member-per-tenant partial unique — `LINE_ALREADY_LINKED` on conflict); an unlinked LINE account → `LINE_NOT_LINKED`, never silently creates or misattributes a session.","Prev","Automated","Continuous","IT Security / Loyalty Admin","P11",
    "loyalty/line-auth.ts (verifyLineIdToken); loyalty/loyalty.controller.ts (staff enroll-line/link-line); member/member.controller.ts (auth/line, link-line); schema/loyalty-members.ts line_user_id + migration 0105_member_line; cutover/compliance.ts (LYL-16 check)","Inspect the idToken verification call, the non-prod-only mock gate, and the tenant+line_user_id resolution.","Re-perform: a linked LINE id mints a member token scoped to the correct member; an unlinked id → 401 LINE_NOT_LINKED; a member links their LINE account (one-per-tenant enforced) — re-performed by the LYL-16 harness check.","pos_members.line_user_id; login response","Implemented")
add("LYL-17","CRM — Loyalty","Application","Loyalty Points Liability (2250)","A member (or a colluding submitter) claims loyalty points for a receipt from a purchase made outside our own POS with no independent review, or re-submits the same receipt to claim points twice — granting unearned or duplicated points liability.","Occurrence/Valuation",
    "Receipt-upload-for-points review queue: a member submits a photo of the receipt + the claimed amount (self-service `/m` app; the member token carries no `crm_points_adjust` permission, so a member can never approve their own submission) into `loyalty_receipt_submissions` (`status='Pending'`). A staff user holding `crm_points_adjust` reviews the photo and approves or rejects; approval re-validates the row is still `Pending` (else `RECEIPT_ALREADY_REVIEWED`) and grants points through the SAME `earnInTx` FOR-UPDATE-locked path POS checkout uses (member.service.ts) — no separate GL logic; the existing points-liability accrual (LYL-03) picks up the resulting `Earn` ledger row on its next run. A partial-unique index on `(tenant_id, member_id, purchase_date, purchase_amount)` (excluding rejected rows) blocks the same receipt being claimed twice while it is pending or approved.","Prev","Automated","Per submission","Loyalty Admin / CRM Reviewer","P10/P11",
    "loyalty/receipt-submissions.service.ts (submit/queue/approve/reject); loyalty/member.service.ts (earnInTx, reused unchanged); member/member.controller.ts (POST/GET /api/member/receipts, MemberGuard); loyalty/loyalty.controller.ts (GET /api/loyalty/receipts, POST .../:id/approve|reject, gated crm_points_adjust/loyalty/exec); schema/loyalty-receipt-submissions.ts + migration 0207 (partial-unique dup guard); cutover/compliance.ts (LYL-17 ToE)","Inspect the submit/approve/reject endpoints' permission gates, the FOR-UPDATE re-validation on approval, and the duplicate-claim unique index.","Re-perform: a member submits a receipt (Pending, no points yet); a staff user with crm_points_adjust approves → points post via earnInTx and the row flips Approved; a second approve/reject on the same id → RECEIPT_ALREADY_REVIEWED; reject leaves the balance untouched; a second submission with the identical member/date/amount while the first is live → DUPLICATE_RECEIPT (re-performed by the LYL-17 harness check).","Receipt submission queue; posMemberLedger Earn row tie-out; LYL-17 harness","Implemented")

add("LYL-18","CRM — Loyalty","Application","Loyalty Points Liability (2250)","A member-to-member point transfer double-spends or loses points (one side of the move commits without the other), drains an account past its balance, launders value in bulk past any daily limit, or silently changes the tenant's points liability — corrupting the 2250 sub-ledger tie-out.","Occurrence/Valuation/Completeness",
    "P2P point transfer (docs/27 W1): `POST /api/member/points/transfer` (member self-service — the sender is ALWAYS the authenticated member, no member_id parameter) and the staff counterpart `POST /api/loyalty/members/:id/transfer` (gated `crm_points_adjust`/`loyalty`/`exec`) execute an ATOMIC two-row ledger move — one 'Transfer' row at −points on the sender and one at +points on the recipient in a single DB transaction, both member rows locked FOR UPDATE in ascending-id order (deadlock-free for opposite-direction transfers). Guards inside the transaction: sender balance must cover the points (INSUFFICIENT_POINTS); recipient must be an active member of the SAME tenant (RECIPIENT_NOT_FOUND — no cross-tenant leak); self-transfer rejected (SELF_TRANSFER); the sender's outgoing total per Bangkok day is capped at `loyalty_config.transfer_day_cap` (TRANSFER_CAP; 0 disables the feature entirely, TRANSFER_DISABLED). The move nets to ZERO on outstanding points, so the TFRS-15 liability accrual (LYL-03) is unchanged by construction — the obligation merely changes owner; `movements.transfer_net_points` on the liability tie-out surfaces the (always-zero) net for the reviewer. Lifetime points are untouched on both sides, so tier standing cannot be gifted; inbound transferred points age from their own transfer date in the expiry model, outbound consume like redemptions.","Prev","Automated","Per transfer","Loyalty Admin / CRM Reviewer","P10/P11",
    "loyalty/member.service.ts (transferPoints; Transfer handling in the expiry model); member/member.controller.ts (POST /api/member/points/transfer, MemberGuard); loyalty/loyalty.controller.ts (POST /api/loyalty/members/:id/transfer); schema/marketing.ts loyalty_config.transfer_day_cap + migration 0221; cutover/compliance.ts (LYL-18 ToE); cutover/loyalty.ts (W1 P2P checks)","Inspect the single-transaction two-row move, the ascending-id FOR-UPDATE lock order, the in-tx day-cap re-check, and the same-tenant recipient resolution.","Re-perform: a staff transfer moves points atomically (two ledger rows netting 0) and the liability tie-out's outstanding_points is unchanged; a member token cannot use the staff route (403) but moves its OWN points via /api/member/points/transfer; self-transfer → SELF_TRANSFER; over-balance → INSUFFICIENT_POINTS; a transfer past the daily cap → TRANSFER_CAP; cap 0 → TRANSFER_DISABLED; a recipient in another tenant → RECIPIENT_NOT_FOUND (re-performed by the LYL-18 compliance ToE + the loyalty-harness W1 section).","posMemberLedger paired Transfer rows; liability tie-out transfer_net_points; LYL-18 harness","Implemented")

add("LYL-19","CRM — Loyalty","Application","Loyalty Points Liability (2250); Intercompany (1150/2150)","A coalition (multi-shop) point movement books points on the wrong shop's ledger or moves value between shops with no offsetting entry — one shop's 2250 liability grows with no compensation while another books revenue it did not fund; or a partner shop resolves/reads another shop's full member PII; or shop staff configure the network themselves.","Occurrence/Completeness/Restricted access",
    "Coalition network (docs/27 W2): earn/burn at a partner shop always lands on the member's HOME ledger through the SAME locked earnInTx/redeemInTx path (`POST /api/coalition/earn|redeem`, staff `loyalty`/`pos`) — the ledger row's tenant is the member's home shop, so each shop's TFRS-15 accrual (LYL-03) keeps deriving from ITS OWN roster by construction. Every cross-shop movement posts a BALANCED intercompany clearing entry at fair value (category 'loyalty-clearing', createIcInternal: home Dr 1150 due-from / Cr 5700; partner Dr 5700 / Cr 2150 due-to — reversed for burns), atomically with the point move (a closed partner period rejects the WHOLE movement: no points without the clearing entry); periodic `settleIc` nets the balances and the IC reconciliation proves elimination. Cross-shop member resolution (`GET /api/coalition/resolve?phone=`) is COALITION-SCOPED (both shops must share an ACTIVE coalition; outsiders → 404, existence never revealed) and PDPA-MINIMAL (code/name/tier/points/home-shop only — never phone/email/birthday/consents). Coalition configuration is HQ-only (perm `users`/`exec` + the Admin-role COALITION_HQ_ONLY guard). Cross-tenant reads/writes run in a deliberate, validated bypass context (`runInTenantContext`) entered ONLY after the shared-active-coalition check; the manual /api/intercompany endpoint cannot create 'loyalty-clearing' entries (dto enum unchanged).","Prev","Automated","Per cross-shop movement","Loyalty Admin / Group Controller","P10/P11",
    "coalition/coalition.service.ts (resolve/earn/redeem/validateCross, hqOnly); coalition/coalition.controller.ts (@NoTx partner-till routes); intercompany/intercompany.service.ts (createIcInternal, 'loyalty-clearing' MAP); schema/coalition.ts + migration 0222 (tables + ic_category value + RLS); cutover/coalition.ts (21-check harness, CI gate); cutover/compliance.ts (LYL-19 ToE)","Inspect the home-ledger routing, the atomic clearing-entry posting, the coalition-membership validation before every bypass block, and the PDPA-minimal resolve payload.","Re-perform: an earn at partner shop B books the Earn row under the member's home tenant A and creates a balanced 'loyalty-clearing' IC (A due-from / B due-to at points × fair value); a burn reverses the direction; both shops' liability tie-outs stay per-shop-true; a non-coalition shop gets 404 on resolve/earn; a non-Admin exec cannot configure the network (COALITION_HQ_ONLY); the resolve payload carries no contact/consent PII; IC reconciliation eliminates after settlement (re-performed by the coalition harness + the LYL-19 compliance ToE).","ic_transactions loyalty-clearing rows + reconciliation; home-tenant pos_member_ledger rows; coalition harness","Implemented")

add("LYL-20","CRM — Loyalty","Application","All","A dissatisfied customer's low NPS score triggers a notification that nobody acts on — no owner, no deadline, no record of whether the member was ever contacted — so churn-signal detection exists but service recovery silently fails.","Occurrence/Completeness",
    "Service-recovery cases (docs/29 V2): every detractor answer (score ≤ 6 on the tokenized single-use NPS survey) AUTO-OPENS exactly one recovery case in `recovery_cases` (idempotent unique (source, source_ref); the atomic single-use answer guard makes a duplicate response impossible) with a 24-hour response SLA (`response_due_at`). The worklist (`GET /api/recovery/cases`, perms crm/loyalty/marketing; web `/loyalty/recovery`) drives ACTOR-STAMPED transitions: `POST .../contact` (Open → Contacted, stamps contacted_by/at; a repeat → CASE_NOT_OPEN) and `POST .../resolve` (requires a resolution note — NOTE_REQUIRED without one; stamps resolved_by/at). An Open case past its SLA reads `overdue` on the worklist, on `GET /api/nps/summary` (`recovery.open/overdue`), and the member 360 flags the open case — an unhandled detractor is surfaced everywhere, never silently dropped. The automation event (`loyalty.nps_detractor` → journeys/notifications) still fires; the case is the accountable record and its creation is NOT best-effort (a write failure fails the submit so the member can retry).","Det","Automated","Per detractor response / daily review","CX Manager / Loyalty Admin","P16",
    "nps/recovery.service.ts (openForDetractor/list/contact/resolve/overdueCount); nps/nps.service.ts (submit detractor branch); nps/nps.controller.ts (RecoveryController); crm/crm.service.ts (360 open-case flag); schema/nps.ts recovery_cases + migration 0224 (unique source_ref, RLS, tenant-leading index); cutover/compliance.ts (LYL-20 ToE); cutover/crm.ts (V2 checks)","Inspect the auto-open in the submit path (non-best-effort), the unique source_ref, the actor-stamped guarded transitions, and the overdue surfacing on worklist/summary/360.","Re-perform: a detractor answer opens exactly one Open case with a 24h due; a second answer on the same token is rejected (single-use); resolve without a note → 400; contact/resolve stamp the acting user and a repeated transition → 409; an Open case past its SLA reads overdue on the worklist AND the NPS summary (re-performed by the LYL-20 compliance ToE + the crm-harness V2 checks).","recovery_cases rows + actor stamps; overdue counts on /api/nps/summary; LYL-20 harness","Implemented")

add("LYL-21","CRM — Loyalty","Application","Revenue (4300); Contract Liability (2410)","A paid VIP membership fee is recognized as revenue up-front instead of over the service period (TFRS 15 violation), a re-run double-recognizes a month, or a member whose membership lapsed keeps the paid tier forever — free VIP status and misstated revenue.","Occurrence/Accuracy/Cutoff",
    "Paid VIP membership (docs/29 V4): the sale (`POST /api/loyalty/memberships/sell`, pos/loyalty; plan config marketing/exec) books Dr 1000 cash / Cr **2410 Contract Liability** for the full fee — revenue is NEVER taken up-front. Monthly recognition (`POST /api/loyalty/memberships/recognize`, gl_post/exec; also the schedulable BI job `membership_revenue_recognize`) releases 2410 → 4300 straight-line (price ÷ period_months; the final month takes the rounding remainder), IDEMPOTENT per (membership, month) via the journal's source_ref dedup — a re-run posts nothing. One ACTIVE membership per member (partial unique → MEMBERSHIP_ACTIVE). The plan's tier is granted with a `loyalty_tier_history` reason 'vip' row; the nightly maintenance sweep EXPIRES lapsed memberships (status → Expired + 'vip-expired' audit row) BEFORE the tier recompute runs, so the member falls back to the EARNED ladder rung automatically — no perpetual free VIP.","Prev","Automated","Per sale / monthly recognition / nightly lapse sweep","Finance / Loyalty Admin","P10/P16",
    "loyalty/membership.service.ts (upsertPlan/sell/recognizeDue/expireLapsed/forMember); loyalty/loyalty.controller.ts (membership routes); loyalty/member.service.ts (sweep order: lapse before recompute); bi.service.ts membership_revenue_recognize; schema/membership.ts + migration 0225 (partial-unique one-active, RLS, tenant-leading indexes); cutover/loyalty.ts (V4 checks); cutover/compliance.ts (LYL-21 ToE)","Inspect the deferral entry, the straight-line release with the source_ref idempotency guard, the one-active partial unique, and the sweep's lapse-before-recompute ordering.","Re-perform: a sale books Dr 1000 / Cr 2410 for the full fee and grants the tier with a 'vip' history row; with N months elapsed the recognition posts exactly N straight-line releases (2410 → 4300) and a re-run posts 0; a second sale to the same member → MEMBERSHIP_ACTIVE; a lapsed membership expires on the sweep and the tier falls back to the earned rung with a 'vip-expired' row (re-performed by the loyalty-harness V4 checks + the LYL-21 compliance ToE).","member_memberships + VIP/VIP-REC journal entries; loyalty_tier_history vip/vip-expired rows; LYL-21 harness","Implemented")

add("LYL-22","CRM — Loyalty","Application","Revenue; Points liability","The SAME source document earns or redeems loyalty points TWICE — a retried checkout, a store-hub replay (BRANCH-04), or an integration retry — so the member balance and the 2250 points liability are overstated or a customer is charged points twice for one meal.","Accuracy/Occurrence",
    "Points-ledger replay guard: earnInTx/redeemInTx first look for an existing pos_member_ledger row for (tenant, member, ref_doc, txn_type) under the member row lock they already hold; when one exists the call returns the points ALREADY booked and mutates nothing. Migration 0315 adds the hard backstop: a PARTIAL UNIQUE index uq_member_ledger_doc on (tenant_id, member_id, ref_doc, txn_type) WHERE ref_doc IS NOT NULL AND txn_type IN ('Earn','Redeem'). Adjust/Transfer/Expire rows and rows without a source document stay repeatable by design.","Prev","Automated","Per points movement","HQ Controller / Loyalty owner","P10",
    "loyalty/member.service.ts (priorLedgerPoints + earnInTx/redeemInTx guards); migration 0315 (uq_member_ledger_doc); schema/loyalty-members.ts; cutover/loyalty.ts (ToE)","Inspect the pre-check under the member row lock and the partial unique index.","Re-perform: earn against a sale, replay it (same points, balance unchanged, one ledger row); redeem and replay (no second deduction); a different document still books; a hand-written duplicate row is rejected (loyalty harness).","pos_member_ledger rows per source document; points-liability (2250) roll-forward","Implemented")

add("MKT-12","CRM — Loyalty","Application","All","A lifecycle journey (multi-step drip) spams a member (no frequency cap), messages an opted-out member (PDPA breach), or a crashed/re-run step delivers the same message twice — eroding consent compliance and brand trust with no audit trail.","Occurrence/Authorization",
    "Lifecycle journeys (Phase G1, docs/25): a journey is a LINEAR list of steps (wait N days → send channel/body unless a whitelisted skip-rule matches). The runner (POST /api/loyalty/journeys/run-due, @NoTx; also the schedulable BI job journey_runner) CLAIMS each due enrollment-step with an atomic guarded UPDATE (next_run_at NULLed) BEFORE delivery — a concurrent/re-run claims 0 rows, so each step fires AT MOST ONCE (a crash mid-send strands the step rather than duplicating it, mirroring MKT-10's claim-first). Every send routes through MessagingService: an opted-out member is recorded 'skipped' (never contacted) and each outcome is audited in message_log (campaign = journey:<code>:<step>). A per-journey FREQUENCY CAP (max N journey messages per member per window) skips-and-audits over-cap sends ('frequency cap'). Enrolment is once-per-member (unique key); config/run is marketing/exec; every query is explicitly tenant-scoped (the cron/Admin path bypasses RLS).","Prev/Det","Automated","Per step / scheduled run","Marketing / Loyalty Admin","P16",
    "journeys/journeys.service.ts (runDue claim + executeStep consent/cap; enroll once-per-member); journeys/journeys.controller.ts (/api/loyalty/journeys*, run-due @NoTx, gated marketing/exec); schema/journeys.ts journeys/journey_steps/journey_enrollments + migration 0212 (RLS); bi.service.ts journey_runner; automation.service.ts enroll_journey action; cutover/compliance.ts (MKT-12 check) + cutover/crm.ts (5 journey checks)","Inspect the claim-first guarded UPDATE, the consent-respecting send path, the frequency-cap check + audited skip, and the tenant scoping.","Re-perform: an opted-out member enrols, the step is 'skipped' + audited in message_log and a re-run fires nothing (at-most-once); an over-cap step is skipped with error 'frequency cap'; a T2 user cannot see/enrol into a T1 journey (404) — re-performed by the MKT-12 compliance check + the crm harness journey checks.","message_log journey:<code>:<step> rows; journey_enrollments claim trail","Implemented")

add("MKT-13","CRM — Loyalty","Application","All","A marketplace buyer (Grab/LINE MAN/foodpanda/Robinhood) is profiled or marketed to WITHOUT consent, raw platform identifiers (phone/customer id) accumulate as unmanaged PII (PDPA breach), or a stolen link QR silently binds someone else's platform account to an attacker's member profile — poisoning CRM attribution.","Occurrence/Authorization",
    "Marketplace-to-member identity capture (G1, docs/45): the aggregator ingest paths (channel-adapter ingestWebhook + restaurant ingestThirdParty) persist ONLY a SHA-256 hash of the platform's stable buyer identifier in channel_customer_refs (raw id/phone is NEVER copied out of the audited webhook payload — data minimization) plus counters. LINKING is consent-gated and identity-bound: the member self-link (POST /api/member/channel-link) requires an authenticated member token (the HMAC QR capability only NAMES which ref — possession alone links nothing, and a cross-tenant token is rejected TENANT_MISMATCH) and a REQUIRED explicit marketing_opt_in decision recorded to member_consents (source='self') in the SAME request tx; the staff link (POST /api/loyalty/channel-refs/:id/link, crm_member/loyalty duty) equally refuses to link without the attested consent boolean (source='pos'). One ref = one member: a second member claiming a linked ref is rejected REF_ALREADY_LINKED (409). Once linked, later ingests auto-attach dine_in_orders.member_id so attribution accrues only along the consented mapping.","Prev","Automated","Per ingest / per link","Marketing / Loyalty Admin","P10/P16",
    "channel-adapter/channel-customer-refs.service.ts (hashCustomerRef data-minimization; captureOnIngest; linkMember/staffLink single-winner); channel-adapter/link-token.util.ts (HMAC capability); channel-adapter/mappers.ts (extCustomerRef); restaurant/channel-order.service.ts + channel-adapter.service.ts (ingest hooks); loyalty/member/member.controller.ts + loyalty.controller.ts (consent-in-same-tx endpoints); schema/channel-customer-refs.ts + migration 0367 (RLS, tenant-leading index); cutover/channel.ts (MKT-13 ToE)","Inspect the hash-only persistence at both ingest sites, the member-token + required-consent link path, the REF_ALREADY_LINKED single-winner, and the tenant-mismatch rejection.","Re-perform: ingest two orders with the same buyer ref → ONE ref row, order_count=2, raw identifier absent from channel_customer_refs; link via member token + marketing_opt_in → consent row written and the next ingest auto-attaches member_id; a second member linking the same ref → 409 REF_ALREADY_LINKED; a token minted for another tenant → 403 TENANT_MISMATCH (re-performed by the channel-harness MKT-13 checks).","channel_customer_refs (hashed refs + link audit trail); member_consents channel:<platform> rows","Implemented")

add("MKT-14","CRM — Loyalty","Application","All","A tenant's Google OAuth refresh/access token (Business Profile reviews, GA4) is stored/leaked in plaintext, a stale OAuth state is replayed to bind a rogue Google account to a tenant's connection, or synced data (reviews/analytics) leaks across tenants.","Occurrence/Authorization",
    "External reputation & analytics ingestion (docs/47): Google OAuth tokens are stored via the transparent `encryptedText` column type (AES-256-GCM, common/crypto.ts) in reputation_connections and are NEVER returned by any read endpoint (list/targets responses expose only has_refresh_token: boolean). The OAuth handshake mirrors the SSO login-state pattern: a single-use, server-persisted, expiring `state` row (reputation_oauth_state) + PKCE code_verifier/code_challenge protects the authorization-code exchange — a replayed/expired/forged state is rejected BAD_STATE. The web callback page forwards window.location.search VERBATIM to the backend in the POST body (never reads code/state by name client-side), keeping the credential out of any URL/log per the CWE-598 lesson. Every table (reputation_connections, external_reviews, analytics_daily_snapshots) is tenant-scoped (RLS + explicit tenant_id filter in every query) so a review/analytics row can never surface for a different tenant. Reviewer name/photo are public data the reviewer already posted to Google Maps — not first-party consent-gated PII, so no ROPA/consent gate applies (distinct from MKT-13/the G3 audience-export control, which push OUR members' hashed PII out).","Prev","Automated","Per connect / per sync","Marketing / Exec","P10/P16",
    "reputation/google-oauth.service.ts (encrypted token storage, single-use state, PKCE, token refresh); reputation/reputation-connections.service.ts (redacted reads, revoke); reputation/reputation-review-sync.service.ts + reputation-analytics-sync.service.ts (tenant-scoped sync); schema/reputation.ts + migration 0402 (RLS, tenant-leading indexes); apps/web reputation/callback/page.tsx (verbatim query forwarding); cutover/reputation.ts (MKT-14 ToE, cross-tenant boundary test)","Inspect the encrypted token columns (never plaintext, never returned by a read), the single-use OAuth state consumption, and the tenant-scoped sync queries.","Re-perform: a connection's list/targets response never contains a token value; a replayed OAuth state is rejected BAD_STATE; a T2 tenant's review/analytics query returns zero T1 rows and a T2 sync only ever touches T2's own connections (re-performed by the reputation harness MKT-14 checks).","reputation_connections (encrypted columns, redacted reads); external_reviews / analytics_daily_snapshots tenant isolation","Implemented")
add("MKT-15","CRM — Loyalty","Application","All","A marketing-mix (MMM) channel ROI / budget-reallocation recommendation is produced with no record of the inputs it used (per-channel spend, window, who ran it) or with opaque non-reproducible math, so a budget-shift decision cannot be audited or re-performed; or one tenant's MMM staging/model data (social feeds, per-channel sales, sentiment, channel results) surfaces for a different tenant.","Occurrence/Accuracy/Authorization",
    "Marketing Mix Modeling (docs/48): every model run persists an AUDITABLE header (mmm_model_runs — window_days, total_spend, spend_by_channel inputs, created_by, created_at) with its per-channel result rows (mmm_channel_results), so any budget recommendation is reproducible from the recorded inputs. The attribution itself is a PURE, deterministic, unit-tested function (mmm-model.ts computeMmm — v1 lift-share heuristic: contribution = attributed revenue × a bounded positive-buzz uplift; ROI = contribution ÷ spend, null when spend is 0; ROI-proportional budget split summing to exactly the total) — no hidden state, identical inputs give identical outputs. Every table in the staging→core→analytics pipeline (mmm_social_raw_feeds, mmm_sales_daily, mmm_sentiment_trends, mmm_customer_behavior, mmm_model_runs, mmm_channel_results) is tenant-scoped (canonical org-clause RLS + explicit tenant_id filter + leading tenant index) so a signal/result row can never surface for another tenant; the derived customer roll-up is keyed by the customer master's business key (customer_no), never a cross-tenant-colliding string PK. Gated to marketing/exec (no GL posting — an analytical read model). The end-to-end ToE (a dedicated cutover harness) now re-performs the full control: ingest → run → the pure-model invariants (ROI null at zero spend, allocations sum to exactly the budget, lift shares sum to 100, buzz uplift), the reproducible audited run header + the append-only audit_log row, BOLA safety (cross-tenant getRun → 404) and the multi-tenant isolation/leak protocol.","Prev","Automated","Per model run","Marketing / Exec","P10/P16",
    "mmm/mmm-model.ts (pure deterministic attribution — unit-tested test/mmm-model.test.ts); mmm/mmm-model.service.ts (audited run header + per-channel results, tenant-scoped, BOLA-safe getRun); mmm/mmm-ingest.service.ts (idempotent staging/core upserts); mmm/mmm-reads.service.ts + mmm-bi-reports.ts (tenant-scoped reads + mmm_run/mmm_summary report types); schema/mmm.ts + migration 0405 (RLS, tenant-leading indexes); bi mmm-summary live read; web /mmm workspace (Signals/Model/Recommendation tabs); cutover/mmm.ts (end-to-end ToE, 16 checks)","Inspect the persisted run header (inputs + actor + timestamp), the pure attribution function + its unit tests, the tenant_id filter on every MMM query + the RLS policy on all six tables, and the cutover ToE harness.","Re-perform (mmm harness, 16 checks): run the model → a mmm_model_runs row records the spend/window/actor + an append-only audit_log row is written and mmm_channel_results holds the per-channel ROI/allocation; computeMmm is deterministic (a re-run reproduces identical per-channel ROI/allocation) and ROI is null (not Infinity) at zero spend, allocations sum to exactly the budget, lift shares sum to 100; a non-marketing user is refused 403; a T2 tenant's MMM reads/getRun return zero T1 rows / 404 (RLS org-sharing also hard-asserted by the pg-core harness for all six tables).","mmm_model_runs audit header + mmm_channel_results + audit_log run row; MMM staging/core tenant isolation; computeMmm unit tests + cutover/mmm.ts ToE","Implemented")
add("MKT-16","CRM — Loyalty","Application","All","A negative external review (Google Maps) is left unanswered past a reasonable response window, silently damaging the business's public rating, with no worklist surfacing which reviews have breached a response SLA; or one tenant's review-response worklist/policy surfaces for another tenant.","Completeness/Timeliness",
    "Review-response SLA governance (docs/47 next-level, MKT-16): a per-tenant policy (reputation_response_settings — sla_rating_threshold, sla_hours; defaults ≤3★ within 48h) defines WHICH external reviews need a timely response and HOW FAST. The detective worklist (GET /api/reputation/response-sla) computes, over the existing external_reviews rows, the reviews that are at/below the rating threshold AND still unreplied, splitting them into BREACHED (older than sla_hours from the review's create time) vs OPEN (within the window) — a review above the threshold or already replied is excluded, and a reply clears it. The policy is upserted via GET/PUT /api/reputation/response-settings (change gated marketing/exec). The same worklist is a schedulable digest (reputation_response_sla BI report, module-owned BiReportSource — same shape as ar_collections_dunning) so a store can be alerted to overdue negative reviews. reputation_response_settings is tenant-scoped (canonical 0232 org-clause RLS + explicit tenant_id filter + leading tenant index) and the worklist reads only the caller's own reviews, so no cross-tenant leak. A read/aggregate model — no GL posting, no review data written.","Det","Automated","Continuous / per review","Marketing / Exec","P13",
    "reputation/reputation-sla.service.ts (getSettings/putSettings policy upsert with range clamps; responseSla breach worklist over external_reviews — rating<=threshold AND unreplied AND age>=sla_hours, split breached/open); reputation.controller.ts GET /api/reputation/response-sla + GET/PUT /response-settings (marketing/exec); reputation-bi-reports.ts reputation_response_sla schedulable digest + bi report-registry entry; schema/reputation.ts reputation_response_settings + migration 0416 (canonical RLS, tenant-leading index); apps/web reputation/page.tsx Response-SLA tab; cutover/reputation.ts (MKT-16 ToE)","Inspect the per-tenant SLA policy (rating threshold + hours), the breach computation (unreplied <=threshold review older than the window), the exclusion of replied/high-rated reviews, and the tenant_id filter on the worklist.","Re-perform (reputation harness, MKT-16 checks): an OLD unreplied 2★ review is flagged breached, a RECENT one open, a 5★ review excluded; tightening the threshold to <=1★ drops the 2★ reviews; a reply clears the breach; a non-marketing user is refused 403; a T2 tenant sees only its OWN breach, never any of T1's reviews.","reputation_response_settings policy; the breach/open worklist (counts + rows); the schedulable reputation_response_sla digest","Implemented")

add("MKT-17","CRM — Loyalty","Application","All","A marketing budget-reallocation decision is taken from an MMM recommendation with no independent approval — the person who proposes the channel spend split also authorises it — so a large budget shift is self-approved; or the recommended allocation is non-reproducible / not tied to a recorded MMM run; or one tenant's budget plans surface for another tenant.","Authorization/Accuracy",
    "Budget Optimizer (docs/60 Phase 1, MKT-17): the /marketing-intel Budget Planner turns a pushed MMM run's per-channel SATURATION (response) curves into a prescriptive allocation. POST /api/marketing-intel/optimize returns the spend split that maximises predicted incremental sales via a PURE, deterministic greedy water-filling allocator over Hill-saturation curves (POST /simulate re-performs any what-if identically), reproducible from the recorded MMM snapshot (basis = its model_run_ref, or 'derived' when the platform has not pushed saturation params). A recommendation NEVER posts spend: it is STAGED as an advisory plan (mi_budget_plans, status Pending) via POST /budget-plan, and requires MAKER-CHECKER approval by a DIFFERENT user — POST /budget-plan/approve routes through assertMakerChecker (approver != requester -> SOD_SELF_APPROVAL, binds even Admin under the enterprise control profile). mi_budget_plans is tenant-scoped (canonical 0232 org-clause RLS + explicit tenant_id filter + leading tenant index) so a plan can never surface for another tenant. Gated to marketing/exec (read/optimise), pr_raise (stage), exec/approvals (approve). A plan/read model — no GL posting.","Prev","Automated","Per budget plan","Marketing / Exec","P10/P29",
    "marketing-intel/mmm-optimizer.ts (pure Hill-saturation response curves + greedy water-filling allocator — unit-tested test/mmm-optimizer.test.ts); marketing-intel.service.ts (responseCurves/simulate/optimize; stageBudgetPlan + approveBudgetPlan maker-checker); marketing-intel.controller.ts GET response-curves + POST simulate/optimize/budget-plan + POST budget-plan/approve (assertMakerChecker); schema/marketing-intel.ts mi_budget_plans + migration 0466 (canonical RLS, tenant-leading index); cutover/ext.ts (MKT-17 ToE, 9 checks)","Inspect the deterministic optimiser + its unit tests, the advisory Pending plan (never posts spend), the assertMakerChecker approver!=requester check, and the tenant_id filter/RLS on mi_budget_plans.","Re-perform (ext harness, 9 MKT-17 checks): response-curves derive per-channel curves; optimize spends ~the whole budget with predicted sales>0 and simulate reproduces it identically; a staged plan is Pending; a DIFFERENT user approves it (Approved) but the requester's self-approval is rejected SOD_SELF_APPROVAL; a missing plan -> 404; every plan is tenant-scoped (cf2 only, none for HQ).","mi_budget_plans staged/approved plans (requester + approver); the deterministic optimiser + its unit tests; the maker-checker SoD test","Implemented")

add("MKT-18","CRM — Loyalty","Application","All","Per-customer marketing scores pushed by the external platform (predicted CLV, churn probability, next-best-action) are treated as authoritative and drive an automatic customer contact / offer without human review or consent; or the pushed scores CLOBBER the ERP's own explainable churn/LTV figures; or one tenant's per-customer scores surface for another tenant.","Accuracy/Authorization/Occurrence",
    "Customer Intelligence (docs/60 Phase 2, MKT-18): the external Marketing Intelligence platform computes per-customer CLV / churn probability / next-best-action and PUSHES them (scope analytics:write) into customer_profiles.mi_clv / mi_churn_risk / mi_nba — columns SEPARATE from the ERP's OWN explainable churn_risk / predicted_ltv (Growth Engine G3), so the two never clobber each other (exactly as mi_rfm_segment stays distinct from rfm_segment). The scores are ADVISORY: GET /api/marketing-intel/segment/:segment/customers is a READ-ONLY drill-down (marketing/exec), and the only contact path remains the consent-gated campaign DRAFT (POST /segments/activate → audience mi_segment, a human edits + sends). Nothing auto-sends. customer_profiles is tenant-scoped (canonical org-clause RLS + explicit tenant_id filter); the drill-down reads pos_members in a SEPARATE query stitched in-app (no cross-domain SQL join). A read/enrichment model — no GL posting.","Prev","Automated","Per push / per drill-down read","Marketing / Exec","P10/P29",
    "marketing-intel.service.ts (applyMemberScores stamps mi_clv/mi_churn_risk/mi_nba, gated on score presence so a segment-only push is untouched; segmentDrilldown read); marketing-intel.controller.ts GET segment/:segment/customers; schema/crm.ts customer_profiles.mi_clv/mi_churn_risk/mi_nba + migration 0467; the external marketing-intelligence-platform rfm_model.customer_intelligence (interpretable CLV/churn/NBA); cutover/ext.ts (MKT-18 ToE, 6 checks)","Inspect that the pushed scores land on SEPARATE mi_* columns (own churn/LTV untouched), the drill-down is read-only + tenant-scoped, and the only contact path is the consent-gated campaign draft.","Re-perform (ext harness, 6 MKT-18 checks): a push with per-customer scores stamps mi_clv/mi_churn_risk/mi_nba WITHOUT clobbering the ERP own columns; the drill-down returns the member's CLV/churn/NBA (sort clv/churn) and is tenant-scoped (no other tenant's member leaks); a segment-only push leaves existing scores intact.","customer_profiles.mi_* scored rows; the read-only drill-down; the consent-gated campaign draft as the sole contact path","Implemented")

add("MKT-19","CRM — Loyalty","Application","All","A marketing campaign's effectiveness is claimed from pre-vs-post sales with no counterfactual (regression-to-the-mean / seasonality booked as 'lift'); or the holdout control group is contacted anyway (contaminating the comparison) or re-selected after the fact to flatter the result; or the outcome read crosses into another tenant's sales.","Accuracy/Occurrence",
    "Closed-loop Measurement (docs/60 Phase 3, MKT-19): activating a pushed mi_segment splits its eligible members ONCE into a TREATMENT arm (contacted) and a randomised HOLDOUT CONTROL arm (deliberately not contacted), fixed at send time. The arms are IMMUTABLE — a deterministic hash assigns them and a unique index (tenant_id, experiment_id, member_id) prevents re-randomisation; the treatment-only campaign uses audience 'members' (an explicit id list) so the control arm is STRUCTURALLY never contacted. After the window elapses (WINDOW_NOT_ELAPSED before), lift = treatment-per-head vs control-per-head on REAL POS revenue read through CrmService.revenueByMembers (a single-domain read over dine_in_orders — NO cross-domain SQL join), with the incremental revenue attributable to the campaign; measurement is idempotent (ALREADY_MEASURED) and read-only. mi_campaign_experiments + mi_experiment_arms are tenant-scoped (canonical 0232 org-clause RLS + explicit tenant_id filter + leading tenant index). Measured outcomes are exposed read-only for the platform pull-back (GET /api/v1/marketing/experiment-outcomes, scope analytics:read) so the next MMM fit can use realised lift as a regressor. A measurement model — no GL posting.","Prev","Automated","Per experiment","Marketing / Exec","P10/P29",
    "marketing-intel/mi-experiments.service.ts (deterministic immutable arm split; treatment-only 'members' campaign; measureExperiment lift via CrmService.revenueByMembers, WINDOW_NOT_ELAPSED/ALREADY_MEASURED/NO_CONTROL guards); crm.service.ts revenueByMembers (single-domain dine_in_orders read); campaigns.service.ts audience 'members'; schema/marketing-intel.ts mi_campaign_experiments/mi_experiment_arms + migration 0468 (canonical RLS, tenant-leading + unique indexes); public-api.controller.ts GET marketing/experiment-outcomes (analytics:read); cutover/ext.ts (MKT-19 ToE, 9 checks)","Inspect the immutable arm split (unique index, no re-randomise), the treatment-only campaign that excludes controls, the read-API lift math (no cross-domain join), and the tenant_id filter/RLS.","Re-perform (ext harness, 9 MKT-19 checks): start splits treatment/control (both non-empty, arms immutable + partition the segment); the treatment-only campaign excludes every control member; measure computes positive lift (seeded ฿1000 vs ฿100/head → ~900%) and is idempotent (ALREADY_MEASURED); measuring before the window → WINDOW_NOT_ELAPSED; empty segment → EMPTY_SEGMENT; outcomes are pullable via the public API (analytics:read), tenant-scoped.","mi_campaign_experiments/mi_experiment_arms fixed arms + measured lift; the treatment-only campaign recipient list; the read-only outcome read","Implemented")

add("MKT-20","CRM — Loyalty","Application","All","Externally-computed analytics that DRIVE spend and customer contact are consumed with no independent review — the same party that pushes a run also acts on it; or a materially DRIFTED / degraded model silently drives a budget or a blast; or there is no auditable record of what model produced a recommendation and what it led to (broken ICFR evidence chain).","Authorization/Accuracy",
    "Model Governance (docs/60 Phase 4, MKT-20): ITGC-grade governance around the pushed analytics that now drive spend/contact. Opt-in per tenant (mi_governance_settings.require_approval; default OFF = back-compat). When governed: (1) MAKER-CHECKER — a pushed run lands status 'Pending' and must be APPROVED by a different user than the pusher (POST /governance/runs/approve → assertMakerChecker, approver != pushed_by -> SOD_SELF_APPROVAL); the consumers are GATED — loadCurves (optimize/simulate/stageBudgetPlan) uses only an Approved mmm run, and activateSegment is blocked (ANALYTICS_NOT_APPROVED) if the latest rfm run is unapproved. (2) MODEL CARDS — each run carries {model_version, training_window, features, metrics} surfaced in-ERP. (3) DRIFT/QUALITY — a new run's R2 is compared to the prior approved run; a material drop beyond the tenant threshold is FLAGGED (into the GOV-01 center via the mi_analytics_run approval queue + the BiLive SSE attention bus) and BLOCKS approval unless a reason is given (DRIFT_REASON_REQUIRED). (4) AUDIT TRAIL — recommendation (run) -> action (budget plan / campaign) -> outcome (Phase-3 experiment lift) linked + queryable (GET /governance/audit-trail). mi_analytics_snapshots + mi_governance_settings tenant-scoped (canonical org-clause RLS). A governance/read model — no GL posting.","Prev","Automated","Per run / per approval","Marketing / Exec","P10/P29",
    "marketing-intel/mi-governance.service.ts (evaluatePush status+drift; approveRun maker-checker + DRIFT_REASON_REQUIRED; getSettings/updateSettings; auditTrail; approvedOnly gate); marketing-intel.service.ts loadCurves Approved-only + activateSegment ANALYTICS_NOT_APPROVED gate; marketing-intel-approval-queues.ts (GOV-01 mi_analytics_run queue); schema/marketing-intel.ts mi_analytics_snapshots.status/model_card/quality + mi_governance_settings + migration 0469; the external platform run.py model_card; cutover/ext.ts (MKT-20 ToE, 11 checks)","Inspect the per-tenant governance toggle, the Pending-until-approved status + the approver!=pusher maker-checker, the drift flag + block-without-reason, the consumption gates (Approved-only curves, ANALYTICS_NOT_APPROVED activate), the GOV-01 queue, and the audit chain.","Re-perform (ext harness, 11 MKT-20 checks): governance defaults OFF (back-compat); enabling it makes a push land Pending with its model card + a drift flag; the pending run surfaces in GOV-01; a drifted run can't be approved without a reason; a different user approves it; activating off an unapproved latest RFM run -> ANALYTICS_NOT_APPROVED, and after approval it succeeds; the audit trail links runs->plans->experiments; settings are tenant-scoped.","mi_analytics_snapshots status/model_card/quality + approvals; mi_governance_settings; the GOV-01 pending queue; the audit chain","Implemented")

add("MKT-23","CRM — Loyalty","Application","All","A cross-sell / next-best-offer recommendation is turned into an automatic customer contact or offer WITHOUT human review or PDPA consent; or the recommendation is opaque / non-reproducible (no record of the co-purchase evidence and margin behind it); or one tenant's per-customer offer scoring / favourites surface for another tenant.","Accuracy/Authorization/Occurrence",
    "Propensity & Cross-Sell Targeting (docs/61 Phase 1, MKT-23): the shared Marketing Fact Layer's scoring surface answers 'who should we sell what to next?' from FACT, not guess. It COMBINES three owning-module reads via their public APIs (no cross-domain SQL join): association rules over real co-purchase (the analytics menu-affinity engine — support/confidence/LIFT), per-customer favourites + CLV (the Fact Layer), and per-item margin (the menu food-cost layer). The ranking itself is the PURE, deterministic propensity-scoring.ts (unit-tested test/propensity-scoring.test.ts): per customer, GET /api/marketing-activation/propensity/customer/:code ranks the 'next product to offer' EXCLUDING what they already buy, scored confidence x lift x marginWeight; per product, GET /propensity/item/:itemId ranks the 'best audiences to push it to' by reach x CLV. ADVISORY ONLY — every endpoint is READ-ONLY and returns a ranked list; it NEVER contacts a customer or posts spend. The sole contact path stays the existing consent-gated campaign DRAFT (activateSegment), so a human edits + sends and PDPA consent is honoured at send time. Gated to marketing/exec; tenant-scoped by RLS (customer_profiles read + a separate pos_members read; a cross-tenant member -> 404). A read/scoring model — no GL posting, no migration.","Prev","Automated","Per scoring read","Marketing / Exec","P10/P29",
    "marketing-activation/propensity-scoring.ts (pure rankNextOffers/rankBestAudiences/marginWeight — unit-tested test/propensity-scoring.test.ts, 11 checks); propensity.service.ts (nextBestOffers/bestAudiences composing menu-affinity + Fact Layer + food-cost via their public APIs); marketing-activation.controller.ts GET propensity/customer/:code + propensity/item/:itemId (marketing/exec); fact-layer.service.ts (the shared facts, incl. marketing_opt_in consent); cutover/ext.ts (MKT-23 ToE, 6 checks)","Inspect the pure deterministic scorer + its unit tests, the read-only advisory endpoints (no contact path), the EXCLUDE-already-owned rule, the consent-gated-draft note, and the tenant_id filter/RLS on the reads.","Re-perform (ext harness, 6 MKT-23 checks): a next-best-offer ranks an un-owned cross-sell (AFF-B) driven by an owned item (AFF-A, lift>1); the offers exclude what the customer already buys; the advisory-only note (MKT-23) is present; best-audiences ranks the segments to push a product to (driven by affinity antecedents); a non-marketing principal -> 403; scoring an HQ member from cf2 -> 404 (tenant-scoped).","the pure scorer + its unit tests; the read-only advisory offer/audience lists; the consent-gated-draft-only contact path","Implemented")

add("MKT-25","CRM — Loyalty","Application","All","A segment x channel budget-reallocation decision is taken from a ranking with no independent approval — the person who proposes the spend split also authorises it; or the recommendation drives spend directly with no maker-checker; or one tenant's segment/channel ranking or staged plan surfaces for another tenant.","Authorization/Accuracy",
    "Segment x Channel ROI Command (docs/61 Phase 2, MKT-25): extends the Budget Optimizer (MKT-17) from CHANNEL to SEGMENT x CHANNEL. It COMBINES three owning-module reads (no cross-domain join): the pushed MMM channel ROI (marketing-intel getSummary), per-segment size + CLV (a customer_profiles aggregation), and MEASURED Phase-3 lift per segment (mi_campaign_experiments, MKT-19 — real counterfactual where an experiment exists, the MMM ROI where it does not). The ranking is the PURE, deterministic segment-channel-scoring.ts (unit-tested test/segment-channel-scoring.test.ts): each cell scored incremental_roi (channel_roi x lift_multiplier) x value (reach x CLV); GET /api/marketing-activation/segment-channel-roi ranks cells + splits a budget toward the best channels. ADVISORY + MAKER-CHECKER: the ranking is READ-ONLY and NEVER posts spend; turning it into money REUSES the MKT-17 path exactly — POST /segment-channel-roi/stage delegates to MarketingIntelService.stageBudgetPlan (a Pending mi_budget_plans row) and approval goes through the existing POST /api/marketing-intel/budget-plan/approve maker-checker (approver != requester -> SOD_SELF_APPROVAL). No new spend path, no new SoD code. Gated to marketing/exec (rank), pr_raise (stage), exec/approvals (approve); tenant-scoped by RLS. A read/scoring model — no GL posting, no migration (reuses mi_budget_plans).","Prev","Automated","Per ranking / per staged plan","Marketing / Exec","P10/P29",
    "marketing-activation/segment-channel-scoring.ts (pure rankSegmentChannel/liftMultiplier — unit-tested test/segment-channel-scoring.test.ts, 9 checks); segment-channel-roi.service.ts (rank composing MMM ROI + customer_profiles segment value + mi_campaign_experiments lift; stage delegating to the MKT-17 maker-checker); marketing-activation.controller.ts GET segment-channel-roi + POST segment-channel-roi/stage; reuses marketing-intel stageBudgetPlan/approveBudgetPlan (mi_budget_plans, MKT-17); cutover/ext.ts (MKT-25 ToE, 6 checks)","Inspect the pure deterministic cell scorer + its unit tests, the read-only advisory ranking (no direct spend), the staging that delegates to the MKT-17 Pending plan + the approver!=requester maker-checker, and the tenant_id filter/RLS on the reads + plans.","Re-perform (ext harness, 6 MKT-25 checks): the ranking returns segment x channel cells + a channel allocation summing to ~the budget (advisory note, MKT-25); staging creates a Pending mi_budget_plans row (no spend posted); a DIFFERENT user approves it (Approved); the requester's self-approval is rejected SOD_SELF_APPROVAL (reused MKT-17 maker-checker); a non-marketing principal -> 403.","the pure cell scorer + its unit tests; the read-only ranking; the staged mi_budget_plans plan + its maker-checker approval","Implemented")

add("MKT-22","CRM — Loyalty","Application","All","A per-customer next-best-action journey is activated and sends WITHOUT independent review — the person who assembles it also launches it; or it contacts a non-consented member (PDPA breach) / a just-purchased member; or the holdout arm is contacted (destroying the lift measurement); or one tenant's journey/targets surface for another tenant.","Authorization/Occurrence",
    "Next-Best-Action Orchestrator (docs/61 Phase 3, MKT-22): turns the advisory mi_nba into SEQUENCED, PRIORITISED action. For each customer it picks the single highest expected-value action now (CLV x action uplift, churn-weighted for retention), applies FATIGUE CAP + CONSENT suppression + RECENT-PURCHASE suppression (enforced server-side at STAGE time and RECORDED per target), and tags each acted-on member to a FIXED holdout arm (the same deterministic hash as MKT-19). STAGED + MAKER-CHECKER: staging persists a Pending mi_journeys row + per-customer mi_journey_targets (treatment/control + suppression evidence); NOTHING is contacted until a DIFFERENT user ACTIVATES it (POST /nba/activate -> assertMakerChecker, approver != requester -> SOD_SELF_APPROVAL), and even then activation only creates a consent-gated campaign DRAFT (audience:'members') for the TREATMENT arm — the control arm is structurally never contacted and nothing auto-sends. The pure ranking/suppression/holdout is nba-scoring.ts (unit-tested test/nba-scoring.test.ts). Reads customer_profiles + pos_members in SEPARATE queries (no cross-domain join). Gated to marketing/exec (preview), crm_campaign (stage/activate); mi_journeys/mi_journey_targets tenant-scoped (canonical 0232 org-clause RLS + leading tenant index, migration 0470). A read/orchestration model — no GL posting.","Prev","Automated","Per journey / per activation","Marketing / Exec","P10/P29",
    "marketing-activation/nba-scoring.ts (pure assembleJourney/expectedValue/suppressionReason/inHoldout — unit-tested test/nba-scoring.test.ts, 13 checks); nba-orchestrator.service.ts (preview/stageJourney/activateJourney; assertMakerChecker on activate; consent-gated draft via CampaignsService); marketing-activation.controller.ts GET nba/preview + POST nba/stage + GET nba/journeys + POST nba/activate; schema/marketing-intel.ts mi_journeys + mi_journey_targets + migration 0470 (canonical RLS, tenant-leading indexes); cutover/ext.ts (MKT-22 ToE, 8 checks)","Inspect the pure deterministic scorer + its unit tests, the server-side suppression (consent/recent-purchase) recorded per target, the Pending-until-activated status + the approver!=requester maker-checker, the treatment-only consent-gated draft (control never contacted), and the tenant_id filter/RLS on the journeys + targets.","Re-perform (ext harness, 8 MKT-22 checks): preview ranks eligible customers by expected value (a high-churn VIP first) and suppresses no-consent/no-action/recent-purchase with the reason recorded; staging persists a Pending journey (nothing contacted); a DIFFERENT user activates it -> Active + a consent-gated draft for the treatment arm only; the requester's self-activation is rejected SOD_SELF_APPROVAL; a non-marketing principal -> 403; journeys are tenant-scoped.","mi_journeys + mi_journey_targets (targets, arms, suppression reasons); the pure scorer + its unit tests; the maker-checker activation; the treatment-only consent-gated draft","Implemented")

add("MKT-21","CRM — Loyalty","Application","All","An AI-generated marketing campaign is SENT automatically without human review; or the copy is hallucinated / not grounded in the segment's real facts; or there is no record of what facts + model produced a campaign; or a non-consented member is contacted; or one tenant's generated drafts / model cards surface for another tenant.","Occurrence/Accuracy/Authorization",
    "AI Campaign Studio (docs/61 Phase 4, MKT-21): generate a FACT-GROUNDED campaign — audience, channel, send-time, offer, th/en copy — from a segment FACT SHEET (size, avg CLV, dominant next-best-action, best channel by MMM ROI, modal send-hour). The fact sheet is fed to the generator as RETRIEVAL-GROUNDED context (facts IN the prompt, not hallucinated); the pure deterministic generator is campaign-studio.ts (unit-tested test/campaign-studio.test.ts), and a live LLM can be swapped behind the same fact sheet + prompt without changing the control. ADVISORY / DRAFT-ONLY: GET /studio/generate/:segment returns the draft + model card and contacts NO ONE; POST /studio/stage creates a consent-gated campaign DRAFT (loyalty_campaigns.status='draft', audience mi_segment) — the actual SEND stays the existing consent-gated, maker-checker campaign flow (nothing auto-sends). Every generation LOGS the model card (fact sheet + prompt + model + produced draft) to mi_campaign_generations as ICFR evidence. Reads the Fact Layer segment roll-up + a customer_profiles aggregation (no cross-domain join). Gated to marketing/exec (generate), crm_campaign (stage); mi_campaign_generations tenant-scoped (canonical 0232 org-clause RLS + leading tenant index, migration 0471). A read/generation model — no GL posting.","Prev","Automated","Per generation","Marketing / Exec","P10/P29",
    "marketing-activation/campaign-studio.ts (pure buildPrompt/draftCampaign — unit-tested test/campaign-studio.test.ts, 8 checks); campaign-studio.service.ts (generate/stageDraft/listGenerations; fact sheet from FactLayerService + a customer_profiles modal-hour aggregation; consent-gated draft via CampaignsService; model card logged); marketing-activation.controller.ts GET studio/generate/:segment + POST studio/stage + GET studio/generations; schema/marketing-intel.ts mi_campaign_generations + migration 0471 (canonical RLS, tenant-leading index); cutover/ext.ts (MKT-21 ToE, 7 checks)","Inspect the pure deterministic generator + its unit tests, the retrieval-grounded prompt (facts in, not hallucinated), the DRAFT-only output (send stays the existing consent-gated maker-checker flow), the logged model card (fact sheet + prompt + model), and the tenant_id filter/RLS on the generations.","Re-perform (ext harness, 7 MKT-21 checks): generate produces a fact-grounded draft (channel/send-hour/th+en copy) whose prompt embeds the segment + its facts; staging creates a consent-gated campaign DRAFT (never auto-sent) + logs the model card, which is listable; an empty segment -> SEGMENT_EMPTY; a non-marketing principal -> 403; generations are tenant-scoped.","mi_campaign_generations model cards (fact sheet + prompt + model + draft + campaign_id); the pure generator + its unit tests; the DRAFT-only consent-gated output","Implemented")

# ---- Expenditure / Procurement / AP ----
add("EXP-01","Expenditure","Application","Accounts Payable; Inventory","Pay supplier for goods not ordered/received or wrong price; or the same person who ran the match force-overrides a variance to push their own invoice through.","Occurrence/Accuracy/Authorization",
    "3-way match (PO ↔ GR ↔ Invoice) within tolerance gates AP payment; a variance blocks the invoice until it passes or is overridden. The override is MAKER-CHECKED: the person who ran the match cannot override its variance — a DIFFERENT user must (overrider ≠ matchedBy → SOD_VIOLATION, binds even Admin) — and the override is reset by any re-match so a stale override can't keep a now-failing invoice payable.","Prev","Automated","Per invoice","AP / Controller","P10",
    "match/three-way-match.service.ts (match gate; override SoD overrider≠matcher); match.controller.ts (override gated creditors/approvals/gl_close); cutover/match.ts (ToE); cutover/compliance.ts (ICFR ToE)","Inspect match + tolerance + payment gate + the override SoD check.","Sample invoices: payment blocked until matched; the matcher's self-override is rejected SOD_VIOLATION, an independent override unblocks, a re-match clears it (re-performed by the match + compliance harnesses).","Match results; override SoD test","Implemented")
add("EXP-02","Expenditure","Application","Accounts Payable","Payment to blocklisted/unapproved vendor.","Validity",
    "Supplier approval-status / blocklist check blocks PO & payment to blocked vendors.","Prev","Automated","Per txn","Procurement / AP","P10",
    "procurement.service.ts (SUPPLIER_BLOCKED)","Inspect vendor-status gate.","Attempt PO to blocked vendor → 422.","Vendor gate test","Implemented")
add("EXP-03","Expenditure","Application","Accounts Payable","PR/PO raised or received without authorization.","Authorization",
    "PR/PO approval workflow (maker-checker) — the approval-workflow engine routes by amount threshold (DoA matrix, ELC-03) to an approver ≠ requester (and enforces SoD); and goods receipt is HARD-GATED on PO approval (a GR against a Pending/Draft/Rejected/Cancelled PO is blocked, PO_NOT_APPROVED) so an unapproved PO can't trigger a receipt + AP liability.","Prev","Auto+Manual","Per PR/PO","Procurement Mgr","P10",
    "workflow/workflow.service.ts (amount-threshold routing + maker-checker + SoD); procurement.service.ts createGr (PO-approval gate); cutover/compliance.ts (ToE)","Inspect approval routing + thresholds + the GR-on-approval gate.","Re-perform: a PR/PO is approved by an authorized approver ≠ requester; a GR against an unapproved PO is blocked (403 PO_NOT_APPROVED).","Approval trail + GR gate ToE","Implemented")
add("EXP-04","Expenditure","Application","Accounts Payable","Match tolerance loosened to force payment.","Validity",
    "Match-tolerance configuration change restricted to 'creditors' permission.","Prev","Automated","Per change","Controller","P10/P11",
    "match.controller.ts (PUT tolerance @Permissions creditors)","Inspect permission on tolerance change.","Attempt change w/o perm → 403; log changes.","Config-change log","Implemented")
add("EXP-05","Expenditure","Application","Operating Expense; Accounts Payable","Employee/maintenance spend recorded in GL but not as a payable (escapes AP aging; AP sub-ledger ≠ GL control).","Completeness/Accuracy",
    "ESS expense approval and EAM work-order completion raise an AP payable via createApTxn (Dr 5100/5710 / Cr 2000) — not a bare GL post — so the liability appears in AP aging, settles through the AP pay flow, and keeps the AP sub-ledger ↔ GL 2000 reconciled (REC-01). Reimbursements vat-exempt; SoD approver ≠ claimant retained.","Prev","Automated","Per claim/WO","AP / Controller","P10",
    "ess.service.ts (approveExpense → createApTxn); eam.service.ts (updateWorkOrderStatus → createApTxn, acct 5710); finance.service.ts (createApTxn expense_account/tenant_id); cutover/ess.ts + basics.ts (ToE)","Inspect approval→AP routing + reconciliation.","Approve a claim / complete a WO → AP payable raised, paid via AP, sub-ledger ties to GL 2000 (re-performed by the harness).","AP sub-ledger; reimbursement/maintenance payables","Implemented")
add("EXP-06","Expenditure","Application","Accounts Payable; Cash","Vendor payment disbursed without independent approval — one person both books and pays a bill.","Authorization",
    "AP disbursement maker-checker — a payment is REQUESTED by a 'creditors' holder and APPROVED by a DIFFERENT user (approvals/gl_close); the bill's paid_amount and the cash-disbursement GL move only on approval. Booking a bill pre-paid in one call is blocked.","Prev","Auto+Manual","Per payment","AP / Controller","P10",
    "finance.service.ts (requestApPayment / approveApPayment requester≠approver / rejectApPayment); finance.controller.ts (creditors requests, approvals|gl_close approves); schema/finance.ts (ap_payments) + migration 0115; cutover/compliance.ts (ToE)","Inspect AP payment approval routing + SoD guard.","Sample payments: approver ≠ requester; no cash/GL effect until approved; self-approval → 403 SOD_VIOLATION; pre-paid creation → 400 (re-performed by the harness).","AP payment approvals","Implemented")
add("FA-06","Fixed Assets","Application","Property, Plant & Equipment","Equipment not maintained; maintenance uncontrolled; preventive maintenance missed; maintenance cost mis-stated or not tracked per asset.","Existence/Valuation",
    "EAM maintenance work orders against the asset register with a guarded lifecycle (open→in_progress→completed/cancelled; BAD_TRANSITION); preventive-maintenance schedules (time/meter) with an idempotent due-generation sweep (cron / daily scheduled job eam_pm_generate). Work-order labor/parts cost lines roll up to the WO actual cost (so the AP posting reflects real spend, not the estimate); per-asset reliability & cost KPIs (corrective failures, MTBF, downtime, total maintenance spend) support maintenance budgeting and repair-vs-replace decisions.","Det","Automated","Per WO / per sweep","Maintenance / FaAccountant","P13/P16",
    "eam.service.ts (work orders, PM schedules, runPmDue, meters, WO cost lines, reliability); eam.controller.ts; bi.service.ts (eam_pm_generate); cutover/basics.ts (ToE)","Inspect WO lifecycle guard + PM due logic; inspect cost-line roll-up into actual cost and reliability KPI computation.","Raise/complete a WO; PM sweep raises due preventive WOs (time + meter) and is idempotent; cost lines roll up to actual cost and drive the AP posting; reliability KPIs computed (re-performed by the harness).","Work-order log; PM schedule + sweep run log; WO cost lines; reliability KPI report","Implemented")

# ---- Inventory / COGS ----
add("INV-01","Inventory & COGS","Application","Inventory; COGS","Two terminals sell last unit → negative/oversold stock.","Existence/Valuation",
    "Bin-stock decrement under FOR UPDATE inside a transaction — concurrent picks serialize (no oversell).","Prev","Automated","Per txn","Eng Lead / Warehouse","P10",
    "wms.service.ts (pick)","Inspect lock + sufficiency check in tx.","Concurrent last-unit test → one PICK_SHORT.","Concurrency test","Implemented")
add("INV-02","Inventory & COGS","Application","Inventory","Stock movements not recorded (completeness of perpetual stock).","Completeness",
    "Perpetual stock-movement + lot ledger logging on every issue/receipt/return.","Det","Automated","Per txn","Warehouse","P13",
    "stock-ops; custStockLog; lotLedger","Inspect movement logging.","Tie sample movements to balances.","Stock ledger","Implemented")
add("INV-03","Inventory & COGS","Application","COGS","COGS misstated; consumption not costed.","Accuracy",
    "Inventory costing → COGS posting on consumption; recipe/BOM deduction + reversal on return.","Auto","Automated","Per txn","Controller","P10",
    "costing; menu/recipe.service.ts","Walkthrough consumption → COGS JE.","Tie sample consumption to COGS.","COGS tie-out","Implemented")
add("INV-04","Inventory & COGS","Application","Inventory","Book vs physical stock diverges; counts adjusted without independent review.","Existence",
    "Periodic stocktake / cycle count → variance computed → posted with an independent review (maker-checker, SoD R11): the person who COUNTED (counted_by) may not post/approve their own count, so the variance is reviewed before it adjusts on-hand + GL. Posting is permission-gated and audit-logged.","Det","Auto+Manual","Periodic","Warehouse Mgr","P16",
    "stock-ops/stock-ops.service.ts postStocktake (counter ≠ poster gate, SOD_SELF_APPROVAL); cutover/stock-ops.ts (ToE)","Inspect the count → variance → independent-review/post flow.","Re-perform: the counter posting their own stocktake is blocked (403 SOD_SELF_APPROVAL); an independent reviewer posts the variance.","Variance review maker-checker ToE","Implemented")
add("INV-05","Inventory & COGS","Application","Inventory","A branch stock-out is fulfilled by BUYING new stock while a sibling branch holds idle surplus (capital tied up / over-ordering); or stock is moved between branches without attribution or segregation of duties.","Existence/Accuracy/Authorization",
    "Branch-aware replenishment routes transfer-before-buy: a low (branch,item) is first covered by an inter-branch TRANSFER from a sibling branch with surplus (tenant-scoped branch_stock move + branch-attributed cust_stock_log, executed under the warehouse-custody duty), and only the residual the transfers cannot cover raises a purchase requisition through the maker-checker buy flow (EXP-03). Transfer execution (wh_custody) is segregated from PR/PO approval (procurement / approvals).","Prev/Det","Auto+Manual","Per replenishment run","Planner / Warehouse / Procurement","P10/P13",
    "wms/replenishment.service.ts (suggest transfer/buy split, autoTransfer, autoPr); wms.controller.ts (auto-transfer @wh_custody vs auto-pr @procurement); schema branch_stock + item_supplier + migration 0130; cutover/wms.ts (ToE)","Inspect transfer-before-buy allocation, branch attribution, and leg segregation.","Deplete branch A below its reorder point with surplus at branch B -> suggest splits into a transfer (from B) + a buy (residual); auto-transfer moves branch_stock and logs both branches; auto-PR raises a PR for the residual; branch_stock reconciles (re-performed by the harness).","Branch replenishment run log; inter-branch transfer log; residual PR","Implemented")
add("INV-06","Inventory & COGS","Application","Inventory; COGS","Perpetual stock VALUE drifts from the GL inventory control account; receipts/issues/adjustments uncosted or not posted to GL → inventory & COGS misstated.","Existence/Valuation/Completeness",
    "Perpetual valued sub-ledger (inv_moves / inv_balances): every receipt/issue/adjustment updates the item's cost (moving-average, or FIFO/FEFO cost layers in inv_cost_layers) AND posts a balanced JE (Dr/Cr 1200 Inventory ↔ 2000 AP / 5000 COGS / 5810 variance). Reconciliation ties sub-ledger value to GL 1200; posting is idempotent on ref (no double-count); negative stock is blocked. FEFO consumes soonest-expiry layers first (perishable waste control). The sub-ledger and the costing module (FIFO/AVG/STD) are mutually exclusive per item (CONFLICTING_COSTING guard on both sides) so inventory is never double-capitalized to 1200.","Prev+Det","Automated","Per txn","Controller / Warehouse","P10",
    "inventory-ledger.service.ts; stock-ops.service.ts (bridge); 0131 inv_moves/inv_balances; 0132 inv_cost_layers (FIFO/FEFO); ledger.postEntry","Walkthrough receipt→issue→adjust + a stock-ops issue/transfer/stocktake on a tracked item, in both moving-avg and FEFO: inspect cost recompute / layer consumption, the balanced JE, and reconcile().","Sample receipt/issue/adjust + stock-ops moves → sub-ledger value ties to GL 1200 (reconciled); FEFO COGS = actual layer cost; over-issue blocked; duplicate ref deduped.","Reconciliation report; layers report; basics + compliance + stock-ops harness","Implemented")
add("INV-07","Inventory & COGS","Application","Inventory; COGS","Stock written off the books without independent review — one person posts a shrinkage/spoilage write-off to conceal a shortage they caused (theft of inventory).","Authorization",
    "Inventory write-off maker-checker (SoD): a NEGATIVE ad-hoc stock adjustment (a write-off) on POST /api/inventory/adjustments is a REQUEST that posts NOTHING — no variance JE, no FIFO/FEFO layer consumption, no balance change — until a DIFFERENT wh_adjust holder approves (POST /api/inventory/writeoffs/:id/approve). On approval the real valued adjustment runs atomically against current state (Dr 5810 / Cr 1200). Self-approval → SOD_VIOLATION (binds even Admin); one write-off pending per item/location; reject leaves stock untouched. A positive adjustment (overage/found) and a stocktake count-variance (the count is itself the authorizing document) post immediately and are out of scope.","Prev","Automated","Per write-off","Warehouse / Controller","P10",
    "inventory-ledger.service.ts requestWriteOff/approveWriteOff/rejectWriteOff/listWriteOffs; inventory-ledger.controller.ts (writeoffs/:id/approve|reject, wh_adjust); schema/inventory.ts inv_writeoff_requests + migration 0136; cutover/basics.ts + compliance.ts (ToE)","Inspect the request→approve flow + the approver≠requester check + that the request posts nothing until approval.","Re-perform: request a write-off (on-hand unchanged), attempt self-approve (SOD_VIOLATION), approve as a different user; confirm the variance JE + balance move only after approval (re-performed by the harnesses).","Write-off request register + SoD test","Implemented")
add("INV-08","Inventory & COGS","Application","Inventory","Stock mis-located or stored beyond a bin's physical capacity — overflow held in an unrecorded location, breaking the perpetual location records and concealing where inventory physically is (loss / shrink risk; inaccurate pick paths).","Completeness; Accuracy",
    "Bin-capacity / location integrity: every storage bin carries a physical position + size + capacity, and putaway (POST /api/wms/putaway) enforces it — a receipt that would fill a bin past its defined capacity is rejected (422 BIN_CAPACITY_EXCEEDED) and no bin_stock moves. Bins without a capacity are unconstrained (back-compat). The warehouse layout (GET /api/wms/layout) reports live utilisation (on-hand ÷ capacity) and flags over-capacity bins; GET /api/wms/locate gives the exact bin(s) holding any item for spatial control.","Prev","Automated","Per putaway","Warehouse","P10",
    "wms.service.ts putaway (capacity guard) / warehouseLayout / locateItem / setBinLayout; wms.controller.ts (layout, locate, bins/:code/layout); schema/wms.ts bins.pos_*/dim_*/capacity + migration 0138; cutover/wms.ts (ToE)","Inspect the putaway capacity guard + the layout utilisation/locate read model.","Re-perform: set a bin capacity, putaway within capacity (accepted), putaway beyond it (422 BIN_CAPACITY_EXCEEDED, stock unchanged); confirm layout reports utilisation and locate finds the item (re-performed by the wms harness).","Bin capacity test + layout/locate read","Implemented")
add("INV-09","Inventory & COGS","Application","Inventory","Available-to-promise mis-stated by leaked stock reservations — allocations that are never released or consumed accumulate so ATP drifts permanently low (false stock-outs), or a reservation oversells stock it never had.","Accuracy; Completeness",
    "ATP reservation integrity: stock reservations carry a lifecycle Open -> Fulfilled (goods shipped/issued) | Cancelled (order released), and ATP nets only OPEN reservations. allocate() is idempotent per (tenant, ref_doc, item) -- re-reserving the same document adjusts the one open row rather than stacking duplicates (a retried order cannot leak the float) -- and the additional reservation may not exceed current ATP (INSUFFICIENT_ATP), so a reservation can never oversell. release() frees a cancelled order's reservation back to ATP; fulfill() retires a shipped reservation from the open pool (the on-hand reduction is posted by the issue path, so the swap is ATP-neutral and never double-counted). A register exposes every reservation for review.","Prev","Automated","Per reservation","Planner / Warehouse","P10",
    "costing/atp.service.ts allocate (idempotent + ATP guard) / releaseAllocation / fulfillAllocation / listAllocations / atp (nets Open only); costing.controller.ts (allocate, allocations/:ref/release|fulfill, allocations); schema/costing.ts stock_allocations.status; cutover/costing.ts (ToE)","Inspect the reservation lifecycle + that ATP nets only Open + the idempotency/over-reserve guards.","Re-perform: allocate (ATP drops), re-allocate same ref (idempotent -- no leak), over-reserve (422 INSUFFICIENT_ATP), release (frees ATP), fulfill + on-hand drop (ATP-neutral) (re-performed by the costing harness).","Reservation register + ATP drift test","Implemented")
add("INV-10","Inventory & COGS","Application","Inventory; Waste/scrap loss","Kitchen/ingredient waste is invisible — spoilage/over-production is not captured, so food-cost loss can't be measured or controlled; OR a perpetual-tracked item is written off as 'waste' to bypass the independent write-off approval (INV-07).","Completeness/Accuracy/Authorization",
    "Waste / spoilage logging with a write-off boundary: POST /api/inventory/waste records reason-coded ingredient waste (damage/expiry/spoilage/overproduction/prep_error/other), decrements the ingredient stock (customer_inventory + cust_stock_log) and, when a unit cost is supplied, posts Dr 5810 Scrap/Waste Loss / Cr 1200 Inventory (idempotent per WASTE- doc — mirrors recipe COGS, which credits 1200 on consumption). A by-reason analytics view (total cost, cost per reason) is the food-cost lever. **Boundary control:** a PERPETUAL-tracked item (an inv_balances row) is REJECTED here (USE_WRITEOFF) and must go through the INV-07 maker-checker write-off — so no one can dodge the independent write-off approval by mislabelling shrinkage as 'waste', and inventory value is never decremented twice.","Det/Prev","Automated","Per waste event","Kitchen / Warehouse / Controller","P10/P13",
    "inventory/waste.service.ts logWaste (perpetual-item guard, GL 5810/1200, stock decrement) + list (by-reason analytics); waste.controller.ts (/api/inventory/waste, warehouse/pos/order_mgt); schema/portal.ts waste_log + migration 0149; cutover/waste.ts (ToE)","Inspect the reason-coded capture + the 5810/1200 GL on costed waste + the perpetual-item USE_WRITEOFF boundary + the by-reason analytics.","Re-perform: costed waste posts Dr 5810 / Cr 1200 + decrements stock; uncosted waste logs with no GL; a perpetual-tracked item is rejected (USE_WRITEOFF); by-reason totals reconcile; trial balance balanced (re-performed by the waste harness).","Waste log + by-reason food-cost analytics","Implemented")

add("INV-11","Inventory & COGS","Application","Inventory; COGS","Theoretical-vs-actual food-cost variance is a single undifferentiated number — a manager sees that COGS ran over the recipe but not WHY or WHERE, so the over-usage can't be acted on (over-portioning vs spoilage vs theft go unaddressed and recur).","Accuracy/Completeness",
    "Reason-coded food-cost variance review: each EOD-count variance (cust_variance — theoretical vs actual ingredient use, valued at cost) is tagged with a normalized reason_code (WASTE/OVERSTOCK/SPOILAGE/PORTIONING/THEFT/OTHER, enum-validated at POST /api/portal/variance) and an optional station. GET /api/menu/food-cost/variance values the variance at ingredient cost and rolls it up three ways — per ingredient (with High/Medium anomaly bands), by_reason and by_station — netting unfavourable/favourable, so 'Sauce station is 8% over theoretical (portioning) → retrain' is actionable. Yield/waste factors on the recipe BoM (INV-03) feed the theoretical baseline so the variance isn't inflated by un-costed trim loss. Tenant-scoped (RLS); read gated by exec/order_mgt.","Det","Auto+Manual","Per EOD count / weekly review","F&B Controller / Kitchen Mgr","P10/P13",
    "menu/food-cost.service.ts foodCostVariance (per-item + by_reason + by_station roll-ups, anomaly bands); portal.service.ts createVariance (persists reason_code/station); portal.controller.ts VarianceBody (reason_code enum); schema/bom.ts cust_variance.reason_code/station + migration 0161; /food-cost variance tab (by-reason/by-station tables); cutover/restaurant.ts (ToE)","Inspect the reason_code enum capture, the valued by_reason/by_station roll-ups, the anomaly bands, and tenant isolation.","Re-perform: seed counts with reason/station; the variance values per ingredient (NOODLE +฿30 High), nets +30/−50 to −20, by_reason PORTIONING +30 / WASTE −50, by_station Sauce +30 (20%); another tenant's counts are excluded (re-performed by the restaurant harness).","Reason-coded variance roll-up + by-station test","Implemented")

add("COST-01","Inventory & COGS","Application","Inventory (1200); Landed-cost accrual (2010); Costing variance (5500)","Landed costs (freight, import duty, insurance, broker fees) on goods received are expensed as period costs instead of being capitalised into inventory unit cost — so on-hand inventory is understated, COGS is distorted (the charge hits P&L in the wrong period), and unit cost is understated for pricing/valuation; OR a landed-cost voucher is posted by the same person who prepared it (no independent check on the capitalised amount / accrued liability), OR the charge is retroactively loaded onto stock that has already been sold (overstating on-hand inventory that no longer exists).","Completeness/Accuracy/Valuation/Authorization",
    "Landed-cost allocation voucher: freight/duty/insurance/broker charges are attached to one or more posted goods receipts and APPORTIONED into inventory unit cost by a chosen basis (value/qty/weight), summing to 100% of the charges (rounding remainder pinned so Σalloc = total). On post, the STILL-ON-HAND share of each line's allocation is capitalised into the perpetual sub-ledger — raising the moving-average value and the open FIFO/FEFO cost layers so FUTURE issues carry the loaded cost (Dr 1200) — while the ALREADY-ISSUED residual is expensed to the costing variance account (Dr 5500, mirroring STD-costing PPV; issued qty is never retroactively re-costed), crediting the landed-cost accrual liability (Dr 1200 + Dr 5500 / Cr 2010). Posting is MAKER-CHECKER: the poster must differ from the preparer (403 SOD_SELF_APPROVAL). The capitalisation JE is inside the INV-06 reconcile scope (source INV-LC) so the sub-ledger still ties to GL 1200 after a voucher posts. Tenant-scoped (RLS).","Prev+Det","Automated","Per voucher","Controller / Warehouse / Procurement","P10",
    "landed-cost/landed-cost.service.ts create/allocate/post (apportion, on-hand vs issued split, maker-checker); landed-cost.controller.ts (/api/costing/landed-cost[/:no][/allocate|/post]); schema/landed-cost.ts landed_cost_vouchers/landed_cost_allocations + migration 0341; ledger-constants.ts account 2010; inventory-ledger.service.ts INV_SOURCES (INV-LC); posting-events.ts LANDEDCOST.CAPITALIZE; cutover/landed-cost.ts (ToE)","Walkthrough create voucher → allocate preview (ties to 100%) → post: inspect the on-hand-vs-issued capitalisation split, the balanced Dr1200/Dr5500/Cr2010 JE, the maker-checker block, and that a future issue carries the loaded cost.","Re-perform: create a voucher, preview apportionment (sums to total), self-post is blocked (403 SOD_SELF_APPROVAL), a distinct approver posts (Dr 1200 / Cr 2010 balanced), a subsequent issue carries the raised moving-average / FIFO-layer cost, and the already-issued residual lands in 5500 — never re-costing sold stock; sub-ledger reconciles to GL 1200 (re-performed by the landed-cost harness).","Landed-cost voucher register + apportionment/maker-checker ToE","Implemented")

add("INV-12","Inventory & COGS","Application","Inventory","Per-branch reorder points are STATIC numbers — set once and never revisited — so a branch whose run-rate has grown carries too small a buffer and stocks out (lost sales), while a slow branch over-orders and ties up cash/spoils stock; neither is flagged.","Accuracy/Completeness",
    "Demand-driven par-level recommendation (layered on the INV-05 branch min-max + transfer-before-buy): for each (branch,item) the system derives the average daily usage from the trailing window of branch-tagged consumption (cust_stock_log Sale/Consume) and recommends reorder_point = ceil(avg_daily x lead_time_days x safety 1.25), flagging rows whose static reorder_point is below that demand-driven buffer (under_buffered). GET /api/replenishment/par-recommendations is read-only; a planner applies a recommendation per row (POST .../apply writes the reorder_point onto branch_stock, planner duty). lead_time_days is per (branch,item) (migration 0163). Tenant-scoped (RLS); gated planner/procurement.","Det","Auto+Manual","Periodic / per planning cycle","Planner / Supply Chain","P13",
    "wms/replenishment.service.ts parRecommendations (avg-daily-usage x lead x safety, under_buffered flag) + applyPar (writes reorder_point, planner); wms.controller.ts (/api/replenishment/par-recommendations[/apply]); schema/portal.ts branch_stock.lead_time_days + migration 0163; /replenishment par-recommendations section; cutover/wms.ts (ToE)","Inspect the avg-daily-usage derivation from consumption logs, the lead-time x safety reorder-point formula, the under_buffered flag, and the planner-gated apply.","Re-perform: seed branch consumption (10/day) at lead 3 -> recommend ROP 38 (under-buffered vs static 10); apply writes 38 onto branch_stock; tenant-isolated (re-performed by the wms harness).","Par recommendation list + apply test","Implemented")
add("INV-13","Inventory & COGS","Application","Inventory; Project WIP","Stock allocated to a project is double-allocated or issued without valuation: the same on-hand qty is reserved for two projects (both draw it, one stocks out), or material is moved to a project with no cost captured, so project WIP is understated and inventory doesn't reconcile.","Accuracy/Completeness/Existence",
    "Stock reservation → issue-to-project (M3, docs/32): a reservation soft-allocates on-hand stock to a project so available-to-issue = on_hand(inv_balances) − Σ(held reservations); the reserve check is ATOMIC (a FOR UPDATE lock on the item+location's held rows) so two concurrent reservations can't over-allocate (INSUFFICIENT_STOCK otherwise). A held reservation is released (frees the stock) or issued to the project — issue-to-project relieves inventory at moving-average / consumed-layer cost and posts Dr 1260 project WIP (project_id) / Cr 1200 Inventory via the valued sub-ledger, so the value is CAPITALISED into project WIP (not expensed to COGS) and inventory 1200 stays tied to the sub-ledger; the issued value is booked as a consumed BoQ-line commitment. Prevents double-allocation and un-valued project draws.","Prev","Automated","Per reservation / issue","Warehouse / ProjectController","P13",
    "reservations.service.ts reserve (FOR UPDATE lock, available = on_hand − held → INSUFFICIENT_STOCK) / release / issueToProject (→ inventory ledger + consumed commitment) / available; reservations.controller.ts (/api/reservations[/:id/issue|release], available); inventory-ledger.service.ts issueToProject (Dr 1260 project_id / Cr 1200, neg-stock guard, moving-avg/FIFO); schema/inventory.ts stock_reservations (migration 0240); cutover/basics.ts (ToE)","Inspect the available = on_hand − held computation, the FOR UPDATE atomicity, the release/consume lifecycle, and the Dr 1260(project)/Cr 1200 issue-to-project posting.","Re-perform: receive stock; reserve part of it (available drops); a reservation beyond available → INSUFFICIENT_STOCK; issue the reservation → inventory relieved, project WIP 1260 debited with project_id, balanced; release restores availability (re-performed by the harness).","Available-to-issue (on_hand − held); the issue-to-project WIP posting","Implemented")

add("INV-14","Inventory & COGS","Application","Inventory; Revenue (delivery channel)","A menu item stays sellable on the delivery aggregators after its ingredients deplete — the store keeps accepting Grab/LINE MAN/Foodpanda/Robinhood orders the kitchen can no longer cook (the #1 aggregator complaint → cancellations, refunds, store-rating penalties), because on-hand availability is not synced OUT to the partners.","Completeness/Accuracy",
    "Auto-86 out-of-stock sync to aggregators (POS-7, migration 0299): the reactive auto-86 (LockingService.recomputeAvailability — run after every stock-depleting sale and on demand via POST /api/pos/scale/availability/recompute) flips a recipe-backed dish is_available=false the moment an ingredient can't cover one serving, and back to true on restock. Each such transition is now MIRRORED to every connected (enabled) aggregator via the outbound channel-adapter provider's setItemAvailability(store_ref, sku, available) op — a depletion PAUSES ('86') the item on the partners, a restock RESUMES ('un-86') it. IDEMPOTENT: the last-pushed per-(tenant,platform,sku) state is held in channel_item_availability, so a transition is pushed ONLY when the desired state differs from what the aggregator already has (a no-op recompute never spams the partner API). AUDITED: every 86/un-86 actually pushed is recorded (reason, push outcome/ref, actor) in the append-only channel_item_86_log, read at GET /api/channels/auto-86. Best-effort — a partner outage records push_ok=false but never poisons the sale. Both tables tenant-scoped (canonical 0232 RLS, tenant-leading indexes).","Prev/Det","Automated","Per depletion / restock event","Store Ops / F&B Controller","P13",
    "pos/scale/locking.service.ts recomputeAvailability (local 86 flip both directions → channelSync.syncAuto86); channel-adapter/channel-adapter.service.ts syncAuto86 (per-channel state diff → push, log) + listAuto86; channel-adapter/providers.ts setItemAvailability (Mock + Http); channel-adapter.controller.ts GET /api/channels/auto-86; schema/pos-scale.ts channel_item_availability + channel_item_86_log (migration 0299); cutover/channel-adapter.ts (ToE)","Inspect the deplete→86 / restock→un-86 mirroring, the channel_item_availability idempotency guard (no push when state unchanged), and the channel_item_86_log transition audit.","Re-perform: deplete a recipe ingredient → recompute 86s the dish and POSTs setItemAvailability(available=false) to the aggregator (bearer + store_ref), state+log recorded; a second recompute with unchanged stock pushes NOTHING new (idempotent); restock → recompute un-86s the dish and POSTs available=true, state resumed, transition audited (re-performed by the channel-adapter harness).","channel_item_availability state; channel_item_86_log 86/un-86 audit trail","Implemented")
add("INV-15","Inventory & COGS","Application","Inventory; COGS; Waste/scrap loss","A cancelled/voided FIRED ticket line (the dish was already prepped/cooked before the void) writes off no ingredients, so its cost vanishes from the food-cost picture; waste is captured only by an undifferentiated reason with no record of WHAT happened to the wasted stock (discarded vs donated vs staff-meal vs re-worked); and the gap between the recipe's theoretical usage and the kitchen's ACTUAL depletion is never quantified, so over-production/spoilage recurs unmeasured.","Completeness/Accuracy",
    "Waste-ledger closing-the-loop (POS-5a, extends INV-10, migration 0301): the SINGLE waste ledger (waste_log) gains (1) a reason + DISPOSITION taxonomy — reason_code WHY (…/void_fire) × disposition WHAT-happened (discard/compost/donate/staff_meal/rework/return_supplier, enum-validated → BAD_DISPOSITION), rolled up in the by_disposition analytics + a ?disposition= filter; (2) VOID-FIRED-ITEM capture — POST /api/inventory/waste/void-fire explodes a voided fired dish's recipe (menu_recipes/menu_recipe_lines, gross qty = qty_per ÷ (yield−waste) ÷ batch yield × dishes) into per-ingredient waste rows (source=void_fire, ref_doc=the voided ticket), decrements the ingredient stock and posts ONE aggregated Dr 5810 Scrap/Waste Loss / Cr 1200 Inventory (idempotent per WASTE- doc); NO_RECIPE/NO_RECIPE_LINES guards; and (3) a THEORETICAL-vs-ACTUAL usage-variance report — GET /api/inventory/waste/variance nets the recipe-COGS theoretical depletion (cust_stock_log 'Consume' rows the recipe deduction writes on every sale) against ACTUAL depletion (theoretical + logged 'Waste'), valuing the waste-explained gap at ingredient cost per item with High/Medium anomaly bands, so a manager sees the baht impact and % of usage that is waste. The INV-07 perpetual-write-off boundary (USE_WRITEOFF) still holds — kitchen ingredients (customer_inventory) only. Tenant-scoped (RLS); gated warehouse/pos/order_mgt.","Det","Automated","Per void / waste event; per shift review","Kitchen / F&B Controller","P10/P13",
    "inventory/waste.service.ts logWaste (disposition) + voidFire (recipe explosion, aggregated 5810/1200 JE) + usageVariance (Consume-vs-Waste depletion) + list (by_disposition); waste.controller.ts (/api/inventory/waste[/void-fire][/variance]); schema/portal.ts waste_log disposition/source/ref_doc + migration 0301; cutover/waste.ts (ToE)","Inspect the reason×disposition taxonomy + the void-fire recipe explosion → ingredient waste + aggregated 5810/1200 JE + the theoretical-vs-actual usage-variance nets Consume vs Waste.","Re-perform: log costed waste with disposition=donate (echoed, by_disposition rolls it up); void-fire a recipe'd dish → 2 ingredient waste lines, one Dr 5810/Cr 1200 JE, ingredient stock decremented; unknown sku → NO_RECIPE; usage-variance shows theoretical (Consume) vs actual (Consume+Waste) with the valued waste gap; trial balance balanced (re-performed by the waste harness, 19 checks).","Waste ledger + by_disposition + void-fire audit + usage-variance report","Implemented")
add("INV-16","Inventory & COGS","Application","Inventory; Goods-in-transit","Inventory moved between warehouses/branches is mis-stated at period end: a single instant transfer either records the stock at BOTH locations (double count) or at NEITHER (existence gap) while goods are physically in transit, and the value in transit sits in no identifiable account — so an auditor cannot cut off in-transit inventory at the balance-sheet date (existence / completeness of inventory).","Existence/Completeness/Cutoff",
    "Two-step ship→receive TRANSFER ORDER with in-transit ownership + GL (INV-2, migration 0341): an inter-warehouse/branch transfer is created Draft (document only), SHIPPED (relieves the source location's valued stock at current cost — moving-average, or consumed FIFO/FEFO layers carried forward — and books Dr 1255 Goods-in-Transit / Cr 1200 Inventory), and RECEIVED by a DIFFERENT custodian (lands the stock at the destination and books Dr 1200 Inventory / Cr 1255). Between ship and receive the value is isolated in the Goods-in-Transit control account (1255, seeded in the COA + the SCF CF_CLASSIFY operating bucket; distinct from 1250 WIP), so it is neither double-counted nor lost. Custody segregation (SoD): the shipper may not receive their own transfer (SOD_SELF_APPROVAL, binds even Admin). A period-end in-transit AGING / cutoff report (GET …/in-transit/aging) lists every still-Shipped order with its days-in-transit + value bucketed (0-7 / 8-30 / 31+) — the population an auditor tests for cutoff. The perpetual sub-ledger stays tied to GL 1200 throughout (INV-GIT included in the reconcile source set). The legacy instant value-neutral stock-ops transfer is unchanged. Tenant-scoped (canonical 0232 RLS); custody duty wh_custody, mirroring the instant transfer.","Prev/Det","Automated","Per transfer; period-end cutoff review","Warehouse / Inventory Controller (segregated ship vs receive)","P10",
    "stock-ops/transfer-order.service.ts create/ship/receive/inTransitAging + inventory/inventory-ledger.service.ts shipToInTransit/receiveFromInTransit (Dr/Cr 1255); transfer-order.controller.ts (/api/stock-ops/transfer-orders[/:no/ship|/receive][/in-transit/aging]); schema/inventory.ts transfer_orders + transfer_order_lines + migration 0341; ledger-constants.ts 1255 COA + CF_CLASSIFY; cutover/transfer-orders.ts (ToE, 21 checks)","Walkthrough create→ship→receive: inspect the ship JE (Dr 1255 / Cr 1200), the source relief, the in-transit aging read model, the receive JE (Dr 1200 / Cr 1255) + dest landing, the shipper≠receiver SoD, and that the perpetual sub-ledger reconciles to GL 1200 across the round-trip.","Re-perform: ship a transfer order → source qty down, Dr 1255 / Cr 1200 balanced, aging lists it; shipper receiving their own order is blocked (403 SOD_SELF_APPROVAL); an independent user receives → dest qty up, Dr 1200 / Cr 1255, in-transit cleared, sub-ledger ties to GL 1200 (re-performed by the transfer-orders harness, 21 checks).","In-transit aging / cutoff report + ship/receive JE pair + SoD test","Implemented")

add("INV-18","Inventory & COGS","Application","Inventory; COGS; Warranty/recall cost","A defective or recalled lot cannot be traced or contained: there is no genealogy linking a batch back to its supplier/goods-receipt or forward to the customers/sales it was issued into (so a recall can't scope who received it), and a suspect lot stays PICKABLE — the FEFO suggestion and the WMS wave keep allocating it — so non-conforming material keeps shipping while the investigation runs.","Existence/Completeness/Occurrence",
    "Lot recall / genealogy traceability + lot hold (INV-5, migration 0341): every lot (lot_ledger) gains a two-way GENEALOGY trace — GET /api/lots/:lotNo/trace resolves BACKWARD (lot → goods_receipt(s) via lot_ledger.gr_no → goods_receipts → PO → supplier/vendor) and FORWARD (lot → issue rows qty_out>0 → ref_doc pick → pick_lists → cust_pos_sales → customer/branch), so a recall investigation can scope both the source supplier and every downstream sale from one call. A one-click QUARANTINE — POST /api/lots/:lotNo/hold (reason-coded, HOLD- doc) — places a lot on hold (lot_holds, status Held); a held lot is EXCLUDED from BOTH the FEFO pick-suggestion (GET /api/lots/fefo/:itemId, excluded_held count returned) AND the WMS wave bin-allocation (wms.service suggestPickBin skips any bin whose lot has an active Held row), so a recalled/suspect lot physically cannot be picked, shipped or sold. POST /api/lots/:lotNo/release lifts the hold (audit trail retained — released_by/released_at/release_reason) and re-enables picking; LOT_NOT_HELD if not held. Hold/release gated to the inventory-control duties (lots/warehouse/wh_adjust); the trace read to lots/warehouse. lot_holds is tenant-scoped (canonical 0232 RLS, tenant-leading index); lot_ledger (no tenant_id) is never rewritten.","Det/Prev","Automated","Per recall / per pick","Warehouse / QA / F&B Controller","P10",
    "modules/lots/lots.service.ts (trace backward/forward genealogy; hold/release quarantine; fefo + heldLotNos exclusion); lots.controller.ts (/api/lots/:lotNo/trace|hold|release); modules/wms/wms.service.ts suggestPickBin (Held-lot exclusion in wave allocation); schema/inventory.ts lot_holds + migration 0341 (RLS, tenant-leading index, HOLD- doc); permissions.ts lots/warehouse/wh_adjust; cutover/lot-trace.ts (ToE)","Inspect the two-way trace (backward GR→supplier, forward pick/sale→customer), the hold/release lifecycle, and that a Held lot is excluded from BOTH the FEFO suggestion and the WMS wave allocation.","Re-perform (lot-trace harness): seed GR→lot→issue→sale; the backward trace returns the supplier + GR; the forward trace returns the customer + sale; holding the lot excludes it from FEFO (excluded_held>0) and from the WMS wave bin-allocation; releasing it re-includes the lot; releasing a non-held lot → LOT_NOT_HELD.","Two-way lot genealogy trace; lot hold/quarantine excluded from FEFO + WMS pick","Implemented")

add("INV-19","Inventory & COGS","Application","Inventory; Project WIP","Unused project material has no governed path back to stock: site returns re-enter inventory as ad-hoc positive adjustments (wrong cost, no link to what was issued), project WIP stays overstated after the material physically left the site, or a fictitious 'return' inflates on-hand stock and deflates project cost with no second pair of eyes.","Accuracy/Completeness/Existence",
    "Material return-to-stock (A1, docs/50 Wave 2, migration 0420): a return request (POST /api/reservations/:id/return) must reference the CONSUMED stock reservation it reverses — quantity is capped at the issued quantity AGGREGATE across the reservation's prior non-rejected returns (OVER_RETURN), a reason is mandatory (REASON_REQUIRED), and the value is the ORIGINAL issue unit cost read off the issue movement (never re-valued at today's average). A return valued at/above the materiality threshold (MATERIAL_RETURN_APPROVAL_THRESHOLD, default THB 1,000) posts NOTHING until a DIFFERENT user approves (maker-checker, SOD_VIOLATION on self-approve — the docs/49 SME seam applies); sub-threshold returns post immediately. Posting is the exact inverse of issue-to-project via the valued sub-ledger: stock back on hand + Dr inventory / Cr 1260 project WIP (project_id dimension), idempotent per MRET ref, and a NEGATIVE consumed commitment un-draws the BoQ line so the material budget frees up. Register at GET /api/reservations/returns.","Prev","Automated","Per return","Warehouse / ProjectController","P13",
    "reservations.service.ts requestReturn (OVER_RETURN/REASON_REQUIRED/RESERVATION_NOT_CONSUMED, original-issue-cost valuation, threshold gate) / approveReturn (assertMakerChecker) / rejectReturn / listReturns / postReturn (negative consumed commitment); inventory-ledger.service.ts returnFromProject (Dr inventory / Cr 1260 project_id, layer reopen, MRET idempotency); reservations.controller.ts (/api/reservations/:id/return, /returns[...]); schema/projects.ts project_material_returns (migration 0420, 0232 RLS); cutover/projects.ts §9f-ter (ToE)","Inspect the qty-aggregate cap, the reason requirement, the original-issue-cost valuation, the ≥-threshold maker-checker gate, and the Dr inventory / Cr 1260 reversal + negative consumed commitment.","Re-perform: issue 30 to a project; return 10 with a reason → posts immediately at the issue cost (stock +10, WIP −value, BoQ committed un-drawn, TB balanced); a return ≥ the threshold parks PendingApproval and moves NO stock; the requester's self-approve → 403 SOD_VIOLATION; a different user approves → stock/WIP move; re-approve → NO_PENDING_RETURN; returning more than issued → OVER_RETURN (re-performed by the projects harness).","Returns register (pending + history); the Dr inventory / Cr 1260 reversal postings; negative consumed commitments","Implemented")

add("INV-17","Inventory & COGS","Application","Inventory; COGS","Inventory existence is not assured between wall-to-wall counts: ad-hoc stocktakes (INV-04) have no schedule and no risk-based cadence, so high-velocity / high-value items — where existence and shrink risk concentrate — are not necessarily counted more often, and shrink can accumulate undetected until year-end. Separately, a counter who can see the SYSTEM (book) quantity can simply write the book number down as the 'physical' count, so a shortage they caused is never surfaced.","Existence/Completeness",
    "Governed cycle-count program with ABC classification + BLIND counts (INV-3, migration 0341): (1) ABC classification — POST /api/stock-ops/abc/recompute ranks the tenant's items by annual CONSUMPTION VALUE (Σ goods-issue qty × moving-average unit cost) and Pareto-bands them A (top ~80% of cumulative value) / B (next ~15%) / C (last ~5%), persisted per (tenant,item) in item_abc_class (rank + cum_pct + computed_at/by); GET /api/stock-ops/abc returns the classification. (2) Cadence — cycle_count_plans holds the days-between-counts per class (seeded A=30 / B=90 / C=180 on first recompute; tunable), so class drives frequency. (3) Due worklist — GET /api/stock-ops/cycle-counts/due lists items whose next count (last POSTED count date + class cadence) is due or overdue, never-counted first. (4) BLIND count — POST /api/stock-ops/cycle-counts captures the system/book qty SERVER-SIDE into a Draft stocktake but NEVER returns it to the counter (the generate response carries only the item list); the counter submits an independent physical count via .../cycle-counts/:taskNo/count. (5) Posting REUSES the existing stocktake path unchanged — POST /api/stocktake/:stNo/post enforces the INV-04 counter≠poster maker-checker (SoD R11: SOD_SELF_APPROVAL) and books the valued GL adjustment (inventory-ledger.postCountVariance, Dr/Cr 5810↔1200). No posting logic is duplicated: the program only SCHEDULES and BLINDS, then feeds the INV-04/INV-06 post path. All three tables tenant-scoped (canonical 0232 RLS, tenant-leading indexes).","Prev/Det","Auto+Manual","Continuous (per class cadence)","Warehouse Mgr / StockCounter / InventoryController (segregated)","P16",
    "modules/stock-ops/cycle-count.service.ts (recomputeAbc — consumption-value Pareto A/B/C; dueWorklist — cadence honoured off the last POSTED count; generateTask — blind Draft stocktake, system_qty captured but withheld; submitCount — independent physical entry) + cycle-count.controller.ts (/api/stock-ops/abc[/recompute], /api/stock-ops/cycle-counts[/due][/:taskNo/count] — recompute wh_adjust, count wh_count); reuses stock-ops.service.ts postStocktake (INV-04 counter≠poster + valued GL); schema/inventory.ts item_abc_class/cycle_count_plans/cycle_count_tasks + migration 0341 (RLS, tenant-leading indexes); cutover/cycle-counts.ts (ToE, 15 checks)","Inspect the ABC consumption-value ranking + Pareto banding, the per-class cadence in cycle_count_plans, the due-worklist next-due computation, that the generate response withholds system_qty (blind), and that posting routes through the unchanged INV-04 counter≠poster gate + valued adjustment.","Re-perform (cycle-counts harness): consume X/Y/Z at 5000/500/50 value → recompute classes them A/B/C; the due worklist lists all three (never counted, A first); generate a blind count for X → the response carries the item list but NO system_qty while the server captured book 500; the counter enters 480 → variance −20; a DIFFERENT user posts via the existing /api/stocktake/:no/post → Posted, valued on-hand corrected to 480 (@10 = 4800); the freshly-counted A item drops off the due worklist (cadence honoured); the counter posting their OWN count → 403 SOD_SELF_APPROVAL.","ABC classification snapshot; cadence-driven due worklist; blind count task + linked stocktake; INV-04 self-approval block + valued adjustment","Implemented")

# ---- Quality (CoA / out-of-spec release) ----
add("QC-03","Inventory & COGS","Application","Inventory; COGS; Warranty/quality cost","Received or produced lots exist (lot_ledger) but their quality is not evidenced by a Certificate of Analysis, and an out-of-spec lot (a measured characteristic outside its acceptable range) can be RELEASED into stock/production with no independent sign-off — one person both records the failing result and decides to release it, so non-conforming material enters the flow (defective finished goods, customer rejects, recalls / warranty cost) with no documented deviation approval and no audit trail of who authorised the exception.","Occurrence/Accuracy/Authorization/Segregation of Duties",
    "Certificate-of-Analysis capture + out-of-spec release maker-checker (QMS-3, migration 0333): a per-item quality_specs catalogue defines an acceptable [min_value, max_value] range per measured characteristic. A coa_certificates CoA is raised against a lot (source incoming/production) and its coa_results measured values are captured; on EVALUATE the CoA's overall_result is computed = fail if ANY characteristic's actual falls outside its [min,max] window, else pass. A PASS (in-spec) CoA can be released by its recorder (routine). A FAIL (out-of-spec) lot can be RELEASED only as a documented DEVIATION: the releaser must (a) hold the quality-approver duty quality_approve/exec (DEVIATION_APPROVER_REQUIRED otherwise), (b) be a DIFFERENT user than the CoA recorder (released_by ≠ created_by → 403 SOD_SELF_APPROVAL, binds even Admin), and (c) supply a mandatory deviation_reason (DEVIATION_REASON_REQUIRED) — so no single person can release failing material on their own authority. Release before evaluation is blocked (COA_NOT_EVALUATED); a decided CoA cannot be re-actioned (COA_NOT_HELD); reject holds the lot (release_status='rejected', never released). DETECTIVE side: GET /api/quality/coa/out-of-spec is the deviation register — CoAs that FAILED spec yet were released — exactly the population an auditor samples. The recorder duty (quality) is segregated from the release-approver duty (quality_approve) — SoD R21. Tenant-scoped (canonical 0232 RLS); references lot_no as text (the read-only lot ledger is never rewritten).","Prev/Det","Automated","Per lot / continuous","QA Recorder / QA Manager (segregated)","P10",
    "modules/quality/coa.service.ts (createSpec range guard; createCoa; addResults per-row pass/fail vs [spec_min,spec_max]; evaluate overall_result=fail if any characteristic out of spec; release QC-03 gate — DEVIATION_APPROVER_REQUIRED / SOD_SELF_APPROVAL / DEVIATION_REASON_REQUIRED / COA_NOT_EVALUATED / COA_NOT_HELD; reject; outOfSpecRegister); coa.controller.ts (/api/quality/specs, /api/quality/coa[/:id/results|evaluate|release|reject], /api/quality/coa/out-of-spec — reads gated quality/exec, record quality/exec, out-of-spec release quality_approve/exec); schema/quality-coa.ts quality_specs/coa_certificates/coa_results + migration 0333 (RLS, tenant-leading indexes, coa_no/spec_no unique per tenant); permissions.ts quality/quality_approve + SoD R21; cutover/quality-coa.ts (ToE, 16 checks)","Inspect the per-item spec range, the per-characteristic actual-vs-[min,max] pass/fail computation, the evaluate overall_result rule (any fail → fail), the out-of-spec release gate (approver duty + released_by ≠ created_by + mandatory deviation_reason), and the out-of-spec deviation register.","Re-perform (quality-coa harness): create a spec (min 10 / max 14); an in-spec CoA (actual 12) evaluates pass and its recorder releases it; an out-of-spec CoA (actual 18) evaluates fail; the recorder self-releasing the fail → 403 SOD_SELF_APPROVAL; a distinct approver releasing without a reason → 400 DEVIATION_REASON_REQUIRED; the distinct approver releasing WITH a reason → released (deviation); reject holds a fail lot; the out-of-spec register lists only the released fail; a second tenant sees none of the HQ CoAs and cannot read one (RLS).","Quality-spec catalogue; CoA + measured-result register; out-of-spec deviation register (released fails); SoD self-approval block","Implemented")

# ---- Multi-Branch & Offline POS ----
add("BRANCH-01","Multi-Branch & Offline POS","Application","Revenue","A POS sale is not attributed to its originating branch, so the consolidated branch roll-up is incomplete and cannot be tied to GL revenue.","Completeness",
    "Branch sale-tagging + HQ consolidation: every POS sale carries cust_pos_sales.branch_id; GET /api/branches/consolidated aggregates per branch (excluding Voided) and surfaces untagged sales as branch '(none)' — a deliberate completeness flag the controller investigates and clears before tying the consolidated total to GL revenue.","Det","Auto+Manual","Per sale / period","HQ Controller","P16",
    "branches.service.ts (consolidated, branch tagging); branches.controller.ts; cust_pos_sales.branch_id; cutover/branch.ts (ToE)","Inspect branch tagging completeness + the '(none)' surfacing + the GL tie.","Sample period: tagged sales group by branch, an untagged sale surfaces as '(none)', consolidated total ties to posted revenue.","Consolidation report; '(none)' investigation log","Implemented")
add("BRANCH-02","Multi-Branch & Offline POS","Application","Revenue","An offline terminal sells at a stale or wrong price/promotion because the cached catalog drifted from the master.","Accuracy",
    "Offline master-bundle export: GET /api/branches/master-bundle returns ONLY the active price-list + active promotions, time-stamped (generated_at). The offline terminal sells from this bundle, so it cannot ring a stale/withdrawn price or promo.","Prev","Automated","Per bundle push","HQ Controller / Pricing","P10",
    "branches.service.ts masterBundle (active price-list + active promos + generated_at); branches.controller.ts; cutover/branch.ts (ToE)","Inspect the bundle exports only active prices/promos with a timestamp.","Re-perform: export the bundle; confirm it carries only active price-list/promotions + generated_at.","Bundle metadata; bundle vs price-master diff","Implemented")
add("BRANCH-03","Multi-Branch & Offline POS","Application","Revenue; Cash","An offline-captured sale is LOST or DUPLICATED when connectivity returns — revenue understated (lost) or double-counted (duplicated), and the GL double-posted.","Completeness/Accuracy",
    "Offline-to-online exactly-once sync: offline-captured sales replay idempotently on (tenant, client_uuid) via the pos_offline_sync dedup ledger. Two paths share the ledger — the portal/inventory POS (POST /api/portal/pos/offline-sync, item_id lines) and the touch register (POST /api/restaurant/offline-sync, menu sku lines, re-running the restaurant order→checkout so the server re-prices + 86-checks). A re-sent batch returns 'duplicate' (no second sale/GL); a failed op is a RETRYABLE tombstone (sale_no NULL) that never blocks a later replay, so a transient error is not a lost sale; each op runs in its own savepoint so one bad sale never poisons the batch.","Det/Prev","Automated","Per sync","HQ Controller / IT","P10/P16",
    "portal/offline-sync.service.ts (item_id path); restaurant/offline-sync.service.ts (register sku path, reuses dineIn create+checkout); pos_offline_sync dedup ledger; web lib/offline-pos.ts + lib/register-offline.ts; cutover/offline-sync.ts + restaurant-offline.ts (ToE) + e2e/register-offline.spec.ts","Inspect the (tenant, client_uuid) dedup gate (sale_no NOT NULL), the per-op savepoint isolation, and the retryable-failure tombstone.","Re-perform: sync a batch (all synced, distinct SALE-), replay it (all duplicate, no double sale/GL), a bad op fails while neighbours sync, same uuid twice in a batch posts once, a transient failure replays to synced after the cause clears (re-performed by the offline-sync + restaurant-offline harnesses).","Sync recon report; terminal vs ledger counts; idempotency tests","Implemented")
add("BRANCH-04","Multi-Branch & Offline POS","Application","Revenue; Cash","A sale captured on an in-store hub (LAN-first store server) never reaches the central cloud ledger, reaches it twice, or reaches it altered — central revenue/GL incomplete, double-counted, or unfaithful to what the store rang.","Completeness/Accuracy/Authenticity",
    "Hub→cloud replay reconciliation (docs/41 Phase 2a): the hub pusher (db:hub:push) reconstructs each hub-captured restaurant sale from its originating order (lines + modifiers + discount/tip/service-charge), signs the batch HMAC-SHA256 with the shared HUB_SYNC_SECRET, and delivers to POST /api/hub/ingest — which verifies the signature timing-safe (fail-closed when the secret is unset) and replays through the SAME idempotent register offline-sync path (BRANCH-03 dedup on (tenant, client_uuid); the client_uuid is DETERMINISTIC hub:{tenant}:{hub_sale_no}, so any re-push lands 'duplicate' — exactly-once even after a lost push-log). The cloud re-prices authoritatively and posts GL on the cloud ledger (book of record). Every outcome is recorded in the hub-side hub_push_log; a sale the pusher cannot faithfully replay (buffet tier, loyalty redemption, no order linkage) is logged 'skipped_unsupported' WITH its reason — a visible exception queue, never a silent drop. GET /api/hub/reconciliation ties hub-ingested ops and their cloud sale values back per device/period for review.","Det/Prev","Automated","Per push run","HQ Controller / IT","P10/P16",
    "modules/hub/hub-sync.service.ts (ingest + reconciliation); database/hub-push.ts (pusher, hub_push_log, migration 0293); restaurant/offline-sync.service.ts (replay target); cutover/hub-snapshot.ts (ToE)","Inspect the HMAC verification (fail-closed, timing-safe), the deterministic client_uuid derivation, and the skipped_unsupported exception rows.","Re-perform: ring sales on a hub, push (cloud sale + GL posted, TB balanced), delete the hub push-log and re-push (all duplicate, zero new cloud ops), tamper the batch (403 HUB_SYNC_BAD_SIGNATURE), an unsupported sale surfaces as skipped_unsupported with a reason, and a buffet-tier session rung on the hub replays with the charge re-priced from the cloud package master (re-performed by the hub-snapshot harness).","Hub push log; reconciliation report; idempotency + tamper tests","Implemented")
add("BRANCH-05","Multi-Branch & Offline POS","Application","Cash; Revenue","A cash session (till/Z-report) captured on an in-store hub is certified against an INCOMPLETE or hub-asserted revenue population — the drawer variance is meaningless, a cash shortfall is hidden, or the over/short never reaches the central ledger.","Completeness/Accuracy/Authorization",
    "Hub till/Z-report ingest with cloud-side re-computation (docs/41 Phase 2c): the hub pushes the session envelope (float, physical closing count, cash movements, denominations) PLUS the hub sale numbers rung during the session; it never sends its own expected-cash figure. The cloud resolves EVERY listed sale through the BRANCH-04 dedup ledger and REFUSES the session (400 TILL_SALES_NOT_SYNCED, listing the missing sales) unless all of them have already replayed — a variance is never certified over a partial revenue population. It then computes expected = opening_float + SUM(cash tender amount + tip) + paid_in - paid_out - drops - cash_refunds from its OWN rows: the TENDER (recorded by the replayed checkout with the real method) says what entered the drawer, so a card/PromptPay sale in the session cannot inflate the expectation, and the tip is added back because payments.amount excludes it while the drawer receives it (matching the 1000 Cash debit), derives variance = counted - expected, and posts the over/short to 5830 on the SAME materiality line as a native close (REV-13): a variance above the threshold posts a DRAFT journal and parks the session PendingApproval for a DIFFERENT user to approve (GL-05 maker-checker); sub-threshold posts immediately. Idempotent on session_no (re-push returns duplicate; no second JE). Blocked/failed sessions stay in hub_push_log with their reason. Phase 4a: each hub reports a signed heartbeat (liveness, un-replayed backlog, failed/skipped counts, clock skew measured against the cloud clock); GET /api/hub/fleet flags a stale or backlogged box so un-replayed cash cannot sit unnoticed.","Det/Prev","Automated","Per till close / per heartbeat","HQ Controller / Branch Manager / IT","P10/P16",
    "modules/hub/hub-sync.service.ts (ingestTill, heartbeat, fleet); database/hub-push.ts (pushHubTills, sendHubHeartbeat); hub_heartbeats + hub_push_log.doc_type (migration 0296); payments.service.ts CASH_VARIANCE_THRESHOLD (shared materiality); cutover/hub-snapshot.ts (ToE)","Inspect the TILL_SALES_NOT_SYNCED completeness gate, the cloud-side expected-cash re-computation (hub figures never trusted), the shared materiality threshold + maker-checker parking, and the heartbeat staleness/backlog flags.","Re-perform: close a till on a hub while one covered sale is un-replayed (session BLOCKED, logged with reason), resolve and re-push (session ingests; expected cash re-derived from the cloud ledger; immaterial short posts 5830 immediately; TB balanced), re-push (idempotent, no second JE), tamper the envelope (403), and confirm the heartbeat surfaces the backlog and is tenant-isolated (re-performed by the hub-snapshot harness).","Hub push log (doc_type='till'); till_sessions + 5830 postings; hub fleet/heartbeat report","Implemented")
add("BRANCH-06","Multi-Branch & Offline POS","Application","COGS; Inventory","Kitchen waste recorded on an in-store hub never reaches the central ledger: the expense (5810) and the inventory relief (1200) exist only on the box, so central COGS is understated, the inventory position drifts, and the shrinkage signal an HQ controller most wants — reason-coded waste by store — is invisible.","Completeness/Accuracy",
    "Hub waste replay (docs/41 Phase 2c-2): the hub pusher sends each waste_log document (item, qty, reason code, unit cost) signed HMAC-SHA256 to POST /api/hub/ingest-waste, which verifies the signature timing-safe (fail-closed when HUB_SYNC_SECRET is unset) and replays it through the SAME WasteService the cloud uses natively — so every native guard applies: positive qty, a known reason code, and the INV-07 perpetual-item guard (a perpetual-tracked item must go through the approved write-off, so such a document fails LOUDLY and stays visible in hub_push_log rather than relieving inventory off-control). The hub's waste_no IS the document identity on both ledgers, so a re-push returns the stored row (duplicate) and neither decrements stock nor posts GL twice. Valuation: unit_cost is the hub kitchen's ingredient cost; the cloud has no independent basis to re-derive it for a non-perpetual ingredient, so it is accepted and carried into the GL (stated, not silently assumed).","Det/Prev","Automated","Per push run","HQ Controller / Branch Manager","P10/P13",
    "modules/hub/hub-sync.service.ts (ingestWaste); database/hub-push.ts (pushHubWaste, hub_push_log doc_type='waste'); inventory/waste.service.ts (logWaste with an existing waste_no, idempotent); cutover/hub-snapshot.ts (ToE)","Inspect the HMAC verification, the waste_no idempotency short-circuit, and that the ingest re-runs the native WasteService guards (incl. INV-07).","Re-perform: log waste on a hub (Dr 5810 / Cr 1200 locally), push it (same waste_no + qty + cost on the cloud, GL posted, TB balanced), re-push (nothing collected; a forced re-send is a duplicate that posts nothing), tamper the envelope (403) — re-performed by the hub-snapshot harness.","hub_push_log (doc_type='waste'); waste_log + 5810/1200 postings; waste-by-reason report","Implemented")
add("BRANCH-07","Multi-Branch & Offline POS","Application","Inventory","A physical count posted on an in-store hub never reaches the central inventory records, or a machine replay LAUNDERS a self-approved count into them: the counter who found the variance also posted it, and the segregation the control depends on is erased by the sync principal.","Completeness/Authorization",
    "Hub stocktake replay with SoD preserved (docs/41 Phase 2c-2): only POSTED count sheets are pushed (a Draft count is not yet evidence), each carrying BOTH humans — counted_by and posted_by (persisted by migration 0318, since the native post previously stored only the counter). The signed document goes to POST /api/hub/ingest-stocktake, which verifies the HMAC timing-safe (fail-closed on HUB_SYNC_SECRET) and REFUSES the sheet when the two names are equal or missing (403/400 STOCKTAKE_NOT_SEGREGATED) — the machine principal hub-sync can never post a count it would have been forbidden to post as a human (SoD R11 / INV-04). Accepted sheets are recreated with the hub's st_no and produce the same Stock In/Out variance movements a native post produces; idempotent on (tenant, st_no) so a re-push creates no second movement. Blocked sheets stay in hub_push_log with STOCKTAKE_NOT_SEGREGATED for review — never silently dropped, never silently accepted.","Prev/Det","Automated","Per push run","Inventory Controller / HQ","P13",
    "modules/hub/hub-sync.service.ts (ingestStocktake); stock-ops/stock-ops.service.ts (ingestHubStocktake, postStocktake records posted_by); database/hub-push.ts (pushHubStocktakes, hub_push_log doc_type='stocktake'); migration 0318; cutover/hub-snapshot.ts (ToE)","Inspect the two-name requirement + the equality refusal, the st_no idempotency, and that the replay creates the same variance movements as a native post.","Re-perform: on a hub post a sheet counted by A and posted by B, and a second sheet counted and posted by A; push — the first lands (both names on the cloud document, one Stock Out movement), the second is BLOCKED with STOCKTAKE_NOT_SEGREGATED and logged; re-push creates no second movement (re-performed by the hub-snapshot harness).","stocktakes.counted_by/posted_by on both ledgers; hub_push_log (doc_type='stocktake'); variance movements","Implemented")

# ---- Manufacturing & Costing ----
add("MFG-01","Manufacturing & Costing","Application","Inventory; COGS","Unauthorized BOM/recipe change mis-states standard cost and every downstream WIP/COGS posting; or the role that maintains the recipe also transacts on it.","Authorization",
    "BOM master maker-checker / SoD: the master BOM library (bom_master) is maintained + distributed by HQ separately from transacting; a tenant BOM submission is reviewed and merged by HQ on approval (a maker-checker over master data). Recipe roll-up (line cost + labor + overhead → cost per unit) is the standard-cost basis. Master-data access is segregated from production (R13).","Prev","Manual+Auto","Per BOM change","HQ MasterSteward / CostAccountant","P13",
    "bom master + submissions (/api/bom/master, /api/bom/submissions, /api/portal/bom); manufacturing.service.ts BOM scaling; cutover/cpq.ts + manufacturing.ts (ToE)","Inspect BOM maintenance access + the submission→approve maker-checker + the costing roll-up.","Sample BOM change is HQ-approved before use; standard cost rolls up correctly.","BOM approval log; costing roll-up","Implemented")
add("MFG-02","Manufacturing & Costing","Application","WIP; Finished Goods; COGS","Production cost is mis-stated: WIP not relieved, the conversion absorption left stranded, or a yield loss (spoilage/waste) silently capitalised into finished-goods inventory instead of expensed.","Valuation/Completeness/Accuracy",
    "Production work-order WIP costing with a balanced JE at each step: ISSUE posts Dr 1250 WIP / Cr 1200 raw materials / Cr 2380 manufacturing-costs-applied (idempotent — re-issue is a no-op); COMPLETE posts Dr 1210 Finished Goods at the standard cost of the ACTUAL quantity produced + books the YIELD VARIANCE to 5810 (produced < planned → debit 5810 loss; over-yield → credit) / Cr 1250 WIP — so WIP is always fully relieved and FG is never over-valued on a short yield. State machine Open→Released→Completed (out-of-order → BAD_STATUS). The 2380/1250 clearing balances tie out at close. Scrap/rework write-off of defective output posts to 5810 with CostAccountant authorization.","Prev","Automated","Per work order","Warehouse / CostAccountant","P13",
    "manufacturing.service.ts issue/complete (yield variance to 5810; fmt exposes yield_variance); manufacturing.controller.ts (bom_master/warehouse/exec); schema/manufacturing.ts work_orders; cutover/manufacturing.ts (ToE)","Inspect the issue/complete JEs + the standard-unit-cost FG valuation + the yield-variance plug + the status guard.","Re-perform: issue (WIP charged), complete at full yield (FG = full cost, no variance) and at a short yield (FG = std×produced, the lost yield to 5810, WIP nets to 0, TB balanced) — re-performed by the harness.","WO costing register (yield_variance per WO); production JEs","Implemented")
add("MFG-03","Manufacturing & Costing","Application","Inventory; COGS","Standard-cost inventory received without isolating the price variance — actual purchase cost buried in inventory, COGS and PPV mis-stated.","Valuation/Accuracy",
    "Goods-receipt capitalisation under the configured costing method (FIFO/AVG/STD per tenant+item): FIFO/AVG → Dr 1200 / Cr 2000 at actual; STD → Dr 1200 at standard, the purchase-price variance booked to 5500 (unfavourable Dr / favourable Cr), Cr 2000 at actual — the PPV (5500) leg is the single balancing plug (= actual − standard, rounded once) so the JE can never reject UNBALANCED on independent per-leg rounding.","Det","Automated","Per receipt","CostAccountant","P13",
    "costing.service.ts (config/valuation, GRV capitalisation + 5500 PPV); costing.controller.ts (masterdata); cutover/costing.ts (ToE)","Inspect the per-method capitalisation routing + the PPV plug.","Re-perform a STD receipt at actual ≠ standard → PPV isolated to 5500, JE balanced; valuation ties to GL 1200/1210/1250.","PPV postings; costing valuation","Implemented")
add("COST-02","Manufacturing & Costing","Application","Inventory; COGS","A standard-cost item's standard is set once and never rolled: as real cost drifts, on-hand inventory (valued at the stale standard) is mis-stated and COGS on issue is wrong; OR one person unilaterally re-values inventory by editing the standard, with no independent review of the revaluation that hits the GL.","Valuation/Accuracy/Authorization",
    "Standard-cost roll / inventory revaluation under MAKER-CHECKER (INV-4). A periodic standard-cost revision is PROPOSED per STD-costed item (a Draft header + per-item lines capturing old_std, the proposed new_std, and an on-hand SNAPSHOT), computing the revaluation = on_hand x (new_std - old_std) with NO posting. A DISTINCT approver (approved_by != prepared_by -> 403 SOD_SELF_APPROVAL) approves it -> for every line the stored standard is rolled forward (so subsequent issues cost at the NEW standard) and a BALANCED revaluation JE posts: standard rose -> Dr 1200 Inventory / Cr 5500 std-cost variance (favourable); standard fell -> Cr 1200 / Dr 5500 (unfavourable) - the two legs are equal by construction so the JE never rejects UNBALANCED. Draft -> Approved only; a non-STD item is rejected (STD_ITEM_REQUIRED); re-approval of an Approved revision is refused (NOT_DRAFT - no double post). The preparer duty is md_config (masterdata); the approver duty is exec - the standing md_config<->exec SoD conflict (MDM-01 rule) already prevents one person holding both, and the in-app self-approval block is the runtime control.","Prev","Automated","Per revision","CostAccountant / FinancialController","P13",
    "modules/costing/std-cost.service.ts (revise snapshots on-hand + STD_ITEM_REQUIRED guard; approve rolls item_costing.standard_cost + posts the 1200<->5500 revaluation JE via LedgerService.postEntry, idempotent on STDREV/rev_no; SOD_SELF_APPROVAL + NOT_DRAFT guards); costing.controller.ts (std-cost/revise @masterdata, std-cost[/:no] @masterdata/exec/planner, std-cost/:no/approve @exec); schema/std-cost.ts std_cost_revisions/std_cost_revision_lines (migration 0341); cutover/std-cost-roll.ts (ToE)","Inspect the revise->approve maker-checker + the on-hand snapshot + the revaluation formula + the 1200/5500 JE routing + the preparer!=approver check + the roll-forward of the stored standard.","Re-perform: revise a STD item (on-hand snapshotted, nothing posted); the preparer self-approves -> 403 SOD_SELF_APPROVAL; a distinct approver approves -> Dr 1200/Cr 5500 (or the reverse on a drop), the standard rolls forward, a subsequent issue costs at the new standard, TB balanced; a non-STD item is rejected (STD_ITEM_REQUIRED) and re-approval refused (NOT_DRAFT) - re-performed by the harness.","Std-cost revision register (old/new std, on-hand snapshot, revaluation, prepared_by/approved_by); revaluation JEs (STDREV)","Implemented")
add("QC-01","Manufacturing & Costing","Application","Inventory; COGS","A failed quality inspection or a customer/supplier complaint is dispositioned by whoever raised it, and a Scrap/Use-as-is/Return decision writes the defective stock off to loss (Dr 5810) with NO independent approval — a single person can create and dispose of a non-conformance, concealing shrink or writing off good stock.","Authorization/Valuation",
    "Non-Conformance (NCR) register with maker-checker disposition (QMS-1). A failed inspection (or a customer/supplier complaint) is raised as a first-class NCR (open → pending_disposition → dispositioned → closed); a FINANCIAL disposition (scrap / use-as-is / return) is proposed as pending_disposition and applied — and the scrap write-off posted (Dr 5810 loss / Cr the source inventory account: WO→1250 WIP, GR→1200 raw materials, else→1210 finished goods) — ONLY when a DIFFERENT user approves (dispositioned_by ≠ raised_by → 403 SOD_SELF_APPROVAL). Reject returns the NCR to open. Raising is the `quality` duty; the disposition is the `quality_approve`/exec duty, segregated by SoD R21. Every status transition is written to the doc_status_log audit trail.","Prev","Automated","Per NCR disposition","QualityController / QualityApprover","P13",
    "modules/mfg-depth/ncr.service.ts (raiseNcr/promoteInspection/disposition/reject; scrap GL via LedgerService.postEntry); mfg-depth.controller.ts NcrController (/api/quality/ncr, /api/quality/defect-codes; quality vs quality_approve); schema/quality-ncr.ts non_conformances/defect_codes (migration 0331); permissions.ts SoD R21; cutover/quality-ncr.ts (ToE)","Inspect the NCR maker-checker (raise → pending → a DIFFERENT approver dispositions) + the scrap write-off JE + the SoD R21 duty split + the status-log trail.","Re-perform: raise an NCR proposing scrap → pending_disposition; the raiser self-dispositions → 403 SOD_SELF_APPROVAL; a distinct approver dispositions scrap → Dr 5810 / Cr 1250 posted, entry_no recorded, TB balanced; reject → NCR returns to open (re-performed by the harness).","NCR register (status, dispositioned_by, entry_no); scrap write-off JEs; doc_status_log","Implemented")

# ---- Project Accounting ----
add("PROJ-01","Project Accounting","Application","Project WIP; COGS","Project cost mis-stated: a recoverable cost not captured, or an UN-recoverable (non-billable) cost capitalised into project WIP as an asset that overstates the unbilled balance and inflates margin.","Valuation/Accuracy/Completeness",
    "Project cost capture with a balanced JE and a billable/non-billable split: a BILLABLE time/expense cost is a recoverable asset → Dr 1260 Project WIP / Cr 2390 Project Costs Applied (accumulates in cost_to_date, relieved to COGS at billing); a NON-BILLABLE cost is unrecoverable → EXPENSED immediately Dr 5800 Project Cost of Services / Cr 2390 (never enters the billable WIP), so the register's total_cost and true margin (billed − recognised − non-billable) reflect the absorbed cost. A non-positive amount → BAD_AMOUNT; first cost flips Open→Active.","Prev","Automated","Per cost entry","ProjectAccountant","P13",
    "projects.service.ts logCost (billable→1260, non-billable→5800; fmt exposes non_billable_cost/total_cost/margin); projects.controller.ts; schema/projects.ts project_entries.billable; cutover/projects.ts (ToE)","Inspect the billable/non-billable GL routing + the WIP vs immediate-expense decision + the margin roll-up.","Re-perform: a billable cost capitalises to 1260; a non-billable cost expenses to 5800 (NOT WIP), cost_to_date unchanged, and the project margin absorbs it (re-performed by the harness).","Project cost JEs; cost register (non_billable_cost)","Implemented")
add("PROJ-02","Project Accounting","Application","Project WIP; Revenue; COGS","Revenue billed without matching cost — WIP not relieved, cost of services mis-stated, margin overstated.","Accuracy/Cut-off",
    "Customer billing recognises revenue (Dr 1100 AR / Cr 4200 Project Revenue) and relieves the unbilled WIP to cost of services up to the unrecognised billable cost (Dr 5800 / Cr 1260) in the same event — matching cost to recognised revenue. Billing is by raw amount (T&M) or by PERCENT of the contract for Fixed-price milestone billing; a Fixed-price contract is CAPPED at the contract value (cumulative billing can never exceed it — BILL_EXCEEDS_CONTRACT), so the customer is never over-billed (billed_pct/remaining_to_bill on the register). Billing is idempotent on (project, cumulative billed amount).","Prev","Automated","Per billing","ProjectController / ArSpecialist","P13",
    "projects.service.ts bill (revenue + WIP relief, idempotent); projects.controller.ts (R07 vs cost initiation); cutover/projects.ts (ToE)","Inspect the bill JE + the WIP-relief matching + idempotency.","Re-perform a billing → revenue recognised, WIP relieved to 5800 up to unrecognised cost, 1260 reduced; margin = billed − recognised cost (re-performed by the harness).","Billing JEs; margin/WIP measurement","Implemented")
add("PROJ-03","Project Accounting","Detective","Project WIP","Unbilled WIP (1260) and the 2390 clearing balance not reviewed at close — stale or unrecoverable WIP carried into the financial statements.","Valuation",
    "Period-end review of unbilled-WIP (1260) aging and the project-costs-applied (2390) clearing tie-out; project margin (billed_to_date − recognised_cost − non-billable) reviewed at close. A PERIOD CLOSE-REVIEW SIGN-OFF (POST /api/projects/close-review) snapshots the WIP(1260) total + the 2390 clearing balance + the open-project count as a Prepared review; an INDEPENDENT approver (SoD: approver ≠ preparer) signs off (Approved) — the auditable record that WIP + clearing were reviewed at close, retained per (tenant, period). SoD: billing authorisation is segregated from cost initiation (R07).","Det","Hybrid","Period","ProjectAccountant / Controller","P16",
    "projects.service.ts (closeSnapshot 1260/2390; prepareCloseReview/approveCloseReview maker-checker); projects.controller.ts (POST /api/projects/close-review[/:period/approve|reject], GET /close-reviews — gated 'exec'); schema/projects.ts project_close_reviews + drizzle/0206_project_close_review.sql; cutover/projects.ts (ToE)","Inspect 1260 aging + 2390 clearing + margin review evidence + the signed close review.","Re-perform: a close review snapshots WIP(1260)+2390 clearing+open projects (Prepared); the preparer cannot self-approve (SOD_VIOLATION); an independent approver signs off (Approved) — re-performed by the projects harness. Sample projects: 1260 WIP agrees to cost_to_date − recognised; 2390 clears; stale WIP investigated.","WIP/clearing close-review sign-off","Implemented")
add("CRM-WL","Project Accounting","Application","Project WIP; Revenue (pipeline → delivery)","A sales opportunity is delivered without an authorized, traceable hand-off: a project is spun up from a deal that was never won (an open or lost deal), or the same won deal spawns duplicate projects — so project revenue / WIP cannot be traced back to an approved, won opportunity and the deal-to-delivery (win/loss) link is unreliable.","Authorization/Accuracy/Completeness",
    "Opportunity→project conversion is gated and traceable: POST /api/projects/from-opportunity/:oppNo converts ONLY a WON crm_opportunity (an open/lost deal → OPP_NOT_WON; an unknown deal → OPP_NOT_FOUND), seeds the project contract from the deal value, and stamps customer_no (→ customer_master) + crm_opp_no (→ crm_opportunities.opp_no). Conversion is IDEMPOTENT on crm_opp_no — a given opportunity converts to at most one project, so a re-submit returns the existing project rather than duplicating it. Win/loss integrity (controlled stage machine, mandatory lost reason, terminal won/lost) is enforced upstream by REV-17.","Prev","Automated","Per conversion","ProjectController / SalesManager","P13",
    "projects.service.ts createFromOpportunity (won-only + idempotent on crm_opp_no); projects.controller.ts POST from-opportunity/:oppNo; schema/projects.ts projects.customer_no/crm_opp_no (migration 0183); crm-pipeline.service.ts (REV-17 stage machine); cutover/projects.ts (ToE)","Inspect the won-only guard, the customer_no/crm_opp_no stamping, and the idempotency key on crm_opp_no.","Re-perform: a won opportunity converts to a project seeded with the deal value + crm_opp_no; re-converting returns the same project (no duplicate); an open deal → OPP_NOT_WON; an unknown deal → OPP_NOT_FOUND (re-performed by the harness).","Conversion audit (project.crm_opp_no → opportunity); won-only / idempotency rejections","Implemented")
add("PROJ-05","Project Accounting","Application","Project cost (labor); Project WIP","Project labor is estimated/charged at an ungoverned or arbitrary rate, or a resource is committed beyond capacity — so planned project cost is unreliable and delivery is over-committed (margin erosion / schedule slip).","Valuation/Accuracy",
    "Resource cost/bill rates are governed by an effective-dated rate card (resource_rates): a project resource assignment resolves and SNAPSHOTS the applicable rate (latest effective_from on/before the assignment date, with effective_to open or on/after), so labor cost/bill estimates trace to an authorized rate (no guessed rate — zero when none is on file). Allocation % is validated to (0,100] (BAD_ALLOC), and a capacity/utilization roll-up sums allocation per resource across projects and flags >100% over-allocation for review.","Prev/Det","Automated","Per assignment / continuous","ProjectManager / ResourceManager","P13",
    "projects.service.ts addRateCard/resolveRate (effective-dated), assignResource (snapshot + BAD_ALLOC), resourceUtilization (over-allocation); projects.controller.ts (rate-cards, :code/resources, resources/utilization); schema/projects.ts resource_rates/project_resources (migration 0185); cutover/projects.ts (ToE)","Inspect the rate-card effective-dating + the snapshot-at-assignment + the allocation guard + the utilization roll-up.","Re-perform: an assignment snapshots the rate-card rate (zero when none on file); alloc_pct 0 → BAD_ALLOC; a resource booked 60%+60% → utilization 120%, over_allocated (re-performed by the harness).","Rate card; resource assignments (snapshot rate); utilization report","Implemented")
add("PROJ-04","Project Accounting","Application","Project cost (labor); Project WIP","Project labor is charged to a project without independent authorization — a person logs time and the same person posts it to project WIP — so labor cost / unbilled WIP can be inflated or misallocated with no review.","Authorization/Accuracy",
    "Timesheet→project labor is maker-checker: a timesheet is submitted Pending (submitted_by recorded) and a DIFFERENT user must approve it (a submitter approving their own → SOD_SELF_APPROVAL, binds even Admin). On approval, if the timesheet targets a project, its labor cost (total hours × the employee's hourly rate) posts ONCE into project WIP through the authorized PRJ-COST path (billable → Dr 1260 / Cr 2390; non-billable → Dr 5800 / Cr 2390); re-approving an already-approved timesheet does not double-post (idempotent). An unknown timesheet → TIMESHEET_NOT_FOUND.","Prev","Automated","Per approval","ProjectManager / Timekeeper (segregated)","P13",
    "hcm.service.ts approveTimesheet (SoD + posts via ProjectsService.logCost); hcm.controller.ts POST timesheets/:id/approve; schema/hcm.ts timesheets.project_id/billable/status/submitted_by/approved_by (migration 0186); projects.service.ts logCost (PRJ-COST); cutover/projects.ts (ToE)","Inspect the submitter≠approver guard + the single-post-on-approval into project WIP.","Re-perform: a submitter self-approving → SOD_SELF_APPROVAL; an independent approver posts hours×rate to project WIP once; re-approval does not double-post (re-performed by the harness).","Timesheet approved_by/submitted_by; PRJ-COST JE; SOD_SELF_APPROVAL rejection","Implemented")
add("PROJ-06","Project Accounting","Detective","Project WIP; Project cost","Project cost / schedule performance is not measured, so an overrun or slippage is detected late — actual cost diverges from earned value with no CPI/SPI signal, and project WIP (1260 actuals) is not reconciled to the work actually earned.","Valuation/Accuracy",
    "Earned-value management: BAC / PV / EV / AC are derived from the project's WBS tasks (planned cost, % complete, planned_end schedule) and its actual cost incurred (cost_to_date + non-billable = the 1260 WIP + 5800 actuals), yielding CPI = EV/AC (cost), SPI = EV/PV (schedule), cost & schedule variance, and EAC/ETC at-completion forecasts. The EVM endpoint reconciles earned value to the project's actual cost (AC ties to the WIP/COGS actuals), giving a detective signal of cost overrun / schedule slip for review.","Det","Automated","Continuous / period","ProjectManager / ProjectAccountant","P16",
    "projects.service.ts evm (BAC/PV/EV/AC → CPI/SPI/EAC; AC = cost_to_date + non-billable); projects.controller.ts GET :code/evm; schema/projects.ts project_tasks (planned_cost/pct_complete/planned_end; depends_on migration 0187); cutover/projects.ts (ToE)","Inspect the EV/PV/AC derivation + the CPI/SPI/variance math + the AC-to-WIP reconciliation.","Re-perform: tasks 1000@100% (scheduled past) + 1000@0% (future) with AC 900 → BAC 2000, EV 1000, PV 1000, CPI 1.1111, SPI 1.0, EAC ~1800 (re-performed by the harness).","EVM report (CPI/SPI/variances/EAC); WIP (1260) reconciliation","Implemented")
add("PROJ-07","Project Accounting","Application","Project cost; Project WIP","A project silently moves its goalposts: the plan (scope/budget/schedule) is re-baselined with no authorization or audit trail, so variance reporting always looks on-target and scope/cost creep is masked.","Authorization/Accuracy",
    "Change-controlled baselines: a project baseline snapshots the approved BAC + critical-path duration at a point in time. The FIRST baseline is free; RE-baselining REQUIRES a reason (BASELINE_REASON_REQUIRED) and supersedes the prior active baseline (history preserved — status active→superseded, captured_by/at recorded), so the goalposts can't move silently. Variance of the CURRENT plan vs the active baseline (bac_delta / bac_pct / duration_delta) surfaces scope/cost creep for review.","Prev","Automated","Per (re)baseline","ProjectController / PMO","P13",
    "projects.service.ts captureBaseline (reason-gated re-baseline + supersede history) / getBaseline (variance vs active) / currentPlan; projects.controller.ts POST+GET :code/baseline; schema/projects.ts project_baselines (migration 0188); cutover/projects.ts (ToE)","Inspect the reason-gated re-baseline, the history (active→superseded), and the current-vs-baseline variance.","Re-perform: capture a baseline (BAC 2000); add scope → variance +500/+25%; re-baseline without a reason → BASELINE_REASON_REQUIRED; with a reason → new active (BAC 2500), variance 0, history 2 (re-performed by the harness).","Baseline history (active/superseded, reason, captured_by); variance report","Implemented")
add("PROJ-08","Project Accounting","Detective","Project delivery (risk register)","A project's threats and problems are not governed: an open HIGH risk (or a materialised issue) goes unmitigated and unreviewed, so a foreseeable cost/schedule overrun is buried instead of surfaced for action at review/close.","Completeness/Valuation",
    "Project risk & issue register: each risk (probability × impact) / issue (5 × impact) is scored 1–25 with a derived RAG, an owner, a mitigation plan and a due date. The register summary and the portfolio top-risks roll-up surface OPEN HIGH (red) items and, specifically, the UNMITIGATED HIGH subset (open high with no mitigation), so an unmitigated exposure is escalated for review — not silently carried.","Det","Automated","Per review / at close","ProjectController / PMO","P13",
    "projects.service.ts addRisk / listRisks (summary high_open + unmitigated_high) / patchRisk (re-score, close) / topRisks (portfolio roll-up); projects.controller.ts POST+GET :code/risks, PATCH risks/:id, GET risks/top; schema/projects.ts project_risks (migration 0192); cutover/projects.ts (ToE)","Inspect the score/RAG derivation, the open-high and unmitigated-high counts, and the portfolio top-risks roll-up.","Re-perform: log a high risk (prob 5 × impact 5 = 25, red) with no mitigation → summary unmitigated_high 1; add a mitigation + close a risk → counts fall; portfolio top-risks ranks the open red item first (re-performed by the harness).","Risk register (RAG, owner, mitigation, due); portfolio top-risks roll-up","Implemented")
add("PROJ-09","Project Accounting","Application","Project Revenue (4200); Contract Asset (1265); Contract Liability (2410); Project WIP (1260); COGS (5800)","Long-duration fixed-price project revenue is recognised only when an invoice is raised (point-in-time), so revenue/cost are mismatched across periods and earnings are mis-stated — or an over-time recognition is computed on an arbitrary/ungoverned basis, letting a single user pull revenue forward.","Accuracy/Cut-off/Valuation",
    "Over-time (percentage-of-completion) revenue recognition on a cost-to-cost basis (TFRS 15 / IFRS 15 / ASC 606 over-time): for a rev_method='poc' fixed-price project, POC% = cost_to_date / estimated_total_cost (EAC), capped at 100%; recognised revenue to date = contract × POC%, and the PERIOD revenue = that minus revenue already recognised — booked Dr 2410 (release any billings-in-excess first) then Dr 1265 Contract Asset / Cr 4200, with the period cost relieved Dr 5800 / Cr 1260. Billing is DECOUPLED from recognition: an invoice on a POC project posts Dr 1100 AR / Cr 1265 (clearing earned-but-unbilled), any excess over recognised revenue parked as a contract liability (2410, billings in excess). So the contract asset/liability position is always recognised-revenue vs billed, revenue is earned as work progresses (not when invoiced), and recognition is idempotent per (project, recognised total). Posts through the PERIOD_LOCKED + GL-audit gates; authorised (gl_post/exec). billing-method projects keep point-in-time recognition unchanged.","Prev","Automated","Per period / at recognition","Financial Controller / PM","P13",
    "projects.service.ts recognizePoc (cost-to-cost %, contract asset/liability mechanics, idempotent) + bill (POC invoice path Dr 1100 / Cr 1265 / Cr 2410) + fmt (poc_pct, contract_asset, billings_in_excess, recognized_revenue); projects.controller.ts POST :code/recognize (gl_post/exec); schema/projects.ts rev_method/estimated_cost/recognized_revenue (migration 0194) + COA 1265; cutover/projects.ts (ToE)","Inspect the cost-to-cost %, the period-revenue delta vs recognised-to-date, the contract asset/liability postings, and that billing on a POC project recognises NO revenue.","Re-perform: POC project (contract 100000, est cost 60000); cost 30000 → recognise @ 50% revenue 50000 / cost 30000 (contract asset 50000); bill 40000 clears the asset (no revenue); cost to 60000 → recognise @ 100% (revenue 100000 total); bill-ahead → billings-in-excess 2410; recognise on a billing-method project → NOT_POC (re-performed by the harness).","Contract asset/liability schedule; period revenue-recognition JEs (4200/1265/2410/5800/1260); POC% reconciliation","Implemented")
add("PROJ-10","Project Accounting","Application","Project contract value; Project budget","A project's contract value / scope is changed unilaterally or without an audit trail — a single person inflates the contract (revenue/billing ceiling) or budget over their own work, and the baseline still reads on-target so scope/price creep is invisible.","Authorization/Segregation of Duties/Accuracy",
    "Change orders are maker-checker: a contract/scope variation is a REQUEST (`pending`) that applies NOTHING; a DIFFERENT user must approve it (the approver ≠ the requester → SOD_SELF_APPROVAL), at which point the contract/budget/EAC deltas are applied to the project AND a new baseline is auto-captured (reason = the change order), so the goalposts move only with authorization, segregation, and a preserved variance trail (ties to PROJ-07). An empty change order (no deltas) is rejected (EMPTY_CHANGE_ORDER); a decided change order can't be re-decided (CHANGE_ORDER_DECIDED).","Prev","Automated","Per change order","ProjectController / PMO","P13",
    "projects.service.ts createChangeOrder (pending, posts nothing, EMPTY_CHANGE_ORDER) / approveChangeOrder (SOD_SELF_APPROVAL, applies deltas + auto re-baseline) / rejectChangeOrder / listChangeOrders; projects.controller.ts POST+GET :code/change-orders, POST change-orders/:id/approve|reject; schema/projects.ts project_change_orders (migration 0195); cutover/projects.ts (ToE)","Inspect the request→approve flow, the approver≠requester check, that a pending CO changes nothing, and the auto re-baseline on approval.","Re-perform: request a +20000 contract change (pending, contract unchanged); self-approve → SOD_SELF_APPROVAL; a different user approves → contract 120000 + a new baseline; empty CO → EMPTY_CHANGE_ORDER; re-approve → CHANGE_ORDER_DECIDED (re-performed by the harness).","Change-order register (pending/approved, requester/approver); the re-baseline on approval","Implemented")
add("PROJ-11","Project Accounting","Detective","Project delivery (governance exceptions)","Governance exceptions are scattered one project at a time, so a maker-checker approval (change order / project timesheet) sits unactioned, a project drifts red or over budget, a milestone slips, an open HIGH risk stays unmitigated, or an in-flight project runs with no baseline / stale health — buried until a periodic review instead of surfaced for action.","Completeness/Timeliness",
    "PMO action center / exception inbox: a single read-only worklist (GET /api/projects/action-center) aggregates, across all the caller's projects, the exceptions that need a person — pending change orders + pending project timesheets awaiting a DIFFERENT approver (maker-checker, PROJ-04/10), open HIGH risks with no mitigation plan (PROJ-08), red projects (CPI/SPI < 0.9) and over-budget projects, overdue-and-unreached milestones, and governance gaps (an in-flight project with no change-controlled baseline (PROJ-07) or no health snapshot within `stale_days`). Each item carries a severity (high/medium/low) and deep-links to the offending project tab; the list is bounded to the caller's RLS-visible projects. It is PROACTIVE: a red health snapshot or a newly-logged unmitigated-HIGH risk publishes a `project_action` event to the live SSE bus so the inbox wakes without a manual refresh. Posts nothing — a detective surfacing layer over existing controls.","Det","Automated","Continuous / per review","PMO / ProjectController","P13",
    "projects.service.ts actionCenter (aggregates over_budget/project_red/no_baseline/stale_health + pending change-orders/timesheets + slipping milestones + topRisks unmitigated-high) + emitAction (SSE on red/unmitigated-high, in snapProject + addRisk); projects.controller.ts GET action-center; bi-live.service.ts/bi-live.module.ts (shared BiLiveService bus); cutover/projects.ts (ToE)","Inspect the aggregation across the exception kinds, the severity/sort, the deep-links, and the proactive SSE emit on red/unmitigated-high.","Re-perform: seed a project with one of every exception → the worklist surfaces all kinds with the right severity (high first); the red snapshot + the unmitigated-high risk push a project_action SSE event; approving the change order clears change_order_pending + no_baseline from the list (re-performed by the harness).","PMO action center worklist (severity-ranked, deep-linked); the project_action SSE feed","Implemented")
add("PROJ-12","Project Accounting","Application","Project material budget (Bill of Quantities)","Material spend on a project exceeds its authorized Bill-of-Quantities budget — staff draw more material against a BoQ line than it is budgeted for, or two concurrent draws each pass an over-permissive check and jointly overrun, so the project silently blows its material budget before anyone reviews it.","Authorization/Accuracy",
    "Commitment/encumbrance control on the BoQ line budget: a project purchase order tagged to a BoQ line RESERVES budget in the `project_commitments` ledger (open+consumed count against the line; released — e.g. a cancelled PO — frees it). A draw is admitted only if `line.budget_amount − Σ(open+consumed) ≥ amount`, checked ATOMICALLY under a FOR UPDATE row-lock on the BoQ line so two concurrent draws cannot jointly overrun (BUDGET_EXCEEDED with the remaining otherwise). The BoQ budget baseline is itself maker-checker (an author-approved BoQ; approver ≠ author → SOD_SELF_APPROVAL syncs the project budget). A cancelled PO releases its encumbrance; a fully-received PO's commitments become consumed (actual). An optional per-project over-budget TOLERANCE (projects.budget_tolerance_pct) lets a draw exceed the line by up to that % of the line budget before it is blocked/needs approval (ceiling = budget × (1+tol%)); 0 = strict. Turns the material budget from OBSERVED into ENFORCED.","Prev","Automated","Per material draw (PO)","Procurement / ProjectController","P13",
    "commitments.service.ts reserve (FOR UPDATE lock on the BoQ line + committed vs budget → BUDGET_EXCEEDED) / release / consume / committedByLine / listForProject; procurement.service.ts createPo (reserve inside the PO tx → over-budget rolls the PO back), cancelPo (release), createGr (consume on full receipt); projects.service.ts getBoq (per-line budget/committed/remaining) + listCommitments; projects.controller.ts GET :code/commitments; schema/projects.ts project_commitments (migration 0237); cutover/projects.ts (ToE)","Inspect the reserve→enforce path, the FOR UPDATE lock, the release-on-cancel/consume-on-receipt lifecycle, and the per-line remaining read model.","Re-perform: approve a BoQ line budget; a PO within budget reserves and lowers remaining; a further PO that would exceed the line → BUDGET_EXCEEDED (PO not created); cancel the first PO → budget released, remaining restored (re-performed by the harness).","BoQ line budget/committed/remaining; the project commitments ledger (open/consumed/released)","Implemented")
add("PROJ-13","Project Accounting","Application","Project material requisition (over-budget draw)","Site staff draw material that exceeds the project's authorized BoQ budget without an authorization gate — an over-budget requisition is fulfilled directly (staff self-approve the overage), or the draw silently bypasses the budget with no independent sign-off, so the project overruns before management is asked.","Authorization/Segregation of Duties",
    "Project Material Requisition (PMR) maker-checker over-budget gate: a requisition is evaluated line-by-line against each BoQ line's remaining budget (budget − open/consumed commitments). WITHIN budget it routes to a project-tagged PR for procurement; OVER budget it is parked `pending` and NOT fulfilled until an authoriser (procurement/exec, ≠ the requester → SOD_SELF_APPROVAL) approves — routed both through the workflow engine (when a PMR definition is configured) and a one-tap LINE approval card (buildApproveCard postback → the same replay-safe confirm flow). On approval the overage is AUTHORISED and a project-tagged Draft PO is auto-drafted (commitment booked with allowOver) for procurement to review + buy; on rejection nothing is drawn. The pending PMR is surfaced on the PMO action center (`pmr_over_budget`, high).","Prev","Automated","Per material requisition","Procurement / ProjectController","P13",
    "pmr.service.ts submit (per-line remaining check → route pr|po) / approve (SOD_SELF_APPROVAL, workflow act, auto-draft Draft PO authorized_over_budget) / reject; pmr.controller.ts POST /api/pmr [+ :pmrNo/approve|reject]; line-webhook.controller.ts chatDecidePmr (PMR- one-tap approval); commitments.service.ts reserve allowOver; procurement.service.ts createPo draft+authorized_over_budget; projects.service.ts actionCenter pmr_over_budget; schema/projects.ts project_material_requisitions+pmr_lines (migration 0239); cutover/projects.ts (ToE)","Inspect the within-vs-over routing, the maker-checker (approver ≠ requester), the LINE approval card, and the auto-drafted Draft PO carrying the authorised overage.","Re-perform: a within-budget PMR raises a project-tagged PR; an over-budget PMR parks pending (action center pmr_over_budget); requester self-approve → SOD_SELF_APPROVAL; an authoriser approves → a project-tagged Draft PO is drafted for the overage and the PMR clears (re-performed by the harness).","PMR register (routed/pending/approved/rejected); the over-budget approval + auto-drafted PO","Implemented")
add("PROJ-14","Project Accounting","Application","Project cost (site cash)","Site cash spent on a project — employee advances, expense-reimbursement claims, petty-cash — is not attributed to the project, so project cost is understated: an advance or reimbursement is booked to a generic expense with no project tag and never shows on the project, defeating cost control and the project margin.","Completeness/Accuracy",
    "Project-costed site cash: employee advances (finance.issueAdvance/settleAdvance), expense-reimbursement claims (ess.submitExpense) and petty-cash requests (petty-cash.createRequest/approveRequest) accept an optional project_code, resolve it to project_id (PROJECT_NOT_FOUND on a bad code), and store it on the entity; the GL expense/advance lines are tagged with that project_id (journal_lines.project_id) so the spend is traceable to the project. GET /api/projects/:code/site-cash rolls up all advances + reimbursements + petty-cash raised against the project with per-category + grand totals, so site cash is managed on the project (and reflected alongside EVM). When the site cash is tagged to a BoQ line it also CONSUMES that line's budget (a consumed commitment on advance settlement / petty-cash approval), so material + site cash sit under one budget ceiling. Advance settlement clears the float (Dr expense/Cr 1180) carrying the project dimension. Maker-checker on the underlying flows is unchanged (petty-cash SoD_VIOLATION, ESS self-approval block).","Prev","Automated","Per advance / reimbursement / petty-cash","Finance / ProjectController","P13",
    "finance.service.ts issueAdvance/settleAdvance (project_code → project_id, tag 1180/expense lines) + resolveProjectId; ess.service.ts submitExpense (project_id); petty-cash.service.ts createRequest/approveRequest (project_id on the debit line); projects.service.ts siteCash + projects.controller.ts GET :code/site-cash; schema employee_advances/expense_claims/expense_requests project_id (migration 0241); cutover/projects.ts (ToE)","Inspect the project_code resolution, the project_id tagging of the GL expense/advance lines, and the site-cash rollup.","Re-perform: issue a project-tagged advance (Dr 1180 carries project_id) → settle (expense line carries project_id); the project site-cash rollup lists the advance with the correct total; an unknown project_code → PROJECT_NOT_FOUND (re-performed by the harness).","Project site-cash rollup (advances/reimbursements/petty-cash + totals); project_id on the GL lines","Implemented")
add("PROJ-15","Project Accounting","Application","Project material scope change (add item to budget)","A requester expands a project's authorized material budget without independent authorization — an item that is not on the approved Bill-of-Quantities is added to the budget (a new BoQ line) by the same person who wants to buy it, so the project's authorized material budget grows with no maker-checker sign-off and the shop-for-a-project budget restriction is defeated from the inside.","Authorization/Segregation of Duties",
    "Material scope-change authorisation (maker-checker on adding a BoQ line): a requisition-raiser (pr_raise) can only REQUEST that a material item not on the approved BoQ be added to the budget — POST /api/pmr/boq-request parks a `pending` request and posts nothing; it never adds the line itself (an item already on the approved BoQ is refused, ITEM_ALREADY_BUDGETED; a project with no approved BoQ is refused, NO_APPROVED_BOQ). Only an independent authoriser (planner/exec, ≠ the requester → SOD_SELF_APPROVAL) may approve (POST …/boq-request/:reqNo/approve, routed through the workflow engine when configured); on approval a new material line is appended to the approved BoQ, the BoQ budget total is re-computed and the project budget synced (the item becomes shoppable and commitment-enforced under PROJ-12), and the requester is notified. Rejection changes nothing. This closes the shop-for-a-project loop: the /shop project surface lists only approved-budget items, and the only way to add one is through this authorised request → so a requester can propose budget but never expand it.","Prev","Automated","Per scope-change request","Planner / Exec / ProjectController","P13",
    "pmr.service.ts requestBoqItem (pending request; ITEM_ALREADY_BUDGETED / NO_APPROVED_BOQ guards) / approveBoqRequest (SOD_SELF_APPROVAL, workflow act, append BoQ line + re-total budget + sync project budget) / rejectBoqRequest / listBoqRequests; pmr.controller.ts POST /api/pmr/boq-request [+ :reqNo/approve|reject], GET /api/pmr/project/:code/boq-requests; schema/projects.ts project_boq_change_requests (migration 0249); web /shop/project/[code] request-to-add form + planner/exec approve; cutover/projects.ts (ToE)","Inspect the request-only requester path, the ITEM_ALREADY_BUDGETED/NO_APPROVED_BOQ guards, the maker-checker (approver ≠ requester), and the append-line-and-grow-budget on approval.","Re-perform: a requester requests an off-budget item → pending (nothing added); the same requester approves → SOD_SELF_APPROVAL; an independent authoriser approves → a new BoQ line appears, the project budget grows, and the item is now shoppable; requesting an already-budgeted item → ITEM_ALREADY_BUDGETED (re-performed by the harness).","Project BoQ change-request register (pending/approved/rejected); the appended BoQ line + grown budget","Implemented")
add("PROJ-16","Project Accounting","Application","Progress billing / retention (งวดงาน)","A construction progress claim bills work not actually done, or is raised and certified by the same person, or retention (เงินประกันผลงาน) is not withheld — so revenue/AR are overstated, the customer is over-billed beyond the contract, and the retained amount is not tracked as a separate receivable to be released later.","Accuracy/Authorization/Segregation of Duties",
    "Progress billing / งวดงาน maker-checker with retention (docs/35 P1): a progress claim values work done to date by BoQ line on a CUMULATIVE basis (value_to_date = boq_line.budget_amount × pct_complete_to_date/100, pct capped 0..100 → cannot certify beyond 100% of a line; value_this_claim = value_to_date − previously certified on prior CERTIFIED claims), so only the genuine movement since the last claim is billed and a line can never be over-certified. Certification is maker-checker — the certifier must differ from the preparer (SOD_SELF_APPROVAL; new SoD rule R17, perms proj_billing vs proj_billing_certify) — and a draft-only guard (CLAIM_NOT_DRAFT) prevents re-certifying. On certify the claim posts a single balanced JE carrying the project dimension: Dr 1100 AR (net) + Dr 1170 Retention Receivable (retention = gross × retention_pct) + Cr 4200 Revenue (gross), relieving unbilled WIP Dr 5800 / Cr 1260; the retention is withheld into the shared retention sub-ledger (RetentionService.withhold, party customer, doc CLAIM) atomically in the same transaction. A Fixed-price contract cannot be certified beyond its contract value (BILL_EXCEEDS_CONTRACT), and certification is idempotent per claim (alreadyPosted PRJ-PCLAIM). RELEASE (docs/35 Depth-1): when a retention tranche falls due it is released back out of the retention account to the ordinary control account with a balanced JE (customer 1170 → 1100 AR), guarded against over-release (RETENTION_OVER_RELEASE) under a FOR UPDATE row-lock and idempotent on the cumulative released amount; an overdue tranche surfaces on the PMO action center as retention_due for the controller to action. TAX + REV-REC (docs/35 Depth-2/3): the claim carries OUTPUT VAT (vat_pct → Cr 2100) so AR = net + VAT; and the certification reconciles with the POC engine — on a rev_method='poc' project the claim is a BILLING event only (Dr 1100/1170 · Cr 1265 contract-asset / Cr 2410 billings-in-excess · Cr 2100), recognising NO revenue (recognizePoc does that over time — no double-count), while a billing-method project recognises revenue (Cr 4200) and relieves WIP as before.","Prev","Automated","Per progress claim","ProjectController / Financial Controller (segregated)","P13",
    "progress-billing.service.ts createClaim (BoQ-line cumulative valuation, BAD_PERCENT/NOTHING_TO_BILL) / certifyClaim (SOD_SELF_APPROVAL, CLAIM_NOT_DRAFT, BILL_EXCEEDS_CONTRACT, JE 1100/1170/4200/5800/1260 + RetentionService.withhold in one tx, idempotent); progress-billing.controller.ts POST /api/progress-billing [+ :claimNo/certify], GET project/:code|:claimNo; schema/projects.ts project_progress_claims+progress_claim_lines (migration 0253); retention_ledger (migration 0252); permissions.ts proj_billing/proj_billing_certify + SoD R17; cutover/projects.ts (ToE)","Inspect the cumulative BoQ-line valuation (no over-certification), the maker-checker certify (certifier ≠ preparer), the AR-net/retention-receivable/revenue split + WIP relief JE, the retention withheld into the sub-ledger, and the Fixed-contract cap.","Re-perform: raise a claim valuing BoQ lines (gross = Σ value_this_claim); preparer self-certify → SOD_SELF_APPROVAL; an independent certifier certifies → JE posts Dr 1100 net + Dr 1170 retention + Cr 4200 gross (WIP relieved to 5800/1260), retention appears on the project retention sub-ledger, and a second claim's value_this_claim nets off the previously certified value; certifying beyond a Fixed contract → BILL_EXCEEDS_CONTRACT (re-performed by the projects harness).","Progress-claim register (draft/certified); the certification JE (1100/1170/4200/5800/1260); retention receivable in the sub-ledger","Implemented")
add("PROJ-17","Project Accounting","Application","Subcontractor valuation / retention payable","A subcontractor is over-paid — a progress valuation is raised and certified by the same person, work not done is certified, retention (เงินประกันผลงาน) is not withheld, or a subcontract commits more than the project's BoQ budget without an authorization gate — so project cost and AP are overstated and the retained amount is not tracked as a payable to release later.","Accuracy/Authorization/Segregation of Duties",
    "Subcontractor management maker-checker with retention payable + budget commitment (docs/35 P2): a subcontract is a priced scope against BoQ lines that on creation REGISTERS a commitment on each scoped BoQ line (docs/32 CommitmentsService, source SUBCON) so it counts against the works budget like a PO — over budget → BUDGET_EXCEEDED (the whole subcontract rolls back) unless explicitly authorised (allow_over). The subcontractor's periodic VALUATIONS certify the % complete on a CUMULATIVE basis (value_to_date = contract_value × pct/100, pct 0..100; gross_this_val = value_to_date − previously certified → only genuine progress; NOTHING_TO_CERTIFY otherwise; capped at the subcontract value → VAL_EXCEEDS_SUBCONTRACT). Certification is maker-checker — certifier ≠ preparer (SOD_SELF_APPROVAL; new SoD rule R18, perms proj_subcon vs proj_subcon_certify) — with a draft-only guard (VALUATION_NOT_DRAFT). On certify a single balanced JE (project-dimensioned) posts: Dr 1260 Project WIP (gross − back_charge) / Cr 2000 AP (net = gross − retention − back_charge) / Cr 2440 Retention Payable (retention); the retention is withheld into the shared retention sub-ledger (RetentionService.withhold, party subcontractor, doc SUBVAL) atomically in the same transaction; back-charges (BAD_BACK_CHARGE if they exceed the net) recover our cost; idempotent per valuation (alreadyPosted PRJ-SUBVAL). RELEASE (docs/35 Depth-1): when a retention tranche falls due it is released out of the retention account to the ordinary control account with a balanced JE (subcontractor 2440 → 2000 AP), over-release-guarded (RETENTION_OVER_RELEASE) and idempotent; an overdue tranche surfaces on the action center as retention_due. WHT (docs/35 Depth-2): the certified valuation withholds Thai construction WITHHOLDING TAX (ภ.ง.ด.53, wht_pct → Cr 2361 Vendor WHT Payable) from the subcontractor's payment, so AP = net − WHT (retention already out) and the WHT is remitted to the RD; a vat_pct also books recoverable INPUT VAT (ภาษีซื้อ, Dr 1300) so AP = net − WHT + VAT — the JE stays balanced (Dr [1260 gross−back + 1300 VAT] = Cr [AP + retention + WHT]).","Prev","Automated","Per subcontract / valuation","Procurement / Financial Controller (segregated)","P13",
    "subcontracts.service.ts createSubcontract (scope → commitment reserve SUBCON, BUDGET_EXCEEDED) / createValuation (cumulative pct valuation, NOTHING_TO_CERTIFY/BAD_BACK_CHARGE) / certifyValuation (SOD_SELF_APPROVAL, VALUATION_NOT_DRAFT, VAL_EXCEEDS_SUBCONTRACT, JE 1260/2000/2440 + RetentionService.withhold in one tx, idempotent); subcontracts.controller.ts POST /api/subcontracts [+ :subNo/valuations, valuations/:valNo/certify], GET project/:code|:subNo|valuations/:valNo; schema/projects.ts project_subcontracts+subcontract_scope+subcontract_valuations (migration 0254); retention_ledger (migration 0252); permissions.ts proj_subcon/proj_subcon_certify + SoD R18; cutover/projects.ts (ToE)","Inspect the BoQ-budget commitment on subcontract creation, the cumulative valuation (no over-certification), the maker-checker certify (certifier ≠ preparer), the AP-net/retention-payable/WIP JE, the retention withheld into the sub-ledger, and the back-charge handling.","Re-perform: issue a subcontract against BoQ scope (commitment reserved on the line; over budget → BUDGET_EXCEEDED); raise a valuation (gross = value_to_date − previously certified); preparer self-certify → SOD_SELF_APPROVAL; an independent certifier certifies → JE posts Dr 1260 (gross−back) / Cr 2000 net / Cr 2440 retention, the retention payable appears on the project retention sub-ledger, a 2nd valuation nets off the prior, and certifying beyond the subcontract → VAL_EXCEEDS_SUBCONTRACT (re-performed by the projects harness).","Subcontract register + valuation JEs (1260/2000/2440); retention payable in the sub-ledger; BoQ commitment","Implemented")
add("PROJ-18","Project Accounting","Application","Tender award → project & budget baseline","A project is spun up from a lost/unsubmitted tender, or an awarded project's budget baseline is set arbitrarily rather than from the priced winning bid, or a single won tender is awarded twice — so the project starts with an uncontrolled or duplicated cost baseline that later EVM/commitment controls are measured against.","Authorization/Accuracy",
    "Tender → award governance (docs/35 P3): a tender is a pre-award ESTIMATE (a draft BoQ with a cost build-up — bid_rate = unit_cost × (1 + markup%); bid_price = Σ) tracked through a controlled status machine estimating → submitted → won/lost (a lost tender REQUIRES a reason → LOSS_REASON_REQUIRED; a decided tender can't be re-decided → TENDER_DECIDED). AWARD is an AUTHORISED act (proj_tender/exec) allowed ONLY on a WON tender (TENDER_NOT_WON) and IDEMPOTENT — one project per tender (a re-award returns the existing project, never a duplicate). On award the winning bid seeds a project (Fixed-price, contract = bid_price) and a BoQ from the tender lines (bid_rate → BoQ rate) — created as DRAFT so the existing BoQ maker-checker approve (PROJ-12: author ≠ approver, syncs the project budget) sets the controlled budget baseline. Nothing hits GL (estimating is a modelling surface); the seeded BoQ's approval is the segregation point.","Prev","Automated","Per tender award","Estimator / Project Controller (segregated on the BoQ approve)","P13",
    "tenders.service.ts createTender/addLine (cost build-up) / submit (EMPTY_TENDER) / setOutcome (won/lost, LOSS_REASON_REQUIRED, TENDER_DECIDED) / award (TENDER_NOT_WON, idempotent, ProjectsService.create + createBoq draft); tenders.controller.ts POST /api/tenders [+ :no/lines|submit|outcome|award], GET /api/tenders[/:no]; schema/projects.ts project_tenders+tender_boq_lines (migration 0255); permissions.ts proj_tender; cutover/projects.ts (ToE)","Inspect the estimate cost build-up (bid_rate/bid_price), the status machine (won/lost terminal, lost-reason required), the won-only + idempotent award, and the seeded DRAFT BoQ whose maker-checker approve sets the budget baseline.","Re-perform: build a tender (2 lines, 20% markup → bid_price 24000); submit; award before won → TENDER_NOT_WON; mark won; award → a Fixed project (contract 24000) + a DRAFT BoQ (rate = bid_rate); an independent approver approves the BoQ → project budget 24000; re-award → already (no duplicate) (re-performed by the projects harness).","Tender register + win-rate; the awarded project + its draft-then-approved BoQ baseline","Implemented")
add("PROJ-19","Project Accounting","Detective","Project schedule performance (earned schedule)","A late project reads on-schedule: the classic SPI (EV/PV) mathematically converges to 1 once planned value saturates at BAC — every task past its planned finish counts fully in PV — so a project months behind still shows SPI ≈ 1, the PROJ-11 red check (SPI < 0.9) never fires, and the schedule slip stays invisible to the PMO until delivery fails.","Completeness/Timeliness",
    "Earned-schedule monitoring (Lipke ES / SV(t) / SPI(t)): GET /api/projects/:code/earned-schedule projects today's EV onto the PLANNED-value curve (the evmSeries month buckets) to find ES — the date the plan said the project would be where it actually is (the last month with cumulative PV ≤ EV, interpolated within the crossing month; a flat plateau at exactly EV is credited as earned, so a stretch with nothing planned never raises a false alarm). SPI(t) = ES / AT (months actually elapsed since the first planned month) and SV(t) = ES − AT stay honest schedule signals to completion where the classic SPI cannot, and forecast the finish (IEAC(t) = planned duration / SPI(t) → forecast finish month). A project with no costed dated plan returns an explicit NO_DATED_PLAN (no phantom metric); a plan that hasn't started returns PLAN_NOT_STARTED. DETECTIVE HOOK: the PMO action center (PROJ-11) surfaces `schedule_slip_es` (medium) whenever SPI(t) < 0.9 while the project does NOT already read red (CPI/SPI < 0.9) — exactly the slip the PV-based signal hides — deep-linked to the project overview where the earned-schedule card shows ES/AT/SV(t)/forecast finish beside the classic EVM. Read-only; posts nothing; no new tables.","Det","Automated","Continuous / per review","PMO / ProjectController","P13",
    "projects-evm.service.ts earnedSchedule (Lipke ES over the evmSeries month buckets + AT + SPI(t)/SV(t)/IEAC(t); NO_DATED_PLAN / PLAN_NOT_STARTED); projects.controller.ts GET :code/earned-schedule; projects.service.ts actionCenter schedule_slip_es (suppressed when already red); web projects/[code] earned-schedule card; cutover/projects.ts (ToE)","Inspect the ES interpolation (last cumulative-PV ≤ EV month + within-month fraction, plateau credited), the AT month arithmetic, the SPI(t)/SV(t)/forecast derivation, and the action-center gate (fires only when the project is not already red).","Re-perform: a 2-month plan 95% earned read at month 6 → classic SPI 0.95 (reads fine) but ES 1.9 / AT 6.0 → SPI(t) 0.3167 RED, SV(t) −4.1 mo, forecast ~6.3 mo; the action center surfaces schedule_slip_es (medium) for it and suppresses the item on an already-red project; an EV sitting on a flat PV plateau reads ahead (no false alarm); a project without a costed dated plan → NO_DATED_PLAN (re-performed by the projects harness).","Earned-schedule endpoint payload (ES/AT/SV(t)/SPI(t)/forecast finish); the schedule_slip_es action-center item","Implemented")

add("PROJ-20","Project Accounting","Detective","Resource capacity (skills/role supply-vs-demand)","A resource heatmap assumes every booked person is at 100% capacity and every named assignment is a real, qualified person — so a part-time or on-leave resource reads as merely 'busy' at 60% instead of critically over-committed, a generic placeholder booking ('Senior Dev TBD') is silently treated as staffed, and a role or skill with more assigned demand than qualified people to do the work goes unnoticed until the project slips.","Completeness/Accuracy/Timeliness",
    "Resource capacity heatmap governed by a REAL per-resource availability calendar + named-vs-generic booking visibility + role/skill supply-vs-demand (PPM-A1): GET /api/projects/resources/capacity's over-allocation flag now compares each month's demand to the resource's TRUE availability ceiling (resource_calendar.available_pct, default 100% absent an override — e.g. a documented 50%-part-time person is flagged over-allocated at 60%, not only above a flat 100% assumption) instead of a hardcoded 100%, and marks each resource `named` (backed by a resource_skills row) vs a GENERIC placeholder booking. GET /api/projects/resources/role-demand rolls assignment demand (Σ alloc_pct tagged with a role) up against role/skill SUPPLY (Σ availability of every resource_skills-tagged person who can fill it, calendar-aware) per month, flagging a role `understaffed` whenever demand exceeds the qualified supply — surfaced before it becomes a schedule slip. Read-only detective layer; posts nothing; existing resourceUtilization/portfolio()/forecast() callers are unaffected (additive fields only, same over-100%-only behaviour when no calendar/skills data exists).",
    "Det","Automated","Continuous / per review","PMO / Resource Manager","P13",
    "projects-resourcing.service.ts resourceCapacity (calendar-aware over_allocated + named flag) / roleSupplyDemand (per-role/month demand vs supply, understaffed_months) / upsertResourceSkill+listResourceSkills / upsertResourceCalendar+listResourceCalendar; projects.controller.ts GET/POST resources/skills, resources/calendar, GET resources/role-demand; schema/projects.ts resource_skills + resource_calendar (migration 0400, 0232 RLS, tenant-leading indexes); web projects/resources heatmap + skills + calendar + role-demand tabs; cutover/projects.ts (ToE)",
    "Inspect the calendar-ceiling substitution in resourceCapacity (default 100% absent an override, else the calendar's available_pct), the named-resource lookup (resource_skills membership), and the role/skill supply-vs-demand roll-up (demand from project_resources.role, supply from resource_skills × resource_calendar).",
    "Re-perform: a resource on a documented 50%-part-time calendar entry assigned 60% reads over_allocated (60 > 50) though under the old flat 100% ceiling it would not; an assignment with no matching resource_skills row reads named=false; a role with 150% assigned demand and only one named 100%-available person reads understaffed for that month; a second tenant cannot see the first tenant's skills/calendar rows (RLS) (re-performed by the projects harness).",
    "Time-phased capacity heatmap with calendar-aware over-allocation + named flag; role/skill supply-vs-demand roll-up with understaffed flag","Implemented")

add("PROJ-21","Project Accounting","Detective","Project schedule (dependency logic / constraints)","The critical-path schedule assumes every dependency is a rigid finish-to-start with zero lag, every task can start the instant its predecessor finishes, and duration is raw calendar days — so a genuinely overlapping or offset relationship (start-to-start, finish-to-finish, a deliberate lead/lag), a hard start-no-earlier-than or finish-no-later-than commitment, and weekends/holidays inflating a dated task's duration all go unmodelled, producing a critical path and project finish date that does not match how the work is actually planned to run.","Completeness/Accuracy",
    "Richer CPM scheduling (PPM-B1), additive to the existing FS/lag-0 engine — a predecessor/successor pair with no edge-metadata row still schedules exactly as before (zero regression): project_task_dependencies carries an optional per-edge dep_type (SS/FF/SF, default FS) and lag_days (negative = lead), applied via the standard CPM-with-lag forward-pass (ES ≥ predecessor bound + lag, form depends on type) and backward-pass (LF ≤ successor bound − lag) formulas. project_tasks.constraint_type/constraint_offset_days adds an optional SNET (start no earlier than) floor on the forward pass or FNLT (finish no later than) cap on the backward pass, in the same day-offset units as es/ef/ls/lf. A per-tenant project_calendars row (DISABLED by default) plus project_calendar_exceptions makes a dated task's duration count only WORKING days (skipping configured non-working weekdays + holidays) instead of raw calendar days, once explicitly enabled — so a tenant that never opts in sees byte-identical duration/schedule output to before PPM-B1.","Prev","Automated","Per schedule computation","PMO / Project Planner","P13",
    "projects-evm.service.ts schedule() (per-edge dep_type/lag lookup via project_task_dependencies, defaulting FS/0; SNET/FNLT constraint floor/cap; calendar-aware dur() via workingDaysBetween when project_calendars.enabled; dependency_details + working_calendar_enabled on the response) / getCalendar+setCalendar+addCalendarException+listCalendarExceptions; projects-wbs.service.ts addTask/patchTask (syncDependencies — a richer `dependencies` list replaces the task's edge rows; a plain depends_on clears them back to FS/lag-0 defaults; BAD_DEPENDENCY self-dependency guard); projects.controller.ts task dependencies/constraint fields, GET/PUT /api/projects/calendar, POST/GET /api/projects/calendar/exceptions; schema/projects.ts project_task_dependencies + project_calendars + project_calendar_exceptions + project_tasks.constraint_type/constraint_offset_days (migration 0401, 0232 RLS, tenant-leading indexes); cutover/projects.ts (ToE)",
    "Inspect the CPM-with-lag forward/backward formulas per dependency type, the SNET/FNLT floor/cap application, the calendar-aware working-day duration substitution (and that it is a no-op when disabled), and that an edge/task with no override defaults to the pre-PPM-B1 FS/lag-0/calendar-day behaviour.",
    "Re-perform: an SS+lag2 edge starts the successor 2 days after the predecessor STARTS (not finishes); an FF+lag-1 edge finishes the successor 1 day before the predecessor finishes; a negative lag (lead) starts a task before its predecessor's late finish; a critical-path/off-path/slack split proves the CPM-with-lag math end to end; an SNET floor forces a task's early start later than its natural (predecessor-driven) start; an FNLT cap on one task shows a materially lower late-finish than an otherwise-identical unconstrained sibling task; a 14-calendar-day dated task reads 14 days duration with the calendar disabled and 10 (skipping the 2 Saturdays + 2 Sundays every 14-day span contains) once enabled; a self-dependency via the richer list → 403/400 BAD_DEPENDENCY (re-performed by the projects harness).",
    "CPM schedule payload with per-edge dependency_details (type/lag) + SNET/FNLT-aware es/ef/ls/lf/slack; the working_calendar_enabled flag + calendar-aware duration; the tenant calendar + holiday-exception register","Implemented")

add("PROJ-22","Project Accounting","Detective","Bottom-up cost-to-complete (ETC) vs formulaic EAC","The evm() estimate-at-completion (EAC) is a PURELY FORMULAIC extrapolation (ac + (bac-ev)/cpi) that assumes the historical cost-performance ratio holds for all remaining work — a project manager's ground-level knowledge that the remaining scope will cost materially more or less than the formula implies (a known risk, a renegotiated rate, remaining work that is genuinely different in nature) has no channel into the reported EAC, so a stale or misleading completion forecast can go unchallenged.","Completeness/Accuracy",
    "Bottom-up cost-to-complete entry (PPM-B2), additive to the existing formulaic evm() EAC — a project with no manual entries computes exactly as before (zero regression). project_etc is an append-only log of a manual estimate-to-complete, entered per task (or a single project-level entry when task_id is omitted); the CURRENT bottom-up figure for a given task/project-level bucket is simply its latest row, summed across every bucket that has one. GET /api/projects/:code/eac-scenarios reports the formulaic EAC and the bottom-up EAC (ac + Σ latest ETC) side by side plus the variance between them, so a material divergence is visible for review rather than silently trusted.","Prev","Automated","Per management estimate submission","PMO / Project Manager","P13",
    "projects-evm.service.ts submitEtc (task-existence guard, TASK_NOT_FOUND) / eacScenarios (latest-per-bucket aggregation, formulaic-vs-bottom-up + variance); projects.controller.ts POST/GET /api/projects/:code/etc, /:code/eac-scenarios; schema/projects.ts project_etc (migration 0402, 0232 RLS, tenant-leading indexes); cutover/projects.ts (ToE)",
    "Inspect the latest-per-bucket aggregation (a superseded entry for the same task/project-level bucket is excluded, only its latest row counts), the formulaic-vs-bottom-up variance computation, and that a project with zero project_etc rows reports bottom_up=null (the formulaic EAC is unaffected).",
    "Re-perform: with no manual entries, eac-scenarios reports the formulaic EAC only (bottom_up null); a second, updated ETC entry for the same task supersedes the first in the aggregation (only the latest counts); entries across multiple tasks plus a project-level entry sum into one bottom-up EAC with a variance against the formulaic figure; an ETC submitted against a task_id not on the project → 400/404 TASK_NOT_FOUND, nothing written (re-performed by the projects harness).",
    "eac-scenarios payload with the formulaic EAC, the bottom-up EAC (entry_count + contributing entries), and the variance between them","Implemented")

add("PROJ-23","Project Accounting","Detective","Resource leveling (over-allocation vs slack)","A resource can be booked over 100% (or over its real availability calendar ceiling) across two or more task assignments in the same month — the capacity heatmap flags the over-allocation, but nothing in the system tells a scheduler WHICH assignment could be moved, or by how much, to resolve it without delaying the project, so resolution is manual trial-and-error against the Gantt.","Completeness/Accuracy",
    "Resource leveling (PPM-A2), read-only/detective and additive — it suggests, it never moves an assignment. GET /api/projects/:code/resource-leveling detects an over-allocated resource-month WITHIN this project's own task-linked assignments (the same calendar-aware ceiling as the tenant-wide resourceCapacity heatmap, PROJ-20), then cross-references the CPM schedule's per-task SLACK (schedule(), PROJ-06/21) to find the contributing task with the MOST slack and suggest shifting it later by up to that slack (in days) — freeing the over-allocated month without delaying the critical path. An over-allocated resource-month where every contributing task is already on the critical path (slack 0) is flagged NO_SLACK: genuinely unresolvable without accepting a project delay, surfaced rather than silently ignored. A project with no over-allocated resource reports empty over_allocations/suggestions/unresolvable — zero regression to the existing capacity/schedule engines.","Prev","Automated","Per schedule/resourcing review","PMO / Project Planner","P13",
    "projects.service.ts resourceLeveling (composes evmSvc.schedule() slack with project_resources capacity, calendar-aware ceiling); projects.controller.ts GET /api/projects/:code/resource-leveling; no new schema (pure computation over project_resources + project_tasks + resource_calendar); cutover/projects.ts (ToE)",
    "Inspect the over-allocation detection (same calendar-aware ceiling as resourceCapacity), the slack-based candidate selection (only positive-slack contributors, largest slack first), and the NO_SLACK fallback when every contributor is on the critical path.",
    "Re-perform: two assignments to the same resource in the same month totalling over 100% with one task on the critical path (slack 0) and one off-path (positive slack) → the off-path task is suggested with suggested_shift_days equal to its slack; a resource-month over-allocated by two CRITICAL-path assignments (both slack 0) → NO_SLACK, no suggestion offered (re-performed by the projects harness).",
    "resource-leveling payload with over_allocations, slack-based suggestions (task/shift-days/target month), and unresolvable (NO_SLACK) resource-months","Implemented")
add("PROJ-24","Project Accounting","Detective","Change-order impact simulation (approve blind)","A pending change order carries only its raw money deltas (contract +/−, budget +/−, estimated-cost +/−); the approver sees the three signed numbers but NOT their compounded effect on the project's gross margin, margin %, budget headroom, and the formulaic estimate-at-completion (EAC vs the re-baselined BAC), so a change order that quietly turns the project margin-negative or pushes the EAC past the new budget can be authorised without that consequence ever being surfaced.","Completeness/Accuracy",
    "Change-order impact simulation (PPM-A3), read-only/detective and additive — it projects, it never mutates. GET /api/projects/change-orders/:coId/simulate takes a PENDING change order (CHANGE_ORDER_NOT_FOUND / CHANGE_ORDER_DECIDED if already approved/rejected) and computes, WITHOUT writing anything, the project's current vs projected contract/budget/estimated-cost, gross margin + margin %, formulaic EAC and budget headroom — applying the CO's signed deltas on top of the live figures and re-running evm() for the EV/AC/CPI basis (bac_basis 'tasks' when the WBS carries planned costs, else 'budget'). The approver reads the compounded margin and headroom swing (favourable/unfavourable per metric) BEFORE authorising; the simulation exactly matches what approveChangeOrder() then persists (re-performed proof), and a read-only impersonation of the endpoint mutates nothing. A CO with all-zero deltas projects an identical position (zero regression to the existing change-order and EVM engines).","Prev","Automated","Per change order","PMO / Project Controller","P13",
    "projects-evm.service.ts simulateChangeOrder (applies contract/budget/estimatedCost deltas, recomputes margin/EAC/headroom off evm() + task-anchored BAC, no writes); projects.service.ts delegator; projects.controller.ts GET /api/projects/change-orders/:coId/simulate (exec/planner/ar gate); no new schema (pure computation over project_change_orders + projects + project_tasks); cutover/projects.ts (ToE)",
    "Inspect the read-only projection (signed-delta application over the live contract/budget/estimated-cost), the margin/EAC/headroom recomputation off evm() and the task-vs-budget BAC basis selection, and the pending-only guard.",
    "Re-perform: a pending CO (contract +50,000 / budget +30,000 / est-cost +45,000) on a project (contract 200,000, est-cost 140,000) simulates projected margin 65,000 (Δ +5,000), bac_basis 'budget', projected EAC 180,000; the endpoint writes nothing (read-only proof); approving the CO reproduces the simulated figures exactly; an already-decided CO → CHANGE_ORDER_DECIDED (re-performed by the projects harness).",
    "Change-order simulation payload (current/projected/delta for contract/budget/est-cost/margin/EAC/headroom, bac_basis)","Implemented")
add("PROJ-25","Project Accounting","Authorization","Portfolio funding committed without authority / over the envelope","A portfolio manager decides which candidate projects to FUND within a constrained budget, but there is no governed record of that selection: a single planner can unilaterally 'commit' a slate of projects — including one whose combined budget exceeds the approved funding envelope — with no independent authorisation and no trail of what was selected, so portfolio capital can be committed beyond the ceiling, or by one person acting alone, without detection.","Authorization/Segregation of Duties",
    "Portfolio selection-scenario commit governance (PPM Wave P4, PROJ-25). A selection scenario (portfolio_scenarios + portfolio_scenario_items, migration 0410) models candidate projects with an include/exclude decision + priority and a budget ENVELOPE; analyze() is a read-only what-if that rolls up the INCLUDED set's contract/budget/margin vs the envelope. A scenario is DRAFT (freely editable) until COMMITTED, and committing is a MAKER-CHECKER decision: the committer must differ from the scenario's author (SOD_SELF_APPROVAL on self-commit) AND the included budget must fit the envelope — an over-envelope commit is rejected (OVER_ENVELOPE) unless an EXEC explicitly overrides with a recorded reason (OVERRIDE_REQUIRES_EXEC for a non-exec). On commit the GO-set is locked (further edits → SCENARIO_LOCKED; re-commit → SCENARIO_NOT_DRAFT) with committed_by/committed_at/override_reason preserved as the authorisation trail. Read-only aggregation over the projects spine — no project row is mutated. So portfolio capital cannot be committed by one person alone, nor silently beyond the ceiling.","Prev","Automated","Per portfolio commit","PMO / Portfolio Exec (segregated)","P13",
    "projects-portfolio.service.ts createScenario/upsertItem/removeItem/analyze/commitScenario (SOD_SELF_APPROVAL + OVER_ENVELOPE/OVERRIDE_REQUIRES_EXEC guards, draft-lock); projects.service.ts delegators; projects.controller.ts /api/projects/portfolio/scenarios* (exec/planner/ar gate); schema/projects.ts portfolio_scenarios + portfolio_scenario_items (migration 0410, canonical RLS); web /projects/portfolio selection-scenarios surface; cutover/projects.ts (ToE)",
    "Inspect the maker-checker commit (committer <> created_by), the over-envelope block + exec-only override with a recorded reason, the draft→committed lock, and the read-only nature of the analysis (no project row mutated).",
    "Re-perform: build a scenario (envelope 100,000) including two projects whose budgets total 110,000 → analyze reports over_envelope with over_by 10,000; the author self-commits → SOD_SELF_APPROVAL; a different user commits without an override → OVER_ENVELOPE; the different user commits with an exec override + reason → committed (committed_by recorded, GO-set locked); a within-envelope scenario commits with no override; a committed scenario rejects edits (SCENARIO_LOCKED) and re-commit (SCENARIO_NOT_DRAFT) — all re-performed by the projects harness.",
    "Portfolio scenario register (draft/committed, envelope, committer, override reason); the committed selection payload (included/excluded, selected budget vs envelope)","Implemented")
add("PROJ-26","Project Accounting","Authorization","Project advances a lifecycle phase without an independent stage-gate decision","A project rolls from one lifecycle phase to the next — or keeps consuming capital in a phase it should have exited or been stopped in — with no documented, independent authorisation: whoever runs the project decides on their own when it moves to planning/execution/closeout, so there is no segregated GO/HOLD/KILL control over project continuation and no auditable record that a phase transition was reviewed and approved.","Authorization/Segregation of Duties",
    "Project phase-gate governance (PPM Wave P4, PROJ-26). A project advances along an ordered lifecycle (concept -> planning -> execution -> closeout -> closed, project_phase_gates, migration 0411) only through a GATE that is SUBMITTED for review (pending) to a target phase — forward-only along the ladder (BAD_PHASE_ORDER on a non-advancing target; BAD_PHASE on an unknown one) with at most one gate pending at a time (GATE_ALREADY_PENDING) — then INDEPENDENTLY decided: an approver records GO / HOLD / KILL and MUST differ from the submitter (SOD_SELF_APPROVAL on self-decide; GATE_ALREADY_DECIDED on a re-decision). A GO advances the project to the gate's target phase (the current phase = the target of the latest GO gate); a HOLD or KILL records the outcome without advancing. Every gate preserves submitted_by / decided_by / decided_at / decision_notes as the authorisation trail. So a project cannot change lifecycle phase on one person's say-so, and every transition carries a segregated, documented review.","Prev","Automated","Per phase gate","PMO / Project Sponsor (segregated)","P13",
    "projects-gate.service.ts submitGate (forward-only ladder, single-pending) / decideGate (GO/HOLD/KILL, SOD_SELF_APPROVAL, GATE_ALREADY_DECIDED) / listGates (current-phase derivation); projects.service.ts delegators; projects.controller.ts /api/projects/:code/gates + /api/projects/gates/:gateId/decide (exec/planner/ar gate); schema/projects.ts project_phase_gates (migration 0411, canonical RLS); web /projects/:code phase-gate panel; cutover/projects.ts (ToE)",
    "Inspect the forward-only submit (BAD_PHASE / BAD_PHASE_ORDER / GATE_ALREADY_PENDING), the maker-checker decide (decider <> submitter, GO advances / HOLD-KILL record), the current-phase derivation from the latest GO gate, and the preserved submitter/decider trail.",
    "Re-perform: a fresh project starts at concept; submit a gate to planning (pending); a second submit → GATE_ALREADY_PENDING; the submitter self-decides → SOD_SELF_APPROVAL; a different user records GO → project advances to planning; re-deciding the gate → GATE_ALREADY_DECIDED; a gate that does not advance past the current phase → BAD_PHASE_ORDER; a HOLD on the next gate records the decision without advancing; an unknown phase → BAD_PHASE and an unknown gate → GATE_NOT_FOUND — all re-performed by the projects harness.",
    "Phase-gate register (per project: gate_key, from/target phase, status, submitter, decider, decision notes); the derived current lifecycle phase","Implemented")
add("PROJ-27","Project Accounting","Detective","Program benefits leakage / self-certified realization","A program is funded on a promise of BENEFITS (a cost saving, a revenue uplift, a service improvement), but once delivery starts nobody tracks whether those benefits actually materialise: the program is declared 'done' when its projects finish, with no measurement of realised vs promised value and no independent confirmation — so a program can consume its budget and be closed while delivering little of what justified the investment, and the person who owns the benefit can simply assert it was achieved.","Completeness/Accuracy",
    "Program benefits-realization tracking (PPM Wave P4, PROJ-27). A program (identified by projects.program_code) declares expected BENEFITS (program_benefits + program_benefit_measurements, migration 0412) with a baseline, a target value and target date, an owner and a financial/non-financial category; a benefit under an unknown program is rejected (PROGRAM_NOT_FOUND). Actual measurements are logged over time as an APPEND-ONLY series (the current actual = the latest measurement) — a closed benefit rejects further measurements (BENEFIT_CLOSED). The realization view computes each benefit's realised % (actual vs target over baseline) and a health band (met / on_track / at_risk, with an overdue-shortfall flag once past the target date under 100%), plus a program roll-up (financial target vs actual, realised / not-realised / at-risk counts, average realisation). CLOSING a benefit as realized / not_realized is a MAKER-CHECKER sign-off: the confirmer MUST differ from the benefit's author (SOD_SELF_APPROVAL on self-confirm; BENEFIT_ALREADY_CONFIRMED on a re-confirmation), preserving confirmed_by/confirmed_at. So benefits leakage is surfaced (realised vs promised is measured and shortfalls flagged) and realisation cannot be self-certified by the benefit owner.","Detect","Automated","Per benefit review / program close","PMO / Program Sponsor (segregated sign-off)","P13",
    "program-benefits.service.ts declareBenefit (PROGRAM_NOT_FOUND) / recordMeasurement (append-only, BENEFIT_CLOSED) / listBenefits (realization % + health + roll-up) / confirmBenefit (maker-checker, SOD_SELF_APPROVAL, BENEFIT_ALREADY_CONFIRMED); projects.service.ts delegators; projects.controller.ts /api/projects/programs/:programCode/benefits + /api/projects/benefits/:benefitId/measurements|confirm (exec/planner/ar gate); schema/projects.ts program_benefits + program_benefit_measurements (migration 0412, canonical RLS); web /projects/program/:code benefits panel; cutover/projects.ts (ToE)",
    "Inspect the append-only measurement series (latest = current actual), the realisation % + health/overdue derivation, the program roll-up, and the maker-checker benefit sign-off (confirmer <> author, closed-benefit guards).",
    "Re-perform: declare a financial benefit (target 1,000,000) under a real program (an unknown program → PROGRAM_NOT_FOUND); record 600,000 → 60% on_track; record 300,000 → the latest is current (30%, at_risk) with the measurement count reflecting both; the author self-confirms → SOD_SELF_APPROVAL; a different user confirms not_realized → status + confirmed_by recorded; a closed benefit rejects a new measurement (BENEFIT_CLOSED) and re-confirmation (BENEFIT_ALREADY_CONFIRMED) — all re-performed by the projects harness.",
    "Program benefits register (baseline/target/target-date/owner, realised % + health, confirmer); the append-only measurement series; the program benefits roll-up","Implemented")

add("PROJ-28","Project Accounting","Application","Free-issue material custody (subcontractor)","Company-owned material FREE-ISSUED to a subcontractor for use in their contracted scope leaves the warehouse (its cost capitalised into project WIP at issue) but nobody tracks it in the subcontractor's CUSTODY: unused, diverted or over-drawn material is invisible, and the subcontract can be certified out to its full value and paid while company material remains unaccounted in the subcontractor's hands — shrinkage the works valuation never surfaces.","Existence/Completeness/Accuracy",
    "Free-issue custody register + final-certification clearance gate (docs/50 Track A parked item, unblocked by A1's return mechanics; migration 0427). A stock reservation may be stamped with the subcontract it is free-issued FOR (POST /api/reservations subcontract_no — fail-closed: SUBCONTRACT_NOT_FOUND / SUBCONTRACT_PROJECT_MISMATCH / SUBCONTRACT_NOT_ACTIVE); the issue rides the existing INV-13 path (Dr 1260 project WIP / Cr 1200) and the material is then tracked IN CUSTODY until it either (a) returns to stock through the governed INV-19 MRET path (qty-capped, reason-mandatory, maker-checker at threshold), or (b) its consumption in the works is acknowledged (POST /api/reservations/:id/custody-ack — capped so acknowledged + posted returns can never exceed the issue, OVER_ACK; who/when stamped). GET /api/reservations/custody?subcontract_no= is the per-subcontract statement (issued / returned / acknowledged / in-custody per reservation + totals). The teeth: certifying the FINAL valuation (the one reaching the subcontract's full contract value, PROJ-17 flow) is BLOCKED while any free-issue reservation still holds unaccounted material (FREE_ISSUE_CUSTODY_OPEN listing the open reservations) — so the subcontractor cannot be fully paid out while company material in their custody is unexplained. Interim valuations are unaffected. GL untouched by ack (the cost already sits in WIP from the issue).","Prev","Automated","Per free-issue + at final certification","Project Manager / QS","P10",
    "reservations.service.ts (reserve subcontract stamping, custodyStatement, ackCustody OVER_ACK); reservations.controller.ts (GET custody, POST :id/custody-ack); subcontracts.service.ts certifyValuation FREE_ISSUE_CUSTODY_OPEN gate (plain filtered custody read — no module cycle); schema stock_reservations.subcontract_id/custody_ack_* + migration 0427; cutover/projects.ts (ToE)","Inspect the fail-closed subcontract stamping, the custody statement arithmetic (issued − Posted returns − acknowledged), the OVER_ACK cap, and the final-certification gate.","Re-perform (projects ToE): free-issue against a subcontract (wrong project → SUBCONTRACT_PROJECT_MISMATCH; unknown → SUBCONTRACT_NOT_FOUND); custody shows issued; a Posted MRET return and an acknowledgment both reduce it; over-ack → OVER_ACK; the FINAL valuation with open custody → FREE_ISSUE_CUSTODY_OPEN, clears after the residual is acknowledged and then certifies; an interim valuation is never gated.","Custody statements (issued/returned/acked/in-custody); FREE_ISSUE_CUSTODY_OPEN rejections; custody_ack who/when stamps","Implemented")

# ---- Real Estate (Developer) — property unit sales (docs/35 Track D / P4) ----
add("RE-01","Real Estate","Application","Unit inventory (double-allocation)","A property developer sells the SAME unit twice — a unit already reserved/contracted is booked or contracted again to another buyer, so two buyers hold a claim on one unit and the availability grid overstates inventory.","Completeness/Accuracy",
    "Unit inventory integrity (docs/35 P4): each re_unit carries a status (available → reserved → contracted → transferred). A BOOKING is admitted only when the unit is AVAILABLE (UNIT_NOT_AVAILABLE otherwise) and flips it to reserved; a CONTRACT is admitted only when the unit is available or reserved (UNIT_NOT_CONTRACTABLE otherwise — a contracted/transferred unit can't be re-sold), re-checked at approval time, and flips it to contracted. The development availability grid (GET /developments/:code/units) reports the live available/reserved/contracted/transferred counts, so inventory is never double-allocated and the grid ties to the unit states. Permission-gated (re_sales) so a non-property tenant never sees the vertical.","Prev","Automated","Per booking / contract","Sales / Developer Ops","P13",
    "realestate.service.ts book (UNIT_NOT_AVAILABLE → reserved) / createContract + approveContract (UNIT_NOT_CONTRACTABLE, re-checked on approve → contracted) / listUnits (availability grid); realestate.controller.ts /api/realestate/*; schema/realestate.ts re_projects/re_units/re_bookings (migration 0256); permissions.ts re_sales; cutover/projects.ts (ToE)","Inspect the unit status machine (available→reserved→contracted), the booking/contract admission guards, and the availability grid tie-out.","Re-perform: book an available unit → reserved; re-book it → UNIT_NOT_AVAILABLE; contract it → contracted; contract it again → UNIT_NOT_CONTRACTABLE; the availability summary reflects the counts (re-performed by the projects harness).","Unit availability grid; booking/contract admission log","Implemented")
add("RE-02","Real Estate","Application","Sale contract (price/discount authority)","A unit is sold at an unauthorised price — a large discount is granted and the contract self-approved by the salesperson (e.g. to a related buyer), with no independent authorisation of the price/discount before the sale is booked and cash is taken.","Authorization/Segregation of Duties",
    "Sale-contract maker-checker (docs/35 P4): a contract is DRAFTED with price = list_price − discount (discount bounded 0..list → BAD_DISCOUNT; down_payment bounded 0..price and ≥ any booking deposit → BAD_DOWN_PAYMENT) and posts NOTHING until approved. An INDEPENDENT approver (re_contract_approve, ≠ the drafter → SOD_SELF_APPROVAL; new SoD rule R19) approves it (draft-only → CONTRACT_NOT_DRAFT), which flips the unit to contracted, converts the booking, posts the down-payment to the contract liability (Dr 1000 cash + Dr 2210 reclass booking deposit / Cr 2410 contract liability) and generates the installment schedule. So the price/discount authority is segregated from the salesperson and every sale carries an independent authorisation before cash is recognised.","Prev","Automated","Per sale contract","Sales Manager / Developer Controller (segregated)","P13",
    "realestate.service.ts createContract (BAD_DISCOUNT/BAD_DOWN_PAYMENT, draft, no GL) / approveContract (SOD_SELF_APPROVAL, CONTRACT_NOT_DRAFT, unit→contracted, JE 1000/2210/2410, schedule); realestate.controller.ts contracts[+ :no/approve]; schema/realestate.ts re_contracts+re_installments (migration 0256); permissions.ts re_sales/re_contract_approve + SoD R19; cutover/projects.ts (ToE)","Inspect the price/discount bounds, the draft-then-approve maker-checker (approver ≠ drafter), and the down-payment → contract-liability posting on approval.","Re-perform: draft a contract (list 1,000,000 − discount 100,000 = 900,000, down 200,000, 4 installments); drafter self-approve → SOD_SELF_APPROVAL; an independent approver approves → unit contracted, JE posts the down payment to 2410 (booking deposit reclassed from 2210), 4 installments generated (re-performed by the projects harness).","Contract register (draft/active); the down-payment JE (1000/2210/2410); installment schedule","Implemented")
add("RE-03","Real Estate","Application","Installment application","An installment receipt is misapplied — a paid installment is paid again (double receipt), or an amount other than the scheduled installment is applied, so the buyer's balance and the contract-liability control are wrong.","Accuracy/Completeness",
    "Installment application integrity (docs/35 P4): each installment is paid EXACTLY ONCE (a paid installment → INSTALLMENT_PAID on a second attempt) for EXACTLY its scheduled amount (a different amount → BAD_AMOUNT), posting Dr 1000 cash / Cr 2410 contract liability and marking the installment paid; posting is idempotent per (contract, installment seq) so a retried receipt can't double-post. The contract read model rolls up installments_paid + outstanding = balance − paid, so the buyer's position and the 2410 control reconcile.","Prev","Automated","Per installment receipt","AR / Sales","P13",
    "realestate.service.ts payInstallment (INSTALLMENT_PAID, BAD_AMOUNT, JE 1000/2410, idempotent RE-INSTALL) / getContract (installments_paid/outstanding rollup); realestate.controller.ts installments/:id/pay; schema/realestate.ts re_installments (migration 0256); cutover/projects.ts (ToE)","Inspect the pay-once / exact-amount guards, the cash → contract-liability posting, and the paid/outstanding rollup.","Re-perform: pay an installment for its exact amount → paid + Dr 1000 / Cr 2410; pay it again → INSTALLMENT_PAID; pay a wrong amount → BAD_AMOUNT; the contract outstanding falls by the paid amount (re-performed by the projects harness).","Installment schedule (paid/pending); receipt JEs (1000/2410); outstanding rollup","Implemented")
add("RE-04","Real Estate","Application","Ownership transfer / revenue recognition","A property sale's revenue is recognised before the buyer has fully paid, or an unauthorised person transfers a unit, or the deferred cash sitting in the contract liability is never recognised at handover — so revenue is misstated (early or missing) and the developer's units/inventory don't clear on transfer.","Accuracy/Cutoff/Authorization",
    "Ownership transfer with revenue recognition (docs/35 P5): revenue on a unit sale is DEFERRED (cash received over the sale sits in the contract liability 2410) and is recognised ONLY at ownership TRANSFER — an AUTHORISED act (re_transfer/exec) allowed ONLY on an ACTIVE, FULLY-SETTLED contract (NOT_FULLY_SETTLED when any installment is outstanding; CONTRACT_NOT_ACTIVE otherwise) and IDEMPOTENT per contract (alreadyPosted RE-TRANSFER). On transfer a balanced JE recognises the price (Dr 2410 Contract Liability / Cr 4200 Revenue) and relieves the unit's construction cost (Dr 5800 COGS / Cr 1200 Inventory), and the unit + contract flip to `transferred`. So revenue lands at the right time (handover, not on cash receipt) for the right amount, cost is matched, and the units clear.","Prev","Automated","Per ownership transfer","Developer Controller / Legal (segregated on the settled-only gate)","P13",
    "realestate.service.ts transferOwnership (NOT_FULLY_SETTLED/CONTRACT_NOT_ACTIVE, idempotent, JE 2410/4200 + 5800/1200, unit+contract → transferred); realestate.controller.ts contracts/:no/transfer (re_transfer); schema/realestate.ts re_units.cost + re_contracts.transfer_entry_no/transferred_at (migration 0258); permissions.ts re_transfer; cutover/projects.ts (ToE)","Inspect the settled-only + authorised transfer gate, the deferred-revenue recognition (2410 → 4200), and the unit-cost relief (5800 ← 1200).","Re-perform: a fully-settled contract transfers → Dr 2410 / Cr 4200 revenue + Dr 5800 / Cr 1200 cost, unit+contract transferred; a contract with an outstanding installment → NOT_FULLY_SETTLED; a re-transfer → already (idempotent) (re-performed by the projects harness).","Transferred contracts + the revenue-recognition JE (2410/4200/5800/1200)","Implemented")

