add("GL-08","General Ledger","Application","All","Standing/period accruals missed, posted unbalanced, or posted without approval; manual re-keying error.","Completeness/Accuracy/Authorization",
    "Recurring/template journal entries: a template's lines are validated balanced (Σdebit=Σcredit) AT SAVE TIME (unbalanced → UNBALANCED), so a broken template can never be persisted. The scheduled job gl_recurring_journals (cron / daily scheduler) posts every due template as a DRAFT JE through the normal maker-checker flow (GL-05) — a different user must approve before it affects balances — and rolls next_run_date forward. Idempotent: next_run_date advanced on posting + the (tenant,source,source_ref,ledger) idempotency key dedupes a same-day re-run. Templates can be paused/resumed without losing history.","Prev","Automated","Per due date / per template","Controller","P10",
    "ledger.service.ts (createRecurring balanced-at-save, runDueRecurring→postEntry pendingApproval, setRecurringActive); ledger.controller.ts (gl_post creates/runs); bi.service.ts (gl_recurring_journals); schema/ledger.ts (recurring_journals) + migration 0119; cutover/basics.ts (ToE)","Inspect template balance validation + scheduled posting as Draft + idempotency.","Unbalanced template → UNBALANCED; due template posts a Draft JE (excluded from TB) into the pending queue; re-run posts nothing; a second user approves → accrual hits the GL (re-performed by the harness).","Recurring-journal templates; scheduled run log; JE approvals","Implemented")
add("GL-09","General Ledger","Application","Prepaid expenses; Operating expense","Prepaid expense not amortized over its term — expense mis-stated, prepaid asset overstated.","Accuracy/Completeness",
    "Prepaid amortization schedules: a prepaid asset (insurance/rent paid up front) is registered once with a total + term; the scheduled job gl_prepaid_amortize posts a straight-line slice each period (Dr expense / Cr 1280), the last period taking the remainder so the asset fully clears. Idempotent per (schedule, period) via the JE idempotency key + next_run_date advance.","Det","Automated","Per period / per schedule","Controller","P10",
    "ledger.service.ts (createPrepaid, runDuePrepaid); ledger.controller.ts (gl_post); bi.service.ts (gl_prepaid_amortize); schema/ledger.ts (prepaid_schedules) + migration 0120; cutover/basics.ts (ToE)","Inspect amortization slice + final-period remainder + idempotency.","Register a 12-month prepaid; run amortizes 1/12 to expense; re-run posts nothing (re-performed by the harness).","Prepaid schedules; amortization run log","Implemented")
add("GL-10","General Ledger","Application","All","A new company starts on a chart of accounts with no industry guidance — staff post to wrong/ambiguous accounts; or an industry template drifts from the GL engine's fixed posting codes so a posting targets an account that does not exist (mis-statement / unposted transaction).","Completeness/Accuracy/Presentation",
    "Industry Chart-of-Accounts templates: the GL engine binds to a FIXED, global account universe (canonical codes are immutable); each tenant additionally gets a per-tenant overlay (tenant_accounts) curating which canonical accounts are active and how they are named/grouped for its industry. At company creation the customer picks an industry (restaurant/retail/distribution/services/general) and the chosen template is materialised into the overlay (provisionTenantCoA) inside the signup transaction, right after fiscal-year provisioning; adopting an industry pack later does the same. Every template code is asserted to exist in the canonical chart at boot (assertTemplatesSubsetOf in seedChartOfAccounts) so a drifted template fails fast and can never reach a tenant. Provisioning is idempotent + additive (never deletes) so re-running only adds missing accounts. The overlay NEVER gates postings — it scopes the picker / Chart-of-Accounts view only; reports surface any account that is active OR carries activity, so a curated-out account that receives a posting still appears.","Prev","Automated","At company creation / per pack adopt","Controller","P10",
    "ledger.service.ts (provisionTenantCoA idempotent+additive, tenant-aware listAccounts, seedChartOfAccounts→assertTemplatesSubsetOf); coa-templates.ts (industry templates + subset assertion); billing.service.ts signup (industry→provisionTenantCoA in-txn); onboarding.service.ts applyPack (pack adopt provisions CoA); schema/ledger.ts tenant_accounts + tenants.industry + migration 0139; cutover/basics.ts + compliance.ts (ToE)","Inspect the boot subset assertion + signup provisioning + the overlay-is-presentation-only read path.","Re-perform: a template referencing an unknown code fails the boot assertion; signup with industry=restaurant materialises a curated, industry-named chart (4000='Food & Beverage Sales') that omits non-F&B accounts; ?all=true still returns the full canonical universe (overlay never gates posting); signup with no industry ⇒ general = the full live chart (re-performed by the harnesses).","Industry templates; tenant_accounts overlay; signup provisioning log","Implemented")
add("GL-11","General Ledger","Application","All","Chart of Accounts changed without authorisation; a tenant's CoA maintainer mutates the GLOBAL, shared canonical account universe that every tenant posts against; account code changed after postings exist; account deactivated while carrying a non-zero balance; manual JE posted directly to a control account (AR/AP/INV/FA), bypassing the sub-ledger and hiding a sub-ledger discrepancy.","Authorization/Completeness/Accuracy",
    "CoA Change Control — two write surfaces, two duties. (1) CANONICAL universe (accounts table: global, no tenant_id, shared by every tenant): create/update/deactivate require the platform Admin/HQ role IN ADDITION to gl_coa; a tenant gl_coa holder (e.g. FinancialController) is refused with COA_ADMIN_ONLY so it can never silently change the chart other tenants post against. Duplicate code -> DUPLICATE_ACCOUNT; disabling postability on an account with posted entries -> CODE_HAS_POSTINGS; deactivation with a non-zero net balance -> ACCOUNT_HAS_BALANCE (no orphaned balance in a closed account). (2) PER-TENANT curation (tenant_accounts overlay, RLS-scoped): a tenant shapes its OWN chart (active / display name / group / sort order) via PATCH /api/ledger/accounts/:code/overlay under gl_coa; tenant_id is taken from the request context, so a tenant can only ever curate its own chart and never another's, and the overlay never gates postings (references existing canonical codes only -> ACCOUNT_NOT_FOUND; missing tenant context -> TENANT_REQUIRED). gl_coa is SoD-separated from gl_post (GlAccountant cannot maintain the CoA). Control accounts 1100 (AR)/2000 (AP)/1200 (INV)/1500 (FA) reject direct JEs without viaSubledger:true (CONTROL_ACCOUNT).","Prev","Automated","Event-driven","Financial Controller / Platform Admin","P10",
    "coa.controller.ts (@Controller('api/ledger/accounts'); canonical create/update/deactivate gated to role Admin via assertPlatformAdmin -> COA_ADMIN_ONLY; PATCH :code/overlay curation endpoint, gl_coa); coa.service.ts (createAccount DUPLICATE_ACCOUNT, updateAccount CODE_HAS_POSTINGS, deactivateAccount ACCOUNT_HAS_BALANCE, curateOverlay tenant_accounts upsert TENANT_REQUIRED/ACCOUNT_NOT_FOUND); ledger.controller.ts (GET /api/ledger/accounts list read, perms exec/creditors/ar/gl_coa); ledger.service.ts postEntry control-account guard (CONTROL_ACCOUNT, viaSubledger flag) + listAccounts overlay merge; schema/ledger.ts (accounts is_control/control_subledger/is_postable/normal_balance; tenant_accounts overlay + migrations 0155/0139); packages/shared/src/permissions.ts (gl_coa sub-permission, FinancialController default)","Inspect the Admin/HQ gate on canonical writes (COA_ADMIN_ONLY), the RLS-scoped overlay curation, and the CODE_HAS_POSTINGS / ACCOUNT_HAS_BALANCE / CONTROL_ACCOUNT guards.","Re-perform (compliance GL-11 ToE): platform Admin creates a canonical account -> 201; a tenant gl_coa holder is blocked -> COA_ADMIN_ONLY; a non-gl_coa role -> 403; duplicate code -> DUPLICATE_ACCOUNT; deactivate an account with balance -> ACCOUNT_HAS_BALANCE; a tenant curates its overlay -> reflected on its own chart but not another tenant's (RLS); overlay curation without gl_coa -> 403; direct JE to 1100 without viaSubledger -> CONTROL_ACCOUNT (TC-GL-11-01..06).","CoA change log (audit_log); compliance GL-11 ToE; control-account guard test","Implemented")
add("GL-12","General Ledger","Application","All","Account-assignment errors introduced by scattered inline account-code literals in service code; a tenant needing a different account for a given business event has no mechanism to override without a code change.","Authorization/Accuracy",
    "Posting / Account-Determination Engine: two tables — posting_event_types (28 seeded event types, e.g. SALE.FOOD, GR.INVENTORY, DEPRECIATION.FA) and posting_rules (maps event × leg-order to semantic role → account_code + DR/CR side) — drive account assignment instead of hard-coded literals. PostingService.post(eventType, ctx) resolves the applicable rules (global defaults, or shadowed by tenant-specific overrides for the same leg_order), translates role-keyed amounts into DR/CR lines, and delegates to LedgerService.postEntry. If no active rules exist for an event the call fails with NO_POSTING_RULE. Tenant-specific rules require gl_posting_rules permission to create/update. PostingService.preview() provides a dry-run for audit.","Prev","Automated","Event-driven","Financial Controller","P10",
    "posting.service.ts (resolveRules, post, preview, listEventTypes, listRules, upsertRule); posting-rules.controller.ts (gl_posting_rules permission gate); schema/posting-rules.ts (posting_event_types, posting_rules tables); migration 0156 (tables + 28 event types + global-default rules); ledger.module.ts (PostingService exported); packages/shared/src/permissions.ts (gl_posting_rules sub-permission); cutover/basics.ts (golden-snapshot ToE)","Inspect the rule-resolution logic + NO_POSTING_RULE fast-fail + tenant-shadow logic + gl_posting_rules permission gate.","Re-perform: preview DEPRECIATION.FA with dep_expense:1000 → DR 5200 / CR 1590; preview GR.INVENTORY with inventory:500 → DR 1200 / CR 2000; preview UNKNOWN_EVENT → NO_POSTING_RULE (400); event-type catalogue returns ≥20 entries (re-performed by TC-GL-12-01/02/03/04 UAT cases + basics.ts harness).","Posting-rule change log; preview dry-run; harness golden snapshot","Implemented")
add("GL-13","General Ledger","Application","All","Revenue or expense mis-attributed to the wrong branch / project — per-location P&L is unintelligible or misleading.","Accuracy/Presentation",
    "Multi-dimensional GL postings: journal_lines carries three optional dimension columns (branch_id, project_id, department_id). PostingService.post() stamps all generated lines from PostingContext (branchId/projectId/departmentId). GET /api/ledger/income-statement/by-branch provides a per-branch P&L view; lines without a branch_id are grouped as 'unassigned'. The departments master table holds a tenant-scoped department registry with RLS isolation.","Det","Automated","Per period","Controller","P10",
    "ledger.service.ts (incomeStatementByBranch); ledger.controller.ts (GET income-statement/by-branch); posting.service.ts (branchId/projectId/departmentId from PostingContext); schema/ledger.ts (branch_id, project_id, department_id on journal_lines); schema/departments.ts (departments table); migration 0157; cutover/basics.ts (GL-13 ToE)","Inspect by-branch query + PostingContext stamping + department RLS.","TC-GL-13-01/02/03: smoke + two branches + unassigned bucket (re-performed by the basics.ts harness).","By-branch P&L report; dimension completeness","Implemented")
add("GL-14","General Ledger","Application","All","GL control-account balances (AR/AP/INV/FA) drift from the underlying sub-ledger detail without detection — the control account no longer represents the sum of its sub-ledger, masking posting errors, unrecorded items, or fraud.","Completeness/Accuracy/Valuation",
    "Sub-ledger tie-out / reconciliation: POST /api/ledger/tie-out/run computes, per control account, the GL balance (Σ debit−credit of posted journal_lines on the control account up to the as-of date, tenant-scoped) and the sub-ledger detail balance (AR = Σ outstanding ar_invoices; AP = Σ outstanding ap_transactions; INV = Σ inv_balances.total_value perpetual valuation; FA = Σ acquire_cost − accumulated_depreciation of non-disposed fixed_assets), records the variance (gl − subledger) and a status (Matched if |variance|<0.01 else Variance). Runs upsert per (tenant, subledger, as-of). Certification is maker-checker: POST /api/ledger/tie-out/:id/certify sets status=Certified and records certifier + timestamp, and REJECTS a certifier equal to the runner (SELF_CERTIFY) — the gl_close certifier must differ from the gl_post/gl_close runner (SoD).","Det","Automated","Monthly","Financial Controller","P10",
    "subledger-tieout.service.ts (runTieOut GL/sub-ledger balance computation + variance/status, certify SELF_CERTIFY maker-checker, list/get); subledger-tieout.controller.ts (gl_close/gl_post run, gl_close certify, gl_close/gl_post/exec/creditors/ar read); schema/subledger-tieout.ts (subledger_tieout_runs table, uq on tenant/subledger/as-of); migration 0160 (table + RLS); ledger.module.ts (service+controller wired); cutover/basics.ts (GL-14 ToE)","Inspect the GL-vs-sub-ledger balance computation + variance/status + SELF_CERTIFY maker-checker gate + gl_close certify permission.","TC-GL-14-01: run AR tie-out → balances + Matched/Variance; TC-GL-14-02: self-certify by the runner → SELF_CERTIFY (400); TC-GL-14-03: certify by a different gl_close user → Certified (re-performed by the basics.ts harness).","Tie-out run log (subledger_tieout_runs) with variance + certification trail; monthly reconciliation sign-off","Implemented")
add("GL-15","General Ledger","Application","All","A period is 'closed' on paper but key close procedures (sub-ledger tie-out, bank rec, depreciation, recurring/prepaid, trial-balance review) were skipped, OR a closed period is silently re-opened and re-posted — the financial statements are produced on an incomplete/altered basis.","Completeness/Accuracy/Cutoff",
    "Hard period close + checklist: POST /api/ledger/close/start opens a close_runs record (status InProgress) per (tenant, period) and seeds a standard checklist of close_run_steps (subledger_tieout, bank_rec, depreciation, recurring, fx_reval[advisory], trial_balance_review). POST /api/ledger/close/step marks a step Done (records completedBy/At); when all REQUIRED steps are Done the run advances to ReadyToLock. POST /api/ledger/close/lock requires ReadyToLock (else STEPS_INCOMPLETE listing the pending required steps) before the period can be locked. Locking writes 'Locked' into fiscal_periods.status; LedgerService.postEntry then REJECTS every posting dated into a Locked period with PERIOD_LOCKED, regardless of the legacy allowClosedPeriod escape (the only exception is the system year-end closing entry, source='CLOSE'). Locked is strictly stronger than the soft 'Closed' status — it is the irreversible hard close.","Prev","Automated","Monthly","Financial Controller","P10",
    "close.service.ts (startClose seeds checklist, completeStep → ReadyToLock when required steps Done, lockPeriod STEPS_INCOMPLETE gate + fiscal_periods Locked write, status/list); close.controller.ts (gl_close start/step/lock, gl_close/gl_post/exec read); schema/close-runs.ts (close_runs + close_run_steps, uq on tenant/period and run/step_key); schema/ledger.ts (period_status enum + 'Locked'); ledger.service.ts (postEntry PERIOD_LOCKED hard gate, source='CLOSE' exemption); migration 0162 (tables + RLS + ALTER TYPE Locked); ledger.module.ts (service+controller wired); cutover/basics.ts (GL-15/GL-16 ToE)","Inspect the seeded checklist + ReadyToLock gating + STEPS_INCOMPLETE lock rejection + PERIOD_LOCKED hard gate in postEntry (incl. the CLOSE exemption).","TC-GL-15-01: start close seeds ≥4 steps (InProgress); TC-GL-15-02: lock before steps done → STEPS_INCOMPLETE (400); TC-GL-15-03: post into locked period → PERIOD_LOCKED (400) (re-performed by the basics.ts harness).","close_runs / close_run_steps with completion trail; fiscal_periods.status=Locked; monthly close sign-off","Implemented")
add("GL-16","General Ledger","Application","All","One person both performs the close and locks the period, defeating segregation of duties — a preparer could conceal a misstatement by closing over their own work without independent review.","Authorization/Segregation of Duties",
    "Segregated period lock (maker-checker): the close_runs.started_by (the user who started the close and ran the checklist steps) is recorded, and POST /api/ledger/close/lock REJECTS a lockedBy equal to startedBy with SELF_LOCK — the gl_close user who locks the period MUST differ from the user who started/ran the close. Both identities and the lock timestamp are retained on the close_runs row (started_by / locked_by / locked_at) as the SoD evidence trail. This complements the existing SoD rule that gl_close is segregated from gl_post (JE posting).","Prev","Automated","Monthly","Financial Controller","P10",
    "close.service.ts (lockPeriod SELF_LOCK maker-checker gate; started_by vs locked_by); close.controller.ts (gl_close lock, acting username from JWT); schema/close-runs.ts (started_by, locked_by, locked_at columns); permissions.ts (gl_post×gl_close SoD pair); cutover/basics.ts (GL-16 ToE)","Inspect the SELF_LOCK gate (startedBy ≠ lockedBy) + the started_by/locked_by/locked_at evidence trail.","TC-GL-16-01: self-lock by the starter → SELF_LOCK (400); TC-GL-16-02: lock by a different gl_close user → Locked, locked_by recorded (re-performed by the basics.ts harness).","close_runs.started_by / locked_by / locked_at SoD trail; monthly close sign-off","Implemented")
add("GL-17","General Ledger","Application","All","A posted journal entry is edited or deleted after the fact — restating history with no trail — instead of being corrected by a transparent reversal; or a correction is made with no record of who/what/why. The general ledger is no longer an immutable, auditable record of record.","Completeness/Accuracy/Authorization",
    "Posted-entry immutability + reversal-only correction + GL audit trail: a journal entry that has reached Posted status is IMMUTABLE — it can never be edited or deleted. Enforcement is twofold: (1) a production DB trigger (gl_block_posted_mutation) that RAISES on any UPDATE/DELETE of a Posted journal_entries row (permitting only the is_reversed bookkeeping flag flip), and (2) an application-level guard (attemptVoidPosted → GL_IMMUTABLE) that refuses and records any mutation attempt. The ONLY way to correct a posted entry is a REVERSAL: reverseEntry posts a NEW, immediately-Posted contra entry that swaps every line's debit/credit (so original + reversal net to zero on every affected account), dimensions carried over, linked via reversal_of, and flags the original is_reversed. A reversal goes through the normal posting path so the period gates (PERIOD_LOCKED/PERIOD_CLOSED) still apply; only Posted entries can be reversed (NOT_POSTED) and only once (ALREADY_REVERSED). Every POST, APPROVE, REVERSE and blocked mutation (MUTATE_BLOCKED) is recorded with actor + detail + timestamp in gl_audit_log (tenant-scoped, RLS).","Prev","Automated","Per entry / continuous","Financial Controller","P10",
    "ledger.service.ts (postEntry stamps posted_at + logs POST; approveEntry stamps posted_at + logs APPROVE; reverseEntry contra-posting with ENTRY_NOT_FOUND/NOT_POSTED/ALREADY_REVERSED + REVERSE log; attemptVoidPosted GL_IMMUTABLE + MUTATE_BLOCKED log; listGlAudit); ledger.controller.ts (gl_post journal/:id/reverse + journal/:id/attempt-void, gl_post/gl_close/exec audit read); schema/ledger.ts (journal_entries posted_at/reversal_of/is_reversed); schema/gl-audit.ts (gl_audit_log table); migration 0164 (columns + gl_audit_log + RLS + gl_block_posted_mutation trigger); ledger.module.ts (LedgerService owns it); cutover/basics.ts (GL-17 ToE)","Inspect the DB immutability trigger + the app GL_IMMUTABLE guard + the reversal contra-posting (swapped Dr/Cr, reversal_of, is_reversed) + the gl_audit_log trail (POST/APPROVE/REVERSE/MUTATE_BLOCKED).","TC-GL-17-01: attempt to void a posted entry → GL_IMMUTABLE (400) + MUTATE_BLOCKED audit row; TC-GL-17-02: reverse a posted entry → contra entry nets to zero, original is_reversed + REVERSE audit row; TC-GL-17-03: reverse again → ALREADY_REVERSED (400) (re-performed by the basics.ts harness).","gl_audit_log trail (POST/APPROVE/REVERSE/MUTATE_BLOCKED); reversal entries with reversal_of linkage; posted-entry immutability","Implemented")
add("GL-18","General Ledger","Application","Accounts Receivable (1100); Accounts Payable (2000); FX Gain/Loss (5400)","Open foreign-currency monetary balances (AR/AP) are not restated to the period-end closing rate, or a revaluation is computed and posted by one person with no independent review — the unrealized FX gain/loss is omitted/mis-stated and a single user can move earnings through the FX line.","Accuracy/Valuation/Authorization/Segregation of Duties",
    "Period-end FX revaluation governance (maker-checker, idempotent per (tenant, period)): POST /api/ledger/fx-reval/run computes the unrealized FX on every OPEN foreign-currency AR/AP balance — delta_thb = open_foreign × (closing_rate − booked_rate) — staging an 'Open' fx_reval_runs row (one per tenant/period; re-running an Open period refreshes it; a Posted period → ALREADY_POSTED). Closing rates come from the request `rates` map first, else the latest APPROVED fx_rates row (FX-04); a currency with no rate from either → MISSING_RATE (an unapproved manual rate can never drive the reval). POST /api/ledger/fx-reval/:id/post is segregated — the poster MUST differ from the runner (SELF_POST) — and posts the net to 5400 (net gain → Cr 5400; net loss → Dr 5400) with the AR/AP control restatements (Dr/Cr 1100, Dr/Cr 2000) via LedgerService.postEntry, so the WS2.1 PERIOD_LOCKED gate + the GL-17 audit trail apply. Marks the run Posted. SIGN: net P&L = Σ(AR delta) − Σ(AP delta).","Prev","Automated","Monthly / period-end","Financial Controller","P10",
    "fx-reval.service.ts (runReval compute+stage Open, idempotent ALREADY_POSTED, rate resolution MISSING_RATE; postReval SELF_POST maker-checker + 5400/1100/2000 posting; list/get); fx-reval.controller.ts (gl_close/gl_post run + :id/post, gl_close/gl_post/exec read); schema/deferred-tax-fx.ts (fx_reval_runs, uq tenant/period); migration 0168 (tables + RLS); ledger.module.ts (service+controller wired); close.service.ts (fx_reval close-checklist step); reuses fx_rates (FX-04) + LedgerService.postEntry; cutover/basics.ts (GL-18 ToE)","Inspect the run→post lifecycle, the rate resolution (explicit/approved-only/MISSING_RATE), the SELF_POST maker-checker, and the 5400/1100/2000 posting through the period-lock gate.","TC-GL-18-01: run on an open foreign AR+AP → net unrealized gain/loss with per-doc detail (Open); TC-GL-18-02: runner self-post → SELF_POST (403), a different user posts → 5400 movement, re-post → ALREADY_POSTED (400) (re-performed by the basics.ts harness).","fx_reval_runs register (Open→Posted, runner/poster); the FXREVAL-RUN JE to 5400; period-end reval sign-off","Implemented")
add("GL-19","General Ledger","Detective","All","A period is locked on the strength of a manual checklist sign-off while the books are not actually clean — an unposted draft journal still sits in the period, or an entry/batch does not balance — so the financial statements are produced on an incomplete or internally-inconsistent basis that the checklist alone could not catch.","Completeness/Accuracy",
    "Programmatic pre-lock validation (read-only, posts nothing): GET /api/ledger/close/validate?period=YYYY-MM asserts the books-are-clean conditions the checklist sign-off cannot by itself — (1) NO unposted Draft journal entries dated in the period, (2) the period's Posted entries balance IN AGGREGATE (Σdebit = Σcredit), (3) EVERY posted entry is individually balanced, and (4) suspense/clearing accounts (2380/2390/1999/9999) net to ~zero through period end (advisory). It returns ready + an explicit blockers/warnings list and a per-check breakdown, surfaced in the period-close screen as advisory blockers BEFORE the GL-16 maker-checker lock — so an unbalanced or draft-laden period is flagged for correction rather than silently locked. Detective and read-only; the hard lock still runs the GL-15 checklist + GL-16 segregation.","Det","Automated","Pre-lock / period-end","Financial Controller","P10",
    "close.service.ts (validate — draft scan, aggregate + per-entry balance, suspense/clearing balance, ready/blockers/warnings); close.controller.ts (GET close/validate, gl_close/gl_post/exec); reuses journal_entries/journal_lines; no migration (read-only); cutover/basics.ts (GL-19 ToE)","Inspect the four readiness checks (unposted_drafts, period_balanced, unbalanced_entries, suspense_clearing) and that a draft in the period sets ready=false with the unposted_drafts blocker.","TC-GL-19-CLOSE-01: validate a clean past period → ready=true, no blockers, drafts/balance checks ok; TC-GL-19-CLOSE-02: a manual JE (posts as Draft, GL-05) in the period → ready=false, unposted_drafts blocker count ≥ 1 (re-performed by the basics.ts harness).","close-validate readiness report (ready/blockers/warnings + per-check detail)","Implemented")
add("GL-20","General Ledger","Detective","All","The trial balance reads the gl_period_balances snapshot (docs/27 R1-2 — maintained transactionally at posting so financial-statement reads stop scanning the full journal); a write path that bypasses LedgerService (direct SQL, ETL) would silently drift the snapshot from the raw ledger, mis-stating the reported balances.","Completeness/Accuracy",
    "Snapshot reconciliation at close: the GL-19 pre-lock validator additionally re-aggregates the period's POSTED journal_lines per account and compares them to the gl_period_balances snapshot — ANY per-account debit/credit mismatch is a HARD close blocker (gl_snapshot_drift, listing the drifted accounts) until the snapshot is resynced (the 0219 backfill recompute). The snapshot itself is written in the SAME transaction as the posting (postEntry → Posted; approveEntry Draft→Posted) and Posted entries are DB-immutable (GL-17/0165), so drift can only come from an out-of-band writer — exactly what this control detects.","Det","Automated","Per close","Financial Controller","P17",
    "ledger.service.ts bumpPeriodBalances (transactional maintenance) + trialBalance (snapshot read); close.service.ts validate gl_snapshot_drift; drizzle/0219_gl_period_balances.sql (table + unique key + backfill); cutover/basics.ts TC-GL-20 (ToE)","Inspect that the snapshot write shares the posting transaction and that validate compares snapshot vs raw per account.","Re-perform: clean period → gl_snapshot_drift ok; INSERT a bogus snapshot row → validate ready=false with the account named; rebuild → clear (basics harness TC-GL-20).","Snapshot-reconciliation ToE (basics)","Implemented")
add("GL-21","General Ledger","Application","Inventory; COGS; Revenue","Inventory / COGS posting accounts are hard-coded control literals, so an item (or item family) that should hit a different GL account has no maintainable mechanism; and any per-item account mapping, if introduced, could point at a non-existent or non-postable account — silently mis-stating the sub-ledger or breaking the control-account tie-out.","Accuracy/Completeness/Valuation",
    "Item-posting account determination (extends GL-12 to the item grain): a per-tenant, opt-in flag (posting_determination, default OFF ⇒ literal parity) lets an item's GL/tax profile drive posting. AccountDeterminationService.resolveItemAccounts resolves each account by precedence item column → its item_categories row → its WAREHOUSE (locations) default → null (caller falls back to the hard-coded control account), so an un-opted-in or unconfigured tenant is byte-for-byte unchanged. The inventory sub-ledger (receive/issue/adjust/issue-to-project) routes its inventory, COGS & adjustment legs through the resolver; reconcile() sums the WHOLE inventory-account set (control 1200 + any item/category/warehouse overrides) so the GL-14-style sub-ledger↔GL tie-out holds under routing. Fail-closed: a resolved override that is not a real, POSTABLE account in the canonical CoA is rejected with INVALID_POSTING_ACCOUNT before any posting — a typo'd/header/control account can never receive a posting. docs/42 hardening: the SAME fail-closed guard now runs inside postEntry itself for EVERY journal line (any source, subledger or manual) — a line naming a non-existent or non-postable account is rejected with INVALID_POSTING_ACCOUNT instead of posting silently and vanishing from the typed reports (they INNER JOIN accounts); and a tenant's ACTIVE posting_rules rows (event_type+role, /setup/posting-rules) re-map the recurring system posters' accounts (payroll PAYROLL.*, FA depreciation DEPRECIATION.FA, lease runs LEASE.*/DEPRECIATION.ROU) as override ?? literal — un-configured tenants post byte-identically, and the posting_determination flag is toggleable from the item-categories setup screen. VAT (docs/33 PR6): a configured tax_code drives the VAT rate + output/input VAT GL account on AR invoices (from the order's uniform item vat_code) and AP bills (from an explicit tax_code); an unknown/non-VAT code fails closed (UNKNOWN_TAX_CODE/NOT_A_VAT_CODE), and the PP30↔GL reconciliation (TAX-04) sums the whole VAT-account set so the tie holds under routing. Further item defaults (docs/33 PR7): a stock move with no explicit location defaults to the item's default_location_id (item→category), and an AR invoice's REVENUE account follows the order's uniform item revenue_account — both flag-gated with literal parity (WH-MAIN / 4000 when off/unset). COA-D2 extension: the postEntry account guard additionally enforces, ONLY when declared on the account (fail-closed, byte-identical otherwise): the effective-date window (a line dated outside effective_from/effective_to → ACCOUNT_NOT_EFFECTIVE — the 'retire with an effective-to date' path now binds) and required dimensions (an account flagged require_dimension {branch|project|department|cost_center} rejects a line missing that stamp → REQUIRED_DIMENSION_MISSING, so dimension reporting on the account is complete); a canonical create naming a non-existent parent is refused at request time (PARENT_NOT_FOUND). Both attributes are maintainable on the /chart-of-accounts dialogs (GL-27-staged).","Prev","Automated","Event-driven / per item","Financial Controller","P10",
    "account-determination.service.ts (resolveItemAccounts item→category→warehouse precedence + assertPostable INVALID_POSTING_ACCOUNT fail-closed, enabled flag, resolveTaxCode); inventory-ledger.service.ts (invAccounts resolver + inventoryAccountSet reconcile); posting.service.ts (resolveRules now evaluates the condition jsonb); feature-flags.service.ts (posting_determination CORE flag, default off); item-setup.service.ts (categories/tax-codes/item-profile/warehouse-account CRUD, /api/item-setup/*, gated md_item/md_config); schema/posting-setup.ts (item_categories, tax_codes) + inventory.ts item + locations account columns; migrations 0243/0244 (journaled); ledger.module.ts (AccountDeterminationService exported); ledger-posting.service.ts postEntry account-universe guard (exists + isPostable on every line, INVALID_POSTING_ACCOUNT); ledger.service.ts postingOverrides (tenant posting_rules role→account map) consumed by payroll.service.ts / assets.service.ts (depreciation) / leases.service.ts (periodic run); cutover/basics.ts + compliance.ts + payroll.ts (GL-21 ToE)","Inspect the item→category→literal precedence, the OFF-by-default parity, the postable-account fail-closed guard, and that reconcile sums the full inventory-account set.","Re-perform (basics): flag OFF → item COGS override ignored, 5001 untouched (parity); enable posting_determination → goods issue routes COGS to the item's 5001 override (Dr 40) while inventory sub-ledger still reconciles to the GL account set; an override at a non-existent account → INVALID_POSTING_ACCOUNT (400); a manual JE naming a non-existent account → INVALID_POSTING_ACCOUNT (compliance); a tenant PAYROLL.GROSS posting-rule re-maps the salaries debit to its override account end-to-end (payroll ToE).","Feature-flag state + posting-rule/override config; harness ToE (basics GL-21)","Implemented")
add("GL-22","General Ledger","Detective","All","A period is locked (or the financial statements are relied upon) without a single, current view of whether the books are actually ready — the sub-ledger↔GL tie-out, the pre-lock readiness checks, and the pending maker-checker queue live on separate screens, so the controller can miss an out-of-balance control account, an unposted draft, or a stale approval and close on an incomplete/inaccurate basis.","Completeness/Accuracy",
    "Controller Close Cockpit — a single read-only period-close readiness board (GET /api/finance/metrics/close/status, perm exec/fin_report/gl_close) that COMPOSES the existing detective controls into one RAG view: the sub-ledger↔GL control-account tie-out (REC-04: AR↔1100, AP↔2000, Inventory↔1200, Gift cards↔2200, Deferred revenue↔2400), the pre-lock readiness checks (GL-19 unposted-draft/aggregate-&-per-entry-balance/suspense + GL-20 snapshot↔raw reconciliation), the pending maker-checker queue with ageing (GOV-01), and the close checklist/state (GL-15/16) — plus a days-to-close metric. Each pillar carries a RAG, and the overall status is RED if any tie-out breaks or a hard readiness blocker exists. Read-only aggregation over the posted GL + sub-ledgers — posts nothing, adds no posting authority (no new SoD conflict). Surfaced on the /finance/close-cockpit web screen so the controller reviews close-readiness in one place before the maker-checker lock.","Det","Hybrid","Per period-close","Financial Controller","P16",
    "finance/finance-metrics.service.ts (closeStatus — composes close.validate GL-19/20, finance.reconcileControls REC-04, finance.pendingApprovals GOV-01, close.status; RAG + days-to-close); finance-metrics.controller.ts (GET /api/finance/metrics/close/status); apps/web close-cockpit (screen); cutover/finance-kpi.ts (ToE); docs/35-finance-oracle-grade-analytics-plan.md","Inspect the cockpit: the tie-out rows (sub-ledger vs GL control + variance), the readiness checks, the pending-approval ageing, and that the overall RAG turns red on any break.","Re-perform (finance-kpi): a seeded tie-out break (AP/inventory sub-ledger ≠ GL control) makes the cockpit report tie-out RED and overall RED while readiness is GREEN; posting the matching sub-ledgers flips tie-out + overall to GREEN with 0 exceptions; a non-finance role is denied the cockpit (403).","Close-readiness cockpit (finance/metrics/close/status); harness ToE (finance-kpi)","Implemented")
add("GL-23","General Ledger","Application","Operating expense; Overhead; Cost centers","Shared / overhead cost is not allocated to the consuming cost-centers or departments — or is allocated by an ad-hoc spreadsheet that is unbalanced, non-repeatable, or posted without review — so departmental / project P&L is mis-stated and the allocation is neither auditable nor idempotent.","Accuracy/Completeness/Presentation",
    "GL allocation engine: a periodic ALLOCATION CYCLE distributes a source POOL (a fixed amount out of a source account / cost-center) to a set of targets by fixed RATIO, a measured DRIVER, or a STATISTICAL KEY (headcount / sqm) — the three methods share one proportional-split engine (target share = pool × basis / Σbasis; the last positive-weight target absorbs the rounding remainder in exact minor-4 units so Σdebits = pool EXACTLY). The cycle is validated UP FRONT at save (bad method/frequency → BAD_METHOD/BAD_FREQUENCY; non-positive pool → BAD_AMOUNT; no targets → NO_TARGETS; zero total basis → NO_BASIS), so a broken cycle can never be persisted and then post an unbalanced/zero JE. The scheduled job gl_allocation_run posts every due cycle as ONE balanced DRAFT JE (Cr the source pool / Dr each target its share) through the normal maker-checker flow (GL-05) — a different user must approve before it affects balances — riding the same recurring rail as GL-08, and rolls next_run_date forward. Idempotent per period: next_run_date advanced on posting + the (tenant,source,source_ref,ledger) idempotency key (source_ref = ALC-<id>-<date>) dedupes a same-day re-run. Cycles can be paused/resumed without losing history.","Prev","Automated","Per due date / per cycle","Controller","P10",
    "ledger-allocation.service.ts (createCycle balanced-at-save validation, runDueAllocations→postEntry pendingApproval balanced split, setCycleActive); ledger.service.ts (AllocationCycleDto + delegators); ledger.controller.ts (gl_post/exec creates/runs, POST/GET /api/ledger/allocation[/:id/active][/run]); bi.service.ts (gl_allocation_run scheduled job); schema/ledger.ts (allocation_cycles, allocation_targets) + migration 0301; cutover/basics.ts (ToE)","Inspect the up-front validation, the exact proportional split (remainder to last target → balanced JE), the scheduled posting as Draft, and the per-period idempotency.","Zero-basis cycle → NO_BASIS; a ratio cycle (pool 10,000 split 3:1) posts a Draft JE excluded from the TB into the pending queue; a same-day re-run posts nothing; a second user approves → 5710 +7,500 / 5720 +2,500 / 5000 −10,000 (balanced); a driver cycle splits a pool by headcount 2:1 → 600/300 (re-performed by the basics.ts harness).","Allocation-cycle definitions; scheduled run log; JE approvals","Implemented")
add("GL-24","General Ledger","Application","All","A tenant posting-rule override re-routes where a recurring system posting (payroll, depreciation, lease runs — and every flow docs/43 wires next) lands in the financial statements, but rule changes were ungoverned: no validation (a typo'd/non-postable account, an unknown role, a sub-ledger control account could be targeted), no second person, no audit trail — a single user could silently repoint expense or liability legs.","Authorization/Accuracy/Completeness",
    "Posting-rule change governance (docs/43 PR-1): every rule write is validated FAIL-CLOSED against the in-code posting-event REGISTRY (posting-events.ts — 74 events, each role carrying its side, REAL default account and override TIER): unknown event/role → UNKNOWN_POSTING_EVENT/UNKNOWN_POSTING_ROLE, wrong side → POSTING_SIDE_MISMATCH, a 'pinned'/'widen' role (sub-ledger controls incl. the five permanently-pinned REC-04 accounts, equity plugs, the cash set; recon-gated Tier B until PR-7 widens the recon) → OVERRIDE_ROLE_PINNED, a non-existent/non-postable account → INVALID_POSTING_ACCOUNT. A valid write lands status=PendingApproval and takes effect ONLY when a DIFFERENT user approves (self-approve → SOD_VIOLATION, binds even Admin); re-editing an approved rule demotes it back to PendingApproval. The resolver (LedgerService.postingOverrides + the per-tenant 5s TtlCache, bust-on-approve) consumes ONLY active+Approved rules, so an unapproved rule can never touch a posting. Every CREATE/APPROVE/REJECT/DEACTIVATE writes an append-only posting_rule_audit row (tenant-scoped, canonical RLS). The registry's role defaults are boot-asserted to exist in the canonical CoA (assertPostingEventDefaults), and the posting_event_types catalogue is seeded FROM the registry (migration 0331) so code and catalogue cannot drift.","Prev","Automated","Event-driven / per rule change","Financial Controller","P10",
    "ledger/posting-events.ts (registry: 74 events / 121 roles, tier free|widen|pinned, assertPostingEventDefaults boot assert from seedChartOfAccounts); ledger/posting.service.ts (validateRule fail-closed, upsertRule→PendingApproval, approveRule SoD + cache bust, rejectRule, deactivateRule, posting_rule_audit rows, resolveRules/preview consume Approved only); ledger/posting-overrides-cache.ts (per-tenant TtlCache, bust-on-write); ledger.service.ts postingOverrides/postingOverridesMany (active+Approved only); posting-rules.controller.ts (Zod body, :id/approve|reject|deactivate, GET registry/audit, gl_posting_rules duty); schema/posting-rules.ts + migration 0331 (status/created_by/approved_by/approved_at, posting_rule_audit + tenant-leading index + canonical RLS); /setup/posting-rules UI (pending badge + approve/reject)","Inspect the registry tiers, the fail-closed validation set, the PendingApproval→distinct-approver flow, the Approved-only resolver + cache bust, and the audit trail.","Re-perform (compliance GL-24 ToE + payroll harness): create a rule for a pinned role → OVERRIDE_ROLE_PINNED; unknown role → UNKNOWN_POSTING_ROLE; bad account → INVALID_POSTING_ACCOUNT; a valid rule lands PendingApproval and a payroll run IGNORES it (posts the default); creator self-approve → 403 SOD_VIOLATION; a different user approves → the next run posts to the override account; audit trail carries CREATE+APPROVE rows.","posting_rule_audit trail; compliance + payroll harness ToE","Implemented")
add("GL-25","General Ledger","Detective","All","Material period-over-period movements in the financial statements are relied upon without a documented management analysis — a large or anomalous swing in a revenue/expense (or balance-sheet) account is neither explained nor independently reviewed, so an error or manipulation that first surfaces as an unexpected fluctuation goes undetected before the books are relied upon / the period is locked.","Completeness/Accuracy/Presentation",
    "Flux / variance analysis with FORCED explanation + independent sign-off (CLS-01): a preparer GENERATES a period movement analysis from the gl_period_balances snapshot (POST /api/close/flux/generate — basis P&L period-activity or Balance-Sheet cumulative-through-period; comparative prior_period / prior_year / vs approved-budget). Each account line carries the current amount, the comparative amount, Δ$ and Δ%, and is flagged BREACHED when |Δ$| ≥ a configurable absolute threshold AND |Δ%| ≥ a configurable percent threshold (both must trip, so a trivial % on a large base or a large % on a trivial base is not noise). A threshold-breaching line REQUIRES a written explanation (PUT …/lines/:lineId/explain) before the analysis can advance from Draft to Explained; review/sign-off (POST …/review) is REFUSED while any breached line is unexplained (UNEXPLAINED_LINES). Sign-off is maker-checker: the reviewer MUST differ from the preparer (SOD_SELF_APPROVAL), and certification locks the analysis (ALREADY_CERTIFIED). Read-only aggregator — posts NOTHING to the GL, adds no posting authority (no new SoD conflict). Surfaced as the advisory 'flux_review' step on the close checklist (GL-15) and as the schedulable flux_analysis BI report.","Det","Automated","Per period-close","Financial Controller","P10",
    "flux/flux.service.ts (generate — signed amounts per account from gl_period_balances, prior_period/prior_year/budget comparatives, abs+pct breach flags; explain forced-explanation + Draft→Explained; review UNEXPLAINED_LINES + SOD_SELF_APPROVAL maker-checker → Certified); flux/flux.controller.ts (POST close/flux/generate, GET close/flux[/:id], PUT :id/lines/:lineId/explain, POST :id/review — gl_close/fin_report/exec); schema/flux.ts (flux_analyses + flux_lines, tenant-leading index) + migration 0348 (canonical RLS); ledger/close.service.ts (advisory flux_review checklist step); bi/report-registry.ts + bi-generate.service.ts (flux_analysis report type); apps/web /close/flux; cutover/flux-analysis.ts (ToE)","Inspect the abs+pct breach logic, the forced-explanation gate before sign-off, the maker-checker reviewer≠preparer rule, and that the analysis posts nothing to the GL.","Re-perform (flux-analysis harness): generate a P&L flux flags the lines breaching abs/pct thresholds and leaves the below-threshold line unflagged; review while a breached line is unexplained → UNEXPLAINED_LINES; the preparer's self-review → SOD_SELF_APPROVAL; after every breached line is explained a DISTINCT reviewer certifies; prior_year/budget comparatives resolve correctly; RLS isolates tenants.","flux_analyses / flux_lines with per-line explanations + reviewer sign-off; flux-analysis harness ToE","Implemented")
add("GL-26","General Ledger","Detective","All","Financial statements / the reporting package are issued without a governed disclosure checklist: required TFRS/IFRS + SEC disclosure notes (related parties, revenue disaggregation, leases, income tax, commitments & contingencies, segments, subsequent events, management disclosure-controls sign-off) may be omitted or incomplete, supporting evidence is not pinned to the note, and one person can compile AND release the package with no independent review — a SEC disclosure-controls failure and an incomplete/inaccurate reporting basis.","Completeness/Accuracy/Presentation/Disclosure",
    "Governed disclosure / close-package checklist (close binder): POST /api/close/disclosure opens a per-period checklist that AUTO-SEEDS the standard TFRS/IFRS + SEC disclosure items — each carries a standard reference (TAS 1/7/12/24, TFRS 8/15/16, TAS 10/37, SEC disclosure controls), an owner and an Open/Complete/NA status with an optional support-doc reference pinned to doc_attachments (docType DISC via assertDocExists). PUT /api/close/disclosure/:id/items/:itemId completes/NAs each item (recording completed_by/at) and attaches its evidence. Review is a MAKER-CHECKER sign-off gate: POST /api/close/disclosure/:id/review is BLOCKED while any item is still Open (ITEMS_INCOMPLETE, listing the open items) and REJECTS a reviewer equal to the preparer (SOD_SELF_APPROVAL) — moving the binder Draft → Reviewed — and only a Reviewed binder can be Issued (POST …/issue → Issued; NOT_REVIEWED otherwise) so the financials are released only after an independent review. An advisory disclosure_review step cross-links the binder into the GL-15/16 close run. Detective/monitoring; tenant-scoped (canonical RLS); posts NOTHING to the GL.","Det","Automated","Per period-close / reporting package","Financial Controller / CFO","P10",
    "disclosure.service.ts (open seeds STANDARD_ITEMS, updateItem complete/NA + support_doc_ref, review ITEMS_INCOMPLETE + SOD_SELF_APPROVAL maker-checker gate Draft→Reviewed, issue Reviewed→Issued NOT_REVIEWED); disclosure.controller.ts (api/close/disclosure open/list/get/item/review/issue, gl_close mutate + gl_close/gl_post/fin_report/exec read); schema/disclosure-checklists.ts (disclosure_checklists + disclosure_items, tenant-leading index + canonical 0232-form RLS); migration 0347 (tables + RLS + app_user grants); procurement/attachments.service.ts (assertDocExists DISC → disclosure_checklists); common/doc-number.service.ts (DISC daily doc number); ledger/close.service.ts (advisory disclosure_review step); app.module.ts (DisclosureModule wired); cutover/disclosure-checklist.ts (ToE)","Inspect the seeded standard-item set with standard refs/owners, the item complete/NA + support-doc attach, the ITEMS_INCOMPLETE review gate, the SOD_SELF_APPROVAL maker-checker (reviewer ≠ preparer), the Reviewed→Issued release, and the tenant RLS isolation.","TC-CLS-02-01: open seeds ≥10 standard disclosure items (Draft, DISC checklist_no); TC-CLS-02-02: review while an item is Open → ITEMS_INCOMPLETE (400); TC-CLS-02-03: self-review by the preparer → SOD_SELF_APPROVAL (403); TC-CLS-02-04: complete/NA all + a DISTINCT reviewer reviews → Reviewed, then issue → Issued; TC-CLS-02-05: attach DISC support evidence to the checklist_no (assertDocExists), a bogus checklist_no → NOT_FOUND; TC-CLS-02-06: another tenant sees 0 checklists (RLS) (re-performed by the disclosure-checklist harness).","disclosure_checklists / disclosure_items with prepared_by/reviewed_by/issued_by sign-off trail + per-item completed_by/support_doc_ref; harness ToE (disclosure-checklist)","Implemented")
add("GL-27","General Ledger","Application","All","The canonical Chart of Accounts is SHARED by every tenant and the posting engine hard-references its codes, but canonical account changes (create / rename / postability flip / cash-flow-bucket reroute / deactivate) were a single-person action with NO record: GL-11 restricts WHO may change it (platform Admin/HQ + gl_coa) yet nothing records WHAT changed, WHEN, or BY WHOM, and no second person reviews a change that re-routes every tenant's financial statements (the audit gap symmetric to the one GL-24 closed for posting rules).","Authorization/Accuracy/Completeness",
    "Canonical CoA maker-checker (COA follow-up C): every canonical account write on /api/ledger/accounts (POST create, PATCH :code update, POST :code/deactivate — all still Admin/HQ-gated per GL-11) is validated FAIL-CLOSED at request time (DUPLICATE_ACCOUNT / ACCOUNT_NOT_FOUND / ACCOUNT_HAS_BALANCE / CODE_HAS_POSTINGS; one pending request per code — CHANGE_ALREADY_PENDING) and staged as a coa_change_requests row (payload + before-snapshot, created_by); the change applies ONLY when a DIFFERENT Admin approves (POST /api/ledger/accounts/change-requests/:id/approve — creator self-approval → 403 SOD_VIOLATION, binds even Admin; re-validated at approve), or is rejected with a recorded reason. SINGLE-ADMIN EXCEPTION (owner decision 2026-07-12): when the system has exactly one ACTIVE Admin a maker-checker would deadlock, so the change applies immediately and the request row records status AutoApplied with the exception reason — the audit trail survives even where the second pair of eyes cannot. The /chart-of-accounts screen carries the pending queue (approve/reject) and stages its create/edit/deactivate dialogs through the same flow. Bulk imports keep their own standing maker-checker (masterdata staged batches, PR-8).","Prev","Automated","Each canonical CoA change","Platform Admin (HQ) x2 / CFO","P10",
    "ledger/coa.service.ts (activeAdminCount, validateChange fail-closed, requestChange stage-or-AutoApply, approveChange SOD_VIOLATION + re-validate, rejectChange, listChanges); ledger/coa.controller.ts (writes route through requestChange; GET change-requests + :id/approve|reject, assertPlatformAdmin defence-in-depth); schema/posting-rules.ts coaChangeRequests + migration 0362 (PLATFORM table — created_tenant_id, app_user grants, status index); /chart-of-accounts pending-queue card + staged-write toasts; apps/api/test coa maker-checker unit (single-admin exception)","Inspect the fail-closed request-time validation, the PendingApproval→distinct-Admin flow, the AutoApplied single-admin exception rows, and the append-only request trail (payload + before snapshot).","Re-perform (compliance GL-27 ToE): Admin stages a create → PendingApproval, account does NOT exist yet; creator self-approve → 403 SOD_VIOLATION; a DIFFERENT Admin approves → account exists; duplicate create for the same code → DUPLICATE_ACCOUNT (or CHANGE_ALREADY_PENDING while staged); reject leaves the chart untouched; unit ToE: with exactly ONE active Admin the write applies immediately and the row reads AutoApplied.","coa_change_requests rows (payload/before/created_by/approved_by/reason); compliance harness + unit ToE","Implemented")
add("GL-28","General Ledger","Detective","All","The GL's preventive gates (GL-05 maker-checker, GL-17 immutability, GL-11/GL-27 CoA governance) stop unauthorised single-person postings, but a colluding or fat-fingered pattern that PASSES the gates — the same journal posted twice, suspiciously round manual amounts, an accounting date backdated far behind its capture time, posting/approval activity at 3 a.m., or a manual entry pairing cash directly with revenue (bypassing AR) — is never systematically looked for: management-override and error patterns accumulate unreviewed in the journal.","Occurrence/Accuracy/Fraud (management override)",
    "Rule-based JE anomaly & control-exception analytics (docs/50 Wave 5 B5): LedgerJeAnomalyService scans Posted journal_entries/journal_lines/gl_audit_log over a rolling window (default 90 days) with five deterministic rules — duplicate_je (same date + total + account set, HIGH), round_amount (Manual ≥ ฿10,000 whole-฿1,000), backdated (accounting date > 7 days before capture), after_hours (POST/APPROVE outside 06:00–22:00 Asia/Bangkok), unusual_pair (Manual cash 10xx ↔ revenue 4xxx, HIGH) — writing an IDEMPOTENT exception register (je_exceptions, one row per tenant × rule × entry; migration 0424, canonical RLS) so a re-scan never re-raises reviewed items. The periodic review is the control: each exception is DISMISSED only with a mandatory reason (DISMISS_REASON_REQUIRED), stamped who/when, and every dismissal appends a gl_audit_log EXCEPTION_DISMISSED row — the review evidence. Surfaced as a Close-Cockpit pillar (RAG: red = any HIGH open) and a schedulable BI sweep (je_exceptions report type). Near-threshold-approval detection is consciously N/A: GL-05 maker-checker applies to every manual JE with no amount threshold to skirt.","Det","Automated","Rolling scan (scheduled sweep + close review)","Financial Controller","P10",
    "ledger/ledger-je-anomaly.service.ts (scan/list/dismiss/cockpitSummary); ledger/ledger-je-anomaly.controller.ts (/api/ledger/je-exceptions, scan gl_close/approvals/exec, dismiss gl_close/exec); schema/gl-audit.ts jeExceptions + migration 0424 (coalesce unique per tenant×rule×entry, canonical RLS); ledger-bi-reports.ts je_exceptions generator + report-registry entry; finance-metrics.service.ts closeStatus je_exceptions pillar; close-cockpit-client.tsx tile (scan + dismiss-with-reason); cutover/basics.ts (ToE)","Inspect the five rules, the idempotent register keying, the mandatory-reason dismissal, and the EXCEPTION_DISMISSED audit rows.","Re-perform (basics ToE): seed one anomaly per rule → scan flags all five (duplicates name their peer, after-hours carries the Bangkok hour); re-scan new=0; dismiss without a reason → 400; dismiss with a reason → dismissed + gl_audit_log EXCEPTION_DISMISSED; re-dismiss → ALREADY_DISMISSED; cockpit pillar red on HIGH open; the je_exceptions BI sweep runs idempotently.","je_exceptions register (open/dismissed + reasons); gl_audit_log EXCEPTION_DISMISSED trail; cockpit pillar; sweep run log","Implemented")
add("GL-29","General Ledger","Application","All (financial-statement issuance)","The formatted statutory financial-statement pack (BS + P&L + SOCE + notes + TFRS-15 disaggregation) can be exported and circulated by one person with no independent review, and nothing binds the issued figures to a point-in-time approval — a preparer could release statements that were never signed off, or the underlying GL could move AFTER a review with the issued PDF still reading as approved, so an incomplete or altered reporting basis is relied upon.","Authorization/Accuracy/Presentation/Segregation of Duties",
    "Financial-statement issuance review & approval (FIN-4 GL-29 maker-checker; complements the GL-26 disclosure-checklist binder by governing the STATEMENT ARTIFACT + its figures). A preparer SUBMITS a fiscal year's statements for review (POST /api/reports/fs/statement-pack/submit) — the service snapshots the as-issued key figures (total assets / liabilities / equity / revenue / net income, computed from balanceSheet + incomeStatement over the year) together with a SHA-256 hash, and stages a PendingApproval review (fs_statement_reviews). A DIFFERENT user approves it (POST …/statement-reviews/:id/approve); the preparer self-approving → 403 SOD_VIOLATION (assertMakerChecker, binds even Admin), and re-approving an approved review → FS_REVIEW_NOT_PENDING. The formatted FS pack (GET …/statement-pack.pdf) then reads the latest Approved review for the period/ledger and STAMPS the cover 'Reviewed & approved by X on DATE (prepared by Y)' instead of 'Unaudited — management accounts'; if the live GL figures no longer match the approved hash the stamp flips to 'figures changed since approval — re-review required' (tamper-evident). The pending review surfaces in the GOV-01 pending-approvals center (fs_statement_review queue provider). Detective/preventive; tenant-scoped (canonical 0232 RLS + tenant-leading index, migration 0449); posts NOTHING to the GL.","Prev/Det","Automated","Per statement issuance / period","Financial Controller / CFO","P10",
    "reports/statutory-fs-reviews.service.ts (submit snapshots figures+SHA-256 hash → PendingApproval; approve assertMakerChecker SOD_VIOLATION + FS_REVIEW_NOT_PENDING; latestApproved live tamper check figures_changed; list); reports/statutory-fs.controller.ts (statement-pack/submit, statement-reviews/:id/approve, statement-reviews — fin_report/exec); reports/reports-pdf.service.ts financialStatementPackHtml reviewStamp (approved / re-review / unaudited); statutory-fs.controller statementPackPdf attaches latestApproved for a full-fiscal-year pack; reports/statutory-fs-review-queue.ts (GOV-01 fs_statement_review ApprovalQueueSource, control GL-29); schema/fs-reports.ts fsStatementReviews + migration 0449 (canonical 0232 RLS + app_user grants + tenant-leading index); cutover/compliance.ts (ToE)","Inspect the submit→snapshot+hash, the distinct-approver requirement, the approved-review→PDF-stamp read, the live tamper check (figures_changed), and the tenant RLS isolation.","Re-perform (compliance ToE): submit a fiscal year → PendingApproval (figures snapshotted); the preparer self-approving → 403 SOD_VIOLATION; a DIFFERENT user approves → Approved; the FS pack PDF stamps 'reviewed & approved by' (not 'unaudited'); post a further JE into the year → the pack flips to 're-review required' (hash mismatch); the pending review appears in GOV-01; another tenant sees 0 reviews (RLS).","fs_statement_reviews register (prepared_by/approved_by sign-off + figures snapshot/hash); FS pack issuance stamp; GOV-01 queue; compliance harness ToE","Implemented")
add("EXP-07","Expenditure","Application","Cash; Operating expense","Petty-cash / employee advance issued but never accounted for — cash leakage, expense unrecorded.","Existence/Completeness",
    "Employee cash advances: issuing an advance debits the 1180 Employee Advances control (Dr 1180 / Cr 1000); settlement clears it against actual spend + returned cash (Dr expense + Dr 1000 / Cr 1180), enforced to reconcile (settled_expense + returned_cash must equal the advance → SETTLE_MISMATCH). The 1180 balance is the outstanding float subject to review.","Det","Automated","Per advance","AP / Controller","P10",
    "finance.service.ts (issueAdvance, settleAdvance reconcile-or-reject, listAdvances outstanding); finance.controller.ts (creditors/exec); schema/finance.ts (employee_advances) + migration 0120; cutover/basics.ts (ToE)","Inspect issue/settle GL + settlement reconciliation guard.","Issue an advance (1180 up); settle 700+300 clears 1180; mismatched settle → SETTLE_MISMATCH (re-performed by the harness).","Advance register; outstanding float","Implemented")
add("EXP-08","Expenditure","Application","Cash; Operating expense","Petty-cash disbursed beyond authority / without independent review, or drawn past the fund's limit — cash leakage, unauthorised or unrecorded expense, over-extended float.","Authorization; Completeness",
    "Petty-cash imprest float + maker-checker on disbursement (SoD): a fund holds cash capped at a credit limit/วงเงิน (1015 Petty Cash, a cash account); each direct EXPENSE or ADVANCE is a REQUEST that posts NOTHING and a DIFFERENT user must approve before the GL posts (expense Dr <expense> / Cr 1015; advance Dr 1180 / Cr 1015) and the fund balance is decremented. Self-approval → SOD_VIOLATION (binds even Admin). A draw beyond the fund balance → INSUFFICIENT_FLOAT; establishing/replenishing above the float limit → OVER_FLOAT. Advances settle (Dr expense + Dr 1015 returned / Cr 1180), returning unused cash to the fund. Every request carries a document reference + receipt key + a status trail (StatusLog) and surfaces in the GOV-01 pending-approvals monitor.","Prev","Automated","Per disbursement","AP / Controller","P10",
    "petty-cash.service.ts (establishFund/replenishFund float guards, createRequest INSUFFICIENT_FLOAT, approveRequest SoD+GL, rejectRequest, settleRequest); petty-cash.controller.ts (creditors/exec); schema/petty-cash.ts (petty_cash_funds, expense_requests) + migration 0139; finance.service.ts pendingApprovals (GOV-01 source 7); cutover/basics.ts + compliance.ts (ToE)","Inspect the float ceiling + the request→approve flow + the approver≠requester check + that the request posts nothing until approval.","Re-perform: establish a fund (Dr 1015), request an expense (no GL), self-approve → SOD_VIOLATION, approve as a different user → Dr expense/Cr 1015 + fund down; over-balance draw → INSUFFICIENT_FLOAT; advance approve→settle clears 1180; replenish past float → OVER_FLOAT (re-performed by the harnesses).","Fund register + disbursement approval log + SoD test","Implemented")
add("EXP-09","Expenditure","Application","Accounts Payable; Cash","A PO-based supplier invoice is paid before it is reconciled to its PO and goods receipt — disbursing cash for goods not received, at the wrong quantity, or above the agreed price (over-payment / duplicate / fictitious-receipt fraud), because the AP-pay flow never consults the 3-way match.","Occurrence/Accuracy/Authorization",
    "3-way-match PAYMENT GATE: the AP disbursement flow (requestApPayment) calls ThreeWayMatchService.assertPayable BEFORE recording the payment request — a PO-based invoice that was run through match() and did NOT pass (qty/price variance beyond tolerance, over-invoiced, or unmatched line) and was NOT independently overridden is BLOCKED (MATCH_BLOCKED) so no cash can be requested or approved against it. The gate FAILS-OPEN for a non-PO bill (utilities / services / reimbursements never have a match row) so legitimate non-PO payables remain payable; it only blocks invoices subject to the match. Complements EXP-01 (the match + the maker-checked override) by wiring the verdict into the cash path and EXP-06 (the AP disbursement maker-checker).","Prev","Automated","Per payment","AP / Controller","P10",
    "finance.service.ts (requestApPayment → matchSvc.assertPayable); match/three-way-match.service.ts (assertPayable fail-open for non-PO, blocks not-payable & not-overridden); finance.controller.ts (ap/transactions/:txnNo/pay); cutover/match.ts (ToE)","Inspect that the AP-pay request consults assertPayable and that a non-PO bill is exempt while a failed PO invoice is blocked.","Re-perform: a PO invoice with a qty/price variance over tolerance → pay request MATCH_BLOCKED; an independently-overridden / matched invoice → pay succeeds; a non-PO bill pays unblocked (re-performed by the match harness).","Blocked-invoice worklist; payment-gate test","Implemented")
add("EXP-10","Expenditure","Application","Accounts Payable","A scanned/keyed vendor invoice is booked against the wrong PO (or twice under the same invoice number), or an intake bill bypasses the 3-way match — a mis-mapped or duplicate document becomes a payable and cash is disbursed for it.","Occurrence/Validity/Accuracy",
    "AP invoice INTAKE pipeline: a scanned invoice — pasted text or a DIRECT IMAGE/PDF UPLOAD (type/size-gated; a digital PDF extracts deterministically from its text layer, a photo/scan via AI vision when keyed, and with no key it queues for human review with empty fields so a blank bill can never book; the source document is stored on the intake for audit) — is extracted (doc-ai), AUTO-MAPPED to its PO (explicit PO number in the document, else vendor + amount scoring) and, on posting, the 3-way match is run in the SAME flow so an intake bill can never exist unmatched — LINE-LEVEL when every vision-extracted invoice line maps unambiguously onto the PO's own lines (identity by item-id-as-token or normalized description, ALL-or-nothing; per-line qty/price tolerance verdicts then apply, so a unit-price variance hidden inside a passing header amount still blocks), else header-level as before — the mapper can only TIGHTEN the verdict, never loosen it. The extracted document currency books onto the AP bill (amount in document units, GL legs converted at the latest APPROVED fx rate) so a foreign-currency scan feeds the EXP-06 multi-currency statement. The mapper only auto-maps an UNAMBIGUOUS winner — weak scores or tied candidates queue as NeedsReview for a human; a duplicate vendor invoice number (vs earlier intakes AND booked AP bills) is refused at post (DUPLICATE_INVOICE) and never auto-posted. Header-level matches enforce a CUMULATIVE guard (all invoices matched to a PO consume its received value, so one PO cannot be double-billed under two invoice numbers). A blocked intake invoice is released only by the scheduled auto re-match (ap_automatch_rerun) after the GR catches up, or by the EXP-01 maker-checked override. Booking (post/auto) requires the creditors duty; payment stays behind EXP-09's gate + EXP-06's maker-checker — the pipeline automates the path TO payment-ready, never the disbursement.","Prev","Automated","Per invoice","AP / Procurement","P17",
    "ap-intake/ap-intake.service.ts (mapToPo, findDuplicate, post→match line-escalated); ap-intake/ap-intake.match-lines.ts (all-or-nothing vision-line mapper); ap-intake/ap-intake.controller.ts (post/auto gated creditors); doc-ai/doc-ai.service.ts (extraction incl. po_no); match/three-way-match.service.ts (header amount match + cumulative guard + rematchBlocked); bi.service.ts (ap_automatch_rerun); schema 0229 ap_invoice_intakes; cutover/match.ts (ToE)","Inspect the mapper's ambiguity/duplicate handling and that posting always runs the match for a PO-mapped intake.","Re-perform: PO-numbered scan auto-posts matched+payable; tied candidates → NeedsReview; duplicate invoice no → 409 DUPLICATE_INVOICE; 2nd invoice on a fully-invoiced PO → over_invoiced blocked; invoice ahead of GR blocked then released by the scheduled re-match (re-performed by the match harness); a mapped vision line with a 12% unit-price variance inside a passing header amount → price_variance blocked (line-level); an unmappable line falls back to the header match; a USD scan books currency=USD at the approved rate and the vendor statement converts it.","Intake worklist; duplicate/cumulative guard tests","Implemented")
add("EXP-11","Expenditure","Application","Accounts Payable; Vendor Master","A vendor's payee bank details (bank_name/bank_account) are changed by a single user with no independent review — the classic Business-Email-Compromise / vendor-payment-fraud vector (an attacker who compromises or colludes with one md_vendor holder silently redirects the next disbursement to their own account).","Authorization",
    "Vendor bank-detail maker-checker: a bank_name/bank_account change is STAGED (PendingApproval, carrying the previous values) by an md_vendor holder and applied to the vendors master only when a DIFFERENT exec/approvals user releases it (self-approval → 403 SOD_VIOLATION, binds even Admin). Re-staging supersedes any still-open request so the approval queue always reflects only the latest ask; reject leaves the vendor untouched.","Prev","Auto+Manual","Per change","Procurement / Controller","P10",
    "procurement.service.ts (stageBankChange/pendingBankChanges/approveBankChange/rejectBankChange); procurement.controller.ts (vendors/:id/bank md_vendor stages; vendor-bank-changes/:reqNo/approve|reject exec/approvals); schema/vendor-bank-change.ts (vendor_bank_change_requests) + migration 0270; cutover/match.ts (ToE)","Inspect the stage→approve routing + the approver≠requester guard + that vendors only changes on approval.","Re-perform: stage a bank change (PendingApproval), self-approval blocked (403 SOD_VIOLATION), a different exec/approvals user approves and vendors.bank_name/bank_account updates; re-staging supersedes the earlier pending request; reject leaves the vendor unchanged (re-performed by the match harness).","Vendor bank-change approval log","Implemented")
add("MDM-01","Expenditure","Application","Vendor Master; Accounts Payable; Cash","Maker-checker on master data covered only BULK imports (masterdata_import_batches) and a vendor's bank_name/bank_account (EXP-11, 0270). A NORMAL single-record UI/CRUD edit of a SENSITIVE vendor field — its payee account-holder NAME (bank_account_name), its CREDIT LIMIT, or its PAYMENT TERMS — was written to the master directly with no second check, so a single md_vendor holder could redirect a disbursement (substitute the payee name on file), inflate credit exposure, or alter the payment schedule with no independent review — a disbursement-fraud / BEC vector alongside the bank-account number already governed by EXP-11.","Authorization/Segregation of Duties",
    "Sensitive master-data single-record maker-checker (GRC-3, migration 0340): a change to a sensitive vendor field (bank_account / bank_name / bank_account_name / credit_limit / payment_terms) does NOT write the vendor master — it is STAGED as a `pending` masterdata_change_requests row (a GENERIC entity_type vendor|customer|item + field + before/after value; old_value/new_value encrypted at rest via the encryptedText column type so a staged bank value is never plaintext). The master is applied ONLY when a DISTINCT user approves it (POST /api/masterdata/change-requests/:reqNo/approve; approved_by ≠ requested_by → 403 SOD_SELF_APPROVAL, binds even Admin), which supersedes the direct-edit path (payment_terms was removed from the vendor-profile direct edit; credit_limit / bank details were already excluded). Reject discards it (the master is untouched). Non-sensitive profile fields keep their direct-edit path (the generic endpoint refuses them → FIELD_NOT_SENSITIVE). The applied change is captured before/after by the DB trigger trg_dcl_vendors (0274) on the master row; the change-request row is the full staging trail (who requested / who released). New SoD rule R22 (master-data maintenance md_vendor/md_item/md_config vs the elevated change-approval authority exec). Tenant-scoped (RLS, canonical 0232 policy); reads/stage gate masterdata/md_vendor/exec, approve/reject gate masterdata/exec.","Prev","Automated","Per change","MasterDataAdmin / Controller (segregated)","P10",
    "modules/masterdata/masterdata-change.service.ts (stageChange NO-write + supersede; approve applies to the master with SOD_SELF_APPROVAL; reject discards; FIELD_NOT_SENSITIVE / NO_CHANGE guards); masterdata-change.controller.ts (/api/masterdata/change-requests[|/:reqNo/approve|/:reqNo/reject]); schema/masterdata-change.ts masterdata_change_requests + vendors.bank_account_name (migration 0336); procurement.service.ts/.controller.ts (payment_terms removed from the vendor-profile direct edit); permissions.ts SoD R22; apps/web /masterdata/change-requests (reviewer queue + propose form); cutover/masterdata-change.ts (ToE).","Inspect the stage→approve routing, the requester≠approver self-approval block, that the vendor master is written ONLY on approval, that reject/pending leave it unchanged, and that a non-sensitive field is refused by the maker-checker (still edits directly).","Re-perform (masterdata-change harness): stage a vendor bank_account_name change → pending, master unchanged; self-approve → 403 SOD_SELF_APPROVAL; a DISTINCT approver → master updated; an encrypted bank_account round-trips; stage credit_limit → reject → master unchanged; payment_terms applies ONLY via the maker-checker; a non-sensitive field (category) still edits directly and the generic endpoint refuses it (FIELD_NOT_SENSITIVE); a second tenant sees 0 requests and cannot approve one (RLS).","Master-data change-request queue (pending/approved/rejected) + before/after; SOD_SELF_APPROVAL / FIELD_NOT_SENSITIVE negatives","Implemented")
add("EXP-12","Expenditure","Application","Inventory; Accounts Payable","Goods 'received' without a physical count (blind confirmation), more stock booked than was ordered (over-receipt → inflated inventory + AP exposure), a short/damaged delivery discovered too late to claim against the supplier, or a short-shipped PO left open indefinitely (stale open commitments).","Existence/Accuracy/Completeness",
    "Blind-count goods receiving with an over-receipt tolerance gate, a time-boxed supplier-claim window, and an explicit shortage decision. (1) The /receiving screen loads the selected PO's lines (ordered / already received / outstanding via GET pos/:poNo/receive-lines) but NEVER pre-fills the counted quantity — the receiver must count and key what actually arrived. (2) createGr BLOCKS any line that would exceed the ordered quantity (422 OVER_RECEIPT), checked on the aggregate requested per item; only a WEIGHT-basis UoM (kg/g/ton) may run over, and only within the configurable receiving tolerance (receiving_settings.over_receipt_weight_pct, default 5%). Changing the tolerance is restricted to procurement/exec — the receiver cannot loosen their own gate (mirrors EXP-04). (3) The post-receipt summary shows ordered vs received per line; a supplier claim (photo evidence stored as a GRC doc_attachment) must be opened within receiving_settings.claim_window_hours of goods_receipts.created_at (default 24h) — after that the window auto-closes and the system refuses the claim (422 CLAIM_WINDOW_CLOSED). (4) On a shortage the receiver decides: keep the PO open for a later delivery, or CLOSE IT SHORT (POST pos/:poNo/close-short) — the close releases open project commitments and is binding at line level (po_items.status=Closed → any further receipt is refused, 422 PO_LINE_CLOSED).","Prev","Automated","Per receipt","Warehouse / Procurement","P17",
    "procurement/procurement-grn.service.ts (receiveLines, createGr OVER_RECEIPT/PO_LINE_CLOSED gates, closePoShort, getReceivingSettings); procurement.controller.ts (receive-lines/close-short/receiving-settings routes); claims/claims.service.ts (createGrClaim CLAIM_WINDOW_CLOSED + GRC photo attachment); schema receiving_settings + goods_receipts.created_at (migration 0290); apps/web /receiving (blind-count form + summary + claim + close-short); cutover/compliance.ts (ToE)","Inspect the over-receipt gate (aggregate per item, weight-UoM tolerance), the claim-window check against the GR timestamp, the close-short line binding, and the tolerance-change permission.","Re-perform: receive 12 on a 10-EA line → 422 OVER_RECEIPT; a kg line accepts up to +5% and refuses beyond; a claim inside the window opens with its photo, the same claim after the window → 422 CLAIM_WINDOW_CLOSED; close-short flips the PO+lines Closed, and a further receipt → 422 PO_LINE_CLOSED (re-performed by the compliance harness).","GR summary (ordered vs received); OVER_RECEIPT / CLAIM_WINDOW_CLOSED / PO_LINE_CLOSED negatives; claim photo attachment","Implemented")
add("QC-04","Expenditure","Application","Inventory; Vendor performance / supplier quality","Supplier defects are captured (gr_claims) and supplier performance is scored (supplier_scorecards), but no FORMAL corrective-action request (8D/SCAR) is issued to the vendor and tracked to closure: a recurring supplier defect is never escalated into a documented root-cause / corrective-action commitment, an issued SCAR is closed on an unverified (or fabricated) 8D response, the SAME person both raises and closes the SCAR (self-sign-off requalifying a defective supplier), or an open corrective action drifts past its due date unactioned — so defective suppliers keep shipping and the quality escape recurs with no evidence of an independent closure review.","Accuracy/Authorization/Segregation of Duties",
    "Supplier Corrective Action Request (SCAR / 8D) register with a closure maker-checker + an overdue detective read (QMS-4, migration 0334). A SCAR is RAISED against a vendor, optionally sourced from a REAL gr_claim (a fabricated claim reference is rejected — CLAIM_NOT_FOUND / CLAIM_VENDOR_MISMATCH), carrying the 8D discipline fields (containment / root_cause / corrective_action / preventive_action). Lifecycle open → supplier_responded → pending_closure → closed | rejected. QC-04 closure gate: a SCAR is CLOSED only (1) after the supplier has responded AND the 8D root_cause + corrective_action are populated (SCAR_INCOMPLETE otherwise) and (2) by a DIFFERENT user than the raiser (closed_by ≠ raised_by → 403 SOD_SELF_APPROVAL, binds even Admin; the closure-reviewer duty quality_approve is segregated from the raise duty quality — SoD R21), recording an effectiveness verdict (effective | ineffective). Closing an 'effective' SCAR is the gate that permits a suppressed supplier to be requalified — the verdict is RECORDED here; the scorecard math (procurement.service.ts recomputeScorecard) is never touched. Reject (≠ raiser, reason required) returns the SCAR for re-work. DETECTIVE: GET /api/quality/scar/open?days=N is the overdue supplier-corrective-action worklist (open SCARs past their due_date). Tenant-scoped (RLS, canonical 0232 policy); reads gate quality/quality_approve/creditors/exec, raise quality/creditors, closure quality_approve/exec.","Prev/Det","Automated","Per SCAR / continuous","Quality Manager / Supplier-Quality Reviewer (segregated)","P17",
    "quality/scar.service.ts (raise — real-gr_claim gate CLAIM_NOT_FOUND/CLAIM_VENDOR_MISMATCH; respond — 8D fields → supplier_responded; submitClosure SCAR_INCOMPLETE → pending_closure; close — QC-04 SCAR_INCOMPLETE + SOD_SELF_APPROVAL + effectiveness verdict; reject REASON_REQUIRED/SOD_SELF_APPROVAL; openWorklist overdue detective); quality/scar.controller.ts (/api/quality/scar[|/open|/:id|/:id/respond|/submit-closure|/close|/reject]); schema/supplier-scar.ts supplier_scars (migration 0334); permissions.ts quality/quality_approve + SoD R21; cutover/supplier-scar.ts (ToE). Builds on gr_claims/vendors; does NOT recompute supplier_scorecards.","Inspect the raise-from-real-claim gate, the 8D-completeness closure precondition, the raiser≠closer self-approval block, the recorded effectiveness verdict (requalification gate), and the overdue detective worklist.","Re-perform (supplier-scar harness): raise a SCAR from a real gr_claim (a non-existent claim ref → CLAIM_NOT_FOUND); close before the supplier response/8D → SCAR_INCOMPLETE; the supplier responds populating root_cause + corrective_action → supplier_responded → submit-closure → pending_closure; the raiser self-closing → SOD_SELF_APPROVAL; a DISTINCT reviewer closes effective → closed + requalifies_supplier; an open past-due SCAR surfaces on GET …/open and a closed one does not; reject with no reason → REASON_REQUIRED, a distinct reviewer rejects → rejected; a second tenant sees 0 HQ SCARs and cannot close one (RLS).","SCAR register (open/responded/pending/closed/rejected) + 8D fields; closure maker-checker log (closed_by/effectiveness); overdue SCAR worklist","Implemented")
add("EXP-13","Expenditure","Application","Accounts Payable; Cash","A batch vendor-payment run selects and disburses many bills at once: a single user could select, approve and release the whole batch (mass disbursement with no independent review), an unmatched/blocked PO invoice could ride into the batch, the file handed to the bank could differ from the approved run (amounts/beneficiaries altered after approval), or a re-run could double-pay every line.","Authorization/Accuracy","AP payment-run maker-checker with a hash-pinned bank file: (1) a 'creditors' holder PROPOSES the run (open approved AP selected by due-date cutoff; EVERY line must pass the 3-way-match payment gate assertPayable — a blocked PO invoice is skipped at proposal and re-checked at approval, MATCH_BLOCKED); lines are editable only while Draft. (2) A DIFFERENT user with the same authority as a manual AP payment approval (approvals/gl_close) APPROVES the run — proposer self-approval → 403 SOD_VIOLATION, binds even Admin. (3) EXECUTION (also blocked for the proposer) posts each line through the EXISTING per-payment path (requestApPayment→approveApPayment: row-locked paid_amount, identical Dr 2000 / Cr 2361 WHT / Cr 1000 GL, WHT on the pre-VAT base) and is IDEMPOTENT per line (run-scoped idempotency key + Paid-line skip; a partial failure leaves per-line status and a re-execute retries only failed lines — a double-execute pays nothing twice). WHT certificates (50-ทวิ) issue via the existing idempotent batch cert job. (4) The Thai bank bulk-transfer file (generic/scb/kbank/bbl CSV or ISO 20022 pain.001) is generated only from an approved/executed run, FAILS CLOSED on a missing vendor bank account (VENDOR_BANK_MISSING — beneficiaries come from the maker-checked vendor master, EXP-11), and its SHA-256 is pinned on the run + status-logged so the file handed to the bank is provably the approved run's file. (5) Bank-statement auto-match clears run lines (per-payment or bulk-total), giving a detective completeness check that the approved outflow actually left the bank.","Prev","Auto+Manual","Per run","AP / Controller / Treasury","P18",
    "finance/ap-payment-run.service.ts (propose/editLines/submit/approve SOD/execute idempotent/bankFile sha256); finance.controller.ts (ap/payment-runs routes — creditors proposes, approvals|gl_close approves/executes); match/three-way-match.service.ts assertPayable (per-line gate); tax/tax-jobs.service.ts runWhtCertBatch (50-ทวิ); bank/bank.service.ts autoMatch (line + run-total clearing); schema/finance.ts ap_payment_runs/ap_payment_run_lines + migration 0296; cutover/compliance.ts (ToE)","Inspect the run lifecycle (Draft→PendingApproval→Approved→Executed), the proposer≠approver/executor guards, the per-line match gate, the per-line idempotency, the fail-closed bank-file generation + hash pinning, and the statement-clearing hook.","Re-perform: propose a run (blocked invoice skipped), self-approve → 403 SOD_VIOLATION, approve as a different user, execute posts each line through the manual path (TB balanced; 2361 credited per WHT line; bill Paid), re-execute is a no-op, bank file generated with its SHA-256 recorded + status-logged, missing vendor bank account → 400 VENDOR_BANK_MISSING, statement auto-match flips lines cleared (re-performed by the compliance harness).","Payment-run approval log; per-line APP/PAY-AP references; bank-file SHA-256 status-log entries; cleared-line progress","Implemented")
add("EXP-14","Expenditure","Application","Accounts Payable; Cash","Dynamic / early-payment (prompt-payment) discounting on the AP payment run: an unauthorised or manipulated discount schedule could be applied without independent review (a single user sets favourable terms and pays against them), a discount could be taken when the bill was NOT actually paid early (fabricated days-early → understated cash / overstated income), or the discount captured on a run could be mis-posted (cash reduced without recognising the income, or vice-versa) — mis-stating disbursements, purchase-discount income and the AP subledger.","Authorization/Accuracy/Occurrence","Early-payment discount policy CHANGE CONTROL + a controlled discount-taken posting on the FIN-2 AP payment run. (1) A sliding-scale discount schedule (ap_discount_terms — per-vendor or a global default; nominal rate, min-days-early threshold, full-discount-days window, prorate flag, income account) is MAKER-CHECKED: a 'creditors' holder creates it Draft; a DIFFERENT approvals/gl_close user ACTIVATES it (self-activation → 403 SOD_VIOLATION, binds even Admin), and activating one supersedes the prior Active policy for the same vendor scope so at most one Active policy governs a vendor. Only an Active policy is applied. (2) At PROPOSE/EDIT the run computes days_early = due_date − pay_date and the resolved sliding-scale rate (prorated up to the full rate at the window), capping the discount so cash-out (amount − WHT − discount) can never go negative; the projected savings are surfaced on the proposal (projected_discount) for the approver. A bill NOT paid early (days_early < min) earns nothing. (3) At EXECUTION each early line rides the UNCHANGED per-payment maker-checker path (identical Dr 2000 / Cr 2361 WHT / Cr 1000 posting settling the FULL payable) and then books an IDEMPOTENT discount adjustment (Dr 1000 restore the cash not paid / Cr 4600 Early-Payment Discount Income) keyed by a distinct source_ref (AP-DISC:<txn>:<payment>), so the net cash disbursed = amount − WHT − discount, the payable is fully cleared, the discount is recognised as income, and a re-execute never double-books it. Maker-checker on the run itself (proposer≠approver≠executor) is unchanged (EXP-13).","Prev","Auto+Manual","Per policy change / per run","AP / Controller / Treasury","P18",
    "finance/ap-payment-run.service.ts (resolveDiscountPolicy/computeDiscount, propose+editLines projected discount, execute AP-DISC adjustment JE idempotent, createDiscountTerm/approveDiscountTerm SOD/rejectDiscountTerm/deactivateDiscountTerm); finance.controller.ts (ap/discount-terms routes — creditors creates, approvals|gl_close activates); ledger.service.ts postEntry/alreadyPosted + COA 4600 (Early-Payment Discount Income); schema/finance.ts ap_discount_terms + ap_payment_run_lines discount cols + migration 0309; cutover/compliance.ts (ToE)","Inspect the policy maker-checker (creator≠activator, one Active policy per vendor scope), the days-early/sliding-scale computation + the cash-out cap, and the balanced Dr 1000 / Cr 4600 discount posting keyed for idempotency.","Re-perform: creditors drafts a 2/20 policy, self-activation → 403 SOD_VIOLATION, a different approver activates; a bill paid 30 days early projects a ฿20 (2%) discount and net ฿980; execute credits 4600 ฿20, fully pays the bill, sets run total_discount ฿20 and keeps the TB balanced; a vendor with NO active policy earns ฿0 (re-performed by the compliance harness).","Discount-policy approval log; per-run projected_discount + total_discount; AP-DISC discount-income journal entries","Implemented")
add("FA-07","Fixed Assets","Application","Property, Plant & Equipment; Equity","Carrying amount not adjusted for revaluation/impairment — asset over/understated.","Valuation",
    "Asset revaluation / impairment: an upward revaluation credits the revaluation surplus in equity (Dr 1500 / Cr 3200); a downward revaluation (impairment) debits impairment loss (Dr 5820 / Cr 1500). The gross 1500 moves by the delta so the register stays tied to the GL; a no-op revaluation is rejected (NO_CHANGE). Every event is logged for the audit trail.","Det","Automated","Per event","FaAccountant / Controller","P10",
    "assets.service.ts (revalue up→3200 / down→5820, listRevaluations; dispose recycles surplus 3200→3100); assets.controller.ts (exec/creditors); schema/assets.ts (asset_revaluations) + migration 0120; cutover/basics.ts (ToE)","Inspect revaluation/impairment routing + audit log + disposal recycling.","Upward revaluation credits 3200; impairment debits 5820; no-change → NO_CHANGE; both events logged; on disposal the revaluation surplus is recycled to retained earnings (Dr 3200 / Cr 3100), not through P&L (re-performed by the harness).","Revaluation log; disposal recycling JE","Implemented")
add("FA-08","Fixed Assets","Application","Property, Plant & Equipment; Equity","Carrying amount changed by fair-value revaluation/impairment without independent review — the preparer revalues the asset and posts to equity/P&L on their own (earnings/equity management).","Authorization",
    "Asset-revaluation maker-checker (SoD): a revalue/impairment request posts its GL entry as a DRAFT (excluded from balances) and records status 'PendingApproval' WITHOUT moving the carrying value; a DIFFERENT user must approve before the JE is effective and the register is re-valued (approver ≠ preparer enforced regardless of permissions, reusing the GL-05 ledger approval). Reject voids the draft; only one revaluation may be pending per asset; the disposal surplus recycle counts only approved revaluations.","Prev","Automated","Per event","FaAccountant / Controller","P10",
    "assets.service.ts revalue(pendingApproval Draft)/approveRevaluation/rejectRevaluation; assets.controller.ts (:assetNo/revalue/approve|reject); schema/assets.ts asset_revaluations.status + migration 0134; cutover/basics.ts + compliance.ts (ToE)","Inspect Draft→approve flow + the approver≠preparer check + deferred carrying-value update.","Re-perform: request a revaluation (Draft JE excluded from 3200), attempt self-approve (SOD_VIOLATION), approve as a different user; confirm the surplus/impairment + carrying value move only after approval (re-performed by the harnesses).","Revaluation approval log + SoD test","Implemented")
add("LSE-01","Leases","Application","Right-of-use assets; Lease liabilities","Lease not capitalised (IFRS 16 / TFRS 16) — ROU asset + lease liability omitted; interest/depreciation mis-stated.","Completeness/Accuracy/Valuation",
    "Lease accounting: at commencement a right-of-use asset and lease liability are recognised at the present value of the lease payments (Dr 1600 / Cr 2600). The scheduled job lease_periodic_run posts each period — interest unwinding on the liability (Dr 5900), the cash payment reducing the liability (Dr 2600 / Cr 1000), and straight-line ROU depreciation (Dr 5210 / Cr 1690) — the last period clearing the liability + ROU exactly. Idempotent per (lease, period).","Det","Automated","Per period / per lease","Controller","P10",
    "leases.service.ts (createLease PV recognition, runDueLeases interest+payment+depreciation, modifyLease remeasurement); leases.controller.ts (gl_post); bi.service.ts (lease_periodic_run); schema/leases.ts (leases, rou_nbv) + migration 0120/0121; cutover/basics.ts (ToE)","Inspect PV recognition + periodic interest/payment/depreciation + final-period clearing + modification remeasurement.","Commencement recognises ROU=liability=PV; periodic run posts interest+principal(=payment)+ROU depreciation; liability + ROU reduce; a modification remeasures the liability at the revised PV and adjusts the ROU by the same delta (Dr/Cr 1600↔2600), then depreciates over the remaining term (re-performed by the harness).","Lease register; periodic run log; modification remeasurement","Implemented")

add("LSE-02","Leases","Application","Net investment in lease; Interest income; Rental income","Lessor lease mis-classified or income mis-recognised (IFRS 16 / TFRS 16 lessor) — a finance lease left on the balance sheet as an asset (no net investment / interest income) or an operating lease derecognised in error; classification set without independent review.","Completeness/Accuracy/Valuation/Presentation",
    "Lessor-side lease accounting (FIN-10). Each lease is classified finance vs operating per the IFRS 16 lessor criteria (transfer of ownership / bargain purchase / lease term a major part of the asset's economic life ≥75% / PV of the payments ≥90% of fair value). Classification + commencement is MAKER-CHECKER: the lease is created 'pending' and a DIFFERENT user approves it (creator self-approval → 403 SOD_SELF_APPROVAL) before any GL posts. FINANCE lease: at approval the underlying asset is derecognised (Cr 1500) and a net investment in lease / lease receivable is booked at the PV of the payments (Dr 1610), selling profit/loss to 1510; the scheduled periodic run recognises interest income on the running receivable (Cr 4620) and collects the cash (Dr 1000), reducing the receivable by the principal — the last period clearing it exactly. OPERATING lease: the asset stays on the lessor's books, the run recognises straight-line rental income (Dr 1000 / Cr 4610) and continues depreciating the asset (Dr 5200 / Cr 1590). A detective net-investment reconciliation ties GL 1610 to the sum of the finance-lease receivable balances on the schedule.","Prev/Det","Automated","Per lease (classification/approval) / per period (income)","Controller","P10/P13",
    "lessor-leases.service.ts (classify, createLease pending, approveLease maker-checker + finance-lease commencement, runDueLeases interest/rental income + depreciation, reconcileReceivable); lessor-leases.controller.ts (gl_post/exec); schema/lessor-leases.ts (lessor_leases) + migration 0309; ledger-constants.ts (COA 1610/4620/4610 + CF_CLASSIFY 1610); cutover/basics.ts (ToE)","Inspect classification against the IFRS 16 lessor criteria, the maker-checker (creator ≠ approver) gate, finance-lease derecognition + net-investment recognition, periodic interest/rental income + depreciation, and the 1610 tie-out.","Classification boundary flips finance↔operating at the 75%/90% bright lines; creator self-approval → SOD_SELF_APPROVAL; a distinct approver books finance-lease commencement (Dr 1610 / Cr 1500); periodic run recognises interest income (finance) or straight-line rental income + continued depreciation (operating); GL 1610 ties to the receivable schedule (reconciled, difference 0) — re-performed by the harness.","Lessor lease register; classification approvals; periodic income log; net-investment reconciliation","Implemented")

# ---- Reconciliation ----
add("REC-01","Reconciliation","Application","All","Subledgers diverge from GL undetected.","Completeness/Accuracy",
    "Subledger-to-GL reconciliation per period: import GL, auto-match, certify (sign-off via 'approvals').","Det","Auto+Manual","Monthly","Controller","P16",
    "reconciliation.service.ts (importGlItems/autoMatch/certify)","Inspect recon + certify gate.","Sample periods: reconciled, unmatched cleared, certified.","Certified recon","Implemented")
add("REC-02","Reconciliation","Application","Cash","Bank balance not reconciled to GL.","Existence/Completeness",
    "Bank reconciliation against statements.","Det","Auto+Manual","Monthly","Controller","P16",
    "bank module; drizzle/0015_bank_reconciliation","Inspect bank-rec process.","Sample months reconciled & reviewed.","Bank rec","Implemented")
add("BANK-02","Cash & Treasury","Application","Cash; Operating expense; Interest income","A bank fee/interest adjustment is posted straight to the GL by one person during reconciliation — a cash outflow mis-booked as interest income, or a fictitious fee posted, with no independent review (single-person posting to the cash account).","Authorization/Accuracy",
    "Bank adjustment maker-checker (SoD): a fee/interest adjustment on a statement line is a REQUEST that posts a DRAFT JE (no balance/GL effect; the line stays unreconciled) until a DIFFERENT user with approval authority approves (POST /api/bank/lines/:id/adjustment/approve). Self-approval → SOD_VIOLATION (binds even Admin); approval flips the line to reconciled and the JE to Posted; reject voids the Draft and frees the line. The Draft JE (source BANKADJ) is also surfaced, aged, by the pending-approvals monitor (GOV-01).","Prev","Automated","Per adjustment","Controller","P10",
    "bank.service.ts requestAdjustment/approveAdjustment/rejectAdjustment/listPendingAdjustments (reuses ledger.approveEntry SoD); bank.controller.ts (lines/:id/adjustment requests; adjustment/approve|reject gated approvals/gl_close); cutover/bankrec.ts (ToE)","Inspect the request→approve flow + the approver≠requester check + that the Draft posts nothing until approval.","Re-perform: request a fee adjustment (line unreconciled, GL difference unchanged), attempt self-approve (SOD_VIOLATION), approve as a different user; confirm the difference closes to 0 only after approval (re-performed by the bankrec harness).","Bank adjustment queue + SoD test","Implemented")
add("REC-03","Reconciliation","Application","Consolidation","Intercompany balances eliminated without an independent reconciliation sign-off.","Accuracy",
    "Per-period intercompany reconciliation sign-off (maker-checker) GATES consolidation elimination: a preparer reconciles the group's IC balances (Due-From 1150 vs Due-To 2150) for the period and signs (Prepared); an independent approver (SoD, approver ≠ preparer) approves only when the balances eliminate (Due-From = Due-To). consolidation.runConsolidation() is hard-gated — it refuses to eliminate until the period's reconciliation is Approved (IC_RECON_NOT_APPROVED).","Det","Auto+Manual","Period","Group Controller","P16",
    "modules/ic-reconciliation/ic-recon.service.ts (prepare/approve, SoD + eliminates gate); consolidation.service.ts runConsolidation (IC_RECON_NOT_APPROVED gate); ic_recon_periods (0205, RLS); cutover/consolidation.ts (ToE)","Inspect the per-period IC reconciliation sign-off + the consolidation gate.","Re-perform: consolidation is blocked before sign-off (IC_RECON_NOT_APPROVED); the preparer cannot approve their own reconciliation (SOD_VIOLATION); an independent approver signs off (balances eliminate) → consolidation proceeds.","IC reconciliation sign-off + consolidation gate ToE","Implemented")
add("REC-04","Reconciliation","Application","All control accounts","A sub-ledger silently drifts from its GL control account at period-end and no single review catches it (incomplete/inaccurate balances reach the financial statements).","Completeness/Accuracy",
    "Period-end control-account reconciliation PACK: one read (GET /api/finance/reconciliation/controls) ties every major sub-ledger to its GL control account and FLAGS any out-of-balance — AR↔1100, AP↔2000, Inventory↔1200, Gift cards/Customer-deposits↔2200, Deferred revenue↔2400 — reporting per line {sub_ledger, gl_control, variance, reconciled} plus an overall all_reconciled flag and an exceptions count. Liability controls are sign-flipped before comparison. The controller's single 'are the books reconciled?' close view; an exception is a control finding to investigate before sign-off.","Det","Automated","Period / on demand","Controller / CFO","P16",
    "finance.service.ts reconcileControls; finance.controller.ts GET reconciliation/controls (exec/ar/creditors); reuses ledger.trialBalance + the AR/AP/inventory/gift-card/deferred sub-ledgers; cutover/giftcards.ts + compliance.ts (ToE)","Inspect the pack: each control account's sub-ledger query + the GL tie + the exceptions roll-up.","Re-perform: with a clean set, every line reconciled + all_reconciled=true; introduce a known sub-ledger/GL difference and confirm it surfaces as an exception (re-performed: gift-card 2200 + inventory 1200 ties asserted by the harnesses).","Reconciliation pack; exceptions list","Implemented")
add("REC-05","Reconciliation","Application","Cash; Bank","Till cash dropped to the safe never reaches the bank, or a deposit isn't matched to the statement — cash sits unbanked (theft/loss exposure) or the bank balance can't be tied to the books.","Completeness/Existence/Authorization",
    "Cash banking — safe-drop → bank deposit → reconciliation: till 'drop's move cash from the drawer to the safe (drawer-only, no GL). Banking BATCHES the undeposited drops into a deposit and posts the GL (Dr <bank account, e.g. 1010> / Cr 1000 Cash), stamping each drop with the deposit id; the deposit is then RECONCILED to the bank statement (status Deposited→Reconciled). A detective read (GET /api/bank/deposits/undeposited-drops) surfaces the CASH STILL IN THE SAFE (drops with deposit_id NULL) — the unbanked exposure to chase. SoD: banking is a treasury duty (exec/ar) — segregated from the cashier (pos_till) who drops the cash, so the person who removes cash from the drawer is not the one who banks it.","Det/Prev","Auto+Manual","Per banking run","FinancialController / Treasury","P16",
    "bank.service.ts undepositedDrops/createDeposit (Dr bank/Cr 1000, stamps deposit_id)/reconcileDeposit/listDeposits; bank.controller.ts (deposits, deposits/undeposited-drops, deposits/:id/reconcile; exec/ar); schema/cash.ts bank_deposits + cash_movements.deposit_id + migration 0152; /cash-banking UI; cutover/cash-banking.ts (ToE)","Inspect the undeposited-drop exposure read + the deposit GL (bank↔1000) + the reconcile step + the SoD (cashier vs treasury).","Re-perform: two till drops → cash-in-safe shows the total; a cashier (pos_till) cannot bank (403); treasury banks → Dr bank / Cr 1000, cash-in-safe back to 0; reconcile the deposit; trial balance balanced (re-performed by the cash-banking harness).","Bank-deposit register; undeposited-drop (cash-in-safe) exposure","Implemented")
add("TR-01","Cash & Treasury","Detective","Cash; Bank","The business runs into a liquidity squeeze because no one holds a forward view of cash — the current cash/bank position, the projected trough over the coming weeks, and the FX exposure sit on separate screens, so a shortfall (or an unhedged currency position) is noticed only when it bites.","Completeness/Accuracy",
    "Treasury / Cash Command — a single read-only liquidity board (GET /api/finance/metrics/cash/position, perm exec/fin_report/ar) that COMPOSES the cash view: the GL cash/bank position per account (ties to the trial balance) + the house-bank accounts, the 13-week direct cash forecast (open AR inflows − AP outflows by due date, reuses the GL-07 forecast) with the projected closing balance and the liquidity TROUGH (lowest projected balance + the week it hits), the liquidity KPI subset (current/quick/cash ratio, working capital, days-cash — same canonical definitions as ELC-07), and FX exposure by non-THB currency (open AR/AP face amounts, net position). Read-only aggregation over the posted GL + sub-ledgers — posts nothing, adds no posting authority (no SoD change). Surfaced on the /finance/treasury web screen so treasury reviews the forward cash position + FX on a cadence.","Det","Hybrid","Weekly / per treasury review","Treasurer / Controller","P16",
    "finance/finance-metrics.service.ts (cashPosition — cash/bank position from the trial balance, cashFlowForecast GL-07 13-week, liquidity KPI subset, fxExposure by currency); finance-metrics.controller.ts (GET /api/finance/metrics/cash/position); apps/web treasury (screen); cutover/finance-kpi.ts (ToE); docs/35-finance-oracle-grade-analytics-plan.md","Inspect the cash/bank position (ties to the trial balance), the 13-week forecast + projected trough, the liquidity KPIs, and the FX exposure by currency.","Re-perform (finance-kpi): on a seeded ledger total_cash ties to the GL cash account (100k), the 13-week forecast opens at 100k, layers the open-AR inflow (50k) and closes at 150k over 14 buckets, the liquidity subset carries cash_ratio 2.5, and a USD payable surfaces as an FX exposure (payable 1000, net −1000); a non-finance role is denied (403).","Cash-position / treasury board (finance/metrics/cash/position); harness ToE (finance-kpi)","Implemented")
add("TRE-01","Cash & Treasury","Application","Short-term Borrowings (2500); Long-term Borrowings (2550); Accrued Interest Payable (2450); Interest Expense (5900); Bank (1010)","A borrowing is recorded, drawn or accrued without control — a debt facility is set up and drawn down by one person with no independent authorisation (unauthorised leverage / cash booked to the drawer), the drawdown mis-posts principal (wrong short-/long-term borrowings control, or omitted), or the interest expense is mis-stated because the effective-interest (EIR) amortized-cost accrual is computed at the wrong rate, applied to the wrong carrying amount, or double-posted for a period — so borrowings, interest expense and the accrued-interest liability are misstated.","Accuracy/Valuation/Completeness/Authorization/Segregation of Duties",
    "Debt & Borrowings register with maker-checker + an idempotent EIR amortized-cost engine (Track C Wave 1). A facility is CREATED as PendingApproval (POST /api/treasury/facilities, maker duty `treasury`); a DIFFERENT user APPROVES it (POST .../:id/approve, checker duty `treasury_approve`) — a self-approve is rejected 403 SOD_SELF_APPROVAL (creator ≠ approver, binds even Admin, mirroring FX-04 / TAX-11). Only an APPROVED facility may be DRAWN (POST .../:id/drawdown), which checks the drawdown against the available limit (LIMIT_EXCEEDED) and posts Dr 1010 Bank / Cr 2500 (short-term) or 2550 (long-term) Borrowings via LedgerService.postEntry (so PERIOD_LOCKED + the GL audit trail apply). Each drawdown carries an amortized-cost carrying amount (= its outstanding principal at par) and a periodic-run cursor (next_run_date / periods_posted) mirroring the lease engine (LSE-01). The EIR accrual (POST .../:id/accrue, checker duty) posts ONE month of effective interest = carrying x EIR/12 (Dr 5900 Interest Expense / Cr 2450 Accrued Interest Payable) per due drawdown and advances the cursor; it is IDEMPOTENT (the cursor moves a month per run AND alreadyPosted('DEBT-ACCR', drawdown+period) guards the JE, so re-running the same as-of posts nothing). Repayment (POST .../:id/repay) clears principal (Dr 2500/2550) + accrued interest (Dr 2450) against cash (Cr 1010), guarded (REPAY_EXCEEDS_PRINCIPAL/INTEREST). A maturity ladder (GET .../maturity-ladder) buckets outstanding principal by time-to-maturity. Tenant-scoped (RLS) so the register never leaks across companies; reads gate treasury/treasury_approve/fin_report/exec, the maker/checker split is enforced by SoD R23.","Prev","Automated","Per drawdown / monthly accrual","Treasury / Financial Controller","P10",
    "treasury-debt/debt.service.ts (createFacility PendingApproval / approveFacility SOD_SELF_APPROVAL maker-checker / drawdown LIMIT_EXCEEDED + Dr 1010 / Cr 2500|2550 / accrue idempotent EIR Dr 5900 / Cr 2450 + alreadyPosted cursor / repay Dr 2500|2550 + 2450 / Cr 1010 / maturityLadder); debt.controller.ts (api/treasury/facilities[/:id/{approve,reject,drawdown,repay,accrue,covenants}], maturity-ladder, covenants[/test,/breaches]); schema/treasury-debt.ts (debt_facilities/debt_drawdowns/debt_covenants/debt_covenant_tests, tenant-leading indexes); migration 0353 (tables + RLS + DEBT.* posting-events + treasury role_enum); ledger-constants 2450/2500/2550 (COA + CF_CLASSIFY 2500/2550 financing, 2450 operating); posting-events.ts DEBT.DRAWDOWN/INTEREST/REPAY; permissions.ts treasury/treasury_approve + SoD R23 + TreasuryAnalyst/TreasuryManager; debt.module.ts (wired, imports LedgerModule); cutover/treasury-debt.ts (TRE-01 ToE, 36 checks)","Inspect the facility create→approve maker-checker (SOD_SELF_APPROVAL), the drawdown limit gate + Dr 1010 / Cr 2500|2550 posting, the EIR accrual (carrying x EIR/12 → Dr 5900 / Cr 2450) tie to a hand-computed amortization table, the accrual idempotency (cursor + alreadyPosted), and the repayment legs.","TC-TRE-01-01: create a facility, self-approve → SOD_SELF_APPROVAL (403), a distinct approver approves; a pre-approval drawdown → FACILITY_NOT_APPROVED; TC-TRE-01-02: draw 600,000 → Dr 1010 / Cr 2550 balanced, an over-limit drawdown → LIMIT_EXCEEDED; TC-TRE-01-03: accrue @ EIR 12% (1%/mo) → interest 6,000 Dr 5900 / Cr 2450, re-accrue same period posts 0 (idempotent), a second month totals 12,000; repay 100,000 principal + 12,000 interest → Dr 2550/Dr 2450/Cr 1010, over-repay → REPAY_EXCEEDS_PRINCIPAL; TC-TRE-01-04: a sibling tenant never sees the facilities (RLS) (re-performed by the treasury-debt harness, 36 checks).","Debt & borrowings register (facility Open→Approved, drawdown/repayment, EIR amortization schedule + cursor); the DEBT-DRAW/DEBT-ACCR/DEBT-REPAY JEs; the maturity ladder","Implemented")
add("TRE-02","Cash & Treasury","Detective","Borrowings; Debt covenants","A financial-covenant breach on a borrowing (a minimum DSCR / current ratio, a maximum leverage) goes unnoticed between reporting cycles — the covenant test is done ad-hoc on a spreadsheet with no persisted result, so a breach that could trigger an event-of-default / reclassification of long-term debt to current is not surfaced, owned or disclosed on time.","Completeness/Timeliness",
    "Covenant tracking + breach detection (TRE-02): each facility carries financial covenants (POST /api/treasury/facilities/:id/covenants — metric, operator gte/lte/gt/lt, threshold, cadence). A covenant test (POST /api/treasury/covenants/test) evaluates each supplied period reading against its threshold/operator, PERSISTS a debt_covenant_tests row with a breached flag (recording the breach IS the detective control), and returns the breaches; GET /api/treasury/covenants/breaches is the outstanding-breach worklist (the latest breached test per covenant) the controller reviews each cycle. Read-mostly monitor over the debt register; tenant-scoped (RLS) so breaches never cross companies. Gated treasury_approve/exec to run tests, treasury/fin_report to read.","Det","Automated","Per covenant cadence (monthly/quarterly)","Treasury / Financial Controller","P16",
    "treasury-debt/debt.service.ts (createCovenant / testCovenants passes()+persist breached / covenantBreaches worklist); debt.controller.ts (facilities/:id/covenants, covenants/test, covenants/breaches); schema/treasury-debt.ts debt_covenants + debt_covenant_tests (tenant-leading indexes); migration 0353; cutover/treasury-debt.ts (TRE-02 ToE)","Inspect the covenant definition (metric/operator/threshold), the pass/breach evaluation, the persisted debt_covenant_tests row with the breached flag, and the breach worklist.","TC-TRE-02-01: define a DSCR ≥ 1.25 covenant; a test at 1.40 passes (not breached); a test at 1.10 breaches and is persisted; the breach worklist surfaces the outstanding DSCR breach; a sibling tenant never sees it (RLS) (re-performed by the treasury-debt harness).","debt_covenants register + debt_covenant_tests (breached readings) + the covenant-breach worklist","Implemented")
add("TRE-03","Cash & Treasury","Application","Investments — Amortized Cost (1350); Investments — FVOCI (1360); Investments — FVTPL (1370); Allowance for Investment ECL (1355); FVOCI Reserve — OCI (3500); Investment Income (4700); Fair-value Gain/Loss FVTPL (5430); Investment Impairment (5440); Bank (1010)","A marketable security is classified, marked-to-market or impaired by one person with no approved prices or independent review — a holding is bought and self-approved (unauthorised investment / cash booked to the drawer), MIS-CLASSIFIED (a fair-value holding parked at amortized cost, or the reverse, so remeasurement is routed to the wrong place — P&L instead of OCI or vice versa), marked to market against an UN-APPROVED / fat-fingered price, or impaired at a manager's discretion — so investment assets, the OCI equity reserve and earnings are misstated.","Accuracy/Valuation/Completeness/Authorization/Segregation of Duties",
    "Investment & Securities register with classification + valuation maker-checker and the reusable OCI-reserve primitive (Track C Wave 2; Wave 3 hedge accounting reuses the OCI reserve). A security is CREATED as PendingApproval (POST /api/treasury/investments, maker duty `treasury`) carrying its classification AMORTIZED_COST | FVOCI | FVTPL; a DIFFERENT user APPROVES it (POST .../:id/approve, checker duty `treasury_approve`) — self-approve is rejected 403 SOD_SELF_APPROVAL (creator ≠ approver, binds even Admin, mirroring FX-04 / TRE-01) — and the buy posts Dr 1350 (amortized cost) | 1360 (FVOCI) | 1370 (FVTPL) / Cr 1010 Bank via LedgerService.postEntry (GL-05 balanced + period-lock). A maker-checker market-PRICE register (POST /api/treasury/prices → PendingApproval; POST .../prices/approve by a DIFFERENT user, SOD_SELF_APPROVAL; mirrors fx_rates / FX-04) drives mark-to-market: MTM (POST .../:id/revalue) values the holding at quantity x the LATEST APPROVED price — an UN-approved price is rejected NO_APPROVED_PRICE — and routes the fair-value delta by classification: FVOCI → the OCI equity RESERVE 3500 (the reusable OCI-reserve primitive), FVTPL → P&L 5430 fair-value gain/loss; an AMORTIZED_COST holding is measured at amortized cost, not marked (MTM_NOT_APPLICABLE). AMORTIZED_COST interest income accretes on the effective-interest carrying (POST .../:id/accrue → Dr 1350 / Cr 4700 Investment Income), reusing the Wave-1 EIR periodic cursor + alreadyPosted idempotency (a re-run of the same period posts nothing). ECL impairment (POST .../:id/impair) posts Dr 5440 Investment Impairment / Cr 1355 Allowance (contra-asset). Tenant-scoped (RLS) so the register never leaks across companies; reads gate treasury/treasury_approve/fin_report/exec, the maker/checker split is enforced by SoD R23.","Prev","Automated","Per trade / month-end valuation","Treasury / Financial Controller","P10",
    "treasury-invest/investment.service.ts (createInvestment PendingApproval / approveInvestment SOD_SELF_APPROVAL maker-checker + buy Dr 1350|1360|1370 / Cr 1010 / postPrice+approvePrice maker-checker price register (FX-04 shape) / revalue MTM from the latest APPROVED price → ociReserveLines 3500 (FVOCI) | plGainLossLines 5430 (FVTPL), MTM_NOT_APPLICABLE for amortized cost, NO_APPROVED_PRICE gate / accrue EIR interest Dr 1350 / Cr 4700 idempotent + alreadyPosted / impair ECL Dr 5440 / Cr 1355 / portfolio); investment.controller.ts (api/treasury/investments[/:id/{approve,reject,revalue,impair,accrue}], prices[/approve,/reject], portfolio); schema/treasury-invest.ts (investments/investment_prices/investment_valuations, tenant-leading indexes); migration 0354 (tables + RLS + INVEST.* posting-events); ledger-constants 1350/1355/1360/1370/3500/4700/5430/5440 (COA + CF_CLASSIFY 1350/1355/1360/1370 investing, 3500 financing); posting-events.ts INVEST.BUY/INCOME/MTM.PL/MTM.OCI/IMPAIR; permissions.ts treasury/treasury_approve + SoD R23; investment.module.ts (wired, imports LedgerModule); cutover/treasury-invest.ts (TRE-03 ToE, 40 checks)","Inspect the investment create→approve maker-checker (SOD_SELF_APPROVAL) + classification routing of the buy (1350/1360/1370), the price-register maker-checker (SOD_SELF_APPROVAL) + the MTM-only-from-Approved-price gate (NO_APPROVED_PRICE), the FVOCI-to-OCI-3500 vs FVTPL-to-P&L-5430 remeasurement split, MTM_NOT_APPLICABLE for amortized cost, the idempotent EIR interest accrual (Dr 1350 / Cr 4700), and the ECL impairment (Dr 5440 / Cr 1355).","TC-TRE-03-01: create an investment, self-approve → SOD_SELF_APPROVAL (403), a distinct approver approves → the buy posts to the class asset; a non-treasury role is denied. TC-TRE-03-02: buy AMORTIZED_COST/FVOCI/FVTPL → Dr 1350/1360/1370 / Cr 1010 balanced. TC-TRE-03-03: an unapproved price cannot drive MTM (NO_APPROVED_PRICE); a self-approved price → SOD_SELF_APPROVAL; a distinct approver approves; FVOCI MTM lands in OCI 3500 (not P&L) and FVTPL MTM lands in P&L 5430; AMORTIZED_COST MTM → MTM_NOT_APPLICABLE. TC-TRE-03-04: AMORTIZED_COST interest ties a hand-computed EIR schedule (1,000 then 1,010), re-run same period posts 0 (idempotent). TC-TRE-03-05: ECL impairment → Dr 5440 / Cr 1355; a sibling tenant never sees the register (RLS) (re-performed by the treasury-invest harness, 40 checks).","Investment & securities register (holding PendingApproval→Approved, classification, MTM/ECL valuation ledger); the INVEST-BUY/MTM/ACCR/DIV/ECL JEs; the maker-checker market-price register; the portfolio roll-up","Implemented")
add("TRE-04","Cash & Treasury","Application","Derivative Asset (1380); Derivative Liability (2460); Cash-Flow Hedge Reserve — OCI (3550); Hedge Ineffectiveness / FV-hedge P&L (5450); the hedged-item carrying account (e.g. Inventory 1200) and its reclassification revenue/P&L line (e.g. 4000)","Hedge accounting is applied without an approved designation/documentation or a passing effectiveness test → OCI/earnings misclassified and the IFRS 9 / TFRS 9 / ASC 815 hedge criteria are unmet (TFRS 9 is Thailand's verbatim adoption of IFRS 9, effective 2020 for PAEs; effectiveness is the principles-based assessment — economic relationship, credit risk not dominant, hedge ratio consistent with actuals — NOT the retired IAS 39 80–125% bright line). A derivative's fair-value change is deferred in the OCI hedge reserve (kept out of earnings) although the relationship was never designated/approved or its effectiveness test failed; the effective/ineffective split is mis-stated so too much (or too little) is parked in OCI vs P&L; a fair-value hedge basis-adjusts the hedged item with no effective hedge; or the deferred OCI is never recycled to earnings when the hedged cash flow occurs — so the OCI equity reserve, the hedged-item carrying amount and earnings are misstated.","Accuracy/Valuation/Presentation/Disclosure/Completeness/Authorization/Segregation of Duties",
    "Hedge accounting register with designation + effectiveness + valuation maker-checker (Track C Wave 3; IFRS 9 / TFRS 9 · ASC 815; reuses the Wave-2 OCI-reserve primitive at a new Cash-Flow Hedge Reserve 3550). A hedge RELATIONSHIP is DESIGNATED as PendingApproval (POST /api/treasury/hedges, maker duty `treasury`) carrying the hedged item, the hedging instrument (derivative), the hedge TYPE (CASH_FLOW | FAIR_VALUE), the hedge ratio and the formal documentation (required, BAD_DOCUMENTATION); a DIFFERENT user APPROVES it (POST .../:id/approve, checker duty `treasury_approve`) — self-approve is rejected 403 SOD_SELF_APPROVAL (creator ≠ approver, binds even Admin, mirroring FX-04 / TRE-03). THE CONTROL GATE: NO hedge/OCI accounting until the relationship is Approved (designation) AND its LATEST effectiveness test (POST .../:id/effectiveness — prospective/retrospective, method, offset ratio %, effective bool) is effective=true. Remeasuring the derivative (POST .../:id/measure) posts the fair-value change Dr 1380 Derivative Asset (gain) / Cr 2460 Derivative Liability (loss) and routes the offset: for a CASH_FLOW hedge the EFFECTIVE portion defers in the Cash-Flow Hedge Reserve 3550 (OCI equity) and the INEFFECTIVE portion hits P&L 5450 — but ONLY when Approved+effective; otherwise the OCI path is refused (HEDGE_NOT_EFFECTIVE) and the whole change is routed to P&L (to_pl). For a FAIR_VALUE hedge the derivative change hits P&L 5450 and the hedged item is BASIS-ADJUSTED (its carrying account) with an offsetting P&L leg (Approved+effective, else HEDGE_NOT_EFFECTIVE). Accounting on an undesignated/unapproved relationship is rejected HEDGE_NOT_DESIGNATED. When the hedged cash flow occurs the deferred OCI is RECLASSIFIED to earnings (POST .../:id/reclassify → Dr 3550 / Cr the hedged-item revenue/P&L line; OCI_INSUFFICIENT guards over-release). Rebalancing (POST .../:id/rebalance) adjusts the hedge ratio/notional of an approved relationship. Every posting routes through LedgerService.postEntry (GL-05 balanced + period-lock). Tenant-scoped (RLS) so the register never leaks across companies; reads gate treasury/treasury_approve/fin_report/exec, the maker/checker split is enforced by SoD R23.","Prev","Automated","Per designation / month-end remeasurement / on the hedged cash flow","Treasury / Financial Controller","P10",
    "treasury-hedge/hedge.service.ts (designate PendingApproval + BAD_DOCUMENTATION / approve SOD_SELF_APPROVAL maker-checker / recordEffectiveness (HEDGE_NOT_DESIGNATED before approval) / measure — the CONTROL GATE: HEDGE_NOT_DESIGNATED if unapproved, CASH_FLOW OCI refused HEDGE_NOT_EFFECTIVE unless Approved+effective else to_pl routes to P&L, effective portion → 3550 / ineffective → 5450, FAIR_VALUE basis-adjusts the hedged item + P&L 5450 / reclassify Dr 3550 / Cr revenue with OCI_INSUFFICIENT guard / rebalance); hedge.controller.ts (api/treasury/hedges[/:id/{approve,reject,effectiveness,measure,rebalance,reclassify}]); schema/treasury-hedge.ts (hedge_relationships/hedge_derivatives/hedge_effectiveness_tests/hedge_oci_movements, tenant-leading indexes); migration 0356 (tables + RLS + HEDGE.* posting-events); ledger-constants 1380/2460/3550/5450 (COA + CF_CLASSIFY 3550 financing, 1380/2460 operating); posting-events.ts HEDGE.DERIVATIVE.MTM/CF.OCI/RECLASSIFY/FV.BASIS; permissions.ts treasury/treasury_approve + SoD R23; hedge.module.ts (wired, imports LedgerModule); cutover/treasury-hedge.ts (TRE-04 ToE, 38 checks)","Inspect the designation create→approve maker-checker (SOD_SELF_APPROVAL), the two-part control gate (Approved designation AND a passing effectiveness test) before any OCI treatment, the CASH_FLOW effective→OCI-3550 / ineffective→P&L-5450 split vs the not-effective route-to-P&L (HEDGE_NOT_EFFECTIVE), the HEDGE_NOT_DESIGNATED bar on unapproved relationships, the FAIR_VALUE hedged-item basis adjustment, and the OCI→P&L reclassification (Dr 3550 / Cr revenue).","TC-TRE-04-01: designate a hedge, self-approve → SOD_SELF_APPROVAL (403), a distinct approver approves; measuring an unapproved relationship → HEDGE_NOT_DESIGNATED; a non-treasury role is denied. TC-TRE-04-02: with the latest effectiveness test effective=false the CASH_FLOW OCI attempt → HEDGE_NOT_EFFECTIVE and the whole change routes to P&L 5450 (nothing to OCI); with effective=true the effective portion lands in OCI 3550 and only the ineffective portion in P&L 5450. TC-TRE-04-03: reclassification recycles the deferred OCI to revenue (Dr 3550 / Cr 4000) on the hedged cash flow; over-release → OCI_INSUFFICIENT. TC-TRE-04-04: a FAIR_VALUE hedge basis-adjusts the hedged item (Cr 1200 / Dr 5450) with the derivative gain to P&L (net ineffectiveness); a sibling tenant never sees the register (RLS) (re-performed by the treasury-hedge harness, 38 checks).","Hedge accounting register (relationship PendingApproval→Approved designation, effectiveness tests, derivative FV, OCI movement ledger); the HEDGE-MTM / HEDGE-RECLASS JEs; the Cash-Flow Hedge Reserve 3550; the FV-hedge basis adjustment","Implemented")
add("TRE-05","Cash & Treasury","Application","Intercompany Loan Receivable (1155); Intercompany Loan Payable (2155); Investment/Interest Income (4700); Interest Expense (5900); Bank (1010); the pool header/member bank accounts (e.g. 1010/1020)","An intercompany loan, cash-pool sweep or pool interest is posted or allocated without approval, or is NOT eliminated on consolidation — so group balances and group finance cost/income are double-counted. An IC loan is registered and drawn down by one person with no independent authorisation (unauthorised intercompany lending / cash mis-booked), the mirrored drawdown or EIR interest mis-posts one side (a receivable without its payable, or interest booked to only one company), a notional pool 'allocates' interest that does NOT sum to zero (value created or destroyed out of thin air), or — the core risk — the IC-loan receivable/payable (1155/2155) and the IC interest (4700 creditor income / 5900 debtor expense) are NOT eliminated on consolidation, so the group balance sheet grosses up an intra-group loan and the group P&L double-counts finance income against finance cost.","Accuracy/Valuation/Completeness/Authorization/Segregation of Duties",
    "Cash pooling / in-house bank / intercompany-loan register with maker-checker + consolidation-elimination integrity (Track C Wave 4, FINAL; reuses the Wave-1 EIR periodic cursor + alreadyPosted idempotency and extends the consolidation IC-elimination loop). An IC LOAN is REGISTERED as PendingApproval (POST /api/treasury/ic-loans, maker duty `treasury`) carrying creditor/debtor tenants, principal and EIR; a DIFFERENT user APPROVES it (POST .../:id/approve, checker duty `treasury_approve`) — self-approve is rejected 403 SOD_SELF_APPROVAL (creator ≠ approver, binds even Admin, mirroring TRE-01/03/04) — and the mirrored drawdown posts Dr 1155 IC-Loan Receivable / Cr 1010 Bank (creditor) AND Dr 1010 Bank / Cr 2155 IC-Loan Payable (debtor) via LedgerService.postEntry (GL-05 balanced + period-lock). EIR interest (POST .../:id/accrue) accrues on the amortized-cost carrying → creditor Dr 1155 / Cr 4700 Investment/Interest Income and debtor Dr 5900 Interest Expense / Cr 2155, idempotently (cursor + alreadyPosted → a re-run of the same period posts nothing). A CASH POOL (POST /api/treasury/pools; notional | physical) models the in-house bank: a PHYSICAL pool SWEEPS cash member→header (POST .../:id/sweep → Dr header-bank / Cr member-bank), a NOTIONAL pool ALLOCATES the pooled interest across members (POST .../:id/allocate-interest) — an allocation that MUST sum to zero (ALLOCATION_NOT_ZERO otherwise; surplus members earn 4700 income, deficit members bear 5900 expense, group net P&L = 0). THE CONTROL CORE: consolidation.runConsolidation is extended so that for a loan whose BOTH legs are in the group the 1155/2155 receivable/payable pair AND the 4700/5900 IC interest ELIMINATE for the period (mirroring the trade-IC 1150/2150 pair), so the consolidated group balance sheet and group finance cost/income net to zero and CON-03's balanced-TB integrity holds. The IC-loan row's tenant_id = the creditor (RLS owner, mirroring ic_transactions); tenant-scoped (RLS + explicit tenant filter) so the register never leaks across companies; reads gate treasury/treasury_approve/fin_report/exec, the maker/checker split is enforced by SoD R23.","Prev","Automated","Per loan / month-end accrual / on consolidation","Treasury / Financial Controller","P10",
    "treasury-pool/pool.service.ts (registerLoan PendingApproval / approveLoan SOD_SELF_APPROVAL maker-checker + mirrored drawdown Dr 1155 / Cr 1010 (creditor) + Dr 1010 / Cr 2155 (debtor) / accrue EIR Dr 1155 / Cr 4700 (creditor) + Dr 5900 / Cr 2155 (debtor) idempotent + alreadyPosted / definePool / sweep Dr header / Cr member NOT_PHYSICAL_POOL gate / allocateInterest zero-sum ALLOCATION_NOT_ZERO gate NOT_NOTIONAL_POOL / poolPosition); pool.controller.ts (api/treasury/pools[/:id/{sweep,allocate-interest,position}], ic-loans[/:id/{approve,reject,accrue}]); consolidation/consolidation.service.ts runConsolidation Step 2b (IC-loan 1155/2155 + 4700/5900 elimination per period → ic_loan_eliminations); schema/treasury-pool.ts (cash_pools/cash_pool_members/ic_loans/ic_loan_accruals, tenant-leading indexes); migration 0357 (tables + RLS + ICLOAN.*/POOL.* posting-events); ledger-constants 1155/2155 (COA + CF_CLASSIFY 1155 investing / 2155 financing); posting-events.ts ICLOAN.DRAWDOWN/INTEREST + POOL.SWEEP/INTEREST; permissions.ts treasury/treasury_approve + SoD R23; pool.module.ts (wired, imports LedgerModule); cutover/treasury-pool.ts (TRE-05 ToE, 46 checks)","Inspect the IC-loan register→approve maker-checker (SOD_SELF_APPROVAL), the mirrored drawdown posting in BOTH tenants (1155 creditor / 2155 debtor), the idempotent EIR interest accrual (4700 creditor income / 5900 debtor expense), the notional zero-sum allocation gate (ALLOCATION_NOT_ZERO), the physical sweep (Dr header / Cr member), and — the control core — the consolidation elimination of the 1155/2155 pair AND the 4700/5900 IC interest (group nets to zero, CON-03 balanced).","TC-TRE-05-01: register an IC loan, self-approve → SOD_SELF_APPROVAL (403), a distinct approver approves → the mirrored drawdown posts Dr 1155 / Cr 1010 (creditor) + Dr 1010 / Cr 2155 (debtor); a non-treasury role is denied; accrue before approval → LOAN_NOT_APPROVED. TC-TRE-05-02: accrue @ EIR 12% on 120,000 → interest 1,200 Dr 1155 / Cr 4700 (creditor) + Dr 5900 / Cr 2155 (debtor); re-accrue same period posts 0 (idempotent). TC-TRE-05-03: a notional allocation that does not sum to zero → ALLOCATION_NOT_ZERO; a zero-sum allocation posts Cr 4700 / Dr 5900 (net group P&L 0); a physical sweep → Dr header 1010 / Cr member 1020; wrong-mode calls → NOT_PHYSICAL_POOL / NOT_NOTIONAL_POOL. TC-TRE-05-04: on consolidation the group 1155/2155 AND 4700/5900 ELIMINATE to 0 (balanced, ic_loan_eliminations=1); a sibling tenant never sees the register (RLS) (re-performed by the treasury-pool harness, 46 checks).","Cash-pool + in-house-bank register (pool header/members, physical sweep, notional zero-sum interest allocation); the intercompany-loan register (loan PendingApproval→Approved, mirrored drawdown, EIR interest accrual ledger); the ICLOAN-DRAW/ICLOAN-ACCR/POOL-SWEEP/POOL-ALLOC JEs; the consolidation IC-loan elimination lines (1155/2155 + 4700/5900)","Implemented")
add("GOV-01","Monitoring","Application","All","A maker-checker approval sits un-actioned and is forgotten — a transaction stalls before it is effective, or (worse) a control is quietly bypassed and no one notices an item never got its independent review.","Authorization/Completeness",
    "Pending-approvals MONITOR (COSO monitoring): a single worklist of EVERY item awaiting independent approval across the system, each with its AGE in days and an overdue roll-up — spanning the manual-JE (GL-05), bank-adjustment (BANK-02), AP-disbursement (EXP-06), payroll (PAY-03), asset-revaluation (FA-08), asset-disposal (FA-09), inventory-write-off (INV-07), till-close cash over/short (REV-13), FX-rate (FX-04), budget (BUD-01) and large-refund (REV-16) maker-checkers. The controller reviews it before close; a stale item (age beyond the threshold) is a control finding to chase or escalate. The /approvals screen also lets a manager approve/reject a material till variance or a large refund inline (the pending types with no dedicated module screen). Read-only worklist; tenant-scoped via the caller's RLS.","Det","Automated","Continuous / pre-close","Controller / CFO","P16",
    "finance.service.ts pendingApprovals; finance.controller.ts GET approvals/pending (exec/approvals/creditors); aggregates journalEntries(Draft incl. BANKADJ→BANK-02)/apPayments/payruns/asset_revaluations/fixed_assets(disposal_pending)/inv_writeoff_requests/till_sessions(PendingApproval)/fx_rates(PendingApproval)/budgets(PendingApproval); cutover/compliance.ts (ToE); COA-D1: + postingRules PendingApproval (GL-24), coaChangeRequests PendingApproval (GL-27, platform-global), masterdataImportBatches PendingApproval (MDM-03), masterdataChangeRequests pending (MDM-01) — with /approvals per-item + batch approve routing for all four","Inspect the aggregation across all pending sources + the age/overdue roll-up.","Re-perform: create a pending item (e.g. a Draft JE) and confirm it appears in the worklist with its control ID, amount and age; the overdue count flags items past the threshold (re-performed by the harness).","Pending-approvals worklist","Implemented")
add("GOV-02","Monitoring","Application","All","Control exceptions surfaced by continuous monitoring are noted but never owned or closed: an anomaly the scanner flags (duplicate invoice/payment, ghost/duplicate vendor, split PO under the approval ceiling, weekend manual JE, dormant-vendor reactivation) is reviewed ad-hoc with no accountable owner, no remediation due date, no documented root cause and no link to the RCM control it relates to, so a real red flag drifts unresolved and management has no key-control-indicator (KCI) view of exception volume, ageing or mean-time-to-remediate.","Monitoring/Completeness",
    "Managed continuous-monitoring program (GRC-4): the read-only scanner (POST /api/controls/scan) runs six tenant-scoped detectors — duplicate vendor invoice (EXP-10), possible duplicate payment (EXP-01), ghost/duplicate vendor via decrypted-tax-ID grouping (EXP-02), split PO under the approval threshold (EXP-02: ≥2 non-Draft POs to one vendor within a 7-day window each below the THB 50,000 ceiling but summing over it), weekend manual JE (GL-05: source=Manual with entry_date on Sat/Sun), and dormant-vendor reactivation (EXP-05: a >180-day gap between a vendor's AP transactions) — each upserting a control_findings row by a stable fingerprint (idempotent; an already-dispositioned finding is never reset) that carries the RCM control it relates to (rcm_ref). Every exception is then DISPOSITIONED (POST /api/controls/findings/:id/disposition): an accountable owner, a remediation due_date and a documented root_cause, with a lifecycle open → investigating → remediated | accepted | false_positive; a closing disposition stamps remediated_by/at so the exception is tracked to closure. GET /api/controls/kci rolls the population up into KEY-CONTROL-INDICATORS — open exceptions by detector/severity/RCM family, an overdue count (open past due_date) and the mean time-to-remediate — the management scorecard reviewed each monitoring cycle. Read-only vs the GL; reads + disposition gate exec/users/creditors; tenant-scoped via the caller's RLS (findings never cross tenants).","Det","Automated","Continuous / per monitoring cycle","Controller / Internal Audit","P16",
    "modules/controls/controls.service.ts (scan 6 detectors + disposition + kci); controls.controller.ts (POST scan, GET findings, POST findings/:id/{review,disposition}, GET kci); schema/controls.ts control_findings (rcm_ref/disposition/owner/due_date/root_cause/remediated_by/at) + migration 0339_control_exceptions; cutover/control-exceptions.ts (ToE)","Inspect the six detectors + fingerprint idempotency, the disposition lifecycle (owner/due/root-cause + closing stamp), the KCI roll-up (overdue + MTTR) and the RLS scoping.","Re-perform: seed data triggering each detector, scan surfaces the findings each with its rcm_ref; disposition a finding (owner/due/root-cause set, still open on the KCI) then remediate it (remediated_by/at stamped, dropped from the open KCI); the KCI returns open-by-detector/severity/family, an overdue count and MTTR; another tenant cannot see the findings (RLS) — re-performed by the control-exceptions harness.","Control-exception disposition register + KCI roll-up","Implemented")
add("ITGC-MON-01","Monitoring","ITGC","All","The control inventory (this RCM), each control's status, and its test-of-effectiveness (ToE) results live only in an offline spreadsheet + scattered CI harness scripts — an external auditor has NO in-product way to browse the control catalogue, see which ToE passed, or pull the underlying evidence, so management's ongoing self-monitoring of ICFR operating effectiveness is neither centralised nor reviewable in-system.","Completeness/Accuracy",
    "In-app CONTROL CONSOLE (auditor-facing): the full ~240-control RCM catalogue (all 17 RCM fields — risk, assertion, description, COSO principle, code reference, TOD/TOE, evidence, status) is surfaced read-only in the product from a build-time census artifact (compliance/rcm-catalog.json, regenerated alongside the RCM xlsx from build_rcm.py so it can never silently drift), grouped by control family with a live census summary. Against each control a tenant records a ToE test-run (pass/fail/na, harness name, checks passed/total, evidence reference, notes); the control-detail view then shows the latest + historical test-runs, any linked continuous-controls-monitoring (CCM) findings, and the recent tamper-evident audit-log evidence for that control. Reads + test-run recording are gated to the compliance/exec function and every test-run row is tenant-isolated by the canonical RLS policy (a tenant sees only its own ToE evidence). Read-heavy monitor; posts NOTHING to the GL.","Det","Automated","Continuous / on-demand","Controller / SOX PMO","P16",
    "modules/control-console/control-console.service.ts (loadCatalog reads compliance/rcm-catalog.json; rcm()/rcmDetail()/recordTestRun()); control-console.controller.ts GET /api/controls/rcm + GET /api/controls/rcm/:id + POST /api/controls/rcm/:id/test-run (exec/users); schema/control-console.ts (control_test_runs, tenant-scoped RLS + (tenant_id,…) index); drizzle/0336_control_console.sql; compliance/build_rcm.py --json -> compliance/rcm-catalog.json (catalogue source of truth); apps/web /controls/rcm (server-shell + rcm-client.tsx island); cutover/control-console.ts (ToE)","Inspect that the catalogue is generated from the same build_rcm.py source as the xlsx (no drift), that reads + test-run recording are permission-gated, and that control_test_runs carries a leading (tenant_id,…) index + the canonical tenant_isolation RLS policy.","Re-perform (control-console harness): the catalogue endpoint returns the full control inventory (>=240 controls) + the census summary; a control-detail read returns the 17 RCM fields + its test-run history; a ToE test-run is recorded against a control and read back with its result/harness/checks; and a second tenant cannot see the first tenant's recorded test-runs (RLS isolation).","Control catalogue + recorded ToE test-runs + linked CCM findings / audit evidence","Implemented")

