add("TAX-02","Tax","Application","Tax; Revenue","Non-compliant e-Tax invoice / not transmitted to ETDA, or a failed SP submission silently lost.","Accuracy/Compliance",
    "e-Tax invoice (ETDA UBL 2.1 XML) generation + email with CC to ETDA timestamp mailbox; pluggable SP adapter (configurable auth scheme + bounded retry); every SP submission attempt (accepted/rejected/error) is persisted (autocommit, survives the request rollback) and swept for retry; PDF/A-3-oriented archival embeds the XML in the human-readable PDF.","Auto","Automated","Per invoice","Tax","P10/P13",
    "tax-docs/etax-xml.ts; etax-email.service.ts; pos-fiscal/etax.service.ts + etax-providers.ts (submit/retryFailed, tested); tax-docs/pdfa3.ts","Inspect XML schema + email composer + submission log.","Sample invoices: valid XML, correct CC/escaping; induce a submission failure and confirm it is retryable, not lost.","e-Tax samples; submission log","Implemented")
add("TAX-03","Tax","Application","Tax (WHT)","Withholding tax mis-computed, not withheld at payment, or not tied to the GL.","Accuracy",
    "WHT withheld at AP payment time and posted to the GL, then tied out: when a vendor payment is approved (maker-checker), WHT is computed on the PRE-VAT base and posted Dr 2000 AP / Cr 2361 Vendor-WHT-Payable / Cr 1000 (vendor paid net), so the liability to the RD is on the books. A monthly ภ.ง.ด.3/53 → GL tie-out (pndTieOut) reconciles the GL 2361 movement to the WHT withheld on approved AP payments AND to the 50-ทวิ certificates issued — flagging out-of-process JEs (gl≠ap) and un-certificated withholdings. Payroll PND1 WHT stays a separate account (2360, PAY-02). Automation (docs/33 PR4): a schedulable, idempotent BI action job **tax_wht_cert_batch** auto-issues the 50-ทวิ certificate (มาตรา 50 ทวิ) for every AP-payment WHT in the period that does not yet have one — keyed on the payment_no so a re-run skips already-certificated payments — CLOSING the pndTieOut un-certificated-WHT gap without manual re-keying (labour/service withholding ค่าจ้างทำของ/ค่าบริการ). A payment whose vendor lacks a valid 13-digit tax ID is skipped (surfaced in the run count), not silently certificated wrong. WHT tax codes (docs/33 PR7): a payment request may carry a WHT `tax_code` that DEFAULTS the income type + rate (from the configured WHT code, ค่าจ้างทำของ/ค่าบริการ) when the operator omits them — an explicit rate/type still wins, and a non-WHT/inactive code is rejected (INVALID_WHT_TAX_CODE).","Auto","Automated","Per payment / monthly","Tax","P10",
    "finance.service.ts approveApPayment (WHT calc + GL 2361 post); tax/tax-jobs.service.ts runWhtCertBatch (auto-issue 50-ทวิ, idempotent per payment_no); bi.service.ts REPORT_TYPES tax_wht_cert_batch; tax/documents/wht.service.ts issue; tax-reports.service.ts pndTieOut (ภ.ง.ด.→GL tie-out); ap_payments wht_* (0204); ledger-constants 2361; cutover/taxdocs.ts (ToE)","Inspect the WHT-at-payment posting + the ภ.ง.ด.→GL tie-out + the scheduled auto-cert batch.","Re-perform: approve a vendor payment with a WHT rate → vendor paid net, GL 2361 credited the WHT; run the tie-out → GL 2361 ties to the AP-withheld total (tied_gl_ap); run tax_wht_cert_batch → a 50-ทวิ is issued for that payment (issued 1), a re-run skips it (issued 0, no duplicate).","WHT GL postings + ภ.ง.ด.→GL tie-out + scheduled 50-ทวิ auto-cert ToE","Implemented")
add("TAX-04","Tax","Application","Tax (VAT); Tax Payable (2100)","Output/input VAT on the filed ภ.พ.30 return does not agree to the GL — VAT liability mis-stated, a filing/penalty exposure, or a posting omission goes undetected before submission.","Completeness/Accuracy",
    "Periodic VAT-return ↔ GL reconciliation (ภ.พ.30): the monthly return (GET /api/tax-reports/pp30) is built from the sales/output-VAT and purchase/input-VAT sub-reports, computes net VAT = output − input, and RECONCILES it to the **GL account 2100 (Tax Payable) net movement** for the same period (Σ credit − Σ debit over Posted entries) — returning `reconciliation.tied` = true only when the two agree within rounding. A non-tie is a detective finding to investigate and clear BEFORE filing (the form also carries the ม.157 deadline = the 15th of the next month). Output VAT is posted to 2100 on every sale (Cr) and reversed on returns (Dr); input VAT is posted on AP bills (Dr) — so 2100's net is the period's VAT payable. Read-only report; exportable to a ภ.พ.30 PDF/HTML. VAT-account routing (docs/33 PR6): when a tenant routes VAT to its own output/input accounts via a tax_code, the reconciliation sums the WHOLE VAT-account set (2100 + the configured tax-code accounts), so the ภ.พ.30↔GL tie stays exact under routing (no tax codes ⇒ set is {2100} ⇒ unchanged).","Det","Automated","Monthly / pre-filing","Tax / FinancialController","P10/P16",
    "tax-reports.service.ts pp30 (outputVat/inputVat + 2100 net-movement tie); tax-reports.controller.ts (GET pp30, pp30/export, exec); tax-reports-pdf.ts; dine-in.service.ts/returns.service.ts/finance.service.ts post 2100 on sale/return/AP; /tax/reports UI; cutover/taxdocs.ts (ToE)","Inspect the pp30 build + the 2100 net-movement query + the tie flag + the filing deadline.","Re-perform: the pp30 return computes net VAT (output − input), the GL 2100 net movement reflects the posted input VAT, and the reconciliation block exposes the gl_account (2100), the report net VAT and a boolean tie verdict (tied iff the two agree within rounding); the ภ.พ.30 export renders (re-performed by the taxdocs harness).","ภ.พ.30 return + GL-2100 reconciliation tie","Implemented")
add("TAX-05","Tax","Application","Tax (VAT/WHT)","A return is computed but there is no evidence it was actually FILED — no record of the figures as filed, the submission date or the Revenue-Department reference — so a missed or late filing (penalty/surcharge exposure) is not detected, and a filed return can be silently recomputed/altered after submission.","Completeness/Accuracy/Cutoff",
    "Thai tax filing register + remittance calendar: a computed ภ.พ.30 (PP30) or ภ.ง.ด.3/53 (PND) return is SNAPSHOTTED into a thai_tax_filings record (one per tenant/type/period) carrying the figures as filed (output/input/net VAT, tax withheld) and a DRAFT→SUBMITTED→ACCEPTED lifecycle. Filing is idempotent per period; submitting REQUIRES a Revenue-Department submission reference (SUBMISSION_REF_REQUIRED) and stamps SUBMITTED + the timestamp; an already-filed (SUBMITTED/ACCEPTED) period is NOT silently overwritten when re-filed (returned as-is, already_filed=true). A remittance calendar (GET /api/tax-reports/remittance-calendar) lists every monthly obligation (ภ.พ.30 by the 15th, ภ.ง.ด. by the 7th of the following month) with its current status (NOT_FILED/DRAFT/SUBMITTED/ACCEPTED), so the controller sees what is due/filed/late before the deadline. Tenant-scoped (RLS); gated exec. Automation (docs/33 PR4): schedulable BI action jobs **tax_pp30_draft** / **tax_pnd_draft** register the period's return as a DRAFT filing (via fileReturn — idempotent, never overwriting a SUBMITTED/ACCEPTED period), and **tax_remittance_reminder** surfaces the period's amounts due + statutory deadlines (ภ.พ.30 15th, ภ.ง.ด. 7th) for a proactive nudge — a human still submits.","Det/Prev","Auto+Manual","Monthly / per filing","Tax / FinancialController","P10/P16",
    "tax-reports.service.ts fileReturn (snapshots pp30/pnd into a DRAFT, idempotent per period; no overwrite of a filed return) / submitFiling (SUBMISSION_REF_REQUIRED → SUBMITTED) / acceptFiling / listFilings / remittanceCalendar; tax-reports.controller.ts (POST filings[/:id/submit|accept], GET filings, remittance-calendar, exec); schema/tax-docs.ts thai_tax_filings + migration 0165; /tax/reports filings & calendar tab; cutover/taxdocs.ts (ToE)","Inspect the filing snapshot + the DRAFT→SUBMITTED→ACCEPTED lifecycle + the mandatory submission reference + the no-overwrite-of-a-filed-return rule + the deadline calendar.","Re-perform: file PP30 → DRAFT with the period figures; re-file refreshes the same DRAFT (idempotent); submit without a reference → 400; submit with a reference → SUBMITTED + timestamp; accept → ACCEPTED; re-filing an accepted period returns it (already_filed); the remittance calendar shows the period ACCEPTED with the 15th-of-next-month deadline (re-performed by the taxdocs harness).","thai_tax_filings register + remittance calendar","Implemented")

add("TAX-06","Tax","Application","Deferred Tax Asset (1700); Deferred Tax Liability (2700); Deferred Tax Expense (5950)","Book-vs-tax TEMPORARY differences (the AR allowance, accelerated depreciation, accruals) are not recognised as deferred tax, or the deferred-tax entry is computed and posted by one person with no review — income tax expense and the deferred tax asset/liability are mis-stated (TAS 12 / TFRS).","Accuracy/Valuation/Completeness/Authorization/Segregation of Duties",
    "Deferred tax (TAS 12, maker-checker, idempotent per (tenant, period)): POST /api/ledger/deferred-tax/run gathers temporary differences — the latest POSTED AR allowance (a DEDUCTIBLE temp diff → DTA = allowance × CIT) and accelerated depreciation (book NBV vs an assumed tax NBV; a TAXABLE temp diff → DTL = (bookNBV − taxNBV) × CIT) — computes net_deferred = DTA − DTL and the DELTA vs the prior posted run, staging an 'Open' deferred_tax_runs row (one per tenant/period; a Posted period → ALREADY_POSTED). CIT rate defaults to 0.20 (Thai). SIMPLIFICATION: no parallel tax-depreciation ledger exists, so tax depreciation is assumed FASTER than book by a documented factor (default 1.5×, capped at the depreciable base) — overridable per run; a deliberate approximation until a tax-dep ledger is modelled. POST /api/ledger/deferred-tax/:id/post is segregated (poster ≠ runner → SELF_POST) and posts the period DELTA via LedgerService.postEntry (delta>0 net asset up = deferred tax benefit → Dr 1700 / Cr 5950; delta<0 → Dr 5950 / Cr 1700), so PERIOD_LOCKED + the GL audit trail apply. Marks the run Posted.","Prev","Automated","Quarterly / year-end","Tax / Financial Controller","P10",
    "deferred-tax.service.ts (runDeferredTax gather temp diffs [AR allowance, accelerated dep] + delta-vs-prior + stage Open, idempotent ALREADY_POSTED; postDeferredTax SELF_POST maker-checker + 1700/5950 delta posting; list/get); deferred-tax.controller.ts (gl_close/gl_post run + :id/post, gl_close/gl_post/exec read); schema/deferred-tax-fx.ts (deferred_tax_runs, uq tenant/period); migration 0168 (tables + RLS); COA 1700/2700/5950 (seedChartOfAccounts); ledger.module.ts (wired); close.service.ts (deferred_tax close-checklist step); reuses ar_allowance (REV-18) + fixed_assets NBV; cutover/basics.ts (TAX-06 ToE)","Inspect the temp-difference gathering (allowance×rate DTA + accelerated-dep DTL with the documented tax-dep simplification), the delta-vs-prior-run, the SELF_POST maker-checker, and the 1700/5950 posting through the period-lock gate.","TC-TAX-06-01: run with a posted AR allowance of 1100 at 20% → DTA 220, net deferred asset 220, delta 220 (Open); TC-TAX-06-02: runner self-post → SELF_POST (403), a different user posts → Dr 1700 / Cr 5950 (220), re-post → ALREADY_POSTED (400) (re-performed by the basics.ts harness).","deferred_tax_runs register (Open→Posted, temp-difference schedule, runner/poster); the DEFTAX JE to 1700/5950; quarterly/year-end deferred-tax sign-off","Implemented")
add("TAX-12","Tax","Application","Deferred Tax Asset (1700); Deferred Tax Expense (5950)","Two mandatory ASC 740 income-tax disclosures are omitted or prepared by one person with no review: (a) the gross deferred tax asset is carried at full value with no more-likely-than-not (MLTN) recoverability assessment, so a DTA that will not be realised against future taxable income is overstated (no valuation allowance); (b) uncertain tax positions (transfer pricing, deductions at risk) are not registered with a recognised benefit / unrecognised reserve, so the tax provision and the FIN 48 disclosure are understated — and a single user could book/release a valuation allowance or close a position to flatter earnings.","Valuation/Accuracy/Completeness/Authorization/Segregation of Duties",
    "ASC 740 disclosures on top of the deferred-tax engine (TAX-06), maker-checker: (1) DTA valuation allowance — POST /api/tax/valuation-allowance/run resolves the GROSS DTA (explicit, else the latest deferred_tax_runs.dta for the tenant) and an MLTN-recoverable amount (management judgment) and computes allowance = max(0, dta_gross − mltn_recoverable) + the DELTA vs the prior posted allowance, staging an 'Open' dta_valuation_allowances row (one per tenant/period; a Posted period → ALREADY_POSTED). POST …/valuation-allowance/:id/post is segregated (poster ≠ runner → SELF_POST) and posts the DELTA via LedgerService.postEntry (allowance increase = a charge → Dr 5950 / Cr 1700; a release → Dr 1700 / Cr 5950), so PERIOD_LOCKED + the GL audit trail apply and the net DTA on the balance sheet is the recoverable portion. (2) Uncertain Tax Positions (FIN 48) — POST /api/tax/utp registers a position (tax year, gross exposure, recognized MLTN-sustainable benefit, reserve = gross − recognized, interest/penalty accrual; BENEFIT_EXCEEDS_EXPOSURE guard) as a MEMO register (no GL leg — the reserve is a disclosure). POST /api/tax/utp/:id/settle is segregated (settler ≠ creator → SELF_SETTLE; only an Open position → NOT_OPEN) and closes it Settled | Lapsed. Both surfaces are tenant-isolated (RLS).","Prev","Automated","Quarterly / year-end","Tax / Financial Controller","P10",
    "tax/tax-utp.service.ts (runValuationAllowance gross-DTA-from-TAX-06 + allowance=max(0,gross−MLTN) + delta-vs-prior + stage Open, idempotent ALREADY_POSTED; postValuationAllowance SELF_POST maker-checker + 5950/1700 delta posting; createUtp reserve=gross−recognized + BENEFIT_EXCEEDS_EXPOSURE; settleUtp SELF_SETTLE/NOT_OPEN maker-checker; list*); tax/tax-utp.controller.ts (valuation-allowance run + :id/post gl_close/gl_post, utp create + :id/settle gl_close/gl_post, reads gl_close/gl_post/exec); tax/tax-utp.module.ts (wired into TaxModule, imports LedgerModule); schema/tax-utp.ts (dta_valuation_allowances uq tenant/period, uncertain_tax_positions uq tenant/position_no) + migration 0351 (tables + leading tenant index + 0232-form RLS); reuses deferred_tax_runs (TAX-06) + COA 1700/5950 + DocNumberService (UTP-…); cutover/tax-utp.ts (TAX-12 ToE)","Inspect the allowance computation (gross DTA sourced from TAX-06, max(0, gross − MLTN)), the delta-vs-prior-run, the SELF_POST maker-checker and the 5950/1700 posting; and the UTP register's reserve = gross − recognized, the BENEFIT_EXCEEDS_EXPOSURE guard, and the SELF_SETTLE create→settle segregation.","TC-TAX-12-01: run a valuation allowance with gross DTA 1000 vs MLTN 600 → allowance 400, delta 400 (Open); TC-TAX-12-02: runner self-post → SELF_POST (403), a different user posts → Dr 5950 / Cr 1700 (400) + trial balance balanced, re-post → ALREADY_POSTED (400); TC-TAX-12-03: run without an explicit gross DTA sources it (500) from deferred_tax_runs; TC-TAX-12-04: register a UTP (gross 100000, recognized 60000 → reserve 40000, Open), recognized > gross → BENEFIT_EXCEEDS_EXPOSURE (400); TC-TAX-12-05: creator self-settle → SELF_SETTLE (403), a different user settles → Settled, re-settle → NOT_OPEN (400); TC-TAX-12-06: a second tenant's positions are not visible cross-tenant (RLS) (re-performed by the tax-utp harness).","dta_valuation_allowances register (Open→Posted, gross/MLTN/allowance, runner/poster); the DTAVA JE to 5950/1700; uncertain_tax_positions register (Open→Settled/Lapsed, exposure/recognized/reserve, creator/settler); quarterly/year-end deferred-tax & UTP sign-off","Implemented")
add("TAX-07","Tax","Application","Tax (VAT); Tax Payable (2100); Revenue (4000); Accounts Receivable (1100)","A sales adjustment (return / price change / defect / undercharge) is not documented on a proper ใบลดหนี้ (ม.86/10) / ใบเพิ่มหนี้ (ม.86/9), so output VAT is not adjusted in the correct filing period; OR the person who issues the note also posts its GL/VAT reversal with no independent review — revenue, output VAT and the ภ.พ.30 return are mis-stated, or a fictitious/over-stated credit note conceals a diversion of receivables.","Accuracy/Completeness/Occurrence/Authorization/Segregation of Duties",
    "Credit/Debit-note maker-checker + VAT adjustment (ม.86/10 / 86/9): a seller (ar/pos) issues a credit note (ใบลดหนี้ — reduces the sale) or debit note (ใบเพิ่มหนี้ — increases it) that MUST reference the original issued full tax invoice (ORIGINAL_NOT_FOUND / ORIGINAL_NOT_ISSUED / CANNOT_ADJUST_A_NOTE) and state a REASON (REASON_REQUIRED, ม.86/10(4)); a credit note cannot exceed the original net value (CREDIT_EXCEEDS_ORIGINAL). The note is issued as status 'PendingApproval' and posts a DRAFT GL entry (credit: Dr 4000 + Dr 2100 / Cr 1100; debit: Dr 1100 / Cr 4000 + Cr 2100, via the AR sub-ledger). A DIFFERENT user (approvals/gl_close/exec) approves — approver ≠ issuer enforced regardless of permissions (SOD_VIOLATION, reusing the GL-05 ledger approval) — which posts the GL AND flips the note to 'Issued'. Only an 'Issued' note feeds the ภ.พ.30 output-VAT report, which SIGNS the note by type (credit − / debit +) into the note's issue period, so the VAT effect and the GL 2100 movement land together and the TAX-04 report↔GL tie holds. Reject voids the note + its draft entry.","Prev","Automated","Per note","Tax / Financial Controller","P10",
    "tax/documents/tax-invoice.service.ts issueAdjustment (reference + reason + credit-cap guards, Draft GL via LedgerService.postEntry pendingApproval)/approveAdjustment (SOD_VIOLATION + approveEntry → Issued)/rejectAdjustment; tax/documents/tax-docs.controller.ts (credit-note/debit-note @ar/pos; :docNo/approve-note|reject-note @approvals/gl_close/exec); tax/reports/tax-reports.service.ts outputVat (sign by type); tax-docs-pdf.service.ts creditDebitNoteHtml; schema/tax-docs.ts (tax_invoice_type credit_note/debit_note + PendingApproval + original_doc_no/reason/gl_entry_no) + migration 0248; cutover/taxdocs.ts (TAX-07 ToE)","Inspect the reference/reason/credit-cap validation, the PendingApproval + Draft-GL issuance, the approver≠issuer SoD, and the signed output-VAT aggregation into the issue period.","TC-TAX-07-01: issue a credit note (net 100) against an issued TIV → PendingApproval + a Draft GL entry, and it is EXCLUDED from output VAT while pending; TC-TAX-07-02: issuer self-approves → SOD_VIOLATION (403); a different user approves → Issued + GL Posted and output VAT falls by 7; TC-TAX-07-03: a debit note (net 50) approved raises output VAT by 3.5; TC-TAX-07-04: a credit exceeding the original → CREDIT_EXCEEDS_ORIGINAL, and a missing reason → 400 (re-performed by the taxdocs harness).","ใบลดหนี้/ใบเพิ่มหนี้ register (PendingApproval→Issued/Voided, original ref + reason, issuer/approver); the CN/DN JE to 4000/2100/1100; the signed output-VAT report row","Implemented")
add("TAX-08","Tax","Application","Input VAT (1300); PP36 VAT Payable (2120); Expense (5100)","VAT on imported services (จ่ายค่าบริการให้ผู้ประกอบการต่างประเทศ) is not self-assessed and remitted via ภ.พ.36 (ม.83/6) — the reverse-charge output VAT the payer owes the RD is omitted (a filing/penalty exposure), or the self-assessed VAT is not tied to the GL before filing.","Completeness/Accuracy/Compliance",
    "Reverse-charge / self-assessed VAT on imported services (ม.83/6): an AP bill for an offshore/non-VAT-registered supplier is flagged reverse_charge — it carries NO vendor input VAT, so createApTxn books it at net (Dr 5100 / Cr 2000) and appends the self-assessment pair Dr 1300 Input VAT / Cr 2120 PP36 VAT Payable (7% of net), a wash on the P&L that records the ภ.พ.36 remittance obligation on a DEDICATED account 2120 kept OUT of the ภ.พ.30/2100 set (a separate return). The ภ.พ.36 report (GET /api/tax-reports/pp36) lists the imported-service bills, computes the self-assessed VAT to remit, and reconciles it to the GL 2120 net credit movement (tie verdict) so a manual JE touching 2120 out-of-process is caught; the filing is registered/submitted/accepted through the same TAX-05 lifecycle and shown on the remittance calendar due the 7th of the following month. DEFAULT-inert: the reverse_charge flag defaults false, so every existing/domestic bill is byte-for-byte unchanged.","Det","Automated","Per bill / monthly","Tax","P10",
    "finance.service.ts createApTxn (reverse_charge → net booking + Dr 1300 / Cr 2120 self-assessment); tax/reports/tax-reports.service.ts pp36 (report + GL 2120 tie) + fileReturn/remittanceCalendar (PP36); tax/reports/tax-reports.controller.ts GET pp36; schema/finance.ts ap_transactions.reverse_charge + migration 0280; ledger-constants 2120 (COA + CF_CLASSIFY); cutover/taxdocs.ts (TAX-08 ToE)","Inspect the reverse_charge net booking + the Dr 1300 / Cr 2120 self-assessment leg, the ภ.พ.36 report + GL 2120 tie, and the filing/remittance-calendar wiring.","TC-TAX-08-01: book a ฿5,000 imported-service bill flagged reverse_charge → ภ.พ.36 self-assesses ฿350 (7%), the line appears, and it ties to the GL 2120 movement (฿350); TC-TAX-08-02: the reverse-charge bill claims 0 vendor input VAT on ภ.พ.30; TC-TAX-08-03: file ภ.พ.36 → DRAFT remitting ฿350, and the remittance calendar lists ภ.พ.36 due the 7th of next month (re-performed by the taxdocs harness).","ภ.พ.36 report + GL 2120 reconciliation tie; the self-assessment JE (1300/2120); the ภ.พ.36 filing register row + remittance calendar","Implemented")

add("TAX-09","Tax","Application","SBT Payable (2130); SBT Expense (5840); Project Revenue (4200)","A commercial immovable-property sale (ขายอสังหาริมทรัพย์เป็นทางค้าหรือหากำไร, ม.91/2(6)) is subject to SPECIFIC BUSINESS TAX — 3% + 10% local tax = 3.3% effective — INSTEAD of VAT, filed monthly on ภ.ธ.40 by the 15th; if the SBT is not accrued at ownership transfer or not filed, the developer under-states its tax liability (filing/penalty exposure) and the RE vertical books transfers tax-free.","Completeness/Accuracy/Compliance",
    "SBT accrual at ownership transfer, driven by an explicit per-project rate: re_projects.sbt_rate (NULL = accrual OFF — legacy books unchanged until a controller opts the project in; set 3.3 for the statutory effective rate). transferOwnership then appends Dr 5840 SBT Expense / Cr 2130 SBT Payable (3.3% of the sale price) to the SAME revenue-recognition JE (atomic with Dr 2410 / Cr 4200) and stamps the contract (re_contracts.sbt_rate/sbt_amount — the ภ.ธ.40 register line). The ภ.ธ.40 report (GET /api/tax-reports/pt40) lists the period's SBT-stamped transfers, computes the SBT to remit, and reconciles it to the GL 2130 net credit movement (tie verdict) so a manual JE touching the SBT payable out-of-process is caught; the return files through the same TAX-05 register lifecycle and shows on the remittance calendar due the 15th. Idempotent via the existing RE-TRANSFER alreadyPosted guard.","Det","Automated","Per transfer / monthly","Tax / Financial Controller","P10",
    "realestate.service.ts transferOwnership (SBT accrual + contract stamp); tax/reports/tax-reports.service.ts pt40 (report + GL 2130 tie) + fileReturn/remittanceCalendar (PT40); tax-reports.controller.ts GET pt40; schema/realestate.ts sbt_rate/sbt_amount + migration 0285; ledger-constants 2130/5840 (COA + CF_CLASSIFY); cutover/projects.ts (TAX-09 ToE)","Inspect the per-project opt-in rate, the atomic Dr 5840 / Cr 2130 accrual inside the transfer JE, the ภ.ธ.40 report + GL 2130 tie, and the filing/remittance-calendar wiring.","TC-TAX-09-01: transfer a ฿500,000 unit under a 3.3% project → sbt_amount ฿16,500 accrued in the transfer JE and the contract stamped; TC-TAX-09-02: ภ.ธ.40 lists the transfer, totals ฿16,500, and ties to the GL 2130 movement; TC-TAX-09-03: a project WITHOUT sbt_rate accrues nothing (default-inert); TC-TAX-09-04: file ภ.ธ.40 → DRAFT remitting ฿16,500 and the remittance calendar lists it due the 15th (re-performed by the projects harness).","ภ.ธ.40 report + GL 2130 reconciliation tie; the transfer JE SBT lines; the ภ.ธ.40 filing register row + remittance calendar","Implemented")

add("TAX-10","Tax","Application","Tax (VAT); Output VAT (2100); Revenue (4000)","A buyer asks the counter to convert an abbreviated tax invoice (ม.86/6 slip) into a FULL tax invoice (ม.86/4) — if the conversion re-keys or recomputes the amounts, issues a SECOND full invoice for the same slip, skips the buyer Tax-ID validation, or leaves BOTH documents counted as Issued, then output VAT is double-counted on the ภ.พ.30 (or drifts from the original supply), a duplicated full invoice lets a buyer over-claim input VAT, and the conversion leaves no audit evidence.","Accuracy/Occurrence/Completeness/Compliance",
    "ABB→full conversion (POST /api/tax-invoices/abbreviated/:docNo/convert-full, gated cust_pos/pos/ar like the sibling issuance endpoints): the buyer block is MANDATORY — name + address (ม.86/4(3)), a checksum-VALIDATED 13-digit Tax ID (INVALID_BUYER_TAXID) and a 5-digit branch code defaulted 00000. The full invoice COPIES the ABB's amounts/VAT/lines and frozen seller snapshot VERBATIM (never recomputed) and keeps the ABB's issue/tax-point dates so the VAT stays in the original filing period; linkage is recorded (full.replaces_doc_no = ABB doc_no) and the ABB flips to status 'Replaced', so the ภ.พ.30 output-VAT report (status='Issued') counts the supply EXACTLY once. IDEMPOTENT — one full invoice per ABB: a re-call returns the same document (already_converted), DB-enforced by the partial unique index uq_tiv_converted_from (migration 0291); a Voided ABB (ABB_VOIDED) or a non-ABB document (NOT_ABBREVIATED) cannot convert. The conversion lands on the hash-chained audit_log (appendAuditMeta: ABB + full doc numbers + buyer Tax ID) and flows into the existing e-Tax XML/PDF path.","Prev","Automated","Per conversion","Store Manager / Tax","P10",
    "tax/documents/tax-invoice.service.ts convertAbbreviatedToFull; tax-docs.controller.ts POST abbreviated/:docNo/convert-full; dto.ts ConvertAbbBody; schema/tax-docs.ts uq_tiv_converted_from + migration 0291; web /tax/invoices conversion card; cutover/taxdocs.ts (TAX-10 ToE)","Inspect the buyer Tax-ID validation, the verbatim amount copy, the Replaced-status single-count, the idempotency backstop index and the audit metadata.","TC-TAX-10-01: convert an issued ABB with a valid buyer block → a full TIV with identical amounts/VAT, linked to the ABB, ABB → Replaced, ภ.พ.30 output VAT unchanged (single count); TC-TAX-10-02: re-convert the same ABB → the SAME full invoice returned (already_converted, no second document); TC-TAX-10-03: an invalid 13-digit Tax ID (bad checksum) or a missing Tax ID is rejected 400; TC-TAX-10-04: a Voided ABB → ABB_VOIDED, a non-ABB document → NOT_ABBREVIATED, cross-tenant → 404 (re-performed by the taxdocs harness).","Converted-invoice pair (ABB Replaced + linked full TIV); ภ.พ.30 single-count assertion; audit_log tax_abb_convert row; taxdocs harness ToE","Implemented")

add("TAX-11","Tax","Application","Corporate Income Tax Expense — current (5960); CIT Payable (2110); Deferred Tax (1700/2700/5950)","The CURRENT income-tax provision is mis-stated — pretax book income is not bridged to taxable income (permanent + temporary book-to-tax adjustments omitted or double-counted), the current CIT is computed at the wrong statutory rate, the temporary difference is re-derived inconsistently with the deferred-tax module (TAX-06), or the provision entry is computed and posted by one person with no review — so income-tax expense, the CIT payable and the effective-tax-rate (ETR) disclosure are misstated (ASC 740 / IAS 12).","Accuracy/Valuation/Completeness/Authorization/Segregation of Duties",
    "Current income-tax provision + ETR reconciliation (ASC 740 / IAS 12, maker-checker, idempotent per (tenant, period)): POST /api/tax/provision/run reads pretax book income from the income statement EXCLUDING income-tax postings (DEFTAX + CITPROV so the base is genuinely pre-tax), applies caller-supplied PERMANENT book-to-tax adjustments (non-deductible expenses +, tax-exempt income −), and REUSES the deferred-tax run's period delta for the TEMPORARY adjustment (temporaryAdjustment = deltaNetDeferred / deferred-rate) rather than re-deriving temporary differences — so the current and deferred modules never disagree. taxable income = pretax + permanent + temporary; current tax = taxable × statutory rate (default 0.20 Thai CIT); it stages an 'Open' income_tax_provisions row (a Posted period → ALREADY_POSTED) and computes the ETR schedule (statutory → effective: permanent differences × rate, rate-change effect, valuation allowance, prior-year deferred), which ties by construction (current + deferred = statutory + permanent×rate). GET /api/tax/provision[/:id] and /:id/etr expose the register + reconciliation. POST /api/tax/provision/:id/post is segregated (poster ≠ runner → SOD_SELF_APPROVAL) and posts the CURRENT tax via LedgerService.postEntry (Dr 5960 Corporate Income Tax Expense / Cr 2110 CIT Payable; a tax benefit reverses the legs), so PERIOD_LOCKED + the GL audit trail apply; the deferred leg is posted by TAX-06. Marks the row Posted.","Prev","Automated","Quarterly / year-end","Tax / Financial Controller","P10",
    "tax-provision.service.ts (runProvision: pretax from incomeStatement excl DEFTAX/CITPROV + permanent M-1 + temporary reused from deferred_tax_runs delta, taxable/current-tax, ETR schedule, stage Open, idempotent ALREADY_POSTED; postProvision SOD_SELF_APPROVAL maker-checker + 5960/2110 posting; list/get/etr); tax-provision.controller.ts (gl_close/gl_post run + :id/post, gl_close/gl_post/exec read + :id/etr); schema/income-tax-provision.ts (income_tax_provisions, uq tenant/period); migration 0349 (table + RLS + TAX.PROVISION posting-event); ledger-constants 5960/2110 (COA + CF_CLASSIFY 2110 operating); posting-events.ts TAX.PROVISION; tax-provision.module.ts (wired, imports LedgerModule); reuses deferred-tax (TAX-06) + ledger.incomeStatement; cutover/tax-provision.ts (TAX-11 ToE, 24 checks)","Inspect the pretax-book-income basis (income-tax postings excluded), the permanent + REUSED-temporary book-to-tax bridge to taxable income, the statutory-rate current tax, the statutory→effective ETR reconciliation tie, the SOD_SELF_APPROVAL maker-checker, and the Dr 5960 / Cr 2110 posting through the period-lock gate.","TC-TAX-11-01: run for a period with pretax book income 600,000, a 50,000 non-deductible permanent add-back and a deferred-tax DTL originating 100,000 → taxable income 550,000, current CIT 110,000 (20%), total income-tax expense 130,000, ETR ≈ 21.67%, and the ETR schedule reconciles statutory 120,000 + permanent 10,000 = 130,000; TC-TAX-11-02: runner self-post → SOD_SELF_APPROVAL (403), a different user posts → Dr 5960 / Cr 2110 (110,000) balanced, re-post → ALREADY_POSTED (400); TC-TAX-11-03: a sibling tenant never sees the provision (RLS) (re-performed by the tax-provision.ts harness, 24 checks).","income_tax_provisions register (Open→Posted, taxable-income bridge + ETR schedule, runner/poster, deferred-tax link); the CITPROV JE to 5960/2110; quarterly/year-end income-tax provision + ETR sign-off","Implemented")

# ---- Payroll ----
add("PAY-01","Payroll","Application","Payroll expense/liability","Payroll, SSO and PIT mis-computed.","Accuracy",
    "Payroll engine — SSO 5% (cap 750), progressive PIT, payslip net; unit-tested.","Auto","Automated","Per run","HR / Payroll","P10",
    "payroll/payroll-calc.ts; test/unit.test.ts","Inspect calc + tests.","Re-perform sample payslips.","Payslip tests","Implemented")
add("PAY-02","Payroll","Application","Payroll liability","Statutory withholdings (SSO/WHT/PF) mis-stated or not remitted, so the liability owed to the authorities diverges from the books.","Accuracy/Compliance",
    "Payroll-liability schedule (GET /api/payroll/liabilities): each statutory account — SSO 2350, WHT/PND1 2360, PF 2370 — shows accrued (GL credits) − remitted (GL debits) = outstanding, tied back to the INDEPENDENT payrun accrual with a `reconciled` flag (a divergence flags a manual JE that touched a payroll-liability account outside the payroll process). Treasury remits the cash (POST .../remit → Dr liability / Cr 1000) which clears the outstanding and keeps the books reconciled to the statutory filings; a remittance beyond the outstanding is blocked (REMIT_EXCEEDS_OUTSTANDING).","Det","Automated","Per run / monthly","HR / Payroll / Treasury","P10",
    "payroll/payroll.service.ts liabilities/remitLiability","Inspect the schedule + the accrued/remitted/outstanding tie-out and the reconciled flag.","Re-perform: run a payroll, confirm the SSO/WHT outstanding equals the payrun accrual; remit part and confirm the outstanding falls and the TB stays balanced; attempt an over-remit (REMIT_EXCEEDS_OUTSTANDING).","Liability schedule + remittance JEs tied to filings","Implemented")
add("PAY-03","Payroll","Application","Payroll expense/liability; Cash","Payroll run posted to the GL without independent review — the preparer both computes and posts their own payroll (ghost employees, inflated rate/hours).","Authorization",
    "Payroll maker-checker (SoD): a run posts its GL entry as a DRAFT (excluded from balances) with the run record 'PendingApproval'; a DIFFERENT user must approve before it becomes effective (approver ≠ preparer enforced regardless of permissions, reusing the GL-05 ledger approval). Reject voids the draft; idempotent per (tenant, period).","Prev","Automated","Per run","HR / Payroll; Controller","P10",
    "payroll/payroll.service.ts approvePayroll/rejectPayroll; migration 0133","Inspect Draft→approve flow + the approver≠preparer check.","Re-perform: run as A, attempt self-approve (SOD_VIOLATION), approve as B; confirm the JE hits balances only after approval.","Approval log + SoD test","Implemented")
add("PAY-04","Payroll","Application","Payroll expense; Labor cost","Overtime is paid at a single flat multiplier with no holiday/night tiers and no statutory cap (Thai LPA OT is mis-paid — too little on holidays, or beyond the 48h/week limit), AND labor cost runs over target as a % of sales with nothing flagging it — margin erosion goes unnoticed until payroll posts.","Accuracy/Completeness",
    "Tiered OT rules engine + labor-% alerting: a per-tenant labor_ot_rules table overrides the Thai LPA statutory defaults (REGULAR_OT 1.5x beyond 8h/day, HOLIDAY 2x, HOLIDAY_OT 3x, NIGHT 1.0x tracked; 48h/week cap) — GET/PUT /api/pos/labor/ot-rules. computeOtPay (POST /api/pos/labor/ot-pay) applies the tier's multiplier and CAPS paid hours at the 48h weekly limit, flagging any over-cap hours (over_cap=true) rather than silently paying them. Separately, POST /api/pos/labor/labor-alert/check computes labor % of sales for a period and, when it exceeds the target (default 35%), persists a LABOR_PCT_EXCEEDED alert (idempotent per period) surfaced on GET /api/pos/labor/alerts for the manager to act on / resolve. Tenant-scoped (RLS); gated pos/users/exec. Operational (no GL).","Det/Prev","Auto+Manual","Per shift / payroll cycle","HR / Store Ops Mgr","P10/P13",
    "pos-loyalty-labor/schedule.service.ts getOtRules/upsertOtRule (Thai defaults overlay) + computeOtPay (tier multiplier + 48h cap, over_cap flag) + checkLaborAlert/listAlerts/resolveAlert; pos-loyalty-labor.controller.ts (ot-rules, ot-pay, labor-alert/check, alerts[/:id/resolve]); schema/pos-scale.ts labor_ot_rules + labor_alerts + migration 0167; /scheduling UI; cutover/scheduling.ts (ToE)","Inspect the statutory-default overlay, the tier multipliers, the 48h cap + over_cap flag, and the labor-% threshold alert (raise/idempotent/resolve).","Re-perform: OT rules expose Thai defaults (1.5/2/3/1.0, cap 48); override REGULAR_OT to 2.0; HOLIDAY_OT 2h x 100 x 3 = 600; a 5h OT entry at 47h already-worked pays only 1h + flags 4h over-cap; labor 8% vs a 5% target raises an alert (idempotent), vs a 50% target raises none; resolve clears it (re-performed by the scheduling harness).","labor_ot_rules + labor_alerts register; OT/labor-% test","Implemented")
add("PAY-05","Payroll","Application","Payroll expense; Labor hours","Time-and-attendance is unverified — one worker clocks a colleague in/out (buddy punching), or punches off-site, so paid labor hours overstate hours actually worked (payroll fraud / inflated labor cost), and there is no attributable override trail when a manager fixes a punch.","Existence/Accuracy/Authorization",
    "Clock-in integrity (anti-buddy-punch): a punch records its capture METHOD (PIN/QR/FACE_HASH/SUPERVISOR) and optional GPS; a re-punch within 15 minutes of the same employee's last clock-out is REJECTED (DUPLICATE_PUNCH) unless a supervisor overrides. A per-branch geofence_zone (lat/lng/radius) lets the clock-in compute geofence_pass when GPS is supplied; an out-of-fence punch is accepted but FLAGGED (geofence_pass=false) for review rather than hard-blocked (kiosks may lack GPS -> null), and a SUPERVISOR override REQUIRES a reason (REASON_REQUIRED), stamps method=SUPERVISOR + the reason on the punch note, and is captured by the append-only audit_log so every override is attributable. The labor report surfaces method + geofence_pass so anomalies are visible. Tenant-scoped (RLS); gated pos/users/exec.","Prev/Det","Automated","Per punch","HR / Store Ops Mgr","P10/P13",
    "pos-loyalty-labor/timeclock.service.ts clockIn (DUPLICATE_PUNCH window, method capture, haversine geofence_pass) + supervisorOverride (REASON_REQUIRED, audited) + setGeofenceZone/listGeofenceZones; pos-loyalty-labor.controller.ts (clock-in, clock-in/override, geofence-zones); schema/pos-scale.ts time_clock.clock_in_method/lat/lng/geofence_pass + geofence_zones + migration 0169; cutover/pos-p2.ts (ToE)","Inspect the 15-min duplicate-punch guard, the method capture, the geofence pass/fail computation, and the supervisor-override reason + audit trail.","Re-perform: a re-punch within 15 min of clock-out -> DUPLICATE_PUNCH; a supervisor override (with a reason) bypasses it and stamps method SUPERVISOR; an override with no reason -> 400; an in-fence GPS punch -> geofence_pass true; an out-of-fence punch is accepted but flagged geofence_pass false (re-performed by the pos-p2 harness).","time_clock method/geofence columns + override note; anti-buddy test","Implemented")
add("PAY-06","Payroll","Application","Payroll PII; Payslip","An employee's payslip (salary, citizen ID, statutory deductions) is exposed to someone other than the employee or authorised HR/payroll — a PDPA confidentiality breach: a self-service user pulls a colleague's payslip by guessing an id, or the full 13-digit citizen ID is printed in the clear on the slip.","Confidentiality/Restricted access",
    "PDPA-scoped payslip access: the employee self-service payslip download (GET /api/ess/payslips/:id/pdf, perm `ess`) resolves the caller to their OWN employee from the JWT username (NEVER a body/query param) and ANDs an employee_id predicate onto the lookup, so a slip id that isn't the caller's own returns 404 — an employee can only ever retrieve their own slip. HR/payroll printing (GET /api/payroll/slips/:id/pdf + POST .../send-email, gate exec/users/creditors) may print/email any slip in the tenant; an ess-only user is denied the HR route (403). The citizen ID is MASKED to the last 4 digits on the face of the slip (data-minimisation), and RLS scopes every lookup to the caller's tenant. Same shared HTML->PDF renderer as the external documents (HTML fallback when Chromium absent).","Prev","Automated","Per access","HR / Payroll; DPO","P10",
    "payroll/payslip-pdf.service.ts (payslipHtml + maskNationalId); payroll.service.ts getSlipForPrint(restrictEmployeeId)/emailPayslip; payroll.controller.ts slips/:id/pdf|send-email; ess.service.ts myPayslipForPrint (me()-scoped); ess.module.ts ess payslips/:id/pdf; cutover/payroll.ts (ToE)","Inspect the me()->employee_id predicate on the ESS route, the HR-route permission gate, and the last-4 citizen-ID mask.","Re-perform: an ESS employee downloads their OWN slip (200) but a colleague's slip id -> 404; HR prints any slip (200) while an ess-only user is denied the HR route (403); the slip shows only the masked citizen ID (no full 13-digit); the email path reaches the transport (503 EMAIL_NOT_CONFIGURED, SMTP unset) - re-performed by the payroll harness.","PDPA payslip-access test (own-200/other-404/HR-403) + masked-ID render","Implemented")
add("HR-01","Payroll","Application","Human Resources (headcount / labour cost)","Staff are hired into positions beyond the approved establishment — an employee is assigned to a position whose budgeted headcount is already full, so the organisation carries unbudgeted headcount (over-establishment) and the resulting salary/labour cost is committed with no independent authorisation; the org chart and the payroll base drift above the approved plan unnoticed.","Authorization/Segregation of Duties",
    "Headcount-governance control on the HR org structure (docs/42 HR-1): each hr_position carries a budgeted_headcount, and creating an hr_assignment (an effective-dated employee→position link) counts the position's currently-active assignments (end_date IS NULL). When that count has already reached the budgeted headcount the assignment is BLOCKED (HEADCOUNT_EXCEEDED, 403) for an ordinary HR maintainer (perm hr_admin) — the establishment cannot be exceeded from the inside. Only a user holding `exec` may OVERRIDE and add the over-establishment seat; the override is AUDIT-LOGGED (a doc_status_log HRASSIGN row carrying HEADCOUNT_OVERRIDE, the position, the count/budget and the reason) in addition to the append-only audit_log the global AuditInterceptor writes for every mutation. A budgeted_headcount of 0 means an unbudgeted seat (no cap). Reads are gated hr/hr_admin/exec and writes hr_admin/exec; the tables are tenant-scoped (RLS) so headcount never leaks across companies. So an HR maintainer can fill the approved plan but never grow it, and every over-establishment hire is an attributable exec decision.","Prev","Automated","Per assignment","HR / Payroll; Exec (override)","P10",
    "hcm/hcm-org.service.ts createAssignment (active-headcount count vs budgeted_headcount → HEADCOUNT_EXCEEDED; exec-only override via canOverride; StatusLogService HRASSIGN HEADCOUNT_OVERRIDE audit) / createDepartment / createPosition / orgChart; hcm-org.controller.ts /api/hcm/org/{departments,positions,assignments,chart}; schema/hcm-org.ts hr_departments/hr_positions/hr_assignments (migration 0320, RLS + tenant-leading indexes); permissions.ts hr/hr_admin; cutover/hcm-org.ts (ToE)","Inspect the active-headcount count against budgeted_headcount, the HEADCOUNT_EXCEEDED block for a non-exec, the exec-only override path, and the HEADCOUNT_OVERRIDE audit row on the doc status log.","Re-perform: create a position with budgeted_headcount=1; assign one employee (within budget, no override); assign a second as a non-exec hr_admin → HEADCOUNT_EXCEEDED (403); assign the second as an exec → succeeds with headcount_overridden=true and a doc_status_log HRASSIGN HEADCOUNT_OVERRIDE row; a budgeted_headcount=0 position accepts multiple assignments with no override (re-performed by the hcm-org harness, incl. RLS tenant isolation).","Position establishment register (budgeted vs current headcount); the HEADCOUNT_OVERRIDE audit trail on over-establishment hires","Implemented")
add("FA-09","Fixed Assets","Application","Property, Plant & Equipment; Cash","Asset disposed without independent review — one person writes an asset off the books and records the proceeds (asset-stripping / theft: dispose a still-held asset, or to a related party below value).","Authorization",
    "Asset-disposal maker-checker (SoD): a disposal REQUEST posts its GL entry as a DRAFT (excluded from balances) and flags the asset disposal_pending WITHOUT marking it disposed or moving the register; a DIFFERENT user must approve before it is effective (status→disposed, revaluation surplus recycled 3200→3100) (approver ≠ requester enforced regardless of permissions, reusing the GL-05 ledger approval). Reject voids the draft and the asset stays in service; only one disposal may be pending per asset; a disposal-pending asset is frozen from depreciation.","Prev","Automated","Per disposal","FaAccountant / Controller","P10",
    "assets.service.ts dispose(pendingApproval Draft)/approveDisposal/rejectDisposal; assets.controller.ts (:assetNo/dispose/approve|reject); schema/assets.ts fixed_assets.disposal_pending + migration 0135; cutover/basics.ts + worldclass.ts + compliance.ts (ToE)","Inspect Draft→approve flow + the approver≠requester check + deferred status/recycle.","Re-perform: request a disposal (Draft JE excluded), attempt self-approve (SOD_VIOLATION), approve as a different user; confirm status→disposed + surplus recycled only after approval (re-performed by the harnesses).","Disposal approval log + SoD test","Implemented")
add("FA-10","Fixed Assets","Application","Property, Plant & Equipment; Accounts Payable","Capital purchases mis-capitalised or capitalised without independent review — the person who receives the goods also decides what enters the asset register and at what cost/useful life (fictitious or over-valued assets; capex/opex mis-classification).","Authorization; Accuracy",
    "Procure-to-Capitalize maker-checker (SoD): a goods-receipt line flagged capital (item-master is_fixed_asset or per-PO-line override) is excluded from inventory capitalisation (1200) at receipt and instead becomes ELIGIBLE for the asset register. Capitalisation is a REQUEST that posts NOTHING to the GL; a DIFFERENT user must approve before the fixed_assets row + acquisition JE (Dr 1500 / Cr 2000) are created (approver ≠ requester enforced regardless of permissions). The created asset carries its source GR/PO for end-to-end PR→PO→GR→FA traceability; a GR line cannot be capitalised twice.","Prev","Automated","Per capital receipt","FaAccountant / Controller","P10",
    "assets.service.ts registerFromGr/approveRegistration/rejectRegistration/eligibleFromGr; assets.controller.ts (registrations*); procurement.service.ts createGr (is_capital routing, costing excluded); schema/assets.ts asset_registration_requests + fixed_assets.source_gr_no/po_no + migration 0137; cutover/basics.ts + compliance.ts (ToE)","Inspect the eligible→request→approve flow + approver≠requester check + the inventory-vs-asset routing of capital lines.","Re-perform: receive a capital line, raise a registration (no GL), attempt self-approve (SOD_VIOLATION), approve as a different user; confirm the asset + Dr 1500/Cr 2000 post only after approval and the line cannot be re-registered (re-performed by the harnesses).","Capitalization approval log + SoD test","Implemented")
add("FA-11","Fixed Assets","Application","Property, Plant & Equipment","Asset moved/reassigned without independent review — a custodian relabels an asset's physical location or holder (or an audit finds it elsewhere) and the register is changed on one person's say-so, enabling misappropriation (reassign to self/related party) or concealment of a missing asset; existence/custody assertions unreliable.","Authorization; Existence",
    "Asset custody-change maker-checker (SoD) + audit-by-scan. A tag scan that CHANGES an asset's location/holder no longer writes the register: it raises a PendingApproval custody-change REQUEST (no GL effect); a DIFFERENT user must approve before the register moves and a 'Scan Update' movement is logged (approver != requester enforced regardless of permissions — binds even Admin; reject leaves the asset in place; only one request pending per asset). Confirming the current location is logged immediately as a non-approval 'Scan Verify' movement (existence evidence). A physical AUDIT (count by scan) classifies each scan Found/Misplaced/Unknown and reconciles Missing against the register; closing the audit raises custody-change requests for the misplaced assets — so no floor-level move rewrites the register without a second person's approval.","Prev / Det","Automated","Per custody move / per audit","FaAccountant / Controller","P10",
    "assets.service.ts scanUpdate(verify vs request)/approveCustody/rejectCustody/openAudit/scanAudit/getAudit/closeAudit; assets.controller.ts (scan-update, custody*, audits*); schema/assets.ts asset_scan_requests + asset_audits + asset_audit_scans + migration 0251; web /assets Audit + Custody-approvals tabs; cutover/module-qr.ts (ToE)","Inspect the scan->request->approve flow + the approver!=requester check + the audit reconcile->custody-request path.","Re-perform: scan a move (PendingApproval, register unmoved), attempt self-approve (SOD_VIOLATION), approve as a different user (register moves + movement logged); run an audit that finds a misplaced asset and confirm closing raises a pending custody request (re-performed by the module-qr harness).","Custody-change approval log + audit reconciliation + SoD test","Implemented")
add("FA-12","Fixed Assets","Detective","Property, Plant & Equipment","Assets exist on the register but are never physically confirmed — a missing/stolen/scrapped asset stays on the books indefinitely because no periodic existence check flags it, overstating PPE and the existence assertion.","Existence; Completeness",
    "Periodic asset-existence exception monitoring. A schedulable BI report (report_type asset_verification_exceptions) lists every ACTIVE asset not physically verified within N days (default 90) — 'verified' = a Scan Verify or approved Scan Update movement (FA-11), with a never-verified asset falling back to its acquisition date as the implicit receipt baseline. Each exception carries days-since-last-seen so the oldest surface first. Scheduled monthly, it drives a recurring existence count before period-end; the companion asset_audit report surfaces recent audit results (found/missing/misplaced/unknown) and the outstanding custody-change queue. Read-only aggregation over fixed_assets + asset_movements — posts nothing, adds no authority (no SoD conflict); complements the FA-11 audit-by-scan (which supplies the verification movements) and the FA-05 register-to-GL tie-out.","Det","Automated","Monthly (scheduled) / on demand","FaAccountant / Controller","P16",
    "assets.service.ts unverifiedAssets/auditReport; assets.controller.ts (unverified, audit-report); bi.service.ts REPORT_TYPES asset_verification_exceptions + asset_audit + generateReport blocks; bi.module.ts imports AssetsModule; cutover/module-qr.ts (ToE)","Inspect the exception query (last Scan Verify/Update vs N-day threshold, acquisition-date fallback) and that the report is a registered, schedulable BI type.","Re-perform: seed an old never-scanned asset, run GET /api/assets/unverified?days=90 (asset flagged) + a recently-scanned asset is NOT flagged; schedule + run the asset_verification_exceptions report and confirm the summary counts the exception (re-performed by the module-qr harness).","Scheduled exception report runs + exception list + verification-movement log","Implemented")
add("FA-13","Fixed Assets","Application","Property, Plant & Equipment; Accounts Payable","Construction-in-progress (CIP/AUC) is capitalised into the productive asset register without independent review — the person who accumulates the construction cost also decides when it is 'complete', at what cost/useful life it enters service, and starts depreciation, so premature/over-valued capitalisation (or deferring capitalisation to delay depreciation) goes unchecked; PPE existence/valuation and the depreciation charge are mis-stated.","Authorization; Accuracy",
    "CIP/AUC settlement maker-checker (SoD): a CIP asset accumulates cost lines (GR/manual/project) into the CIP GL account (Dr 1520 / Cr 2000 AP | 1000 Cash) and is NOT depreciated while under construction. Capitalising it is a settlement REQUEST that posts NOTHING and requires a MANDATORY reason; a DIFFERENT user must approve before the fixed_assets row + reclassification JE (Dr 1500 / Cr 1520, for the accumulated construction cost) are created and depreciation begins (approver != requester enforced regardless of permissions — binds even Admin; the created asset carries its source CIP for traceability and gets its own parallel tax book). Only an Open CIP accepts cost (CIP_NOT_OPEN); a CIP with no accumulated cost cannot be settled (CIP_NO_COST); reject re-opens the CIP. Pairs with the FIN-6a parallel TAX depreciation book, which keeps a memo tax basis (Thai caps + first-year initial allowance) feeding the book-vs-tax temporary difference straight into deferred tax (TAX-06) instead of a manual GAAP adjustment.","Prev","Automated","Per capitalisation","FaAccountant / Controller","P10",
    "assets.service.ts openCip/addCipCost/settleCip/approveCipSettlement/rejectCipSettlement + runTaxDepreciation + acquire(taxBookInit, creditAccount 1520); assets.controller.ts (cip*, tax-depreciation/run); deferred-tax.service.ts (prefers the stored tax NBV); ledger-constants.ts COA 1520 + CF_CLASSIFY; schema/assets.ts cip_assets + cip_cost_lines + fixed_assets tax-book/source_cip_no cols + migration 0299; cutover/basics.ts (ToE)","Inspect the accumulate->settle->approve flow + the approver!=requester check + the Dr 1500/Cr 1520 reclassification, and that deferred tax consumes the real tax NBV.","Re-perform: open a CIP, accumulate cost into 1520 (not 1500), raise a settlement (no GL), attempt self-approve (SOD_VIOLATION), approve as a different user (asset + Dr 1500/Cr 1520 post); confirm CIP_NOT_OPEN/CIP_NO_COST guards and that the parallel tax book feeds the deferred-tax difference (re-performed by the basics harness).","CIP settlement approval log + SoD test + tax-book/deferred-tax tie-out","Implemented")

